\usepackage<<5>>comment<<5>>
\usepackage<<6>>html,makeidx<<6>>
\begin<<9520>>tex2html_deferred<<9520>>\par\end<<9521>>tex2html_deferred<<9521>>
\DeclareMathOperator* <<7>>\argmax<<7>><<8>>arg\,max<<8>>
\DeclareMathOperator* <<9>>\argmin<<9>><<10>>arg\,min<<10>>
\begin<<9522>>tex2html_deferred<<9522>>\par\end<<9523>>tex2html_deferred<<9523>>
\begin<<11>>document<<11>>
\begin<<9524>>tex2html_deferred<<9524>>\par\end<<9525>>tex2html_deferred<<9525>>
\section*<<12>>Optimization<<12>>
\begin<<9526>>tex2html_deferred<<9526>>\par\end<<9527>>tex2html_deferred<<9527>>
The goal of mathematical optimization or mathematical programming
is to solve an optimization problem of a given real multivariate 
function \begin<<6742>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6742>>$y=f(<<13>>\begin<<9528>>tex2html_deferred<<9528>>\bf\end<<9529>>tex2html_deferred<<9529>>x<<13>>)=f(x_1,\cdots,x_N)$\end<<6743>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6743>>\space by searching its domain, 
an N-dimensional space, to find the optimal point 
\begin<<6744>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6744>>$<<14>>\begin<<9530>>tex2html_deferred<<9530>>\bf\end<<9531>>tex2html_deferred<<9531>>x<<14>>^*=[x_1^2,\cdots,x_N^*]^T\in\begin<<9532>>tex2html_wrap<<9532>>\mathbb<<15>>R<<15>>\end<<9533>>tex2html_wrap<<9533>>^N$\end<<6745>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6745>>\space at which the 
corresponding function value \begin<<6746>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6746>>$f(<<16>>\begin<<9534>>tex2html_deferred<<9534>>\bf\end<<9535>>tex2html_deferred<<9535>>x<<16>>^*)$\end<<6747>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6747>>\space is either maximized or
minimized. As maximizing \begin<<6748>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6748>>$f(<<17>>\begin<<9536>>tex2html_deferred<<9536>>\bf\end<<9537>>tex2html_deferred<<9537>>x<<17>>)$\end<<6749>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6749>>\space is equivalent to minimizing 
\begin<<6750>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6750>>$-f(<<18>>\begin<<9538>>tex2html_deferred<<9538>>\bf\end<<9539>>tex2html_deferred<<9539>>x<<18>>)$\end<<6751>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6751>>, we can only consider minimization problems.
\begin<<9540>>tex2html_deferred<<9540>>\par\end<<9541>>tex2html_deferred<<9541>>
\begin<<19>>equation<<19>>
  <<20>>\begin<<9542>>tex2html_deferred<<9542>>\bf\end<<9543>>tex2html_deferred<<9543>>x<<20>>^*=\argmin_<<21>>\begin<<9544>>tex2html_deferred<<9544>>\bf\end<<9545>>tex2html_deferred<<9545>>x<<21>> f(<<22>>\begin<<9546>>tex2html_deferred<<9546>>\bf\end<<9547>>tex2html_deferred<<9547>>x<<22>>),\;\;\;\;\;\;\mbox<<23>>i.e.,<<23>>\;\;\;\;\;
  f(<<24>>\begin<<9548>>tex2html_deferred<<9548>>\bf\end<<9549>>tex2html_deferred<<9549>>x<<24>>^*)=\min_<<25>>\begin<<9550>>tex2html_deferred<<9550>>\bf\end<<9551>>tex2html_deferred<<9551>>x<<25>> f(<<26>>\begin<<9552>>tex2html_deferred<<9552>>\bf\end<<9553>>tex2html_deferred<<9553>>x<<26>>)
\end<<27>>equation<<27>>
If the independent variables in \begin<<6752>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6752>>$<<28>>\begin<<9554>>tex2html_deferred<<9554>>\bf\end<<9555>>tex2html_deferred<<9555>>x<<28>>$\end<<6753>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6753>>\space are allowed to take 
any values inside the function domain \begin<<6754>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6754>>$\begin<<9556>>tex2html_wrap<<9556>>\mathbb<<29>>R<<29>>\end<<9557>>tex2html_wrap<<9557>>^N$\end<<6755>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6755>>, then the 
optimization problem is unconstrained, otherwise if \begin<<6756>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6756>>$<<30>>\begin<<9558>>tex2html_deferred<<9558>>\bf\end<<9559>>tex2html_deferred<<9559>>x<<30>>$\end<<6757>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6757>>\space has
to be inside a subset of \begin<<6758>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6758>>$\begin<<9560>>tex2html_wrap<<9560>>\mathbb<<31>>R<<31>>\end<<9561>>tex2html_wrap<<9561>>^N$\end<<6759>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6759>>, the problem is constrained.
\begin<<9562>>tex2html_deferred<<9562>>\par\end<<9563>>tex2html_deferred<<9563>>
Typically the real function \begin<<6760>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6760>>$f(<<32>>\begin<<9564>>tex2html_deferred<<9564>>\bf\end<<9565>>tex2html_deferred<<9565>>x<<32>>)$\end<<6761>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6761>>\space is an <<33>>\begin<<9566>>tex2html_deferred<<9566>>\em\end<<9567>>tex2html_deferred<<9567>>objective<<33>> or 
<<34>>\begin<<9568>>tex2html_deferred<<9568>>\em\end<<9569>>tex2html_deferred<<9569>>cost function<<34>> which is to be either minimized or maximized. 
For example, in machine learning, we need to carry out regression 
analysis and classification, and we may need to develop a model 
\begin<<6762>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6762>>$y=f(<<35>>\begin<<9570>>tex2html_deferred<<9570>>\bf\end<<9571>>tex2html_deferred<<9571>>x<<35>>,<<36>>\begin<<9572>>tex2html_deferred<<9572>>\bf\end<<9573>>tex2html_deferred<<9573>>a<<36>>)$\end<<6763>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6763>>\space to fit a set of observed data points 
\begin<<6764>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6764>>$<<37>>\cal D<<37>>=\{ (<<38>>\begin<<9574>>tex2html_deferred<<9574>>\bf\end<<9575>>tex2html_deferred<<9575>>x<<38>>_n,\,y_n),\;\;n=1,\cdots,N \}$\end<<6765>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6765>>, by estimating
the parameters in \begin<<6766>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6766>>$<<39>>\begin<<9576>>tex2html_deferred<<9576>>\bf\end<<9577>>tex2html_deferred<<9577>>a<<39>>=[a_1,\cdots,a_M]^T$\end<<6767>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6767>>\space of the function.
Typically the function is assumed to be known, such as the linear
model \begin<<6768>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6768>>$y=f(x)=ax+b$\end<<6769>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6769>>, containing two model parameters \begin<<6770>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6770>>$a$\end<<6771>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6771>>\space (slope)
and \begin<<6772>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6772>>$b$\end<<6773>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6773>>\space (intercept), to be estimated based on the observed data.
\begin<<9578>>tex2html_deferred<<9578>>\par\end<<9579>>tex2html_deferred<<9579>>
Different methods can be used to solve this parameter estimation
problem. If the least square method is used, the objective function 
can be the squared error, the difference between the model and the 
given data, which is to be minimized:
\begin<<40>>equation<<40>>
  o(<<41>>\begin<<9580>>tex2html_deferred<<9580>>\bf\end<<9581>>tex2html_deferred<<9581>>a<<41>>)=\sum_<<42>>n=1<<42>>^N [y_n-f((<<43>>\begin<<9582>>tex2html_deferred<<9582>>\bf\end<<9583>>tex2html_deferred<<9583>>x<<43>>_n,<<44>>\begin<<9584>>tex2html_deferred<<9584>>\bf\end<<9585>>tex2html_deferred<<9585>>a<<44>>))]^2
\end<<45>>equation<<45>>
Alternatively, if the Bayesian method is used, the objective 
functioin can be the likelihood function of the parameters in
\begin<<6774>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6774>>$<<46>>\begin<<9586>>tex2html_deferred<<9586>>\bf\end<<9587>>tex2html_deferred<<9587>>a<<46>>$\end<<6775>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6775>>, which is to be maximized:
\begin<<47>>equation<<47>>
  o(<<48>>\begin<<9588>>tex2html_deferred<<9588>>\bf\end<<9589>>tex2html_deferred<<9589>>a<<48>>)=L(<<49>>\begin<<9590>>tex2html_deferred<<9590>>\bf\end<<9591>>tex2html_deferred<<9591>>a<<49>>|<<50>>\cal D<<50>>) =p(<<51>>\cal D<<51>>|<<52>>\begin<<9592>>tex2html_deferred<<9592>>\bf\end<<9593>>tex2html_deferred<<9593>>a<<52>>)
  =\prod_<<53>>n=1<<53>>^N p(y_n|<<54>>\begin<<9594>>tex2html_deferred<<9594>>\bf\end<<9595>>tex2html_deferred<<9595>>x<<54>>_n,<<55>>\begin<<9596>>tex2html_deferred<<9596>>\bf\end<<9597>>tex2html_deferred<<9597>>a<<55>>)
\end<<56>>equation<<56>>
Solving suth optimization problems we get the optimal model 
parameters in \begin<<6776>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6776>>$<<57>>\begin<<9598>>tex2html_deferred<<9598>>\bf\end<<9599>>tex2html_deferred<<9599>>a<<57>>^*$\end<<6777>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6777>>.
\begin<<9600>>tex2html_deferred<<9600>>\par\end<<9601>>tex2html_deferred<<9601>>
If an optimization problem is unconstrained, and the analytical 
expression of the objective function is explicitly given, then the 
solution \begin<<6778>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6778>>$<<58>>\begin<<9602>>tex2html_deferred<<9602>>\bf\end<<9603>>tex2html_deferred<<9603>>x<<58>>^*$\end<<6779>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6779>>\space at which the objective function \begin<<6780>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6780>>$f(<<59>>\begin<<9604>>tex2html_deferred<<9604>>\bf\end<<9605>>tex2html_deferred<<9605>>x<<59>>)$\end<<6781>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6781>> 
is minimized may be found by solving the following equation system 
obtained by setting the gradient of the \begin<<6782>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6782>>$f(<<60>>\begin<<9606>>tex2html_deferred<<9606>>\bf\end<<9607>>tex2html_deferred<<9607>>x<<60>>)$\end<<6783>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6783>>\space to be zero:
\begin<<61>>equation<<61>>
  <<62>>\begin<<9608>>tex2html_deferred<<9608>>\bf\end<<9609>>tex2html_deferred<<9609>>g<<62>>_f=\bigtriangledown_<<63>>\begin<<9610>>tex2html_deferred<<9610>>\bf\end<<9611>>tex2html_deferred<<9611>>x<<63>> f(<<64>>\begin<<9612>>tex2html_deferred<<9612>>\bf\end<<9613>>tex2html_deferred<<9613>>x<<64>>)
  =\frac<<6497>>d f(<<65>>\begin<<9614>>tex2html_deferred<<9614>>\bf\end<<9615>>tex2html_deferred<<9615>>x<<65>>)<<6497>><<6498>>d<<66>>\begin<<9616>>tex2html_deferred<<9616>>\bf\end<<9617>>tex2html_deferred<<9617>>x<<66>><<6498>> 
  =\left[\frac<<6499>>\partial f(<<67>>\begin<<9618>>tex2html_deferred<<9618>>\bf\end<<9619>>tex2html_deferred<<9619>>x<<67>>)<<6499>><<68>>\partial x_1<<68>>,\cdots,
    \frac<<6500>>\partial f(<<69>>\begin<<9620>>tex2html_deferred<<9620>>\bf\end<<9621>>tex2html_deferred<<9621>>x<<69>>)<<6500>><<70>>\partial x_N<<70>>\right]^T =<<71>>\begin<<9622>>tex2html_deferred<<9622>>\bf\end<<9623>>tex2html_deferred<<9623>>0<<71>>
\end<<72>>equation<<72>>
where \begin<<6784>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6784>>$<<73>>\begin<<9624>>tex2html_deferred<<9624>>\bf\end<<9625>>tex2html_deferred<<9625>>g<<73>>_f=\bigtriangledown_<<74>>\begin<<9626>>tex2html_deferred<<9626>>\bf\end<<9627>>tex2html_deferred<<9627>>x<<74>> f(<<75>>\begin<<9628>>tex2html_deferred<<9628>>\bf\end<<9629>>tex2html_deferred<<9629>>x<<75>>)=d\,f(<<76>>\begin<<9630>>tex2html_deferred<<9630>>\bf\end<<9631>>tex2html_deferred<<9631>>x<<76>>)/d<<77>>\begin<<9632>>tex2html_deferred<<9632>>\bf\end<<9633>>tex2html_deferred<<9633>>x<<77>>$\end<<6785>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6785>> 
denotes the gradient vector of a scalar function \begin<<6786>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6786>>$f(<<78>>\begin<<9634>>tex2html_deferred<<9634>>\bf\end<<9635>>tex2html_deferred<<9635>>x<<78>>)$\end<<6787>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6787>>\space with
respect to its vector argument \begin<<6788>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6788>>$<<79>>\begin<<9636>>tex2html_deferred<<9636>>\bf\end<<9637>>tex2html_deferred<<9637>>x<<79>>=[<<80>>\begin<<9638>>tex2html_deferred<<9638>>\bf\end<<9639>>tex2html_deferred<<9639>>x<<80>>_1,\cdots,<<81>>\begin<<9640>>tex2html_deferred<<9640>>\bf\end<<9641>>tex2html_deferred<<9641>>x<<81>>_N]^T$\end<<6789>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6789>>.
The root \begin<<6790>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6790>>$<<82>>\begin<<9642>>tex2html_deferred<<9642>>\bf\end<<9643>>tex2html_deferred<<9643>>x<<82>>^*$\end<<6791>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6791>>\space of the equation \begin<<6792>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6792>>$<<83>>\begin<<9644>>tex2html_deferred<<9644>>\bf\end<<9645>>tex2html_deferred<<9645>>g<<83>>_f=<<84>>\begin<<9646>>tex2html_deferred<<9646>>\bf\end<<9647>>tex2html_deferred<<9647>>0<<84>>$\end<<6793>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6793>>\space is called a 
<<85>>\begin<<9648>>tex2html_deferred<<9648>>\em\end<<9649>>tex2html_deferred<<9649>>critical, stationary, or stable point<<85>> of \begin<<6794>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6794>>$f(<<86>>\begin<<9650>>tex2html_deferred<<9650>>\bf\end<<9651>>tex2html_deferred<<9651>>x<<86>>)$\end<<6795>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6795>>.
\begin<<9652>>tex2html_deferred<<9652>>\par\end<<9653>>tex2html_deferred<<9653>>
Whether the function value \begin<<6796>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6796>>$f(<<87>>\begin<<9654>>tex2html_deferred<<9654>>\bf\end<<9655>>tex2html_deferred<<9655>>x<<87>>^*)$\end<<6797>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6797>>\space at this stationary point 
is a maximum, minimum, or saddle point, depending on its Hessian 
matrix for its second order derivatives:
\begin<<88>>equation<<88>>
  <<89>>\begin<<9656>>tex2html_deferred<<9656>>\bf\end<<9657>>tex2html_deferred<<9657>>H<<89>>_f=\left[ \begin<<90>>array<<90>><<91>>ccc<<91>>
      \frac<<6501>>\partial^2 f(<<92>>\begin<<9658>>tex2html_deferred<<9658>>\bf\end<<9659>>tex2html_deferred<<9659>>x<<92>>)<<6501>><<93>>\partial x_1^2<<93>> ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; 
      \frac<<6502>>\partial^2 f(<<94>>\begin<<9660>>tex2html_deferred<<9660>>\bf\end<<9661>>tex2html_deferred<<9661>>x<<94>>)<<6502>><<95>>\partial x_1\partial x_N<<95>> \\ 
      \vdots ;SPMamp; \ddots ;SPMamp; \vdots \\ 
      \frac<<6503>>\partial^2 f(<<96>>\begin<<9662>>tex2html_deferred<<9662>>\bf\end<<9663>>tex2html_deferred<<9663>>x<<96>>)<<6503>><<97>>\partial x_N\partial x_1<<97>> ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; 
      \frac<<6504>>\partial^2 f(<<98>>\begin<<9664>>tex2html_deferred<<9664>>\bf\end<<9665>>tex2html_deferred<<9665>>x<<98>>)<<6504>><<99>>\partial x_N^2<<99>>
    \end<<100>>array<<100>> \right]_<<6505>><<101>>\begin<<9666>>tex2html_deferred<<9666>>\bf\end<<9667>>tex2html_deferred<<9667>>x<<101>>=<<102>>\begin<<9668>>tex2html_deferred<<9668>>\bf\end<<9669>>tex2html_deferred<<9669>>x<<102>>^*<<6505>>
  \nonumber
\end<<103>>equation<<103>>
\begin<<9670>>tex2html_deferred<<9670>>\par\end<<9671>>tex2html_deferred<<9671>>
\begin<<104>>itemize<<104>>
\item If \begin<<6798>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6798>>$<<105>>\begin<<9672>>tex2html_deferred<<9672>>\bf\end<<9673>>tex2html_deferred<<9673>>H<<105>>_f;SPMgt;0$\end<<6799>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6799>>\space is positive definite (all eigenvalues are positive),
  \begin<<6800>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6800>>$f(<<106>>\begin<<9674>>tex2html_deferred<<9674>>\bf\end<<9675>>tex2html_deferred<<9675>>x<<106>>^*)$\end<<6801>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6801>>\space is a minimum;
\item If \begin<<6802>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6802>>$<<107>>\begin<<9676>>tex2html_deferred<<9676>>\bf\end<<9677>>tex2html_deferred<<9677>>H<<107>>_f;SPMlt;0$\end<<6803>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6803>>\space is negative definite (all eigenvalues are negative), 
  \begin<<6804>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6804>>$f(<<108>>\begin<<9678>>tex2html_deferred<<9678>>\bf\end<<9679>>tex2html_deferred<<9679>>x<<108>>^*)$\end<<6805>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6805>>\space is a maximum;
\item If \begin<<6806>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6806>>$<<109>>\begin<<9680>>tex2html_deferred<<9680>>\bf\end<<9681>>tex2html_deferred<<9681>>H<<109>>_f$\end<<6807>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6807>>\space is indefinite (with both positive and negative 
  eigenvalues), \begin<<6808>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6808>>$f(<<110>>\begin<<9682>>tex2html_deferred<<9682>>\bf\end<<9683>>tex2html_deferred<<9683>>x<<110>>^*)$\end<<6809>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6809>>\space is a saddle point (maximum in some directions,
  but minimum in others). 
\end<<111>>itemize<<111>>
\begin<<9684>>tex2html_deferred<<9684>>\par\end<<9685>>tex2html_deferred<<9685>>
For  example, the gradient vectors and Hessian matrices of three 
functions \begin<<6810>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6810>>$f_1(x,y)=x^2+y^2$\end<<6811>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6811>>, \begin<<6812>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6812>>$f_2(x,y)=-x^2-y^2$\end<<6813>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6813>>, and \begin<<6814>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6814>>$f_3(x,y)=x^2-y^2$\end<<6815>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6815>>:
\begin<<112>>equation<<112>>
  <<113>>\begin<<9686>>tex2html_deferred<<9686>>\bf\end<<9687>>tex2html_deferred<<9687>>g<<113>>_<<114>>f_1<<114>>=\left[\begin<<115>>array<<115>><<116>>c<<116>>2x\\ 2y\end<<117>>array<<117>>\right], 
  \;\;\;\;
  <<118>>\begin<<9688>>tex2html_deferred<<9688>>\bf\end<<9689>>tex2html_deferred<<9689>>g<<118>>_<<119>>f_2<<119>>=\left[\begin<<120>>array<<120>><<121>>c<<121>>-2x\\ -2y\end<<122>>array<<122>>\right], 
  \;\;\;\;
  <<123>>\begin<<9690>>tex2html_deferred<<9690>>\bf\end<<9691>>tex2html_deferred<<9691>>g<<123>>_<<124>>f_3<<124>>=\left[\begin<<125>>array<<125>><<126>>r<<126>>2x\\ -2y\end<<127>>array<<127>>\right]
  \nonumber
\end<<128>>equation<<128>>
\begin<<9692>>tex2html_deferred<<9692>>\par\end<<9693>>tex2html_deferred<<9693>>
\begin<<129>>equation<<129>>
  <<130>>\begin<<9694>>tex2html_deferred<<9694>>\bf\end<<9695>>tex2html_deferred<<9695>>H<<130>>_<<131>>f_1<<131>>=\left[\begin<<132>>array<<132>><<133>>rr<<133>>2 ;SPMamp; 0\\ 0 ;SPMamp; 2\end<<134>>array<<134>>\right];SPMgt;0;
  \;\;\;\;
  <<135>>\begin<<9696>>tex2html_deferred<<9696>>\bf\end<<9697>>tex2html_deferred<<9697>>H<<135>>_<<136>>f_2<<136>>=\left[\begin<<137>>array<<137>><<138>>rr<<138>>-2 ;SPMamp; 0\\ 0 ;SPMamp; -2\end<<139>>array<<139>>\right];SPMlt;0;
  \;\;\;\;
  <<140>>\begin<<9698>>tex2html_deferred<<9698>>\bf\end<<9699>>tex2html_deferred<<9699>>H<<140>>_<<141>>f_3<<141>>=\left[\begin<<142>>array<<142>><<143>>rr<<143>>2 ;SPMamp; 0\\ 0 ;SPMamp; -2\end<<144>>array<<144>>\right]
  \nonumber
\end<<145>>equation<<145>>
At the common stationary point \begin<<6816>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6816>>$<<146>>\begin<<9700>>tex2html_deferred<<9700>>\bf\end<<9701>>tex2html_deferred<<9701>>x<<146>>^*=[0,\,0]^T$\end<<6817>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6817>>\space for all three 
functions at which \begin<<6818>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6818>>$f_1(x,y)=f_2(x,y)=f_3(x,y)=0$\end<<6819>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6819>>, \begin<<6820>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6820>>$f_1(<<147>>\begin<<9702>>tex2html_deferred<<9702>>\bf\end<<9703>>tex2html_deferred<<9703>>x<<147>>^*)$\end<<6821>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6821>>\space is 
a minimum, \begin<<6822>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6822>>$f_2(<<148>>\begin<<9704>>tex2html_deferred<<9704>>\bf\end<<9705>>tex2html_deferred<<9705>>x<<148>>^*)$\end<<6823>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6823>>\space is a maximum, and \begin<<6824>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6824>>$f_3(<<149>>\begin<<9706>>tex2html_deferred<<9706>>\bf\end<<9707>>tex2html_deferred<<9707>>x<<149>>^*)$\end<<6825>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6825>>\space is a 
saddle point, i.e., \begin<<6826>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6826>>$f_3(<<150>>\begin<<9708>>tex2html_deferred<<9708>>\bf\end<<9709>>tex2html_deferred<<9709>>x<<150>>^*)$\end<<6827>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6827>>\space is a minimum in \begin<<6828>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6828>>$x$\end<<6829>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6829>>\space direction but 
a maximum in \begin<<6830>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6830>>$y$\end<<6831>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6831>>\space direction.
\begin<<9710>>tex2html_deferred<<9710>>\par\end<<9711>>tex2html_deferred<<9711>>
We show that the problems of minimization and equation solving can be
converted to each other.
\begin<<9712>>tex2html_deferred<<9712>>\par\end<<9713>>tex2html_deferred<<9713>>
\begin<<151>>itemize<<151>>
\item First, the problem of minimizing an objective function \begin<<6832>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6832>>$f(<<152>>\begin<<9714>>tex2html_deferred<<9714>>\bf\end<<9715>>tex2html_deferred<<9715>>x<<152>>)$\end<<6833>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6833>>
  is equivalent to solving the following equation system:
  \begin<<153>>equation<<153>> 
    <<154>>\begin<<9716>>tex2html_deferred<<9716>>\bf\end<<9717>>tex2html_deferred<<9717>>g<<154>>_f(<<155>>\begin<<9718>>tex2html_deferred<<9718>>\bf\end<<9719>>tex2html_deferred<<9719>>x<<155>>)=\bigtriangledown_<<156>>\begin<<9720>>tex2html_deferred<<9720>>\bf\end<<9721>>tex2html_deferred<<9721>>x<<156>> f(<<157>>\begin<<9722>>tex2html_deferred<<9722>>\bf\end<<9723>>tex2html_deferred<<9723>>x<<157>>)
    =\frac<<6506>>d f(<<158>>\begin<<9724>>tex2html_deferred<<9724>>\bf\end<<9725>>tex2html_deferred<<9725>>x<<158>>) <<6506>><<6507>>d<<159>>\begin<<9726>>tex2html_deferred<<9726>>\bf\end<<9727>>tex2html_deferred<<9727>>x<<159>><<6507>> 
    =\left[\begin<<160>>array<<160>><<161>>c<<161>>\partial f/\partial x_1\\ \vdots\\ 
        \partial f/\partial x_N\end<<162>>array<<162>>\right] =<<163>>\begin<<9728>>tex2html_deferred<<9728>>\bf\end<<9729>>tex2html_deferred<<9729>>0<<163>> 
  \end<<164>>equation<<164>>
  If its root \begin<<6834>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6834>>$<<165>>\begin<<9730>>tex2html_deferred<<9730>>\bf\end<<9731>>tex2html_deferred<<9731>>x<<165>>^*$\end<<6835>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6835>>\space is not a saddle point, it is the solution of the
  optimization problem that either maximizes or minimizes \begin<<6836>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6836>>$f(<<166>>\begin<<9732>>tex2html_deferred<<9732>>\bf\end<<9733>>tex2html_deferred<<9733>>x<<166>>)$\end<<6837>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6837>>. 
\begin<<9734>>tex2html_deferred<<9734>>\par\end<<9735>>tex2html_deferred<<9735>>
This equation system can be solved by any of the methods discussed previously,
  such as the \htmladdnormallink<<167>>Newton-Raphson method<<167>><<168>>../ch2/node6.html<<168>>,
  which finds the root of a general equation \begin<<6838>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6838>>$<<169>>\begin<<9736>>tex2html_deferred<<9736>>\bf\end<<9737>>tex2html_deferred<<9737>>f<<169>>(<<170>>\begin<<9738>>tex2html_deferred<<9738>>\bf\end<<9739>>tex2html_deferred<<9739>>x<<170>>)=<<171>>\begin<<9740>>tex2html_deferred<<9740>>\bf\end<<9741>>tex2html_deferred<<9741>>0<<171>>$\end<<6839>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6839>>\space by the 
  iteration \begin<<6840>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6840>>$<<172>>\begin<<9742>>tex2html_deferred<<9742>>\bf\end<<9743>>tex2html_deferred<<9743>>x<<172>>_<<173>>n+1<<173>>=<<174>>\begin<<9744>>tex2html_deferred<<9744>>\bf\end<<9745>>tex2html_deferred<<9745>>x<<174>>_n-<<175>>\begin<<9746>>tex2html_deferred<<9746>>\bf\end<<9747>>tex2html_deferred<<9747>>J<<175>>_f^<<176>>-1<<176>>(<<177>>\begin<<9748>>tex2html_deferred<<9748>>\bf\end<<9749>>tex2html_deferred<<9749>>x<<177>>_n)\,<<178>>\begin<<9750>>tex2html_deferred<<9750>>\bf\end<<9751>>tex2html_deferred<<9751>>f<<178>>(<<179>>\begin<<9752>>tex2html_deferred<<9752>>\bf\end<<9753>>tex2html_deferred<<9753>>x<<179>>_n)$\end<<6841>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6841>>. 
  Here, specifically, to solve the equation \begin<<6842>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6842>>$<<180>>\begin<<9754>>tex2html_deferred<<9754>>\bf\end<<9755>>tex2html_deferred<<9755>>g<<180>>_f(<<181>>\begin<<9756>>tex2html_deferred<<9756>>\bf\end<<9757>>tex2html_deferred<<9757>>x<<181>>)=<<182>>\begin<<9758>>tex2html_deferred<<9758>>\bf\end<<9759>>tex2html_deferred<<9759>>0<<182>>$\end<<6843>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6843>>, we
  first get the Jacobian \begin<<6844>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6844>>$<<183>>\begin<<9760>>tex2html_deferred<<9760>>\bf\end<<9761>>tex2html_deferred<<9761>>J<<183>>_g(<<184>>\begin<<9762>>tex2html_deferred<<9762>>\bf\end<<9763>>tex2html_deferred<<9763>>x<<184>>)=<<185>>\begin<<9764>>tex2html_deferred<<9764>>\bf\end<<9765>>tex2html_deferred<<9765>>H<<185>>_f(<<186>>\begin<<9766>>tex2html_deferred<<9766>>\bf\end<<9767>>tex2html_deferred<<9767>>x<<186>>)$\end<<6845>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6845>>\space of the gradient
  \begin<<6846>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6846>>$<<187>>\begin<<9768>>tex2html_deferred<<9768>>\bf\end<<9769>>tex2html_deferred<<9769>>g<<187>>_f(<<188>>\begin<<9770>>tex2html_deferred<<9770>>\bf\end<<9771>>tex2html_deferred<<9771>>x<<188>>)$\end<<6847>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6847>>\space of \begin<<6848>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6848>>$f(<<189>>\begin<<9772>>tex2html_deferred<<9772>>\bf\end<<9773>>tex2html_deferred<<9773>>x<<189>>)$\end<<6849>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6849>>, which is the Hessian of \begin<<6850>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6850>>$f(<<190>>\begin<<9774>>tex2html_deferred<<9774>>\bf\end<<9775>>tex2html_deferred<<9775>>x<<190>>)$\end<<6851>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6851>>, 
  and then carry out the iteration below to eventually find \begin<<6852>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6852>>$<<191>>\begin<<9776>>tex2html_deferred<<9776>>\bf\end<<9777>>tex2html_deferred<<9777>>x<<191>>^*$\end<<6853>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6853>>\space that 
  minimizes \begin<<6854>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6854>>$f(<<192>>\begin<<9778>>tex2html_deferred<<9778>>\bf\end<<9779>>tex2html_deferred<<9779>>x<<192>>)$\end<<6855>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6855>>:
  \begin<<193>>equation<<193>>
    <<194>>\begin<<9780>>tex2html_deferred<<9780>>\bf\end<<9781>>tex2html_deferred<<9781>>x<<194>>_<<195>>n+1<<195>>=<<196>>\begin<<9782>>tex2html_deferred<<9782>>\bf\end<<9783>>tex2html_deferred<<9783>>x<<196>>_n-<<197>>\begin<<9784>>tex2html_deferred<<9784>>\bf\end<<9785>>tex2html_deferred<<9785>>J<<197>>_g^<<198>>-1<<198>>(<<199>>\begin<<9786>>tex2html_deferred<<9786>>\bf\end<<9787>>tex2html_deferred<<9787>>x<<199>>_n)\,<<200>>\begin<<9788>>tex2html_deferred<<9788>>\bf\end<<9789>>tex2html_deferred<<9789>>g<<200>>_f(<<201>>\begin<<9790>>tex2html_deferred<<9790>>\bf\end<<9791>>tex2html_deferred<<9791>>x<<201>>_n)
    =<<202>>\begin<<9792>>tex2html_deferred<<9792>>\bf\end<<9793>>tex2html_deferred<<9793>>x<<202>>_n-<<203>>\begin<<9794>>tex2html_deferred<<9794>>\bf\end<<9795>>tex2html_deferred<<9795>>H<<203>>_g^<<204>>-1<<204>>(<<205>>\begin<<9796>>tex2html_deferred<<9796>>\bf\end<<9797>>tex2html_deferred<<9797>>x<<205>>_n)\,<<206>>\begin<<9798>>tex2html_deferred<<9798>>\bf\end<<9799>>tex2html_deferred<<9799>>g<<206>>_f(<<207>>\begin<<9800>>tex2html_deferred<<9800>>\bf\end<<9801>>tex2html_deferred<<9801>>x<<207>>_n)
  \end<<208>>equation<<208>>
  The second equality is due to the fact that the Jacobian of the gradient
  \begin<<6856>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6856>>$<<209>>\begin<<9802>>tex2html_deferred<<9802>>\bf\end<<9803>>tex2html_deferred<<9803>>g<<209>>_f$\end<<6857>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6857>>\space of function \begin<<6858>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6858>>$<<210>>\begin<<9804>>tex2html_deferred<<9804>>\bf\end<<9805>>tex2html_deferred<<9805>>f<<210>>(<<211>>\begin<<9806>>tex2html_deferred<<9806>>\bf\end<<9807>>tex2html_deferred<<9807>>x<<211>>)$\end<<6859>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6859>>\space is the Hessian of the function,
  i.e., \begin<<6860>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6860>>$<<212>>\begin<<9808>>tex2html_deferred<<9808>>\bf\end<<9809>>tex2html_deferred<<9809>>J<<212>>_g=<<213>>\begin<<9810>>tex2html_deferred<<9810>>\bf\end<<9811>>tex2html_deferred<<9811>>H<<213>>_f$\end<<6861>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6861>>.
\begin<<9812>>tex2html_deferred<<9812>>\par\end<<9813>>tex2html_deferred<<9813>>
\item On the other hand, to solve the equation system 
  \begin<<6862>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6862>>$<<214>>\begin<<9814>>tex2html_deferred<<9814>>\bf\end<<9815>>tex2html_deferred<<9815>>g<<214>>(<<215>>\begin<<9816>>tex2html_deferred<<9816>>\bf\end<<9817>>tex2html_deferred<<9817>>x<<215>>)=[g_1(<<216>>\begin<<9818>>tex2html_deferred<<9818>>\bf\end<<9819>>tex2html_deferred<<9819>>x<<216>>),\cdots,g_N(<<217>>\begin<<9820>>tex2html_deferred<<9820>>\bf\end<<9821>>tex2html_deferred<<9821>>x<<217>>)]^T=<<218>>\begin<<9822>>tex2html_deferred<<9822>>\bf\end<<9823>>tex2html_deferred<<9823>>0<<218>>$\end<<6863>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6863>>, 
  we can minimize the objective function defined as
  \begin<<219>>equation<<219>>
    f(<<220>>\begin<<9824>>tex2html_deferred<<9824>>\bf\end<<9825>>tex2html_deferred<<9825>>x<<220>>)=\frac<<221>>1<<221>><<222>>2<<222>><<223>>\begin<<9826>>tex2html_deferred<<9826>>\bf\end<<9827>>tex2html_deferred<<9827>>g<<223>>^T(<<224>>\begin<<9828>>tex2html_deferred<<9828>>\bf\end<<9829>>tex2html_deferred<<9829>>x<<224>>)<<225>>\begin<<9830>>tex2html_deferred<<9830>>\bf\end<<9831>>tex2html_deferred<<9831>>g<<225>>(<<226>>\begin<<9832>>tex2html_deferred<<9832>>\bf\end<<9833>>tex2html_deferred<<9833>>x<<226>>)
    =\frac<<227>>1<<227>><<228>>2<<228>>||<<229>>\begin<<9834>>tex2html_deferred<<9834>>\bf\end<<9835>>tex2html_deferred<<9835>>g<<229>>(<<230>>\begin<<9836>>tex2html_deferred<<9836>>\bf\end<<9837>>tex2html_deferred<<9837>>x<<230>>)||^2 
    =\frac<<231>>1<<231>><<232>>2<<232>>\sum_<<233>>i=1<<233>>^N |g_i(<<234>>\begin<<9838>>tex2html_deferred<<9838>>\bf\end<<9839>>tex2html_deferred<<9839>>x<<234>>)|^2
  \end<<235>>equation<<235>>
  To solve this minimization problem, we solve the equations:
  \begin<<236>>equation<<236>>
    \frac<<6741>>\partial<<6508>>f(<<237>>\begin<<9840>>tex2html_deferred<<9840>>\bf\end<<9841>>tex2html_deferred<<9841>>x<<237>>)<<6508>><<6741>><<238>>\partial x_j<<238>>
    =\frac<<239>>\partial<<239>><<240>>\partial x_j<<240>>\left(\frac<<241>>1<<241>><<242>>2<<242>>\sum_<<243>>i=1<<243>>^N (g_i(<<244>>\begin<<9842>>tex2html_deferred<<9842>>\bf\end<<9843>>tex2html_deferred<<9843>>x<<244>>))^2\right)
    =\sum_<<245>>i=1<<245>>^N g_i(<<246>>\begin<<9844>>tex2html_deferred<<9844>>\bf\end<<9845>>tex2html_deferred<<9845>>x<<246>>)\frac<<6509>>\partial g_i(<<247>>\begin<<9846>>tex2html_deferred<<9846>>\bf\end<<9847>>tex2html_deferred<<9847>>x<<247>>)<<6509>><<248>>\partial x_j<<248>>=0,\;\;\;\;\;\;
    (j=1,\cdots,N)
  \end<<249>>equation<<249>>
  Combining all \begin<<6864>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6864>>$N$\end<<6865>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6865>>\space of such equations we get the gradient vector of
  function \begin<<6866>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6866>>$f(<<250>>\begin<<9848>>tex2html_deferred<<9848>>\bf\end<<9849>>tex2html_deferred<<9849>>x<<250>>)=<<251>>\begin<<9850>>tex2html_deferred<<9850>>\bf\end<<9851>>tex2html_deferred<<9851>>g<<251>>^T<<252>>\begin<<9852>>tex2html_deferred<<9852>>\bf\end<<9853>>tex2html_deferred<<9853>>g<<252>>$\end<<6867>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6867>>:
  \begin<<253>>equation<<253>>
    \bigtriangledown_<<254>>\begin<<9854>>tex2html_deferred<<9854>>\bf\end<<9855>>tex2html_deferred<<9855>>x<<254>> f(<<255>>\begin<<9856>>tex2html_deferred<<9856>>\bf\end<<9857>>tex2html_deferred<<9857>>x<<255>>)
    =\frac<<256>>d<<256>><<6510>>d<<257>>\begin<<9858>>tex2html_deferred<<9858>>\bf\end<<9859>>tex2html_deferred<<9859>>x<<257>><<6510>>\left[\frac<<258>>1<<258>><<259>>2<<259>><<260>>\begin<<9860>>tex2html_deferred<<9860>>\bf\end<<9861>>tex2html_deferred<<9861>>g<<260>>^T(<<261>>\begin<<9862>>tex2html_deferred<<9862>>\bf\end<<9863>>tex2html_deferred<<9863>>x<<261>>)<<262>>\begin<<9864>>tex2html_deferred<<9864>>\bf\end<<9865>>tex2html_deferred<<9865>>g<<262>>(<<263>>\begin<<9866>>tex2html_deferred<<9866>>\bf\end<<9867>>tex2html_deferred<<9867>>x<<263>>) \right]
    =\frac<<264>>d<<264>><<6511>>d<<265>>\begin<<9868>>tex2html_deferred<<9868>>\bf\end<<9869>>tex2html_deferred<<9869>>x<<265>><<6511>><<266>>\begin<<9870>>tex2html_deferred<<9870>>\bf\end<<9871>>tex2html_deferred<<9871>>g<<266>>(<<267>>\begin<<9872>>tex2html_deferred<<9872>>\bf\end<<9873>>tex2html_deferred<<9873>>x<<267>>)\;\;<<268>>\begin<<9874>>tex2html_deferred<<9874>>\bf\end<<9875>>tex2html_deferred<<9875>>g<<268>>(<<269>>\begin<<9876>>tex2html_deferred<<9876>>\bf\end<<9877>>tex2html_deferred<<9877>>x<<269>>)
    =<<270>>\begin<<9878>>tex2html_deferred<<9878>>\bf\end<<9879>>tex2html_deferred<<9879>>J<<270>>_<<271>>\begin<<9880>>tex2html_deferred<<9880>>\bf\end<<9881>>tex2html_deferred<<9881>>g<<271>> (<<272>>\begin<<9882>>tex2html_deferred<<9882>>\bf\end<<9883>>tex2html_deferred<<9883>>x<<272>>)\,<<273>>\begin<<9884>>tex2html_deferred<<9884>>\bf\end<<9885>>tex2html_deferred<<9885>>g<<273>>(<<274>>\begin<<9886>>tex2html_deferred<<9886>>\bf\end<<9887>>tex2html_deferred<<9887>>x<<274>>)=<<275>>\begin<<9888>>tex2html_deferred<<9888>>\bf\end<<9889>>tex2html_deferred<<9889>>0<<275>> 
  \end<<276>>equation<<276>>
  where \begin<<6868>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6868>>$<<277>>\begin<<9890>>tex2html_deferred<<9890>>\bf\end<<9891>>tex2html_deferred<<9891>>J<<277>>_<<278>>\begin<<9892>>tex2html_deferred<<9892>>\bf\end<<9893>>tex2html_deferred<<9893>>g<<278>> (<<279>>\begin<<9894>>tex2html_deferred<<9894>>\bf\end<<9895>>tex2html_deferred<<9895>>x<<279>>)$\end<<6869>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6869>>\space is the Jicobian of \begin<<6870>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6870>>$<<280>>\begin<<9896>>tex2html_deferred<<9896>>\bf\end<<9897>>tex2html_deferred<<9897>>g<<280>>(<<281>>\begin<<9898>>tex2html_deferred<<9898>>\bf\end<<9899>>tex2html_deferred<<9899>>x<<281>>)$\end<<6871>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6871>>.
  As in general \begin<<6872>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6872>>$<<282>>\begin<<9900>>tex2html_deferred<<9900>>\bf\end<<9901>>tex2html_deferred<<9901>>J<<282>>_<<283>>\begin<<9902>>tex2html_deferred<<9902>>\bf\end<<9903>>tex2html_deferred<<9903>>g<<283>>(<<284>>\begin<<9904>>tex2html_deferred<<9904>>\bf\end<<9905>>tex2html_deferred<<9905>>x<<284>>)$\end<<6873>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6873>>\space has full rank, the homogeneous 
  equation above only has a zero solution \begin<<6874>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6874>>$<<285>>\begin<<9906>>tex2html_deferred<<9906>>\bf\end<<9907>>tex2html_deferred<<9907>>g<<285>>(<<286>>\begin<<9908>>tex2html_deferred<<9908>>\bf\end<<9909>>tex2html_deferred<<9909>>x<<286>>)=<<287>>\begin<<9910>>tex2html_deferred<<9910>>\bf\end<<9911>>tex2html_deferred<<9911>>0<<287>>$\end<<6875>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6875>>. 
\begin<<9912>>tex2html_deferred<<9912>>\par\end<<9913>>tex2html_deferred<<9913>>
\end<<288>>itemize<<288>>
\begin<<9914>>tex2html_deferred<<9914>>\par\end<<9915>>tex2html_deferred<<9915>>
\section*<<289>>Unconstrained Optimization<<289>>
\begin<<9916>>tex2html_deferred<<9916>>\par\end<<9917>>tex2html_deferred<<9917>>
\subsection*<<290>>Golden section search<<290>>
\begin<<9918>>tex2html_deferred<<9918>>\par\end<<9919>>tex2html_deferred<<9919>>
The golden section search algorithm can be used for finding a minimum (or
maximum) of a single-variable function \begin<<6876>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6876>>$f(x)$\end<<6877>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6877>>. If it is known that the
function has a minimum between some two points, then we can search for it 
iteratively, in a manner similar to the bisection search for the root of 
an equation \begin<<6878>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6878>>$f(x)=0$\end<<6879>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6879>>. Specifically, if in the neighborhood of the minimum
we can find three points \begin<<6880>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6880>>$x_0;SPMlt;x_1;SPMlt;x_2$\end<<6881>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6881>>\space corresponding to \begin<<6882>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6882>>$f(x_0);SPMgt;f(x_1);SPMlt;f(x_2)$\end<<6883>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6883>>,
then there exists a minimum between \begin<<6884>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6884>>$x_0$\end<<6885>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6885>>\space and \begin<<6886>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6886>>$x_2$\end<<6887>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6887>>. To search for this
minimum, we can choose another point \begin<<6888>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6888>>$x_3$\end<<6889>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6889>>\space between \begin<<6890>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6890>>$x_1$\end<<6891>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6891>>\space and \begin<<6892>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6892>>$x_2$\end<<6893>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6893>>\space as shown
in the figure below, with the following two possible outcomes:
\begin<<291>>itemize<<291>>
\item If \begin<<6894>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6894>>$f(x_3)=f_<<292>>3a<<292>>;SPMgt;f(x_1)$\end<<6895>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6895>>, the minimum is inside the interval \begin<<6896>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6896>>$x_3-x_0=a+c$\end<<6897>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6897>> 
  associated with three new points \begin<<6898>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6898>>$x_0;SPMlt;x_1;SPMlt;x_3$\end<<6899>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6899>>, i.e., \begin<<6900>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6900>>$x_2$\end<<6901>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6901>>\space is replaced by 
  \begin<<6902>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6902>>$x_3$\end<<6903>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6903>>.
\item If \begin<<6904>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6904>>$f(x_3)=f_<<293>>3b<<293>>;SPMlt;f(x_1)$\end<<6905>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6905>>, the minimum is inside the interval \begin<<6906>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6906>>$x_2-x_1=b$\end<<6907>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6907>>
  associated with three new points \begin<<6908>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6908>>$x_1;SPMlt;x_3;SPMlt;x_2$\end<<6909>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6909>>, i.e., \begin<<6910>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6910>>$x_0$\end<<6911>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6911>>\space is replaced by 
  \begin<<6912>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6912>>$x_1$\end<<6913>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6913>>.
\end<<294>>itemize<<294>>
In either case, the new search interval \begin<<6914>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6914>>$x_3-x_0=a+c$\end<<6915>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6915>>\space or \begin<<6916>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6916>>$x_2-x_1=b$\end<<6917>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6917>>\space is 
smaller than the old one \begin<<6918>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6918>>$x_2-x_0=a+b$\end<<6919>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6919>>, i.e., such an iteration is guaranteed
to converge. Of course \begin<<6920>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6920>>$x_3$\end<<6921>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6921>>\space can also be between \begin<<6922>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6922>>$x_0$\end<<6923>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6923>>\space and \begin<<6924>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6924>>$x_1$\end<<6925>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6925>>, the 
iteration can be similarly carried out accordingly.
\begin<<9920>>tex2html_deferred<<9920>>\par\end<<9921>>tex2html_deferred<<9921>>
\htmladdimg<<295>>figures/GoldenRatio.png<<295>>
\begin<<9922>>tex2html_deferred<<9922>>\par\end<<9923>>tex2html_deferred<<9923>>
Similar to the bisection search for the root of \begin<<6926>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6926>>$f(x)=0$\end<<6927>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6927>>, here to search
for the minimum of \begin<<6928>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6928>>$f(x)$\end<<6929>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6929>>, we also want to avoid the worst possible case 
in which the minimum always happens to be in the larger one of the two 
sections \begin<<6930>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6930>>$a+c$\end<<6931>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6931>>\space and \begin<<6932>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6932>>$b$\end<<6933>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6933>>. We therefore choose \begin<<6934>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6934>>$x_3$\end<<6935>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6935>>\space in such a way that the
two resulting search intervals will always be the same:
\begin<<296>>equation<<296>>
  a+c=b,\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\mbox<<297>>i.e.<<297>>\;\;\;\;\;\;\;c=b-a
\end<<298>>equation<<298>>
In other words, through out the iteration, the search interval should 
always be partitioned into two sections with the same ratio:
\begin<<299>>equation<<299>> 
  \frac<<300>>a+b<<300>><<301>>b<<301>>=\frac<<302>>a+c<<302>><<303>>a<<303>>=\frac<<304>>b<<304>><<305>>a<<305>>
  \;\;\;\;\;\mbox<<306>>or<<306>>\;\;\;\;\;
  \frac<<307>>a+b<<307>><<308>>b<<308>>=\frac<<309>>b<<309>><<310>>b-c<<310>>=\frac<<311>>b<<311>><<312>>a<<312>>
\end<<313>>equation<<313>>
In either case, we get
\begin<<314>>equation<<314>> 
  a^2+ab-b^2=0 
\end<<315>>equation<<315>>
Solving this quadratic equation for \begin<<6936>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6936>>$a$\end<<6937>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6937>>\space in terms of \begin<<6938>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6938>>$b$\end<<6939>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6939>>\space we get
\begin<<316>>equation<<316>>
  a_<<317>>1,2<<317>>=\frac<<6512>>-1\pm\sqrt<<318>>5<<318>><<6512>><<319>>2<<319>>\;b 
  =\left\{\begin<<320>>array<<320>><<321>>r<<321>>0.618\,b\\ -1.618\,b\end<<322>>array<<322>>\right.
\end<<323>>equation<<323>>
We keep the positive result and get
\begin<<324>>equation<<324>> 
 \frac<<325>>a<<325>><<326>>b<<326>>=0.618,\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;
 \frac<<327>>b<<327>><<328>>a+b<<328>>=\frac<<329>>b<<329>><<330>>0.618b+b<<330>>=\frac<<331>>1<<331>><<332>>1.618<<332>>=0.618 
\end<<333>>equation<<333>>
This is the <<334>>\begin<<9924>>tex2html_deferred<<9924>>\em\end<<9925>>tex2html_deferred<<9925>>golden ratio<<334>> between the two sections \begin<<6940>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6940>>$a$\end<<6941>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6941>>\space and \begin<<6942>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6942>>$b$\end<<6943>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6943>>\space of 
the search interval.
\begin<<9926>>tex2html_deferred<<9926>>\par\end<<9927>>tex2html_deferred<<9927>>
The iteration of the golden section search can terminate when the size 
of the search brackets \begin<<6944>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6944>>$|x_2-x_0|$\end<<6945>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6945>>\space is small enough, compared with some
tolerance, such as \begin<<6946>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6946>>$10^<<335>>-9<<335>>$\end<<6947>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6947>>, pre-determined based on some prior knowledge 
of the scale of the problem. However, this scale may be unknown, or it may
vary drastically, and an absolute tolerance may be too large for a small 
scale problem but too small for a large scale problem. This problem can 
be resolved by using a relative tolerance with a scale comparable with 
that of the size of the problem:
\begin<<336>>equation<<336>> 
  |x_2-x_0| ;SPMlt; \epsilon(|x_1|+|x_3|)
\end<<337>>equation<<337>>
where \begin<<6948>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6948>>$\epsilon$\end<<6949>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6949>>\space is a small value such as \begin<<6950>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6950>>$10^<<338>>-9<<338>>$\end<<6951>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6951>>, and \begin<<6952>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6952>>$|x_2-x_0|$\end<<6953>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6953>>
represents the size of the search interval and \begin<<6954>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6954>>$|x_1|+|x_3|$\end<<6955>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6955>>\space represents
the scale of the problem. When the inequality is satisfied, the iteration 
is terminated.
\begin<<9928>>tex2html_deferred<<9928>>\par\end<<9929>>tex2html_deferred<<9929>>
It is possible that the three initial points chosen are such that either 
\begin<<6956>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6956>>$f(x_0);SPMlt;f(x_1);SPMlt;f(x_2)$\end<<6957>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6957>>\space or \begin<<6958>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6958>>$f(x_0);SPMgt;f(x_1);SPMgt;f(x_2)$\end<<6959>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6959>>, then we have to search 
toward the descending direction of \begin<<6960>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6960>>$f(x)$\end<<6961>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6961>>\space until it starts to ascend. 
For example, if \begin<<6962>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6962>>$f(x_0);SPMgt;f(x_1);SPMgt;f(x_2)$\end<<6963>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6963>>, they can be iteratively updated 
by the following
\begin<<339>>equation<<339>> 
  x^<<340>>new<<340>>_0=x^<<341>>old<<341>>_1,\;\;\;\;x^<<342>>new<<342>>_1=x^<<343>>old<<343>>_2,
  \;\;\;\;x^<<344>>new<<344>>_2=x^<<345>>old<<345>>_2+c(x^<<346>>old<<346>>_2-x^<<347>>old<<347>>_1) 
\end<<348>>equation<<348>>
where \begin<<6964>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6964>>$c;SPMgt;1$\end<<6965>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6965>>\space (e.g., \begin<<6966>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6966>>$c=1.618$\end<<6967>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6967>>), until we reach a point \begin<<6968>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6968>>$x_2$\end<<6969>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6969>>\space at which
\begin<<6970>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6970>>$f(x_2);SPMgt;f(x_1)$\end<<6971>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6971>>. Obviously the distance \begin<<6972>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6972>>$d=x_2-x_1$\end<<6973>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6973>>\space grows exponentially 
\begin<<6974>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6974>>$d\propto c^n$\end<<6975>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6975>>. 
\begin<<9930>>tex2html_deferred<<9930>>\par\end<<9931>>tex2html_deferred<<9931>>
\subsection*<<349>>Parabolic Interpolation<<349>>
\begin<<9932>>tex2html_deferred<<9932>>\par\end<<9933>>tex2html_deferred<<9933>>
If a function \begin<<6976>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6976>>$f(x)$\end<<6977>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6977>>\space can be approximated by a parabola in the neighborhood 
of its minimum, then the vertex of the parabola can be used to approximate 
the minimum. Assuming we have available three points \begin<<6978>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6978>>$a;SPMlt;b;SPMlt;c$\end<<6979>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6979>>\space on the x-axis 
corresponding to function values \begin<<6980>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6980>>$f(a);SPMgt;f(b);SPMlt;f(c)$\end<<6981>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6981>>, then a quadratic function 
\begin<<6982>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6982>>$q(x)$\end<<6983>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6983>>\space that goes through these points can be uniquely determined by the 
method of \htmladdnormallink<<350>>Lagrange interpolation<<350>>
<<351>>../ch7/node3.html<<351>>:
\begin<<352>>equation<<352>>
  q(x)=f(a)\frac<<353>>(x-b)(x-c)<<353>><<354>>(a-b)(a-c)<<354>>+f(b)\frac<<355>>(x-c)(x-a)<<355>><<356>>(b-c)(b-a)<<356>>
  +f(c)\frac<<357>>(x-a)(x-b)<<357>><<358>>(c-a)(c-b)<<358>> 
\end<<359>>equation<<359>>
To find the minimum \begin<<6984>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6984>>$q(x_<<360>>min<<360>>)$\end<<6985>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6985>>\space at the vertex of this quadratic function, 
we first set its derivative to zero:
\begin<<361>>equation<<361>> 
  q'(x)=f(a)\frac<<362>>(x-b)+(x-c)<<362>><<363>>(a-b)(a-c)<<363>>+f(b)\frac<<364>>(x-c)+(x-a)<<364>><<365>>(b-c)(b-a)<<365>>
  +f(c)\frac<<366>>(x-a)+(x-b)<<366>><<367>>(c-a)(c-b)<<367>>=0 
\end<<368>>equation<<368>>
and multiply both sides by \begin<<6986>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6986>>$(a-b)(b-c)(c-a)$\end<<6987>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6987>>:
\begin<<369>>eqnarray<<369>>
  ;SPMamp;;SPMamp;f(a)(c-b)(2x-b-c)+f(b)(a-c)(2x-c-a)+f(c)(b-a)(2x-a-b)
  \nonumber \\ 
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;2x[f(a)(c-b)+f(b)(a-c)+f(c)(b-a)]
  -[f(a)(c^2-b^2)+f(b)(a^2-c^2)+f(c)(b^2-a^2)]=0 
\end<<370>>eqnarray<<370>>
and then solve the equation for \begin<<6988>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6988>>$x$\end<<6989>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6989>>\space to get:
\begin<<371>>eqnarray<<371>>
  x_<<372>>min<<372>>;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;\frac<<373>>1<<373>><<374>>2<<374>>\frac<<375>>f(a)(c^2-b^2)+f(b)(a^2-c^2)+f(c)(b^2-a^2)<<375>><<376>>f(a)(c-b)+f(b)(a-c)+f(c)(b-a)<<376>>
  \nonumber \\ 
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;b+\frac<<377>>1<<377>><<378>>2<<378>>\frac<<379>>f(a)(c-b)(c+b-2b)+f(b)(a-c)(a+c-2b)+f(c)(b-a)(b+a-2b)<<379>><<380>>f(a)(c-b)+f(b)(a-c)+f(c)(b-a)<<380>> 
  \nonumber \\ 
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;b+\frac<<381>>1<<381>><<382>>2<<382>>\frac<<383>>f(a)(c-b)^2+f(b)(a-c)(a+c-2b)-f(c)(b-a)^2<<383>><<384>>f(a)(c-b)+f(b)(a-c)+f(c)(b-a)<<384>> 
  \nonumber \\ 
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;b+\frac<<385>>1<<385>><<386>>2<<386>>\frac<<387>>[f(a)-f(b)](c-b)^2-[f(c)-f(b)](b-a)^2<<387>><<388>>[f(a)-f(b)](c-b)+[f(c)-f(b)](b-a)<<388>> 
  \label<<389>>vertex<<389>>
\end<<390>>eqnarray<<390>>
Unless \begin<<6990>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6990>>$b$\end<<6991>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6991>>\space is already at the vertex of \begin<<6992>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6992>>$q(x)$\end<<6993>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6993>>, \begin<<6994>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6994>>$f(x_<<391>>min<<391>>)$\end<<6995>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6995>>\space is smaller than 
\begin<<6996>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6996>>$f(b)$\end<<6997>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6997>>, i.e., \begin<<6998>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6998>>$x_<<392>>min<<392>>$\end<<6999>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<6999>>\space is closer to the minimum of \begin<<7000>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7000>>$f(x)$\end<<7001>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7001>>\space than \begin<<7002>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7002>>$b$\end<<7003>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7003>>. This 
interpolation process can then be repeated using a set of three new points 
of \begin<<7004>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7004>>$\{a, x_<<393>>min<<393>>, b\}$\end<<7005>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7005>>\space if \begin<<7006>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7006>>$x_<<394>>min<<394>>;SPMlt;b$\end<<7007>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7007>>\space or \begin<<7008>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7008>>$\{b, x_<<395>>min<<395>>, c\}$\end<<7009>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7009>>\space if \begin<<7010>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7010>>$x_<<396>>min<<396>>;SPMgt;b$\end<<7011>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7011>>.
\begin<<9934>>tex2html_deferred<<9934>>\par\end<<9935>>tex2html_deferred<<9935>>
In the unlikely case where the numerator of the second term in 
Eq. (\ref<<397>>vertex<<397>>) is zero, i.e., \begin<<7012>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7012>>$[f(a)-f(b)](c-b)^2=[f(c)-f(b)](b-a)^2$\end<<7013>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7013>>,
we get \begin<<7014>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7014>>$x_<<398>>min<<398>>=b$\end<<7015>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7015>>\space and the iteration cannot proceed. We could choose some 
different point nearby to proceed.
\begin<<9936>>tex2html_deferred<<9936>>\par\end<<9937>>tex2html_deferred<<9937>>
\htmladdimg<<399>>figures/ParabolicInterpolate.png<<399>>
\htmladdimg<<400>>figures/ParabolicInterpolate1.png<<400>>
\begin<<9938>>tex2html_deferred<<9938>>\par\end<<9939>>tex2html_deferred<<9939>>
\subsection*<<401>>Nelder-Mead method<<401>>
\begin<<9940>>tex2html_deferred<<9940>>\par\end<<9941>>tex2html_deferred<<9941>>
<<402>>\begin<<9942>>tex2html_deferred<<9942>>\em\end<<9943>>tex2html_deferred<<9943>>There are occasions where it has been spectacularly good ...
Mathematicians hate it because you can’t prove convergence; engineers
seem to love it because it often works.<<402>> ---- John Nelder
\begin<<9944>>tex2html_deferred<<9944>>\par\end<<9945>>tex2html_deferred<<9945>>
The <<403>>\begin<<9946>>tex2html_deferred<<9946>>\em\end<<9947>>tex2html_deferred<<9947>>Nelder-Mead (NM) method<<403>> (also called <<404>>\begin<<9948>>tex2html_deferred<<9948>>\em\end<<9949>>tex2html_deferred<<9949>>downhill simplex 
method<<404>> is a heuristic (search method for minimizing an objective 
function \begin<<7016>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7016>>$f(<<405>>\begin<<9950>>tex2html_deferred<<9950>>\bf\end<<9951>>tex2html_deferred<<9951>>x<<405>>$\end<<7017>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7017>>\space given in an N-dimensional space. The key 
concept of the mehtod is the \htmladdnormallink<<406>>\begin<<9952>>tex2html_deferred<<9952>>\em\end<<9953>>tex2html_deferred<<9953>>simplex<<406>>
<<407>>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simplex<<407>>, an \begin<<7018>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7018>>$N$\end<<7019>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7019>>\space dimensional 
\htmladdnormallink<<408>>polytope<<408>><<409>>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polytope<<409>>
that is a \htmladdnormallink<<410>>convex hull<<410>>
<<411>>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Convex_hull<<411>> of a set of \begin<<7020>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7020>>$N+1$\end<<7021>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7021>> 
linearly independent points \begin<<7022>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7022>>$<<412>>\begin<<9954>>tex2html_deferred<<9954>>\bf\end<<9955>>tex2html_deferred<<9955>>x<<412>>_0,\cdots,<<413>>\begin<<9956>>tex2html_deferred<<9956>>\bf\end<<9957>>tex2html_deferred<<9957>>x<<413>>_N$\end<<7023>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7023>>. These
points are linearly independent in the sense that the \begin<<7024>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7024>>$N$\end<<7025>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7025>>\space vectors
\begin<<7026>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7026>>$<<414>>\begin<<9958>>tex2html_deferred<<9958>>\bf\end<<9959>>tex2html_deferred<<9959>>x<<414>>_i=<<415>>\begin<<9960>>tex2html_deferred<<9960>>\bf\end<<9961>>tex2html_deferred<<9961>>x<<415>>_0\\ ;\;(i=1,\cdots,N)$\end<<7027>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7027>>\space are linearliy independent
(no three points are colinear):
\begin<<416>>equation<<416>>
  S=\left\{\sum_<<417>>i=0<<417>>^Nc_i<<418>>\begin<<9962>>tex2html_deferred<<9962>>\bf\end<<9963>>tex2html_deferred<<9963>>x<<418>>_i \;\bigg|\;\sum_<<419>>i=0<<419>>^Nc_i=1,\;\;\;\;c_i\ge 0\right\}
\end<<420>>equation<<420>>
Intuitively, a simplex is a volumn in the N-D space enclosed by 
flat surfaces and spanned by \begin<<7028>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7028>>$N+1$\end<<7029>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7029>>\space verticies. For example, a 
simplex is a line sigment spanned by 2 points in 1-D space, a 
triangle spanned by 3 points in 2-D space, and a tetrahedron
spanned by 4 points in 3-D space.
\begin<<9964>>tex2html_deferred<<9964>>\par\end<<9965>>tex2html_deferred<<9965>>
The NM method is an iterative process which transforms an 
initial simplex iteratively into a different one following a
path in the space along which the function values are progressively 
reduced. The initial simplex can be generated based on a single
point \begin<<7030>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7030>>$<<421>>\begin<<9966>>tex2html_deferred<<9966>>\bf\end<<9967>>tex2html_deferred<<9967>>x<<421>>_0$\end<<7031>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7031>>, an initial guess, by adding a constant along
each of the \begin<<7032>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7032>>$N$\end<<7033>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7033>>\space dimensions spanned by the standard basis
\begin<<7034>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7034>>$\{<<422>>\begin<<9968>>tex2html_deferred<<9968>>\bf\end<<9969>>tex2html_deferred<<9969>>e<<422>>_1,\cdots,<<423>>\begin<<9970>>tex2html_deferred<<9970>>\bf\end<<9971>>tex2html_deferred<<9971>>e<<423>>_N\}$\end<<7035>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7035>>:
\begin<<424>>equation<<424>>
  <<425>>\begin<<9972>>tex2html_deferred<<9972>>\bf\end<<9973>>tex2html_deferred<<9973>>x<<425>>_i=<<426>>\begin<<9974>>tex2html_deferred<<9974>>\bf\end<<9975>>tex2html_deferred<<9975>>x<<426>>_0+c<<427>>\begin<<9976>>tex2html_deferred<<9976>>\bf\end<<9977>>tex2html_deferred<<9977>>e<<427>>_i
\end<<428>>equation<<428>>
In the subsequent iterations, the initial simplex is transformed 
based on four parameters:
\begin<<429>>itemize<<429>>
\item <<430>>\begin<<9978>>tex2html_deferred<<9978>>\em\end<<9979>>tex2html_deferred<<9979>>reflection coefficient:<<430>> \begin<<7036>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7036>>$\alpha;SPMgt;0$\end<<7037>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7037>>, e.g., \begin<<7038>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7038>>$\alpha=1$\end<<7039>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7039>>\space  
\item <<431>>\begin<<9980>>tex2html_deferred<<9980>>\em\end<<9981>>tex2html_deferred<<9981>>expansion coefficient:<<431>> \begin<<7040>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7040>>$0;SPMlt;\beta;SPMlt;1$\end<<7041>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7041>>, e.g., \begin<<7042>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7042>>$\beta=1/2$\end<<7043>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7043>>\space  
\item <<432>>\begin<<9982>>tex2html_deferred<<9982>>\em\end<<9983>>tex2html_deferred<<9983>>contraction coefficient:<<432>> \begin<<7044>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7044>>$\gamma;SPMgt;1$\end<<7045>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7045>>, e.g., \begin<<7046>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7046>>$\gamma=2$\end<<7047>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7047>>\space  
\item <<433>>\begin<<9984>>tex2html_deferred<<9984>>\em\end<<9985>>tex2html_deferred<<9985>>shrink coefficient:<<433>> \begin<<7048>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7048>>$0;SPMlt;\delta;SPMlt;1$\end<<7049>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7049>>, e.g., \begin<<7050>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7050>>$\delta=1/2$\end<<7051>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7051>>\space  
\end<<434>>itemize<<434>>
\begin<<9986>>tex2html_deferred<<9986>>\par\end<<9987>>tex2html_deferred<<9987>>
Specially here are the steps in each iteration:
\begin<<435>>itemize<<435>>
\item <<436>>\begin<<9988>>tex2html_deferred<<9988>>\em\end<<9989>>tex2html_deferred<<9989>>Order<<436>> all \begin<<7052>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7052>>$N+1$\end<<7053>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7053>>\space vertex points according to their 
  function values:
  \begin<<437>>equation<<437>>
    f(<<438>>\begin<<9990>>tex2html_deferred<<9990>>\bf\end<<9991>>tex2html_deferred<<9991>>x<<438>>_0)\le f(<<439>>\begin<<9992>>tex2html_deferred<<9992>>\bf\end<<9993>>tex2html_deferred<<9993>>x<<439>>_1)\le\cdots\le f(<<440>>\begin<<9994>>tex2html_deferred<<9994>>\bf\end<<9995>>tex2html_deferred<<9995>>x<<440>>_N)
  \end<<441>>equation<<441>>
  Denote the best point with lowest function value by \begin<<7054>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7054>>$<<442>>\begin<<9996>>tex2html_deferred<<9996>>\bf\end<<9997>>tex2html_deferred<<9997>>x<<442>>_0=<<443>>\begin<<9998>>tex2html_deferred<<9998>>\bf\end<<9999>>tex2html_deferred<<9999>>x<<443>>_l$\end<<7055>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7055>>,
  the worst point with the highest function value by \begin<<7056>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7056>>$<<444>>\begin<<10000>>tex2html_deferred<<10000>>\bf\end<<10001>>tex2html_deferred<<10001>>x<<444>>_N=<<445>>\begin<<10002>>tex2html_deferred<<10002>>\bf\end<<10003>>tex2html_deferred<<10003>>x<<445>>_h$\end<<7057>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7057>>,
  and the second worst point by \begin<<7058>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7058>>$<<446>>\begin<<10004>>tex2html_deferred<<10004>>\bf\end<<10005>>tex2html_deferred<<10005>>x<<446>>_<<447>>N-1<<447>>=<<448>>\begin<<10006>>tex2html_deferred<<10006>>\bf\end<<10007>>tex2html_deferred<<10007>>x<<448>>_s$\end<<7059>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7059>>.
\item Find the centroid of all points except the worst one 
  \begin<<7060>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7060>>$<<449>>\begin<<10008>>tex2html_deferred<<10008>>\bf\end<<10009>>tex2html_deferred<<10009>>x<<449>>_N=<<450>>\begin<<10010>>tex2html_deferred<<10010>>\bf\end<<10011>>tex2html_deferred<<10011>>x<<450>>_h$\end<<7061>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7061>>:
  \begin<<451>>equation<<451>>
    <<452>>\begin<<10012>>tex2html_deferred<<10012>>\bf\end<<10013>>tex2html_deferred<<10013>>c<<452>>=\frac<<453>>1<<453>><<454>>N<<454>>\sum_<<455>>i=1<<455>>^N<<456>>\begin<<10014>>tex2html_deferred<<10014>>\bf\end<<10015>>tex2html_deferred<<10015>>x<<456>>_i
  \end<<457>>equation<<457>>
\item Find a new <<458>>\begin<<10016>>tex2html_deferred<<10016>>\em\end<<10017>>tex2html_deferred<<10017>>reflection<<458>> point:
  \begin<<459>>equation<<459>>
    <<460>>\begin<<10018>>tex2html_deferred<<10018>>\bf\end<<10019>>tex2html_deferred<<10019>>x<<460>>_r=<<461>>\begin<<10020>>tex2html_deferred<<10020>>\bf\end<<10021>>tex2html_deferred<<10021>>c<<461>>+\alpha(<<462>>\begin<<10022>>tex2html_deferred<<10022>>\bf\end<<10023>>tex2html_deferred<<10023>>c<<462>>-<<463>>\begin<<10024>>tex2html_deferred<<10024>>\bf\end<<10025>>tex2html_deferred<<10025>>x<<463>>_h)
  \end<<464>>equation<<464>>
  Depending on the function value \begin<<7062>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7062>>$f(<<465>>\begin<<10026>>tex2html_deferred<<10026>>\bf\end<<10027>>tex2html_deferred<<10027>>x<<465>>_r)$\end<<7063>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7063>>, we will do one of
  the following:
  \begin<<466>>itemize<<466>>
  \item If \begin<<7064>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7064>>$f(<<467>>\begin<<10028>>tex2html_deferred<<10028>>\bf\end<<10029>>tex2html_deferred<<10029>>x<<467>>_s;SPMlt;f(<<468>>\begin<<10030>>tex2html_deferred<<10030>>\bf\end<<10031>>tex2html_deferred<<10031>>x<<468>>_r);SPMlt;f(<<469>>\begin<<10032>>tex2html_deferred<<10032>>\bf\end<<10033>>tex2html_deferred<<10033>>x<<469>>_l)$\end<<7065>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7065>>, then replace 
    \begin<<7066>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7066>>$<<470>>\begin<<10034>>tex2html_deferred<<10034>>\bf\end<<10035>>tex2html_deferred<<10035>>x<<470>>_h$\end<<7067>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7067>>\space by \begin<<7068>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7068>>$<<471>>\begin<<10036>>tex2html_deferred<<10036>>\bf\end<<10037>>tex2html_deferred<<10037>>x<<471>>_r$\end<<7069>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7069>>.
  \item If \begin<<7070>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7070>>$f(<<472>>\begin<<10038>>tex2html_deferred<<10038>>\bf\end<<10039>>tex2html_deferred<<10039>>x<<472>>_r);SPMlt;f(<<473>>\begin<<10040>>tex2html_deferred<<10040>>\bf\end<<10041>>tex2html_deferred<<10041>>x<<473>>_l)$\end<<7071>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7071>>, get an <<474>>\begin<<10042>>tex2html_deferred<<10042>>\em\end<<10043>>tex2html_deferred<<10043>>expansion<<474>> point
    \begin<<475>>equation<<475>>
      <<476>>\begin<<10044>>tex2html_deferred<<10044>>\bf\end<<10045>>tex2html_deferred<<10045>>x<<476>>_e=<<477>>\begin<<10046>>tex2html_deferred<<10046>>\bf\end<<10047>>tex2html_deferred<<10047>>c<<477>>+\gamma(<<478>>\begin<<10048>>tex2html_deferred<<10048>>\bf\end<<10049>>tex2html_deferred<<10049>>x<<478>>_r-<<479>>\begin<<10050>>tex2html_deferred<<10050>>\bf\end<<10051>>tex2html_deferred<<10051>>c<<479>>)
    \end<<480>>equation<<480>>
    Replace \begin<<7072>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7072>>$<<481>>\begin<<10052>>tex2html_deferred<<10052>>\bf\end<<10053>>tex2html_deferred<<10053>>x<<481>>_h$\end<<7073>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7073>>\space by the better (with lower function value) of
    \begin<<7074>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7074>>$<<482>>\begin<<10054>>tex2html_deferred<<10054>>\bf\end<<10055>>tex2html_deferred<<10055>>x<<482>>_r$\end<<7075>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7075>>\space and \begin<<7076>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7076>>$<<483>>\begin<<10056>>tex2html_deferred<<10056>>\bf\end<<10057>>tex2html_deferred<<10057>>x<<483>>_e$\end<<7077>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7077>>. This is called <<484>>\begin<<10058>>tex2html_deferred<<10058>>\em\end<<10059>>tex2html_deferred<<10059>>greedy optimization<<484>>.
  \item \begin<<7078>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7078>>$f(<<485>>\begin<<10060>>tex2html_deferred<<10060>>\bf\end<<10061>>tex2html_deferred<<10061>>x<<485>>_r);SPMgt;f(<<486>>\begin<<10062>>tex2html_deferred<<10062>>\bf\end<<10063>>tex2html_deferred<<10063>>x<<486>>_s)$\end<<7079>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7079>>, i.e., \begin<<7080>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7080>>$<<487>>bf x<<487>>_r-<<488>>\begin<<10064>>tex2html_deferred<<10064>>\bf\end<<10065>>tex2html_deferred<<10065>>c<<488>>$\end<<7081>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7081>>\space is a 
    wrong direction, get a <<489>>\begin<<10066>>tex2html_deferred<<10066>>\em\end<<10067>>tex2html_deferred<<10067>>contraction<<489>> point
    \begin<<490>>equation<<490>>
      <<491>>\begin<<10068>>tex2html_deferred<<10068>>\bf\end<<10069>>tex2html_deferred<<10069>>x<<491>>_c=<<492>>\begin<<10070>>tex2html_deferred<<10070>>\bf\end<<10071>>tex2html_deferred<<10071>>c<<492>>+\beta(<<493>>\begin<<10072>>tex2html_deferred<<10072>>\bf\end<<10073>>tex2html_deferred<<10073>>x<<493>>_h-<<494>>\begin<<10074>>tex2html_deferred<<10074>>\bf\end<<10075>>tex2html_deferred<<10075>>c<<494>>)
    \end<<495>>equation<<495>>
    If \begin<<7082>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7082>>$f(<<496>>\begin<<10076>>tex2html_deferred<<10076>>\bf\end<<10077>>tex2html_deferred<<10077>>x<<496>>_c);SPMlt;f(<<497>>\begin<<10078>>tex2html_deferred<<10078>>\bf\end<<10079>>tex2html_deferred<<10079>>x<<497>>_h)$\end<<7083>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7083>>\space is better than \begin<<7084>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7084>>$<<498>>\begin<<10080>>tex2html_deferred<<10080>>\bf\end<<10081>>tex2html_deferred<<10081>>x<<498>>_h$\end<<7085>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7085>>, replace
    \begin<<7086>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7086>>$<<499>>\begin<<10082>>tex2html_deferred<<10082>>\bf\end<<10083>>tex2html_deferred<<10083>>x<<499>>_h$\end<<7087>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7087>>\space by \begin<<7088>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7088>>$<<500>>\begin<<10084>>tex2html_deferred<<10084>>\bf\end<<10085>>tex2html_deferred<<10085>>x<<500>>_c$\end<<7089>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7089>>
  \item 
\begin<<10086>>tex2html_deferred<<10086>>\par\end<<10087>>tex2html_deferred<<10087>>
\item Terminate the iteration when the variance of the \begin<<7090>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7090>>$N+1$\end<<7091>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7091>> 
    function values at the vertices of the current simplex is smaller
    than a tolerance. The best point \begin<<7092>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7092>>$<<501>>\begin<<10088>>tex2html_deferred<<10088>>\bf\end<<10089>>tex2html_deferred<<10089>>x<<501>>_0$\end<<7093>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7093>>\space with lowest function
    value is returned as the solution.
  \end<<502>>itemize<<502>>
\end<<503>>itemize<<503>>
\begin<<10090>>tex2html_deferred<<10090>>\par\end<<10091>>tex2html_deferred<<10091>>
\subsection*<<504>>Newton's method<<504>>
\begin<<10092>>tex2html_deferred<<10092>>\par\end<<10093>>tex2html_deferred<<10093>>
Newton's method is based on the Taylor series expansion of the function
\begin<<7094>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7094>>$f(x)$\end<<7095>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7095>>\space to be minimized near some point \begin<<7096>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7096>>$x_0$\end<<7097>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7097>>:
\begin<<505>>eqnarray<<505>>
  f(x);SPMamp;=;SPMamp;f(x_0)+f'(x_0)(x-x_0)+\frac<<506>>1<<506>><<507>>2<<507>>f;SPMrdquo;(x_0)(x-x_0)^2 + \cdots
  +\frac<<508>>1<<508>><<509>>n!<<509>>f^<<510>>(n)<<510>>(x_0)(x-x_0)^n + \cdots
  \nonumber\\ 
  ;SPMamp;\approx;SPMamp; f(x_0)+f'(x_0)(x-x_0)+\frac<<511>>1<<511>><<512>>2<<512>>f;SPMrdquo;(x_0)(x-x_0)^2 =q(x)
\end<<513>>eqnarray<<513>>
If \begin<<7098>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7098>>$f(x)=q(t)$\end<<7099>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7099>>\space is a quadratic function, then the Taylor series only
contains the first three terms (constant, linear, and quadratic terms).
\begin<<10094>>tex2html_deferred<<10094>>\par\end<<10095>>tex2html_deferred<<10095>>
\htmladdimg<<514>>figures/NewtonEx1.png<<514>>
\begin<<10096>>tex2html_deferred<<10096>>\par\end<<10097>>tex2html_deferred<<10097>>
In this case, we can find the vertex point at which \begin<<7100>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7100>>$f(x)=q(x)$\end<<7101>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7101>>\space reaches
its extremum, by first setting its derivative to zero:
\begin<<515>>eqnarray<<515>>
  q'(x);SPMamp;=;SPMamp;\frac<<516>>d<<516>><<517>>dx<<517>>q(x)=\frac<<518>>d<<518>><<519>>dx<<519>>\left[ f(x_0)+f'(x_0)(x-x_0)
    +\frac<<520>>1<<520>><<521>>2<<521>>f;SPMrdquo;(x_0)(x-x_0)^2 \right]
  \nonumber\\ 
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;f'(x_0)+f;SPMrdquo;(x_0)(x-x_0)=0
\end<<522>>eqnarray<<522>>
and then solving the resulting equation for \begin<<7102>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7102>>$x$\end<<7103>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7103>>\space to get:
\begin<<523>>equation<<523>> 
  x^*=x=x_0-\frac<<524>>f'(x_0)<<524>><<525>>f;SPMrdquo;(x_0)<<525>>=x_0+\Delta x_0
  \label<<526>>OptimalNewton<<526>>
\end<<527>>equation<<527>>
where \begin<<7104>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7104>>$\Delta x_0=-f'(x_0)/f;SPMrdquo;(x_0)$\end<<7105>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7105>>\space is the step we need to take to go
from any initial point \begin<<7106>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7106>>$x_0$\end<<7107>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7107>>\space to the solution \begin<<7108>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7108>>$x^*$\end<<7109>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7109>>\space in a single step. 
Note that \begin<<7110>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7110>>$f(x^*)$\end<<7111>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7111>>\space is a minimum if \begin<<7112>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7112>>$f;SPMrdquo;(x^*);SPMgt;0$\end<<7113>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7113>>\space but a maximum if 
\begin<<7114>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7114>>$f;SPMrdquo;(x^*);SPMlt;0$\end<<7115>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7115>>.
\begin<<10098>>tex2html_deferred<<10098>>\par\end<<10099>>tex2html_deferred<<10099>>
If \begin<<7116>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7116>>$f(x)\ne q(x)$\end<<7117>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7117>>\space is not quadratic, the result above can still be 
considered as an approximation of the solution, which can be improved 
iteratively from an initial guess \begin<<7118>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7118>>$x_0$\end<<7119>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7119>>\space to eventually approach the 
solution:
\begin<<528>>equation<<528>>
  x_<<529>>n+1<<529>>=x_n+\Delta x_n=x_n-\frac<<530>>f'(x_n)<<530>><<531>>f;SPMrdquo;(x_n)<<531>>
\end<<532>>equation<<532>>
We see that in each step \begin<<7120>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7120>>$x_n$\end<<7121>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7121>>\space of the iteration, the function \begin<<7122>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7122>>$f(x)$\end<<7123>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7123>>\space is
fitted by a quadratic functions \begin<<7124>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7124>>$q(x_n)$\end<<7125>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7125>>\space and its vertex at \begin<<7126>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7126>>$x_<<533>>n+1<<533>>$\end<<7127>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7127>>\space is 
used as the updated approximated solution, at which the function is again
fitted by another quadratic function \begin<<7128>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7128>>$q(x_<<534>>n+1<<534>>)$\end<<7129>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7129>>\space for the next iteration. 
Through this process the solution can be approached as \begin<<7130>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7130>>$n\rightarrow\infty$\end<<7131>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7131>>.
\begin<<10100>>tex2html_deferred<<10100>>\par\end<<10101>>tex2html_deferred<<10101>>
We note that the iteration \begin<<7132>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7132>>$x_<<535>>n+1<<535>>=x_n-f'(x_n)/f;SPMrdquo;(x_n)$\end<<7133>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7133>>\space above is just 
the \htmladdnormallink<<536>>Newton-Raphson method<<536>><<537>>../ch2/node5.html<<537>> for
solving an equation \begin<<7134>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7134>>$f(x)=0$\end<<7135>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7135>>\space but now applied to equation \begin<<7136>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7136>>$f'(x)=0$\end<<7137>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7137>>, as
a necessary condition for an extremum of \begin<<7138>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7138>>$f(x)$\end<<7139>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7139>>.
\begin<<10102>>tex2html_deferred<<10102>>\par\end<<10103>>tex2html_deferred<<10103>>
This quadratic function
\begin<<538>>equation<<538>>
  q(x)=f(x_0)+f'(x_0)(x-x_0)+\frac<<539>>1<<539>><<540>>2<<540>>f;SPMrdquo;(x_0)(x-x_0)^2
  \label<<541>>qofx<<541>>
\end<<542>>equation<<542>>
can also be expressed as
\begin<<543>>equation<<543>>
  q(x)=\frac<<544>>a<<544>><<545>>2<<545>>(x-b)^2+c
  \label<<546>>qofxnew<<546>>
\end<<547>>equation<<547>>
in terms of the following three parameters:
\begin<<548>>equation<<548>>
\left\{\begin<<549>>array<<549>><<550>>l<<550>>a=f;SPMrdquo;(x_0)\\ 
b=x_0-f'(x_0)/f;SPMrdquo;(x_0)\\ c=f(x_0)-f'^2(x_0)/2f;SPMrdquo;(x_0)
\end<<551>>array<<551>>\right.
\end<<552>>equation<<552>>
(Substituting \begin<<7140>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7140>>$a$\end<<7141>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7141>>, \begin<<7142>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7142>>$b$\end<<7143>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7143>>\space and \begin<<7144>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7144>>$c$\end<<7145>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7145>>\space into Eq. (\ref<<553>>qofxnew<<553>>) one gets Eq. (\ref<<554>>qofx<<554>>).)
Now it becomes obvious that when \begin<<7146>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7146>>$x=b$\end<<7147>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7147>>, the function \begin<<7148>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7148>>$q(x)=q(b)=c$\end<<7149>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7149>>\space reaches its 
minimum at the point \begin<<7150>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7150>>$x=b$\end<<7151>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7151>>. Note that the expression of \begin<<7152>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7152>>$b$\end<<7153>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7153>>\space above is actually the
same as Eq. (\ref<<555>>OptimalNewton<<555>>).
\begin<<10104>>tex2html_deferred<<10104>>\par\end<<10105>>tex2html_deferred<<10105>>
<<556>>\begin<<10106>>tex2html_deferred<<10106>>\bf\end<<10107>>tex2html_deferred<<10107>>Example<<556>>
\begin<<10108>>tex2html_deferred<<10108>>\par\end<<10109>>tex2html_deferred<<10109>>
The function to be minimized and its first and second order derivatives are
given below:
\begin<<557>>equation<<557>>
  f(x)=2x^3-4x^2+x,\;\;\;\;\;f'(x)=6x^2-8x+1,\;\;\;\;\;\;\;f;SPMrdquo;(x)=12x-8 
  \nonumber
\end<<558>>equation<<558>>
Solving \begin<<7154>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7154>>$f'(x)=0$\end<<7155>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7155>>\space we get the optimal solution \begin<<7156>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7156>>$x^*=1.333$\end<<7157>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7157>>, at which 
\begin<<7158>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7158>>$f(x^*)=-1.037$\end<<7159>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7159>>. But here we will use the Newton's method to obtain the 
solution iteratively based on an initial guess \begin<<7160>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7160>>$x_0=3$\end<<7161>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7161>>, at which we have
\begin<<559>>equation<<559>>
  f(x_0)=f(3)=21,\;\;\;\;\;\;\;f'(x_0)=f'(3)=31,\;\;\;\;\;\;f;SPMrdquo;(x_0)=f;SPMrdquo;(3)=28
  \nonumber
\end<<560>>equation<<560>>
Here \begin<<7162>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7162>>$f;SPMrdquo;(x_0);SPMgt;0$\end<<7163>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7163>>\space indicates that the function \begin<<7164>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7164>>$x(x)$\end<<7165>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7165>>\space has a minimum in the
neighborhood of \begin<<7166>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7166>>$x_0=3$\end<<7167>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7167>>. We use the parabola below to approximate \begin<<7168>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7168>>$f(x)$\end<<7169>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7169>>:
\begin<<561>>equation<<561>>
  q(x)=\frac<<562>>a<<562>><<563>>2<<563>>(x-b)^2+c
  \nonumber
\end<<564>>equation<<564>>
based on these parameters:
\begin<<565>>equation<<565>>
  \left\{\begin<<566>>array<<566>><<567>>l<<567>>
  a=f;SPMrdquo;(3)=28\\ 
  b=3-f'(3)/f;SPMrdquo;(3)=1.8929\\ 
  c=f(3)-f'^2(3)/2f;SPMrdquo;(3)=3.8393\end<<568>>array<<568>>\right.
  \nonumber
\end<<569>>equation<<569>>
At the vertex of \begin<<7170>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7170>>$q(x)$\end<<7171>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7171>>\space at \begin<<7172>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7172>>$x_1=b=1.8929$\end<<7173>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7173>>, we have \begin<<7174>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7174>>$f(x_1)=f(1.8929)=1.1251$\end<<7175>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7175>>,
much smaller than \begin<<7176>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7176>>$f(x_0)=f(3)=21$\end<<7177>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7177>>. The estimated solution 
\begin<<7178>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7178>>$x=b=x_0-f'(x_0)/f;SPMrdquo;(x_0)$\end<<7179>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7179>>\space is used as an iterative step 
\begin<<7180>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7180>>$x_1=x_0-f'(x_0)/f;SPMrdquo;(x_0)$\end<<7181>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7181>>\space for further improving the estimate.
\begin<<10110>>tex2html_deferred<<10110>>\par\end<<10111>>tex2html_deferred<<10111>>
We can further generalize Newton's method for single-variable function 
\begin<<7182>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7182>>$f(x)$\end<<7183>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7183>>\space to mult-variable function \begin<<7184>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7184>>$f(<<570>>\begin<<10112>>tex2html_deferred<<10112>>\bf\end<<10113>>tex2html_deferred<<10113>>x<<570>>)=f(x_1,\cdots,x_N)$\end<<7185>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7185>>, which 
can be approximated by a quadratic function \begin<<7186>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7186>>$q(<<571>>\begin<<10114>>tex2html_deferred<<10114>>\bf\end<<10115>>tex2html_deferred<<10115>>x<<571>>)$\end<<7187>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7187>>\space containing the 
first three terms of its Taylor series at some point \begin<<7188>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7188>>$<<572>>\begin<<10116>>tex2html_deferred<<10116>>\bf\end<<10117>>tex2html_deferred<<10117>>x<<572>>_0$\end<<7189>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7189>>:
\begin<<573>>equation<<573>> 
  f(<<574>>\begin<<10118>>tex2html_deferred<<10118>>\bf\end<<10119>>tex2html_deferred<<10119>>x<<574>>)\approx  f(<<575>>\begin<<10120>>tex2html_deferred<<10120>>\bf\end<<10121>>tex2html_deferred<<10121>>x<<575>>_0)+<<576>>\begin<<10122>>tex2html_deferred<<10122>>\bf\end<<10123>>tex2html_deferred<<10123>>g<<576>>_0^T(<<577>>\begin<<10124>>tex2html_deferred<<10124>>\bf\end<<10125>>tex2html_deferred<<10125>>x<<577>>-<<578>>\begin<<10126>>tex2html_deferred<<10126>>\bf\end<<10127>>tex2html_deferred<<10127>>x<<578>>_0)
  +\frac<<579>>1<<579>><<580>>2<<580>>(<<581>>\begin<<10128>>tex2html_deferred<<10128>>\bf\end<<10129>>tex2html_deferred<<10129>>x<<581>>-<<582>>\begin<<10130>>tex2html_deferred<<10130>>\bf\end<<10131>>tex2html_deferred<<10131>>x<<582>>_0)^T<<583>>\begin<<10132>>tex2html_deferred<<10132>>\bf\end<<10133>>tex2html_deferred<<10133>>H<<583>>_0\,(<<584>>\begin<<10134>>tex2html_deferred<<10134>>\bf\end<<10135>>tex2html_deferred<<10135>>x<<584>>-<<585>>\begin<<10136>>tex2html_deferred<<10136>>\bf\end<<10137>>tex2html_deferred<<10137>>x<<585>>_0)
  =q(<<586>>\begin<<10138>>tex2html_deferred<<10138>>\bf\end<<10139>>tex2html_deferred<<10139>>x<<586>>)
\end<<587>>equation<<587>>
where \begin<<7190>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7190>>$<<588>>\begin<<10140>>tex2html_deferred<<10140>>\bf\end<<10141>>tex2html_deferred<<10141>>g<<588>>_0$\end<<7191>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7191>>\space and \begin<<7192>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7192>>$<<589>>\begin<<10142>>tex2html_deferred<<10142>>\bf\end<<10143>>tex2html_deferred<<10143>>H<<589>>_0$\end<<7193>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7193>>\space are respectively the gradient vector and 
Hessian matrix of the function \begin<<7194>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7194>>$f(<<590>>\begin<<10144>>tex2html_deferred<<10144>>\bf\end<<10145>>tex2html_deferred<<10145>>x<<590>>)$\end<<7195>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7195>>\space at \begin<<7196>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7196>>$<<591>>\begin<<10146>>tex2html_deferred<<10146>>\bf\end<<10147>>tex2html_deferred<<10147>>x<<591>>_0$\end<<7197>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7197>>:
\begin<<592>>eqnarray<<592>>
  <<593>>\begin<<10148>>tex2html_deferred<<10148>>\bf\end<<10149>>tex2html_deferred<<10149>>g<<593>>_0;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;<<594>>\begin<<10150>>tex2html_deferred<<10150>>\bf\end<<10151>>tex2html_deferred<<10151>>g<<594>>_f(<<595>>\begin<<10152>>tex2html_deferred<<10152>>\bf\end<<10153>>tex2html_deferred<<10153>>x<<595>>_0)=\frac<<596>>d<<596>><<6513>>d<<597>>\begin<<10154>>tex2html_deferred<<10154>>\bf\end<<10155>>tex2html_deferred<<10155>>x<<597>><<6513>> f(<<598>>\begin<<10156>>tex2html_deferred<<10156>>\bf\end<<10157>>tex2html_deferred<<10157>>x<<598>>_0)
  =\left[\begin<<599>>array<<599>><<600>>c<<600>>\frac<<6514>>\partial f(<<601>>\begin<<10158>>tex2html_deferred<<10158>>\bf\end<<10159>>tex2html_deferred<<10159>>x<<601>>_0)<<6514>><<602>>\partial x_1<<602>>\\ 
      \vdots \\  \frac<<6515>>\partial f(<<603>>\begin<<10160>>tex2html_deferred<<10160>>\bf\end<<10161>>tex2html_deferred<<10161>>x<<603>>_0)<<6515>><<604>>\partial x_N<<604>>\end<<605>>array<<605>>\right],
  \nonumber\\ 
  <<606>>\begin<<10162>>tex2html_deferred<<10162>>\bf\end<<10163>>tex2html_deferred<<10163>>H<<606>>_0;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;<<607>>\begin<<10164>>tex2html_deferred<<10164>>\bf\end<<10165>>tex2html_deferred<<10165>>H<<607>>_f(<<608>>\begin<<10166>>tex2html_deferred<<10166>>\bf\end<<10167>>tex2html_deferred<<10167>>x<<608>>_0)=\frac<<609>>d<<609>><<6516>>d<<610>>\begin<<10168>>tex2html_deferred<<10168>>\bf\end<<10169>>tex2html_deferred<<10169>>x<<610>><<6516>> <<611>>\begin<<10170>>tex2html_deferred<<10170>>\bf\end<<10171>>tex2html_deferred<<10171>>g<<611>>(<<612>>\begin<<10172>>tex2html_deferred<<10172>>\bf\end<<10173>>tex2html_deferred<<10173>>x<<612>>_0)
  =\frac<<613>>d^2<<613>><<6517>>d<<614>>\begin<<10174>>tex2html_deferred<<10174>>\bf\end<<10175>>tex2html_deferred<<10175>>x<<614>>^2<<6517>> f(<<615>>\begin<<10176>>tex2html_deferred<<10176>>\bf\end<<10177>>tex2html_deferred<<10177>>x<<615>>_0)
  =\left[\begin<<616>>array<<616>><<617>>ccc<<617>> \frac<<6518>>\partial^2 f(<<618>>\begin<<10178>>tex2html_deferred<<10178>>\bf\end<<10179>>tex2html_deferred<<10179>>x<<618>>_0)<<6518>><<619>>\partial x_1^2<<619>> ;SPMamp; 
      \cdots ;SPMamp; \frac<<6519>>\partial^2 f(<<620>>\begin<<10180>>tex2html_deferred<<10180>>\bf\end<<10181>>tex2html_deferred<<10181>>x<<620>>_0)<<6519>><<621>>\partial x_1\partial x_N<<621>> \\ 
      \vdots ;SPMamp; \ddots ;SPMamp; \vdots \\ 
      \frac<<6520>>\partial^2 f(<<622>>\begin<<10182>>tex2html_deferred<<10182>>\bf\end<<10183>>tex2html_deferred<<10183>>x<<622>>_0)<<6520>><<623>>\partial x_N\partial x_1<<623>> ;SPMamp; 
      \cdots ;SPMamp; \frac<<6521>>\partial^2 f(<<624>>\begin<<10184>>tex2html_deferred<<10184>>\bf\end<<10185>>tex2html_deferred<<10185>>x<<624>>_0)<<6521>><<625>>\partial x_N^2<<625>>
    \end<<626>>array<<626>>\right]
\end<<627>>eqnarray<<627>>
The stationary point of \begin<<7198>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7198>>$f(<<628>>\begin<<10186>>tex2html_deferred<<10186>>\bf\end<<10187>>tex2html_deferred<<10187>>x<<628>>)=q(<<629>>\begin<<10188>>tex2html_deferred<<10188>>\bf\end<<10189>>tex2html_deferred<<10189>>x<<629>>)$\end<<7199>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7199>>\space can be found from any point
\begin<<7200>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7200>>$<<630>>\begin<<10190>>tex2html_deferred<<10190>>\bf\end<<10191>>tex2html_deferred<<10191>>x<<630>>_0$\end<<7201>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7201>>\space by setting its derivative to zero
\begin<<631>>equation<<631>>
  \frac<<632>>d<<632>><<6522>>d<<633>>\begin<<10192>>tex2html_deferred<<10192>>\bf\end<<10193>>tex2html_deferred<<10193>>x<<633>><<6522>>\left[f(<<634>>\begin<<10194>>tex2html_deferred<<10194>>\bf\end<<10195>>tex2html_deferred<<10195>>x<<634>>_0)+<<635>>\begin<<10196>>tex2html_deferred<<10196>>\bf\end<<10197>>tex2html_deferred<<10197>>g<<635>>_0^T(<<636>>\begin<<10198>>tex2html_deferred<<10198>>\bf\end<<10199>>tex2html_deferred<<10199>>x<<636>>-<<637>>\begin<<10200>>tex2html_deferred<<10200>>\bf\end<<10201>>tex2html_deferred<<10201>>x<<637>>_0)
    +\frac<<638>>1<<638>><<639>>2<<639>>(<<640>>\begin<<10202>>tex2html_deferred<<10202>>\bf\end<<10203>>tex2html_deferred<<10203>>x<<640>>-<<641>>\begin<<10204>>tex2html_deferred<<10204>>\bf\end<<10205>>tex2html_deferred<<10205>>x<<641>>_0)^T<<642>>\begin<<10206>>tex2html_deferred<<10206>>\bf\end<<10207>>tex2html_deferred<<10207>>H<<642>>_0\,(<<643>>\begin<<10208>>tex2html_deferred<<10208>>\bf\end<<10209>>tex2html_deferred<<10209>>x<<643>>-<<644>>\begin<<10210>>tex2html_deferred<<10210>>\bf\end<<10211>>tex2html_deferred<<10211>>x<<644>>_0)\right]
  =<<645>>\begin<<10212>>tex2html_deferred<<10212>>\bf\end<<10213>>tex2html_deferred<<10213>>g<<645>>_0+<<646>>\begin<<10214>>tex2html_deferred<<10214>>\bf\end<<10215>>tex2html_deferred<<10215>>H<<646>>_0\,(<<647>>\begin<<10216>>tex2html_deferred<<10216>>\bf\end<<10217>>tex2html_deferred<<10217>>x<<647>>-<<648>>\begin<<10218>>tex2html_deferred<<10218>>\bf\end<<10219>>tex2html_deferred<<10219>>x<<648>>_0)=<<649>>\begin<<10220>>tex2html_deferred<<10220>>\bf\end<<10221>>tex2html_deferred<<10221>>0<<649>>
\end<<650>>equation<<650>>
and solving the resulting equation to get
\begin<<651>>equation<<651>>
  <<652>>\begin<<10222>>tex2html_deferred<<10222>>\bf\end<<10223>>tex2html_deferred<<10223>>x<<652>>^*=<<653>>\begin<<10224>>tex2html_deferred<<10224>>\bf\end<<10225>>tex2html_deferred<<10225>>x<<653>>=<<654>>\begin<<10226>>tex2html_deferred<<10226>>\bf\end<<10227>>tex2html_deferred<<10227>>x<<654>>_0-<<655>>\begin<<10228>>tex2html_deferred<<10228>>\bf\end<<10229>>tex2html_deferred<<10229>>H<<655>>(<<656>>\begin<<10230>>tex2html_deferred<<10230>>\bf\end<<10231>>tex2html_deferred<<10231>>x<<656>>_0)^<<657>>-1<<657>><<658>>\begin<<10232>>tex2html_deferred<<10232>>\bf\end<<10233>>tex2html_deferred<<10233>>g<<658>>(<<659>>\begin<<10234>>tex2html_deferred<<10234>>\bf\end<<10235>>tex2html_deferred<<10235>>x<<659>>_0)
\end<<660>>equation<<660>>
Similar to the 1-D case where whether \begin<<7202>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7202>>$f(<<661>>\begin<<10236>>tex2html_deferred<<10236>>\bf\end<<10237>>tex2html_deferred<<10237>>x<<661>>^*)$\end<<7203>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7203>>\space is a minimum or 
maximum depends on whether the second order derivative \begin<<7204>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7204>>$f;SPMrdquo;(<<662>>\begin<<10238>>tex2html_deferred<<10238>>\bf\end<<10239>>tex2html_deferred<<10239>>x<<662>>^*)$\end<<7205>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7205>> 
is greater or smaller than zero, here whether \begin<<7206>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7206>>$f(<<663>>\begin<<10240>>tex2html_deferred<<10240>>\bf\end<<10241>>tex2html_deferred<<10241>>x<<663>>^*)$\end<<7207>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7207>>\space is a minimum,
maximum, or neither, depends on the second order derivatives, the Hessiam 
matrix \begin<<7208>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7208>>$<<664>>\begin<<10242>>tex2html_deferred<<10242>>\bf\end<<10243>>tex2html_deferred<<10243>>H<<664>>^*=<<665>>\begin<<10244>>tex2html_deferred<<10244>>\bf\end<<10245>>tex2html_deferred<<10245>>H<<665>>(<<666>>\begin<<10246>>tex2html_deferred<<10246>>\bf\end<<10247>>tex2html_deferred<<10247>>x<<666>>^*)$\end<<7209>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7209>>:
\begin<<667>>itemize<<667>>
\item If \begin<<7210>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7210>>$<<668>>\begin<<10248>>tex2html_deferred<<10248>>\bf\end<<10249>>tex2html_deferred<<10249>>H<<668>>^*;SPMgt;0$\end<<7211>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7211>>\space is positive definite (all eigenvalues are positive),
  \begin<<7212>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7212>>$f(<<669>>\begin<<10250>>tex2html_deferred<<10250>>\bf\end<<10251>>tex2html_deferred<<10251>>x<<669>>^*)$\end<<7213>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7213>>\space is a local minimum;
\begin<<10252>>tex2html_deferred<<10252>>\par\end<<10253>>tex2html_deferred<<10253>>
\item If \begin<<7214>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7214>>$<<670>>\begin<<10254>>tex2html_deferred<<10254>>\bf\end<<10255>>tex2html_deferred<<10255>>H<<670>>^*;SPMlt;0$\end<<7215>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7215>>\space is negative definite (all eigenvalues are negative),
  \begin<<7216>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7216>>$f(<<671>>\begin<<10256>>tex2html_deferred<<10256>>\bf\end<<10257>>tex2html_deferred<<10257>>x<<671>>^*)$\end<<7217>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7217>>\space a local maximum;
\begin<<10258>>tex2html_deferred<<10258>>\par\end<<10259>>tex2html_deferred<<10259>>
\item If \begin<<7218>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7218>>$<<672>>\begin<<10260>>tex2html_deferred<<10260>>\bf\end<<10261>>tex2html_deferred<<10261>>H<<672>>^*$\end<<7219>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7219>>\space is indefinite (has both positive and negative 
  eigenvalues), \begin<<7220>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7220>>$f(<<673>>\begin<<10262>>tex2html_deferred<<10262>>\bf\end<<10263>>tex2html_deferred<<10263>>x<<673>>^*)$\end<<7221>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7221>>\space is a saddle point (neither minimum nor 
  maximum).  
\end<<674>>itemize<<674>>
\begin<<10264>>tex2html_deferred<<10264>>\par\end<<10265>>tex2html_deferred<<10265>>
If \begin<<7222>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7222>>$f(<<675>>\begin<<10266>>tex2html_deferred<<10266>>\bf\end<<10267>>tex2html_deferred<<10267>>x<<675>>)\ne q(<<676>>\begin<<10268>>tex2html_deferred<<10268>>\bf\end<<10269>>tex2html_deferred<<10269>>x<<676>>)$\end<<7223>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7223>>\space is not quadratic, the result above is not
a minimum or maximum, but it can still be used as an approximation of the
solution, which can be improved to approached the true solution iteratively:
\begin<<677>>equation<<677>> 
  <<678>>\begin<<10270>>tex2html_deferred<<10270>>\bf\end<<10271>>tex2html_deferred<<10271>>x<<678>>_<<679>>n+1<<679>>=<<680>>\begin<<10272>>tex2html_deferred<<10272>>\bf\end<<10273>>tex2html_deferred<<10273>>x<<680>>_n+\Delta<<681>>\begin<<10274>>tex2html_deferred<<10274>>\bf\end<<10275>>tex2html_deferred<<10275>>x<<681>>_n
  =<<682>>\begin<<10276>>tex2html_deferred<<10276>>\bf\end<<10277>>tex2html_deferred<<10277>>x<<682>>_n-<<683>>\begin<<10278>>tex2html_deferred<<10278>>\bf\end<<10279>>tex2html_deferred<<10279>>H<<683>>_n^<<684>>-1<<684>><<685>>\begin<<10280>>tex2html_deferred<<10280>>\bf\end<<10281>>tex2html_deferred<<10281>>g<<685>>_n =<<686>>\begin<<10282>>tex2html_deferred<<10282>>\bf\end<<10283>>tex2html_deferred<<10283>>x<<686>>_n+<<687>>\begin<<10284>>tex2html_deferred<<10284>>\bf\end<<10285>>tex2html_deferred<<10285>>d<<687>>_n
\end<<688>>equation<<688>>
where \begin<<7224>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7224>>$<<689>>\begin<<10286>>tex2html_deferred<<10286>>\bf\end<<10287>>tex2html_deferred<<10287>>g<<689>>_n=<<690>>\begin<<10288>>tex2html_deferred<<10288>>\bf\end<<10289>>tex2html_deferred<<10289>>g<<690>>(<<691>>\begin<<10290>>tex2html_deferred<<10290>>\bf\end<<10291>>tex2html_deferred<<10291>>x<<691>>_n)$\end<<7225>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7225>>, \begin<<7226>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7226>>$<<692>>\begin<<10292>>tex2html_deferred<<10292>>\bf\end<<10293>>tex2html_deferred<<10293>>H<<692>>_n=<<693>>\begin<<10294>>tex2html_deferred<<10294>>\bf\end<<10295>>tex2html_deferred<<10295>>H<<693>>(<<694>>\begin<<10296>>tex2html_deferred<<10296>>\bf\end<<10297>>tex2html_deferred<<10297>>x<<694>>_n)$\end<<7227>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7227>>, and 
\begin<<7228>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7228>>$<<695>>\begin<<10298>>tex2html_deferred<<10298>>\bf\end<<10299>>tex2html_deferred<<10299>>d<<695>>_n=\Delta<<696>>\begin<<10300>>tex2html_deferred<<10300>>\bf\end<<10301>>tex2html_deferred<<10301>>x<<696>>_n=-<<697>>\begin<<10302>>tex2html_deferred<<10302>>\bf\end<<10303>>tex2html_deferred<<10303>>H<<697>>_n^<<698>>-1<<698>><<699>>\begin<<10304>>tex2html_deferred<<10304>>\bf\end<<10305>>tex2html_deferred<<10305>>g<<699>>_n$\end<<7229>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7229>>\space is the increment in 
the nth step, called <<700>>\begin<<10306>>tex2html_deferred<<10306>>\em\end<<10307>>tex2html_deferred<<10307>>Newton search direction<<700>>.
\begin<<10308>>tex2html_deferred<<10308>>\par\end<<10309>>tex2html_deferred<<10309>>
We note that the iteration above is just a generalization of 
\begin<<7230>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7230>>$x_<<701>>n+1<<701>>=x_n-f'(x_n)/f;SPMrdquo;(x_n)$\end<<7231>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7231>>\space in 1-D case with \begin<<7232>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7232>>$<<702>>\begin<<10310>>tex2html_deferred<<10310>>\bf\end<<10311>>tex2html_deferred<<10311>>g<<702>>_n=f'(x_n)$\end<<7233>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7233>> 
and \begin<<7234>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7234>>$<<703>>\begin<<10312>>tex2html_deferred<<10312>>\bf\end<<10313>>tex2html_deferred<<10313>>H<<703>>_n=f;SPMrdquo;(x_n)$\end<<7235>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7235>>. Also, the iteration 
\begin<<7236>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7236>>$<<704>>\begin<<10314>>tex2html_deferred<<10314>>\bf\end<<10315>>tex2html_deferred<<10315>>x<<704>>_<<705>>n+1<<705>>=<<706>>\begin<<10316>>tex2html_deferred<<10316>>\bf\end<<10317>>tex2html_deferred<<10317>>x<<706>>_n-<<707>>\begin<<10318>>tex2html_deferred<<10318>>\bf\end<<10319>>tex2html_deferred<<10319>>H<<707>>_n^<<708>>-1<<708>>\,<<709>>\begin<<10320>>tex2html_deferred<<10320>>\bf\end<<10321>>tex2html_deferred<<10321>>g<<709>>_n$\end<<7237>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7237>>\space above is just the
\htmladdnormallink<<710>>Newton-Raphson method<<710>><<711>>../ch2/node6.html<<711>> for 
solving equation \begin<<7238>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7238>>$<<712>>\begin<<10322>>tex2html_deferred<<10322>>\bf\end<<10323>>tex2html_deferred<<10323>>f<<712>>(<<713>>\begin<<10324>>tex2html_deferred<<10324>>\bf\end<<10325>>tex2html_deferred<<10325>>x<<713>>)=<<714>>\begin<<10326>>tex2html_deferred<<10326>>\bf\end<<10327>>tex2html_deferred<<10327>>0<<714>>$\end<<7239>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7239>>\space but here applied to
solving \begin<<7240>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7240>>$<<715>>\begin<<10328>>tex2html_deferred<<10328>>\bf\end<<10329>>tex2html_deferred<<10329>>g<<715>>_f(<<716>>\begin<<10330>>tex2html_deferred<<10330>>\bf\end<<10331>>tex2html_deferred<<10331>>x<<716>>)=<<717>>\begin<<10332>>tex2html_deferred<<10332>>\bf\end<<10333>>tex2html_deferred<<10333>>0<<717>>$\end<<7241>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7241>>\space as a necessary condition for
an extremum of \begin<<7242>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7242>>$<<718>>\begin<<10334>>tex2html_deferred<<10334>>\bf\end<<10335>>tex2html_deferred<<10335>>f<<718>>$\end<<7243>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7243>>.
\begin<<10336>>tex2html_deferred<<10336>>\par\end<<10337>>tex2html_deferred<<10337>>
The speed of convergence of the iteration can be controlled by a parameter 
\begin<<7244>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7244>>$\delta;SPMgt;0$\end<<7245>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7245>>\space that controls the step size:
\begin<<719>>equation<<719>> 
  <<720>>\begin<<10338>>tex2html_deferred<<10338>>\bf\end<<10339>>tex2html_deferred<<10339>>x<<720>>_<<721>>n+1<<721>>=<<722>>\begin<<10340>>tex2html_deferred<<10340>>\bf\end<<10341>>tex2html_deferred<<10341>>x<<722>>_n+\delta_n \; \Delta<<723>>\begin<<10342>>tex2html_deferred<<10342>>\bf\end<<10343>>tex2html_deferred<<10343>>x<<723>>_n
  =<<724>>\begin<<10344>>tex2html_deferred<<10344>>\bf\end<<10345>>tex2html_deferred<<10345>>x<<724>>_n-\delta_n \; <<725>>\begin<<10346>>tex2html_deferred<<10346>>\bf\end<<10347>>tex2html_deferred<<10347>>H<<725>>_n^<<726>>-1<<726>><<727>>\begin<<10348>>tex2html_deferred<<10348>>\bf\end<<10349>>tex2html_deferred<<10349>>g<<727>>_n 
\end<<728>>equation<<728>>
\begin<<10350>>tex2html_deferred<<10350>>\par\end<<10351>>tex2html_deferred<<10351>>
This quadratic function can also be expressed as (show it as 
\htmladdnormallink<<729>>homework<<729>><<730>>../sub1/sub1.html<<730>>):
\begin<<731>>equation<<731>>
  q(<<732>>\begin<<10352>>tex2html_deferred<<10352>>\bf\end<<10353>>tex2html_deferred<<10353>>x<<732>>)=\frac<<733>>1<<733>><<734>>2<<734>>(<<735>>\begin<<10354>>tex2html_deferred<<10354>>\bf\end<<10355>>tex2html_deferred<<10355>>x<<735>>-<<736>>\begin<<10356>>tex2html_deferred<<10356>>\bf\end<<10357>>tex2html_deferred<<10357>>b<<736>>)^T<<737>>\begin<<10358>>tex2html_deferred<<10358>>\bf\end<<10359>>tex2html_deferred<<10359>>A<<737>>(<<738>>\begin<<10360>>tex2html_deferred<<10360>>\bf\end<<10361>>tex2html_deferred<<10361>>x<<738>>-<<739>>\begin<<10362>>tex2html_deferred<<10362>>\bf\end<<10363>>tex2html_deferred<<10363>>b<<739>>)+c
\end<<740>>equation<<740>>
where
\begin<<741>>equation<<741>>
  \left\{\begin<<742>>array<<742>><<743>>l<<743>>
           <<744>>\begin<<10364>>tex2html_deferred<<10364>>\bf\end<<10365>>tex2html_deferred<<10365>>A<<744>>=<<745>>\begin<<10366>>tex2html_deferred<<10366>>\bf\end<<10367>>tex2html_deferred<<10367>>H<<745>>_0\\ 
           <<746>>\begin<<10368>>tex2html_deferred<<10368>>\bf\end<<10369>>tex2html_deferred<<10369>>b<<746>>=<<747>>\begin<<10370>>tex2html_deferred<<10370>>\bf\end<<10371>>tex2html_deferred<<10371>>x<<747>>_0-<<748>>\begin<<10372>>tex2html_deferred<<10372>>\bf\end<<10373>>tex2html_deferred<<10373>>H<<748>>^<<749>>-1<<749>><<750>>\begin<<10374>>tex2html_deferred<<10374>>\bf\end<<10375>>tex2html_deferred<<10375>>g<<750>>_0\\ 
           c=f(<<751>>\begin<<10376>>tex2html_deferred<<10376>>\bf\end<<10377>>tex2html_deferred<<10377>>x<<751>>_0)-<<752>>\begin<<10378>>tex2html_deferred<<10378>>\bf\end<<10379>>tex2html_deferred<<10379>>g<<752>>_0^T<<753>>\begin<<10380>>tex2html_deferred<<10380>>\bf\end<<10381>>tex2html_deferred<<10381>>H<<753>>_0^<<754>>-1<<754>><<755>>\begin<<10382>>tex2html_deferred<<10382>>\bf\end<<10383>>tex2html_deferred<<10383>>g_0<<755>>/2
\end<<756>>array<<756>>\right.
\end<<757>>equation<<757>>
and we have
\begin<<758>>equation<<758>>
  <<759>>\begin<<10384>>tex2html_deferred<<10384>>\bf\end<<10385>>tex2html_deferred<<10385>>g<<759>>_0=<<760>>\begin<<10386>>tex2html_deferred<<10386>>\bf\end<<10387>>tex2html_deferred<<10387>>g<<760>>_f(<<761>>\begin<<10388>>tex2html_deferred<<10388>>\bf\end<<10389>>tex2html_deferred<<10389>>x<<761>>_0)=<<762>>\begin<<10390>>tex2html_deferred<<10390>>\bf\end<<10391>>tex2html_deferred<<10391>>A<<762>>(<<763>>\begin<<10392>>tex2html_deferred<<10392>>\bf\end<<10393>>tex2html_deferred<<10393>>x<<763>>_0-<<764>>\begin<<10394>>tex2html_deferred<<10394>>\bf\end<<10395>>tex2html_deferred<<10395>>b<<764>>)=<<765>>\begin<<10396>>tex2html_deferred<<10396>>\bf\end<<10397>>tex2html_deferred<<10397>>A<<765>><<766>>\begin<<10398>>tex2html_deferred<<10398>>\bf\end<<10399>>tex2html_deferred<<10399>>e<<766>>_0,
  \;\;\;\;\;\;\;
  <<767>>\begin<<10400>>tex2html_deferred<<10400>>\bf\end<<10401>>tex2html_deferred<<10401>>H<<767>>_0=<<768>>\begin<<10402>>tex2html_deferred<<10402>>\bf\end<<10403>>tex2html_deferred<<10403>>H<<768>>_f(<<769>>\begin<<10404>>tex2html_deferred<<10404>>\bf\end<<10405>>tex2html_deferred<<10405>>x<<769>>_0)=<<770>>\begin<<10406>>tex2html_deferred<<10406>>\bf\end<<10407>>tex2html_deferred<<10407>>A<<770>>
\end<<771>>equation<<771>>
where \begin<<7246>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7246>>$<<772>>\begin<<10408>>tex2html_deferred<<10408>>\bf\end<<10409>>tex2html_deferred<<10409>>e<<772>>_0=<<773>>\begin<<10410>>tex2html_deferred<<10410>>\bf\end<<10411>>tex2html_deferred<<10411>>x<<773>>_0-<<774>>\begin<<10412>>tex2html_deferred<<10412>>\bf\end<<10413>>tex2html_deferred<<10413>>b<<774>>$\end<<7247>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7247>>\space is the error, and \begin<<7248>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7248>>$||<<775>>\begin<<10414>>tex2html_deferred<<10414>>\bf\end<<10415>>tex2html_deferred<<10415>>e<<775>>_0||$\end<<7249>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7249>>\space is the
distance from \begin<<7250>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7250>>$<<776>>\begin<<10416>>tex2html_deferred<<10416>>\bf\end<<10417>>tex2html_deferred<<10417>>x<<776>>_0$\end<<7251>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7251>>\space to the vertex \begin<<7252>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7252>>$<<777>>\begin<<10418>>tex2html_deferred<<10418>>\bf\end<<10419>>tex2html_deferred<<10419>>x<<777>>=<<778>>\begin<<10420>>tex2html_deferred<<10420>>\bf\end<<10421>>tex2html_deferred<<10421>>b<<778>>$\end<<7253>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7253>>\space of the quadratic 
function, at which it may take the extremum \begin<<7254>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7254>>$q(<<779>>\begin<<10422>>tex2html_deferred<<10422>>\bf\end<<10423>>tex2html_deferred<<10423>>b<<779>>)=c$\end<<7255>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7255>>\space (if \begin<<7256>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7256>>$<<780>>\begin<<10424>>tex2html_deferred<<10424>>\bf\end<<10425>>tex2html_deferred<<10425>>H<<780>>$\end<<7257>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7257>>\space is
either positive or negative definite).
\begin<<10426>>tex2html_deferred<<10426>>\par\end<<10427>>tex2html_deferred<<10427>>
<<781>>\begin<<10428>>tex2html_deferred<<10428>>\bf\end<<10429>>tex2html_deferred<<10429>>Example 0:<<781>> Consider the following quadratic function:
\begin<<782>>equation<<782>>
  q(x,y)=\frac<<783>>1<<783>><<784>>2<<784>> [x,\;y]\left[\begin<<785>>array<<785>><<786>>cc<<786>>a;SPMamp;b/2\\ b/2;SPMamp;c\end<<787>>array<<787>>\right]
  \left[\begin<<788>>array<<788>><<789>>c<<789>>x\\ y\end<<790>>array<<790>>\right]=\frac<<791>>1<<791>><<792>>2<<792>>(ax^2+bxy+cy^2)
  \nonumber
\end<<793>>equation<<793>>
We have
\begin<<794>>equation<<794>>
  <<795>>\begin<<10430>>tex2html_deferred<<10430>>\bf\end<<10431>>tex2html_deferred<<10431>>g<<795>>=\left[\begin<<796>>array<<796>><<797>>c<<797>>ax+by/2\\ bx/2+cy\end<<798>>array<<798>>\right],
  \;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;
  <<799>>\begin<<10432>>tex2html_deferred<<10432>>\bf\end<<10433>>tex2html_deferred<<10433>>H<<799>>=\left[\begin<<800>>array<<800>><<801>>cc<<801>>a;SPMamp;b/2\\ b/2;SPMamp;c\end<<802>>array<<802>>\right],
  \;\;\;\;\;\;\det<<803>>\begin<<10434>>tex2html_deferred<<10434>>\bf\end<<10435>>tex2html_deferred<<10435>>H<<803>>=ac-b^2/4
  \nonumber
\end<<804>>equation<<804>>
We let \begin<<7258>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7258>>$a=1$\end<<7259>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7259>>, \begin<<7260>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7260>>$c=2$\end<<7261>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7261>>, and consider the following values of \begin<<7262>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7262>>$b$\end<<7263>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7263>>:
\begin<<805>>itemize<<805>>
\item \begin<<7264>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7264>>$b=-2$\end<<7265>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7265>>, \begin<<7266>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7266>>$\lambda_1=2.618$\end<<7267>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7267>>, \begin<<7268>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7268>>$\lambda_2=0.382$\end<<7269>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7269>>, \begin<<7270>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7270>>$\det<<806>>\begin<<10436>>tex2html_deferred<<10436>>\bf\end<<10437>>tex2html_deferred<<10437>>H<<806>>=\lambda_1\lambda_2=1$\end<<7271>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7271>>, 
  \begin<<7272>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7272>>$<<807>>\begin<<10438>>tex2html_deferred<<10438>>\bf\end<<10439>>tex2html_deferred<<10439>>H<<807>>;SPMgt;0$\end<<7273>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7273>>\space is positive definite, \begin<<7274>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7274>>$f(0,\,0)=0$\end<<7275>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7275>>\space is the minimum.
\item \begin<<7276>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7276>>$b=0$\end<<7277>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7277>>, \begin<<7278>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7278>>$\lambda_1=2$\end<<7279>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7279>>, \begin<<7280>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7280>>$\lambda_2=1$\end<<7281>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7281>>, \begin<<7282>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7282>>$\det<<808>>\begin<<10440>>tex2html_deferred<<10440>>\bf\end<<10441>>tex2html_deferred<<10441>>H<<808>>=\lambda_1\lambda_2=2$\end<<7283>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7283>>, 
  \begin<<7284>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7284>>$<<809>>\begin<<10442>>tex2html_deferred<<10442>>\bf\end<<10443>>tex2html_deferred<<10443>>H<<809>>;SPMgt;0$\end<<7285>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7285>>\space is positive definite, \begin<<7286>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7286>>$f(0,\,0)=0$\end<<7287>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7287>>\space is the minimum.
\item \begin<<7288>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7288>>$b=2$\end<<7289>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7289>>, \begin<<7290>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7290>>$\lambda_1=2.618$\end<<7291>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7291>>, \begin<<7292>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7292>>$\lambda_2=0.382$\end<<7293>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7293>>, \begin<<7294>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7294>>$\det<<810>>\begin<<10444>>tex2html_deferred<<10444>>\bf\end<<10445>>tex2html_deferred<<10445>>H<<810>>=\lambda_1\lambda_2=1$\end<<7295>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7295>>, 
  \begin<<7296>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7296>>$<<811>>\begin<<10446>>tex2html_deferred<<10446>>\bf\end<<10447>>tex2html_deferred<<10447>>H<<811>>;SPMgt;0$\end<<7297>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7297>>\space is positive definite, \begin<<7298>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7298>>$f(0,\,0)=0$\end<<7299>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7299>>\space is the minimum.
\item \begin<<7300>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7300>>$b=4$\end<<7301>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7301>>, \begin<<7302>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7302>>$\lambda_1=3.562$\end<<7303>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7303>>, \begin<<7304>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7304>>$\lambda_2=-0.562$\end<<7305>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7305>>, \begin<<7306>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7306>>$\det<<812>>\begin<<10448>>tex2html_deferred<<10448>>\bf\end<<10449>>tex2html_deferred<<10449>>H<<812>>=\lambda_1\lambda_2=-2$\end<<7307>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7307>>, 
  \begin<<7308>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7308>>$<<813>>\begin<<10450>>tex2html_deferred<<10450>>\bf\end<<10451>>tex2html_deferred<<10451>>H<<813>>$\end<<7309>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7309>>\space is indefinite, \begin<<7310>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7310>>$f(0,\,0)=0$\end<<7311>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7311>>\space is a saddle point (minimum in one direction
  but maximum in another).
\end<<814>>itemize<<814>>
\begin<<10452>>tex2html_deferred<<10452>>\par\end<<10453>>tex2html_deferred<<10453>>
\htmladdimg<<815>>figures/QuadraticSurf.png<<815>>
\begin<<10454>>tex2html_deferred<<10454>>\par\end<<10455>>tex2html_deferred<<10455>>
We can speed up the convergence by a bigger step size \begin<<7312>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7312>>$\delta;SPMgt;1$\end<<7313>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7313>>. However, 
if \begin<<7314>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7314>>$\delta$\end<<7315>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7315>>\space is too big, the solution may be skipped and the iteration may 
not converge if it gets into an oscillation around the solution. Even worse,
the iteration may become divergent. For such reasons, a smaller step size 
\begin<<7316>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7316>>$\delta;SPMlt;1$\end<<7317>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7317>>\space may be preferred sometimes.
\begin<<10456>>tex2html_deferred<<10456>>\par\end<<10457>>tex2html_deferred<<10457>>
In summary, Newton's method approximates the function \begin<<7318>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7318>>$f(<<816>>\begin<<10458>>tex2html_deferred<<10458>>\bf\end<<10459>>tex2html_deferred<<10459>>x<<816>>)$\end<<7319>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7319>>\space at an
estimated solution \begin<<7320>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7320>>$<<817>>\begin<<10460>>tex2html_deferred<<10460>>\bf\end<<10461>>tex2html_deferred<<10461>>x<<817>>_n$\end<<7321>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7321>>\space by a quadratic equation (the first three 
terms of the Taylor's series) based on the gradient \begin<<7322>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7322>>$<<818>>\begin<<10462>>tex2html_deferred<<10462>>\bf\end<<10463>>tex2html_deferred<<10463>>g<<818>>_n$\end<<7323>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7323>>\space and Hessian 
\begin<<7324>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7324>>$<<819>>\begin<<10464>>tex2html_deferred<<10464>>\bf\end<<10465>>tex2html_deferred<<10465>>H<<819>>$\end<<7325>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7325>>\space of the function at \begin<<7326>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7326>>$<<820>>\begin<<10466>>tex2html_deferred<<10466>>\bf\end<<10467>>tex2html_deferred<<10467>>x<<820>>_n$\end<<7327>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7327>>, and treat the vertex of the 
quadratic equation as the updated estimate \begin<<7328>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7328>>$<<821>>\begin<<10468>>tex2html_deferred<<10468>>\bf\end<<10469>>tex2html_deferred<<10469>>x<<821>>_<<822>>n+1<<822>>$\end<<7329>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7329>>.
\begin<<10470>>tex2html_deferred<<10470>>\par\end<<10471>>tex2html_deferred<<10471>>
Newton's method requires the Hessian matrix as well as the gradient to be 
available. Moreover, it is necessary calculate the inverse of the Hessian 
matrix in each iteration, which may be computationally expensive. 
\begin<<10472>>tex2html_deferred<<10472>>\par\end<<10473>>tex2html_deferred<<10473>>
<<823>>\begin<<10474>>tex2html_deferred<<10474>>\bf\end<<10475>>tex2html_deferred<<10475>>Example 1<<823>> 
\begin<<10476>>tex2html_deferred<<10476>>\par\end<<10477>>tex2html_deferred<<10477>>
The Newton's method is applied to solving the following non-linear equation 
system of \begin<<7330>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7330>>$N=3$\end<<7331>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7331>>\space variables:
\begin<<824>>equation<<824>>
  \left\{\begin<<825>>array<<825>><<826>>l<<826>>
  f_1(x_1,\,x_2,\,x_3)=3x_1-(x_2x_3)^2-3/2\\ 
  f_2(x_1,\,x_2,\,x_3)=4x_1^2-625\,x_2^2+2x_2-1\\ 
  f_3(x_1,\,x_2,\,x_3)=exp(-x_1x_2)+20x_3+9\end<<827>>array<<827>>\right.
  \nonumber
\end<<828>>equation<<828>>
with the exact solution \begin<<7332>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7332>>$(x_1=0.5,\;x_2=0,\;x_3=-0.5)$\end<<7333>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7333>>. These equations can 
be expressed in vector form as \begin<<7334>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7334>>$<<829>>\begin<<10478>>tex2html_deferred<<10478>>\bf\end<<10479>>tex2html_deferred<<10479>>f<<829>>(<<830>>\begin<<10480>>tex2html_deferred<<10480>>\bf\end<<10481>>tex2html_deferred<<10481>>x<<830>>)=<<831>>\begin<<10482>>tex2html_deferred<<10482>>\bf\end<<10483>>tex2html_deferred<<10483>>0<<831>>$\end<<7335>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7335>>\space and solved as an 
optimization problem with the objective function 
\begin<<7336>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7336>>$o(<<832>>\begin<<10484>>tex2html_deferred<<10484>>\bf\end<<10485>>tex2html_deferred<<10485>>x<<832>>)=<<833>>\begin<<10486>>tex2html_deferred<<10486>>\bf\end<<10487>>tex2html_deferred<<10487>>f<<833>>^T(<<834>>\begin<<10488>>tex2html_deferred<<10488>>\bf\end<<10489>>tex2html_deferred<<10489>>x<<834>>)<<835>>\begin<<10490>>tex2html_deferred<<10490>>\bf\end<<10491>>tex2html_deferred<<10491>>f<<835>>(<<836>>\begin<<10492>>tex2html_deferred<<10492>>\bf\end<<10493>>tex2html_deferred<<10493>>x<<836>>)$\end<<7337>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7337>>. The iteration from an 
initial guess \begin<<7338>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7338>>$<<837>>\begin<<10494>>tex2html_deferred<<10494>>\bf\end<<10495>>tex2html_deferred<<10495>>x<<837>>_0=<<838>>\begin<<10496>>tex2html_deferred<<10496>>\bf\end<<10497>>tex2html_deferred<<10497>>0<<838>>$\end<<7339>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7339>>\space is shown below. 
\begin<<839>>equation<<839>>
\begin<<840>>array<<840>><<841>>c||c|c<<841>>\hline 
n ;SPMamp; <<842>>\begin<<10498>>tex2html_deferred<<10498>>\bf\end<<10499>>tex2html_deferred<<10499>>x<<842>>=[x_1,\,x_2,\,x_3]  ;SPMamp; ||<<843>>\begin<<10500>>tex2html_deferred<<10500>>\bf\end<<10501>>tex2html_deferred<<10501>>f<<843>>(<<844>>\begin<<10502>>tex2html_deferred<<10502>>\bf\end<<10503>>tex2html_deferred<<10503>>x<<844>>)|| \\ \hline\hline
0 ;SPMamp;	0.000000,\;\; 0.000000,\;\;  0.000000 ;SPMamp;	1.016120e+01  \\ \hline
1 ;SPMamp;	0.500000,\;\; 0.500000,\;\; -0.500000 ;SPMamp;	1.552502e+02  \\ \hline
2 ;SPMamp;	0.499550,\;\; 0.250800,\;\; -0.493801 ;SPMamp;	3.881300e+01  \\ \hline
3 ;SPMamp;	0.500096,\;\; 0.126206,\;\; -0.496852 ;SPMamp;	9.702208e+00  \\ \hline
4 ;SPMamp;	0.500025,\;\; 0.063914,\;\; -0.498405 ;SPMamp;	2.425198e+00  \\ \hline
5 ;SPMamp;	0.500010,\;\; 0.032778,\;\; -0.499181 ;SPMamp;	6.059054e-01  \\ \hline
6 ;SPMamp;	0.500005,\;\; 0.017231,\;\; -0.499570 ;SPMamp;	1.510777e-01  \\ \hline
7 ;SPMamp;	0.500003,\;\; 0.009498,\;\; -0.499763 ;SPMamp;	3.737330e-02  \\ \hline
8 ;SPMamp;	0.500002,\;\; 0.005712,\;\; -0.499857 ;SPMamp;	8.959365e-03  \\ \hline
9 ;SPMamp;	0.500001,\;\; 0.003968,\;\; -0.499901 ;SPMamp;	1.900145e-03  \\ \hline
10 ;SPMamp;	0.500001,\;\; 0.003326,\;\; -0.499917 ;SPMamp;	2.577603e-04  \\ \hline
11 ;SPMamp;	0.500001,\;\; 0.003206,\;\; -0.499920 ;SPMamp;	8.932714e-06  \\ \hline
12 ;SPMamp;	0.500001,\;\; 0.003202,\;\; -0.499920 ;SPMamp;	1.238536e-08  \\ \hline
13 ;SPMamp;	0.500001,\;\; 0.003202,\;\; -0.499920 ;SPMamp;	2.371437e-14  \\ \hline
\end<<845>>array<<845>>
\end<<846>>equation<<846>>
We see that after 13 iterations the algorithm converges to 
the following approximated solution with accuracy of 
\begin<<7340>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7340>>$o(<<847>>\begin<<10504>>tex2html_deferred<<10504>>\bf\end<<10505>>tex2html_deferred<<10505>>x<<847>>)=||<<848>>\begin<<10506>>tex2html_deferred<<10506>>\bf\end<<10507>>tex2html_deferred<<10507>>f<<848>>(<<849>>\begin<<10508>>tex2html_deferred<<10508>>\bf\end<<10509>>tex2html_deferred<<10509>>x<<849>>^*)||^2\approx 10^<<850>>-28<<850>>$\end<<7341>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7341>>:
\begin<<851>>equation<<851>>
  <<852>>\begin<<10510>>tex2html_deferred<<10510>>\bf\end<<10511>>tex2html_deferred<<10511>>x<<852>>^*=\left[\begin<<853>>array<<853>><<854>>r<<854>>0.5000008539707297\\ 0.0032017070323056\\ 
      -0.4999200212218281\end<<855>>array<<855>>\right]
\end<<856>>equation<<856>>
\begin<<10512>>tex2html_deferred<<10512>>\par\end<<10513>>tex2html_deferred<<10513>>
\subsection*<<857>>Gradient Descent Method<<857>>
\begin<<10514>>tex2html_deferred<<10514>>\par\end<<10515>>tex2html_deferred<<10515>>
Newton's method discussed above is based on the Hessian \begin<<7342>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7342>>$<<858>>\begin<<10516>>tex2html_deferred<<10516>>\bf\end<<10517>>tex2html_deferred<<10517>>H<<858>>_f(<<859>>\begin<<10518>>tex2html_deferred<<10518>>\bf\end<<10519>>tex2html_deferred<<10519>>x<<859>>)$\end<<7343>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7343>>
of the function \begin<<7344>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7344>>$f(<<860>>\begin<<10520>>tex2html_deferred<<10520>>\bf\end<<10521>>tex2html_deferred<<10521>>x<<860>>)$\end<<7345>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7345>>\space to be minimized as well as its gradient 
\begin<<7346>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7346>>$<<861>>\begin<<10522>>tex2html_deferred<<10522>>\bf\end<<10523>>tex2html_deferred<<10523>>g<<861>>_f(<<862>>\begin<<10524>>tex2html_deferred<<10524>>\bf\end<<10525>>tex2html_deferred<<10525>>x<<862>>)$\end<<7347>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7347>>. The method is not applicable if the Hessian 
\begin<<7348>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7348>>$<<863>>\begin<<10526>>tex2html_deferred<<10526>>\bf\end<<10527>>tex2html_deferred<<10527>>H<<863>>_f$\end<<7349>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7349>>\space is not available, or the cost of computing the inverse 
\begin<<7350>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7350>>$<<864>>\begin<<10528>>tex2html_deferred<<10528>>\bf\end<<10529>>tex2html_deferred<<10529>>H<<864>>^<<865>>-1<<865>>_f$\end<<7351>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7351>>\space is too high. In such a case, the gradient descent method
can be used without using the Hessian matrix.
\begin<<10530>>tex2html_deferred<<10530>>\par\end<<10531>>tex2html_deferred<<10531>>
We first consider the minimization of a single-variable function 
\begin<<7352>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7352>>$f(x)$\end<<7353>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7353>>. From any inital point \begin<<7354>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7354>>$x_0$\end<<7355>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7355>>, we can move to a nearby point
\begin<<866>>equation<<866>>
  x_1=x_0+\Delta x_0=x_0-\delta f'(x_0),\;\;\;\;\;
  \mbox<<867>>where<<867>>\;\;\;\;\Delta x_0=-\delta f'(x_0)
\end<<868>>equation<<868>> 
No matter whether \begin<<7356>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7356>>$f'(x_0)$\end<<7357>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7357>>\space is positive or negative, the function value 
\begin<<7358>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7358>>$f(x_1)$\end<<7359>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7359>>\space (approximated by the first two terms of its Taylor series) is 
always reduced if the positive step size \begin<<7360>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7360>>$delta ;SPMgt;0$\end<<7361>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7361>>\space is small enough:
\begin<<869>>equation<<869>>
  f(x_1)\approx f(x_0)+f'(x_0)\Delta x_0=f(x_0)-|f'(x_0)|^2\delta;SPMlt;f(x_0)
\end<<870>>equation<<870>>
This process can be carried out iteratively 
\begin<<871>>equation<<871>>
  x_<<872>>n+1<<872>>=x_n-\delta_n \; f'(x_n) 
\end<<873>>equation<<873>>
until eventually reaching a point \begin<<7362>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7362>>$x^*$\end<<7363>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7363>>\space at which \begin<<7364>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7364>>$f'(x^*)=0$\end<<7365>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7365>>\space and no 
further progress can be made, i.e. a local minimum of the function is 
obtained.
\begin<<10532>>tex2html_deferred<<10532>>\par\end<<10533>>tex2html_deferred<<10533>>
This simple method can be generalized to minimize a multi-variable 
objective function \begin<<7366>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7366>>$f(<<874>>\begin<<10534>>tex2html_deferred<<10534>>\bf\end<<10535>>tex2html_deferred<<10535>>x<<874>>)=f(x_1,\cdots,x_N)$\end<<7367>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7367>>\space in N-D space. The 
derivative of the 1-D case is generalized to the gradient vector 
\begin<<7368>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7368>>$<<875>>\begin<<10536>>tex2html_deferred<<10536>>\bf\end<<10537>>tex2html_deferred<<10537>>g<<875>>(<<876>>\begin<<10538>>tex2html_deferred<<10538>>\bf\end<<10539>>tex2html_deferred<<10539>>x<<876>>)=df(<<877>>\begin<<10540>>tex2html_deferred<<10540>>\bf\end<<10541>>tex2html_deferred<<10541>>x<<877>>)/d<<878>>\begin<<10542>>tex2html_deferred<<10542>>\bf\end<<10543>>tex2html_deferred<<10543>>x<<878>>$\end<<7369>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7369>>\space of function \begin<<7370>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7370>>$f(<<879>>\begin<<10544>>tex2html_deferred<<10544>>\bf\end<<10545>>tex2html_deferred<<10545>>x<<879>>)$\end<<7371>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7371>>,
which is in the direction along which the function increases most rapidly 
with the steepest slope, perpendicular to the contour or iso-lines of the
function \begin<<7372>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7372>>$f(<<880>>\begin<<10546>>tex2html_deferred<<10546>>\bf\end<<10547>>tex2html_deferred<<10547>>x<<880>>)$\end<<7373>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7373>>. The fastest way to reduce \begin<<7374>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7374>>$f(<<881>>\begin<<10548>>tex2html_deferred<<10548>>\bf\end<<10549>>tex2html_deferred<<10549>>x<<881>>)$\end<<7375>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7375>>\space is to go 
down hill along the opposite direction of the gradient vector. 
\begin<<10550>>tex2html_deferred<<10550>>\par\end<<10551>>tex2html_deferred<<10551>>
Specifically the gradient descent method (also called steepest 
descent or down hill method) carries out the following approximation
\begin<<7376>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7376>>$<<882>>\begin<<10552>>tex2html_deferred<<10552>>\bf\end<<10553>>tex2html_deferred<<10553>>x<<882>>_<<883>>n+1<<883>>=<<884>>\begin<<10554>>tex2html_deferred<<10554>>\bf\end<<10555>>tex2html_deferred<<10555>>x<<884>>_n+\Delta<<885>>\begin<<10556>>tex2html_deferred<<10556>>\bf\end<<10557>>tex2html_deferred<<10557>>x<<885>>_n$\end<<7377>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7377>>\space (the first two terms of the 
Taylor series) with \begin<<7378>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7378>>$\Delta<<886>>\begin<<10558>>tex2html_deferred<<10558>>\bf\end<<10559>>tex2html_deferred<<10559>>x<<886>>=-\delta<<887>>\begin<<10560>>tex2html_deferred<<10560>>\bf\end<<10561>>tex2html_deferred<<10561>>g<<887>>\;(\delta;SPMgt;0)$\end<<7379>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7379>>:
\begin<<888>>equation<<888>>
  f(<<889>>\begin<<10562>>tex2html_deferred<<10562>>\bf\end<<10563>>tex2html_deferred<<10563>>x<<889>>_1)=f(<<890>>\begin<<10564>>tex2html_deferred<<10564>>\bf\end<<10565>>tex2html_deferred<<10565>>x<<890>>_0+\Delta<<891>>\begin<<10566>>tex2html_deferred<<10566>>\bf\end<<10567>>tex2html_deferred<<10567>>x<<891>>)
  \approx f(<<892>>\begin<<10568>>tex2html_deferred<<10568>>\bf\end<<10569>>tex2html_deferred<<10569>>x<<892>>_0)+<<893>>\begin<<10570>>tex2html_deferred<<10570>>\bf\end<<10571>>tex2html_deferred<<10571>>g<<893>>^T_0 \Delta<<894>>\begin<<10572>>tex2html_deferred<<10572>>\bf\end<<10573>>tex2html_deferred<<10573>>x<<894>>
  =f(<<895>>\begin<<10574>>tex2html_deferred<<10574>>\bf\end<<10575>>tex2html_deferred<<10575>>x<<895>>_0)-\delta  <<896>>\begin<<10576>>tex2html_deferred<<10576>>\bf\end<<10577>>tex2html_deferred<<10577>>g<<896>>^T_0 <<897>>\begin<<10578>>tex2html_deferred<<10578>>\bf\end<<10579>>tex2html_deferred<<10579>>g<<897>>_0
  =f(<<898>>\begin<<10580>>tex2html_deferred<<10580>>\bf\end<<10581>>tex2html_deferred<<10581>>x<<898>>_0)-\delta  ||<<899>>\begin<<10582>>tex2html_deferred<<10582>>\bf\end<<10583>>tex2html_deferred<<10583>>g<<899>>||^2 ;SPMlt; f(<<900>>\begin<<10584>>tex2html_deferred<<10584>>\bf\end<<10585>>tex2html_deferred<<10585>>x<<900>>_0)
\end<<901>>equation<<901>>
iteratively:
\begin<<902>>equation<<902>> 
  <<903>>\begin<<10586>>tex2html_deferred<<10586>>\bf\end<<10587>>tex2html_deferred<<10587>>x<<903>>_<<904>>n+1<<904>>=<<905>>\begin<<10588>>tex2html_deferred<<10588>>\bf\end<<10589>>tex2html_deferred<<10589>>x<<905>>_n-\delta_n \, <<906>>\begin<<10590>>tex2html_deferred<<10590>>\bf\end<<10591>>tex2html_deferred<<10591>>g<<906>>_n
  =(<<907>>\begin<<10592>>tex2html_deferred<<10592>>\bf\end<<10593>>tex2html_deferred<<10593>>x<<907>>_<<908>>n-1<<908>>-\delta_<<909>>n-1<<909>>\,<<910>>\begin<<10594>>tex2html_deferred<<10594>>\bf\end<<10595>>tex2html_deferred<<10595>>g<<910>>_<<911>>n-1<<911>>)-\delta_n \, <<912>>\begin<<10596>>tex2html_deferred<<10596>>\bf\end<<10597>>tex2html_deferred<<10597>>g<<912>>_n=\cdots=
  <<913>>\begin<<10598>>tex2html_deferred<<10598>>\bf\end<<10599>>tex2html_deferred<<10599>>x<<913>>_0-\sum_<<914>>i=0<<914>>^n \delta_n\,<<915>>\begin<<10600>>tex2html_deferred<<10600>>\bf\end<<10601>>tex2html_deferred<<10601>>g<<915>>_i 
\end<<916>>equation<<916>>
untill eventually reaching a point at which \begin<<7380>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7380>>$<<917>>\begin<<10602>>tex2html_deferred<<10602>>\bf\end<<10603>>tex2html_deferred<<10603>>g<<917>>=<<918>>\begin<<10604>>tex2html_deferred<<10604>>\bf\end<<10605>>tex2html_deferred<<10605>>0<<918>>$\end<<7381>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7381>>\space and the 
minimum of the function \begin<<7382>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7382>>$f(<<919>>\begin<<10606>>tex2html_deferred<<10606>>\bf\end<<10607>>tex2html_deferred<<10607>>x<<919>>)$\end<<7383>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7383>>\space is reached.
\begin<<10608>>tex2html_deferred<<10608>>\par\end<<10609>>tex2html_deferred<<10609>>
Comparing the gradient descent method with Newton's method we see that
here the Hessian matrix is no longer used. The iteration simply follows 
a search direction \begin<<7384>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7384>>$<<920>>\begin<<10610>>tex2html_deferred<<10610>>\bf\end<<10611>>tex2html_deferred<<10611>>d<<920>>_n=-<<921>>\begin<<10612>>tex2html_deferred<<10612>>\bf\end<<10613>>tex2html_deferred<<10613>>g<<921>>_n$\end<<7385>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7385>>, which is different from the 
search direction \begin<<7386>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7386>>$<<922>>\begin<<10614>>tex2html_deferred<<10614>>\bf\end<<10615>>tex2html_deferred<<10615>>d<<922>>_n=-<<923>>\begin<<10616>>tex2html_deferred<<10616>>\bf\end<<10617>>tex2html_deferred<<10617>>H<<923>>^<<924>>-1<<924>>_n<<925>>\begin<<10618>>tex2html_deferred<<10618>>\bf\end<<10619>>tex2html_deferred<<10619>>g<<925>>_n$\end<<7387>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7387>>\space of Newton's method,
based on \begin<<7388>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7388>>$<<926>>\begin<<10620>>tex2html_deferred<<10620>>\bf\end<<10621>>tex2html_deferred<<10621>>H<<926>>_n$\end<<7389>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7389>>\space as well as \begin<<7390>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7390>>$<<927>>\begin<<10622>>tex2html_deferred<<10622>>\bf\end<<10623>>tex2html_deferred<<10623>>g<<927>>_n$\end<<7391>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7391>>. Specially, when \begin<<7392>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7392>>$<<928>>\begin<<10624>>tex2html_deferred<<10624>>\bf\end<<10625>>tex2html_deferred<<10625>>H<<928>>=<<929>>\begin<<10626>>tex2html_deferred<<10626>>\bf\end<<10627>>tex2html_deferred<<10627>>I<<929>>$\end<<7393>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7393>>, 
the two methods become the same.
\begin<<10628>>tex2html_deferred<<10628>>\par\end<<10629>>tex2html_deferred<<10629>>
As the gradient descent method relies only on the gradient vector of the
objective function without any information contained in the second order 
derivatives in the Hessian matrix, it does not have as much information as
Newton's method and therefore may not be as efficient. For example, when 
the function is quadratic, as discussed before, Newton's method can find 
the solution in a single step from any initial guess, but it may take the 
gradient descent method many steps to reach the solution, because it always 
follows the negative direction of the local gradient, which typically does 
not point to the solution directly. However, for the same reason, the 
gradient descent method is computationally less expensive and will be 
effective when the Hessian matrix is not used.
\begin<<10630>>tex2html_deferred<<10630>>\par\end<<10631>>tex2html_deferred<<10631>>
<<930>>\begin<<10632>>tex2html_deferred<<10632>>\bf\end<<10633>>tex2html_deferred<<10633>>Example:<<930>> Consider a two-variable quadratic function in the following
general form:
\begin<<931>>equation<<931>>
  f(<<932>>\begin<<10634>>tex2html_deferred<<10634>>\bf\end<<10635>>tex2html_deferred<<10635>>x<<932>>)=<<933>>\begin<<10636>>tex2html_deferred<<10636>>\bf\end<<10637>>tex2html_deferred<<10637>>x<<933>>^T<<934>>\begin<<10638>>tex2html_deferred<<10638>>\bf\end<<10639>>tex2html_deferred<<10639>>Ax<<934>>+<<935>>\begin<<10640>>tex2html_deferred<<10640>>\bf\end<<10641>>tex2html_deferred<<10641>>b<<935>>^T<<936>>\begin<<10642>>tex2html_deferred<<10642>>\bf\end<<10643>>tex2html_deferred<<10643>>x<<936>>+c
  =[x_1\;x_2]\left[\begin<<937>>array<<937>><<938>>cc<<938>>a_<<939>>11<<939>> ;SPMamp; a_<<940>>12<<940>>\\ a_<<941>>21<<941>> ;SPMamp; a_<<942>>22<<942>>\end<<943>>array<<943>>\right]
  \left[\begin<<944>>array<<944>><<945>>c<<945>>x_1\\ x_2\end<<946>>array<<946>>\right]
  +[b_1\;b_2]\left[\begin<<947>>array<<947>><<948>>c<<948>>x_1\\ x_2\end<<949>>array<<949>>\right]+c
  \nonumber
\end<<950>>equation<<950>>
where \begin<<7394>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7394>>$<<951>>\begin<<10644>>tex2html_deferred<<10644>>\bf\end<<10645>>tex2html_deferred<<10645>>A<<951>>$\end<<7395>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7395>>\space is a symmetric positive semidefinite matrix,
i.e., \begin<<7396>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7396>>$a_<<952>>12<<952>>=a_<<953>>21<<953>>$\end<<7397>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7397>>\space and \begin<<7398>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7398>>$<<954>>\begin<<10646>>tex2html_deferred<<10646>>\bf\end<<10647>>tex2html_deferred<<10647>>A<<954>>\ge 0$\end<<7399>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7399>>. Specially, if we let 
\begin<<955>>equation<<955>>
  <<956>>\begin<<10648>>tex2html_deferred<<10648>>\bf\end<<10649>>tex2html_deferred<<10649>>A<<956>>=\left[\begin<<957>>array<<957>><<958>>cc<<958>>2 ;SPMamp; 1\\ 1 ;SPMamp; 1\end<<959>>array<<959>>\right],\;\;\;\;\;
  <<960>>\begin<<10650>>tex2html_deferred<<10650>>\bf\end<<10651>>tex2html_deferred<<10651>>b<<960>>=\left[\begin<<961>>array<<961>><<962>>c<<962>>0 \\ 0\end<<963>>array<<963>>\right],\;\;\;\;\;  c=0
  \nonumber
\end<<964>>equation<<964>> 
then we have the following function:
\begin<<965>>equation<<965>>
  f(x_1,x_2)=\frac<<966>>1<<966>><<967>>2<<967>>[x_1\;x_2]\left[\begin<<968>>array<<968>><<969>>cc<<969>>2;SPMamp;1\\ 1;SPMamp;1\end<<970>>array<<970>>\right]
  \left[\begin<<971>>array<<971>><<972>>c<<972>>x_1\\ x_2\end<<973>>array<<973>>\right]=\frac<<974>>1<<974>><<975>>2<<975>>(2x_1^2+2x_1x_2+x_2^2)
  \nonumber
\end<<976>>equation<<976>>
which has a minimum \begin<<7400>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7400>>$f(x_1,\,x_2)=0$\end<<7401>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7401>>\space at \begin<<7402>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7402>>$x=y=0$\end<<7403>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7403>>. 
\begin<<10652>>tex2html_deferred<<10652>>\par\end<<10653>>tex2html_deferred<<10653>>
\htmladdimg<<977>>figures/gradient1.png<<977>>
\begin<<10654>>tex2html_deferred<<10654>>\par\end<<10655>>tex2html_deferred<<10655>>
We assume the initial guess is \begin<<7404>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7404>>$<<978>>\begin<<10656>>tex2html_deferred<<10656>>\bf\end<<10657>>tex2html_deferred<<10657>>x<<978>>_0=[1,\;2]^T$\end<<7405>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7405>>, at which the
gradient is \begin<<7406>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7406>>$<<979>>\begin<<10658>>tex2html_deferred<<10658>>\bf\end<<10659>>tex2html_deferred<<10659>>g<<979>>_0=[4,\;3]^T$\end<<7407>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7407>>. Now we compare the gradient method
with Newton's method, in terms of the search direction \begin<<7408>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7408>>$<<980>>\begin<<10660>>tex2html_deferred<<10660>>\bf\end<<10661>>tex2html_deferred<<10661>>d<<980>>$\end<<7409>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7409>>\space and 
progress of the iterations:
\begin<<981>>itemize<<981>>
\item Newton's method: Here we have
  \begin<<982>>equation<<982>>
    <<983>>\begin<<10662>>tex2html_deferred<<10662>>\bf\end<<10663>>tex2html_deferred<<10663>>g<<983>>=\left[\begin<<984>>array<<984>><<985>>c<<985>>2x_1+x_2\\ x_1+x_2\end<<986>>array<<986>>\right],\;\;\;\;\;
    <<987>>\begin<<10664>>tex2html_deferred<<10664>>\bf\end<<10665>>tex2html_deferred<<10665>>H<<987>>=<<988>>\begin<<10666>>tex2html_deferred<<10666>>\bf\end<<10667>>tex2html_deferred<<10667>>A<<988>>=\left[\begin<<989>>array<<989>><<990>>cc<<990>>2;SPMamp;1\\ 1;SPMamp;1\end<<991>>array<<991>>\right],\;\;\;\;
    <<992>>\begin<<10668>>tex2html_deferred<<10668>>\bf\end<<10669>>tex2html_deferred<<10669>>H<<992>>^<<993>>-1<<993>>=\left[\begin<<994>>array<<994>><<995>>rr<<995>>1;SPMamp;-1\\ -1;SPMamp;2\end<<996>>array<<996>>\right]
    \nonumber
  \end<<997>>equation<<997>>
  and the search direction is 
  \begin<<7410>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7410>>$<<998>>\begin<<10670>>tex2html_deferred<<10670>>\bf\end<<10671>>tex2html_deferred<<10671>>d<<998>>_0=-<<999>>\begin<<10672>>tex2html_deferred<<10672>>\bf\end<<10673>>tex2html_deferred<<10673>>H<<999>>^<<1000>>-1<<1000>><<1001>>\begin<<10674>>tex2html_deferred<<10674>>\bf\end<<10675>>tex2html_deferred<<10675>>g<<1001>>_0=-[1,\;2]^T$\end<<7411>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7411>>\space (the red arrow in the figure).
  The iteration is:
  \begin<<1002>>equation<<1002>>
    <<1003>>\begin<<10676>>tex2html_deferred<<10676>>\bf\end<<10677>>tex2html_deferred<<10677>>x<<1003>>_1=<<1004>>\begin<<10678>>tex2html_deferred<<10678>>\bf\end<<10679>>tex2html_deferred<<10679>>x<<1004>>_0-<<1005>>\begin<<10680>>tex2html_deferred<<10680>>\bf\end<<10681>>tex2html_deferred<<10681>>H<<1005>>^<<1006>>-1<<1006>><<1007>>\begin<<10682>>tex2html_deferred<<10682>>\bf\end<<10683>>tex2html_deferred<<10683>>g<<1007>>_0=\left[\begin<<1008>>array<<1008>><<1009>>rr<<1009>>1\\ 
        2\end<<1010>>array<<1010>>\right]
    -\left[\begin<<1011>>array<<1011>><<1012>>rr<<1012>>1;SPMamp;-1\\ -1;SPMamp;2\end<<1013>>array<<1013>>\right]
    \left[\begin<<1014>>array<<1014>><<1015>>r<<1015>>4\\ 3\end<<1016>>array<<1016>>\right]
    =\left[\begin<<1017>>array<<1017>><<1018>>r<<1018>>0\\ 0\end<<1019>>array<<1019>>\right]
    \nonumber
  \end<<1020>>equation<<1020>>
  which is the minimum of the function.
\item The gradient descent method: the search direction is
  \begin<<7412>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7412>>$<<1021>>\begin<<10684>>tex2html_deferred<<10684>>\bf\end<<10685>>tex2html_deferred<<10685>>d<<1021>>_0=-<<1022>>\begin<<10686>>tex2html_deferred<<10686>>\bf\end<<10687>>tex2html_deferred<<10687>>g<<1022>>_0=-[4,\;3]^T$\end<<7413>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7413>>, perpendicular to the contour of 
  the function. The first iteration is:
  \begin<<1023>>equation<<1023>>
    <<1024>>\begin<<10688>>tex2html_deferred<<10688>>\bf\end<<10689>>tex2html_deferred<<10689>>x<<1024>>_1=<<1025>>\begin<<10690>>tex2html_deferred<<10690>>\bf\end<<10691>>tex2html_deferred<<10691>>x<<1025>>_0-\delta<<1026>>\begin<<10692>>tex2html_deferred<<10692>>\bf\end<<10693>>tex2html_deferred<<10693>>g<<1026>>_0
    =\left[\begin<<1027>>array<<1027>><<1028>>r<<1028>>1\\ 2\end<<1029>>array<<1029>>\right]
    -\delta\left[\begin<<1030>>array<<1030>><<1031>>r<<1031>>4\\ 3\end<<1032>>array<<1032>>\right]
    =\left[\begin<<1033>>array<<1033>><<1034>>r<<1034>>1-\delta 4\\ 2-\delta 3\end<<1035>>array<<1035>>\right]
    \nonumber
  \end<<1036>>equation<<1036>>
  We need to determine the step size \begin<<7414>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7414>>$\delta$\end<<7415>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7415>>\space (to be considered later)
  to find \begin<<7416>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7416>>$<<1037>>\begin<<10694>>tex2html_deferred<<10694>>\bf\end<<10695>>tex2html_deferred<<10695>>x<<1037>>_1$\end<<7417>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7417>>, and then continue the iteration.
\end<<1038>>itemize<<1038>>
\begin<<10696>>tex2html_deferred<<10696>>\par\end<<10697>>tex2html_deferred<<10697>>
The figure below compares the search directions of the gradient descent
method (blue) based only on the gradient vector \begin<<7418>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7418>>$<<1039>>\begin<<10698>>tex2html_deferred<<10698>>\bf\end<<10699>>tex2html_deferred<<10699>>g<<1039>>_0$\end<<7419>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7419>>, the local 
information at the point \begin<<7420>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7420>>$<<1040>>\begin<<10700>>tex2html_deferred<<10700>>\bf\end<<10701>>tex2html_deferred<<10701>>x<<1040>>_0$\end<<7421>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7421>>, and Newton's method (red) based on 
the Hessian matrix \begin<<7422>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7422>>$<<1041>>\begin<<10702>>tex2html_deferred<<10702>>\bf\end<<10703>>tex2html_deferred<<10703>>H<<1041>>$\end<<7423>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7423>>, the global of the quadratic function, as well
as the gradient \begin<<7424>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7424>>$<<1042>>\begin<<10704>>tex2html_deferred<<10704>>\bf\end<<10705>>tex2html_deferred<<10705>>g<<1042>>_0$\end<<7425>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7425>>.
\begin<<10706>>tex2html_deferred<<10706>>\par\end<<10707>>tex2html_deferred<<10707>>
\htmladdimg<<1043>>figures/QuadraticContourEx2.png<<1043>>
\begin<<10708>>tex2html_deferred<<10708>>\par\end<<10709>>tex2html_deferred<<10709>>
We see that Newton's method finds the solution in a single step, but
the gradient descent method requires an iteration, and therefore less
effective. This is because the gradient descent method only has available
the local information provided by the first order derivative \begin<<7426>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7426>>$<<1044>>\begin<<10710>>tex2html_deferred<<10710>>\bf\end<<10711>>tex2html_deferred<<10711>>g<<1044>>$\end<<7427>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7427>>, 
the gradient direction of the function at a single point, while Newton's
method can make use of the second order derivative \begin<<7428>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7428>>$<<1045>>\begin<<10712>>tex2html_deferred<<10712>>\bf\end<<10713>>tex2html_deferred<<10713>>H<<1045>>$\end<<7429>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7429>>, representing
the global information of the elliptical shape of the contour line of the
quadratic function, as well as the local information. 
\begin<<10714>>tex2html_deferred<<10714>>\par\end<<10715>>tex2html_deferred<<10715>>
Moreover, in the gradient descent method, we still need to determine 
a proper step size \begin<<7430>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7430>>$\delta$\end<<7431>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7431>>. If \begin<<7432>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7432>>$\delta$\end<<7433>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7433>>\space is too small, the iteration
may converge very slowly, especially when \begin<<7434>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7434>>$f(x)$\end<<7435>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7435>>\space reduces slowly toward 
its minimum. On the other hand, if \begin<<7436>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7436>>$\delta$\end<<7437>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7437>>\space is too large but \begin<<7438>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7438>>$f(x)$\end<<7439>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7439>>\space has
some rapid variations in the local region, the minimum of the function 
may be skipped and the iteration may not converge. We will consider how
to find the optimal step size in the next section.
\begin<<10716>>tex2html_deferred<<10716>>\par\end<<10717>>tex2html_deferred<<10717>>
\subsection*<<1046>>Line minimization<<1046>>
\begin<<10718>>tex2html_deferred<<10718>>\par\end<<10719>>tex2html_deferred<<10719>>
In both Newton's method and the radient descent method, an iteration 
\begin<<7440>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7440>>$<<1047>>\begin<<10720>>tex2html_deferred<<10720>>\bf\end<<10721>>tex2html_deferred<<10721>>x<<1047>>_<<1048>>n+1<<1048>>=<<1049>>\begin<<10722>>tex2html_deferred<<10722>>\bf\end<<10723>>tex2html_deferred<<10723>>x<<1049>>_n+\delta_n<<1050>>\begin<<10724>>tex2html_deferred<<10724>>\bf\end<<10725>>tex2html_deferred<<10725>>d<<1050>>_n$\end<<7441>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7441>>\space is carried out to gradually 
reduce the value of the objective function \begin<<7442>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7442>>$f(<<1051>>\begin<<10726>>tex2html_deferred<<10726>>\bf\end<<10727>>tex2html_deferred<<10727>>x<<1051>>)$\end<<7443>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7443>>. Here both the
search direction \begin<<7444>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7444>>$<<1052>>\begin<<10728>>tex2html_deferred<<10728>>\bf\end<<10729>>tex2html_deferred<<10729>>d<<1052>>_n$\end<<7445>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7445>>\space and the step size \begin<<7446>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7446>>$\delta$\end<<7447>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7447>>\space need to be 
determined to maximally reduce the function value \begin<<7448>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7448>>$f(<<1053>>\begin<<10730>>tex2html_deferred<<10730>>\bf\end<<10731>>tex2html_deferred<<10731>>x<<1053>>_<<1054>>n+1<<1054>>)$\end<<7449>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7449>>.
\begin<<10732>>tex2html_deferred<<10732>>\par\end<<10733>>tex2html_deferred<<10733>>
First, we realize that to reduce \begin<<7450>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7450>>$f(<<1055>>\begin<<10734>>tex2html_deferred<<10734>>\bf\end<<10735>>tex2html_deferred<<10735>>x<<1055>>_<<1056>>n+1<<1056>>)$\end<<7451>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7451>>\space the search 
direction \begin<<7452>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7452>>$<<1057>>\begin<<10736>>tex2html_deferred<<10736>>\bf\end<<10737>>tex2html_deferred<<10737>>d<<1057>>$\end<<7453>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7453>>\space needs to point away from the gradient \begin<<7454>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7454>>$<<1058>>\begin<<10738>>tex2html_deferred<<10738>>\bf\end<<10739>>tex2html_deferred<<10739>>g<<1058>>_n$\end<<7455>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7455>> 
along which \begin<<7456>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7456>>$f(<<1059>>\begin<<10740>>tex2html_deferred<<10740>>\bf\end<<10741>>tex2html_deferred<<10741>>x<<1059>>_n)$\end<<7457>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7457>>\space increases most rapidly, i.e., the angle 
\begin<<7458>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7458>>$\theta$\end<<7459>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7459>>\space between \begin<<7460>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7460>>$<<1060>>\begin<<10742>>tex2html_deferred<<10742>>\bf\end<<10743>>tex2html_deferred<<10743>>d<<1060>>_n$\end<<7461>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7461>>\space and \begin<<7462>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7462>>$<<1061>>\begin<<10744>>tex2html_deferred<<10744>>\bf\end<<10745>>tex2html_deferred<<10745>>g<<1061>>_n$\end<<7463>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7463>>\space should be greater than 
\begin<<7464>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7464>>$\pi/2$\end<<7465>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7465>>:
\begin<<1062>>equation<<1062>>
  \theta=\cos^<<1063>>-1<<1063>>\frac<<6523>><<1064>>\begin<<10746>>tex2html_deferred<<10746>>\bf\end<<10747>>tex2html_deferred<<10747>>d<<1064>>_n^T<<1065>>\begin<<10748>>tex2html_deferred<<10748>>\bf\end<<10749>>tex2html_deferred<<10749>>g<<1065>>_n<<6523>><<6524>>||<<1066>>\begin<<10750>>tex2html_deferred<<10750>>\bf\end<<10751>>tex2html_deferred<<10751>>d<<1066>>_n||\;||<<1067>>\begin<<10752>>tex2html_deferred<<10752>>\bf\end<<10753>>tex2html_deferred<<10753>>g<<1067>>_n||<<6524>>
  ;SPMgt;\frac<<1068>>\pi<<1068>><<1069>>2<<1069>>
\;\;\;\;\;<<1070>>i.e.,<<1070>>\;\;\;\;\;  <<1071>>\begin<<10754>>tex2html_deferred<<10754>>\bf\end<<10755>>tex2html_deferred<<10755>>d<<1071>>_n^T<<1072>>\begin<<10756>>tex2html_deferred<<10756>>\bf\end<<10757>>tex2html_deferred<<10757>>g<<1072>>_n;SPMlt;0
\end<<1073>>equation<<1073>>
so that \begin<<7466>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7466>>$f(<<1074>>\begin<<10758>>tex2html_deferred<<10758>>\bf\end<<10759>>tex2html_deferred<<10759>>x<<1074>>)$\end<<7467>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7467>>\space will decrease along \begin<<7468>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7468>>$<<1075>>\begin<<10760>>tex2html_deferred<<10760>>\bf\end<<10761>>tex2html_deferred<<10761>>d<<1075>>_n$\end<<7469>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7469>>. 
We see that this condition is indeed satisfied in both the gradient
descent method with \begin<<7470>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7470>>$<<1076>>\begin<<10762>>tex2html_deferred<<10762>>\bf\end<<10763>>tex2html_deferred<<10763>>d<<1076>>_n=-<<1077>>\begin<<10764>>tex2html_deferred<<10764>>\bf\end<<10765>>tex2html_deferred<<10765>>g<<1077>>_n$\end<<7471>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7471>>\space and Newton's method with
\begin<<7472>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7472>>$<<1078>>\begin<<10766>>tex2html_deferred<<10766>>\bf\end<<10767>>tex2html_deferred<<10767>>d<<1078>>_n=-<<1079>>\begin<<10768>>tex2html_deferred<<10768>>\bf\end<<10769>>tex2html_deferred<<10769>>H<<1079>>_n^<<1080>>-1<<1080>><<1081>>\begin<<10770>>tex2html_deferred<<10770>>\bf\end<<10771>>tex2html_deferred<<10771>>g<<1081>>_n$\end<<7473>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7473>>\space (with \begin<<7474>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7474>>$<<1082>>\begin<<10772>>tex2html_deferred<<10772>>\bf\end<<10773>>tex2html_deferred<<10773>>H<<1082>>_n$\end<<7475>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7475>>\space being positive 
definite):
\begin<<1083>>equation<<1083>>
  <<1084>>\begin<<10774>>tex2html_deferred<<10774>>\bf\end<<10775>>tex2html_deferred<<10775>>d<<1084>>_n^T<<1085>>\begin<<10776>>tex2html_deferred<<10776>>\bf\end<<10777>>tex2html_deferred<<10777>>g<<1085>>_n=-<<1086>>\begin<<10778>>tex2html_deferred<<10778>>\bf\end<<10779>>tex2html_deferred<<10779>>g<<1086>>_n^T<<1087>>\begin<<10780>>tex2html_deferred<<10780>>\bf\end<<10781>>tex2html_deferred<<10781>>H<<1087>>_n^<<1088>>-1<<1088>><<1089>>\begin<<10782>>tex2html_deferred<<10782>>\bf\end<<10783>>tex2html_deferred<<10783>>g<<1089>>_n ;SPMlt;0,\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;
  <<1090>>\begin<<10784>>tex2html_deferred<<10784>>\bf\end<<10785>>tex2html_deferred<<10785>>d<<1090>>_n^T<<1091>>\begin<<10786>>tex2html_deferred<<10786>>\bf\end<<10787>>tex2html_deferred<<10787>>g<<1091>>_n=-<<1092>>\begin<<10788>>tex2html_deferred<<10788>>\bf\end<<10789>>tex2html_deferred<<10789>>g<<1092>>_n^T<<1093>>\begin<<10790>>tex2html_deferred<<10790>>\bf\end<<10791>>tex2html_deferred<<10791>>g<<1093>>_n=-||<<1094>>\begin<<10792>>tex2html_deferred<<10792>>\bf\end<<10793>>tex2html_deferred<<10793>>g<<1094>>_n||^2 ;SPMlt;0
\end<<1095>>equation<<1095>>
\begin<<10794>>tex2html_deferred<<10794>>\par\end<<10795>>tex2html_deferred<<10795>>
Second, the optimal step size \begin<<7476>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7476>>$\delta_n$\end<<7477>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7477>>\space needs to be determined so that 
the function velue at the next step \begin<<7478>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7478>>$f(<<1096>>\begin<<10796>>tex2html_deferred<<10796>>\bf\end<<10797>>tex2html_deferred<<10797>>x<<1096>>_<<1097>>n+1<<1097>>)=f(<<1098>>\begin<<10798>>tex2html_deferred<<10798>>\bf\end<<10799>>tex2html_deferred<<10799>>x<<1098>>_n+\delta_n<<1099>>\begin<<10800>>tex2html_deferred<<10800>>\bf\end<<10801>>tex2html_deferred<<10801>>d<<1099>>_n)$\end<<7479>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7479>> 
is minimized along the search direction \begin<<7480>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7480>>$<<1100>>\begin<<10802>>tex2html_deferred<<10802>>\bf\end<<10803>>tex2html_deferred<<10803>>d<<1100>>_n$\end<<7481>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7481>>. To find such a \begin<<7482>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7482>>$\delta$\end<<7483>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7483>>,
we set to zero the derivative of the function with respect to \begin<<7484>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7484>>$\delta_n$\end<<7485>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7485>>, the 
<<1101>>\begin<<10804>>tex2html_deferred<<10804>>\em\end<<10805>>tex2html_deferred<<10805>>directional derivative<<1101>> along the direction of \begin<<7486>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7486>>$<<1102>>\begin<<10806>>tex2html_deferred<<10806>>\bf\end<<10807>>tex2html_deferred<<10807>>d<<1102>>_n$\end<<7487>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7487>>, and get 
(by chain rule):
\begin<<1103>>equation<<1103>>
  \frac<<1104>>d<<1104>><<1105>>d\delta_n<<1105>> f(<<1106>>\begin<<10808>>tex2html_deferred<<10808>>\bf\end<<10809>>tex2html_deferred<<10809>>x<<1106>>_<<1107>>n+1<<1107>>)
  =\frac<<1108>>d<<1108>><<1109>>d\delta_n<<1109>>f(<<1110>>\begin<<10810>>tex2html_deferred<<10810>>\bf\end<<10811>>tex2html_deferred<<10811>>x<<1110>>_n+\delta_n<<1111>>\begin<<10812>>tex2html_deferred<<10812>>\bf\end<<10813>>tex2html_deferred<<10813>>d<<1111>>_n)
  =\left(\frac<<6525>>d\,f(<<1112>>\begin<<10814>>tex2html_deferred<<10814>>\bf\end<<10815>>tex2html_deferred<<10815>>x<<1112>>_<<1113>>n+1<<1113>>)<<6525>><<6526>>d<<1114>>\begin<<10816>>tex2html_deferred<<10816>>\bf\end<<10817>>tex2html_deferred<<10817>>x<<1114>><<6526>>\right)^T\;
  \frac<<6527>>d(<<1115>>\begin<<10818>>tex2html_deferred<<10818>>\bf\end<<10819>>tex2html_deferred<<10819>>x<<1115>>_n+\delta_n<<1116>>\begin<<10820>>tex2html_deferred<<10820>>\bf\end<<10821>>tex2html_deferred<<10821>>d<<1116>>_n)<<6527>><<1117>>d\delta_n<<1117>>
  =<<1118>>\begin<<10822>>tex2html_deferred<<10822>>\bf\end<<10823>>tex2html_deferred<<10823>>g<<1118>>^T_<<1119>>n+1<<1119>><<1120>>\begin<<10824>>tex2html_deferred<<10824>>\bf\end<<10825>>tex2html_deferred<<10825>>d<<1120>>_n=0
\end<<1121>>equation<<1121>>
This result indicates that the gradient \begin<<7488>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7488>>$<<1122>>\begin<<10826>>tex2html_deferred<<10826>>\bf\end<<10827>>tex2html_deferred<<10827>>g<<1122>>_<<1123>>n+1<<1123>>=f'(<<1124>>\begin<<10828>>tex2html_deferred<<10828>>\bf\end<<10829>>tex2html_deferred<<10829>>x<<1124>>_<<1125>>n+1<<1125>>)$\end<<7489>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7489>> 
at \begin<<7490>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7490>>$<<1126>>\begin<<10830>>tex2html_deferred<<10830>>\bf\end<<10831>>tex2html_deferred<<10831>>x<<1126>>_<<1127>>n+1<<1127>>$\end<<7491>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7491>>\space needs to be perpendicular to the previous search 
direction \begin<<7492>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7492>>$<<1128>>\begin<<10832>>tex2html_deferred<<10832>>\bf\end<<10833>>tex2html_deferred<<10833>>d<<1128>>_n$\end<<7493>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7493>>. In other words, when traversing along the 
search direction \begin<<7494>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7494>>$<<1129>>\begin<<10834>>tex2html_deferred<<10834>>\bf\end<<10835>>tex2html_deferred<<10835>>d<<1129>>_n$\end<<7495>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7495>>, we should stop at the point 
\begin<<7496>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7496>>$<<1130>>\begin<<10836>>tex2html_deferred<<10836>>\bf\end<<10837>>tex2html_deferred<<10837>>x<<1130>>_<<1131>>n+1<<1131>>=<<1132>>\begin<<10838>>tex2html_deferred<<10838>>\bf\end<<10839>>tex2html_deferred<<10839>>x<<1132>>_n+\delta<<1133>>\begin<<10840>>tex2html_deferred<<10840>>\bf\end<<10841>>tex2html_deferred<<10841>>d<<1133>>_n$\end<<7497>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7497>>\space at which the gradient 
\begin<<7498>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7498>>$<<1134>>\begin<<10842>>tex2html_deferred<<10842>>\bf\end<<10843>>tex2html_deferred<<10843>>g<<1134>>_<<1135>>n+1<<1135>>$\end<<7499>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7499>>\space has zero component along the direction \begin<<7500>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7500>>$<<1136>>\begin<<10844>>tex2html_deferred<<10844>>\bf\end<<10845>>tex2html_deferred<<10845>>d<<1136>>_n$\end<<7501>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7501>>, 
and the corresponding \begin<<7502>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7502>>$\delta$\end<<7503>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7503>>\space is the optimal step size.
\begin<<10846>>tex2html_deferred<<10846>>\par\end<<10847>>tex2html_deferred<<10847>>
Finding the optimal step size \begin<<7504>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7504>>$\delta$\end<<7505>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7505>>\space is a 1-D optimization problem, 
which can be solved by Newton's method. Specifically, we treat
\begin<<7506>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7506>>$f(<<1137>>\begin<<10848>>tex2html_deferred<<10848>>\bf\end<<10849>>tex2html_deferred<<10849>>x<<1137>>_<<1138>>n+1<<1138>>)=f(<<1139>>\begin<<10850>>tex2html_deferred<<10850>>\bf\end<<10851>>tex2html_deferred<<10851>>x<<1139>>_n+\delta<<1140>>\begin<<10852>>tex2html_deferred<<10852>>\bf\end<<10853>>tex2html_deferred<<10853>>d<<1140>>_n)$\end<<7507>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7507>>\space as a function of the signle
variable \begin<<7508>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7508>>$\delta$\end<<7509>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7509>>, and approximate it by the first three terms of its 
Taylor series at \begin<<7510>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7510>>$\delta=0$\end<<7511>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7511>>:
\begin<<1141>>equation<<1141>>
  f(<<1142>>\begin<<10854>>tex2html_deferred<<10854>>\bf\end<<10855>>tex2html_deferred<<10855>>x<<1142>>_<<1143>>n+1<<1143>>)=f(<<1144>>\begin<<10856>>tex2html_deferred<<10856>>\bf\end<<10857>>tex2html_deferred<<10857>>x<<1144>>_n+\delta<<1145>>\begin<<10858>>tex2html_deferred<<10858>>\bf\end<<10859>>tex2html_deferred<<10859>>d<<1145>>_n)\approx
  \left[f(<<1146>>\begin<<10860>>tex2html_deferred<<10860>>\bf\end<<10861>>tex2html_deferred<<10861>>x<<1146>>_n+\delta<<1147>>\begin<<10862>>tex2html_deferred<<10862>>\bf\end<<10863>>tex2html_deferred<<10863>>d<<1147>>_n)\right]_<<1148>>\delta=0<<1148>>
  +\delta\;\left[\frac<<1149>>d<<1149>><<1150>>d\delta<<1150>>f(<<1151>>\begin<<10864>>tex2html_deferred<<10864>>\bf\end<<10865>>tex2html_deferred<<10865>>x<<1151>>_n+\delta<<1152>>\begin<<10866>>tex2html_deferred<<10866>>\bf\end<<10867>>tex2html_deferred<<10867>>d<<1152>>_n)\right]_<<1153>>\delta=0<<1153>>
  +\frac<<1154>>\delta^2<<1154>><<1155>>2<<1155>>\;\left[\frac<<1156>>d^2<<1156>><<1157>>d\delta^2<<1157>>f(<<1158>>\begin<<10868>>tex2html_deferred<<10868>>\bf\end<<10869>>tex2html_deferred<<10869>>x<<1158>>_n+\delta<<1159>>\begin<<10870>>tex2html_deferred<<10870>>\bf\end<<10871>>tex2html_deferred<<10871>>d<<1159>>_n)\right]_<<1160>>\delta=0<<1160>>
  \label<<1161>>OptimalStepTaylor<<1161>>
\end<<1162>>equation<<1162>>
where
\begin<<1163>>eqnarray<<1163>>
  \left[f(<<1164>>\begin<<10872>>tex2html_deferred<<10872>>\bf\end<<10873>>tex2html_deferred<<10873>>x<<1164>>_n+\delta<<1165>>\begin<<10874>>tex2html_deferred<<10874>>\bf\end<<10875>>tex2html_deferred<<10875>>d<<1165>>_n)\right]_<<1166>>\delta=0<<1166>>;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;f(<<1167>>\begin<<10876>>tex2html_deferred<<10876>>\bf\end<<10877>>tex2html_deferred<<10877>>x<<1167>>_n)  \\ 
  \left[\frac<<1168>>d<<1168>><<1169>>d\delta<<1169>>f(<<1170>>\begin<<10878>>tex2html_deferred<<10878>>\bf\end<<10879>>tex2html_deferred<<10879>>x<<1170>>_n+\delta<<1171>>\begin<<10880>>tex2html_deferred<<10880>>\bf\end<<10881>>tex2html_deferred<<10881>>d<<1171>>_n)\right]_<<1172>>\delta=0<<1172>>
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;<<1173>>\begin<<10882>>tex2html_deferred<<10882>>\bf\end<<10883>>tex2html_deferred<<10883>>g<<1173>>(<<1174>>\begin<<10884>>tex2html_deferred<<10884>>\bf\end<<10885>>tex2html_deferred<<10885>>x<<1174>>_n+\delta<<1175>>\begin<<10886>>tex2html_deferred<<10886>>\bf\end<<10887>>tex2html_deferred<<10887>>d<<1175>>_n)^T<<1176>>\begin<<10888>>tex2html_deferred<<10888>>\bf\end<<10889>>tex2html_deferred<<10889>>d<<1176>>_n\bigg|_<<1177>>\delta=0<<1177>>
  =<<1178>>\begin<<10890>>tex2html_deferred<<10890>>\bf\end<<10891>>tex2html_deferred<<10891>>g<<1178>>^T_n<<1179>>\begin<<10892>>tex2html_deferred<<10892>>\bf\end<<10893>>tex2html_deferred<<10893>>d<<1179>>_n\\ 
  \left[\frac<<1180>>d^2<<1180>><<1181>>d\delta^2<<1181>>f(<<1182>>\begin<<10894>>tex2html_deferred<<10894>>\bf\end<<10895>>tex2html_deferred<<10895>>x<<1182>>_n+\delta<<1183>>\begin<<10896>>tex2html_deferred<<10896>>\bf\end<<10897>>tex2html_deferred<<10897>>d<<1183>>_n)\right]_<<1184>>\delta=0<<1184>>
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;\left[\frac<<1185>>d<<1185>><<1186>>d\delta<<1186>><<1187>>\begin<<10898>>tex2html_deferred<<10898>>\bf\end<<10899>>tex2html_deferred<<10899>>g<<1187>>(<<1188>>\begin<<10900>>tex2html_deferred<<10900>>\bf\end<<10901>>tex2html_deferred<<10901>>x<<1188>>_n
  +\delta<<1189>>\begin<<10902>>tex2html_deferred<<10902>>\bf\end<<10903>>tex2html_deferred<<10903>>d<<1189>>_n)^T\right]_<<1190>>\delta=0<<1190>><<1191>>\begin<<10904>>tex2html_deferred<<10904>>\bf\end<<10905>>tex2html_deferred<<10905>>d<<1191>>_n
  =\left[\frac<<1192>>d<<1192>><<6528>>d<<1193>>\begin<<10906>>tex2html_deferred<<10906>>\bf\end<<10907>>tex2html_deferred<<10907>>x<<1193>><<6528>> <<1194>>\begin<<10908>>tex2html_deferred<<10908>>\bf\end<<10909>>tex2html_deferred<<10909>>g<<1194>>(<<1195>>\begin<<10910>>tex2html_deferred<<10910>>\bf\end<<10911>>tex2html_deferred<<10911>>x<<1195>>)\;
    \frac<<1196>>d<<1196>><<1197>>d\delta<<1197>>(<<1198>>\begin<<10912>>tex2html_deferred<<10912>>\bf\end<<10913>>tex2html_deferred<<10913>>x<<1198>>_n+\delta<<1199>>\begin<<10914>>tex2html_deferred<<10914>>\bf\end<<10915>>tex2html_deferred<<10915>>d<<1199>>_n)\right]^T_<<1200>>\delta=0<<1200>>
  <<1201>>\begin<<10916>>tex2html_deferred<<10916>>\bf\end<<10917>>tex2html_deferred<<10917>>d<<1201>>_n
  \nonumber\\ 
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;(<<1202>>\begin<<10918>>tex2html_deferred<<10918>>\bf\end<<10919>>tex2html_deferred<<10919>>H<<1202>>_n<<1203>>\begin<<10920>>tex2html_deferred<<10920>>\bf\end<<10921>>tex2html_deferred<<10921>>d<<1203>>_n)^T<<1204>>\begin<<10922>>tex2html_deferred<<10922>>\bf\end<<10923>>tex2html_deferred<<10923>>d<<1204>>_n=<<1205>>\begin<<10924>>tex2html_deferred<<10924>>\bf\end<<10925>>tex2html_deferred<<10925>>d<<1205>>^T_n<<1206>>\begin<<10926>>tex2html_deferred<<10926>>\bf\end<<10927>>tex2html_deferred<<10927>>H<<1206>>_n<<1207>>\begin<<10928>>tex2html_deferred<<10928>>\bf\end<<10929>>tex2html_deferred<<10929>>d<<1207>>_n
\end<<1208>>eqnarray<<1208>>
where \begin<<7512>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7512>>$<<1209>>\begin<<10930>>tex2html_deferred<<10930>>\bf\end<<10931>>tex2html_deferred<<10931>>H<<1209>>_n=<<1210>>\begin<<10932>>tex2html_deferred<<10932>>\bf\end<<10933>>tex2html_deferred<<10933>>H<<1210>>_n^T$\end<<7513>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7513>>\space is the Hessian matrix of \begin<<7514>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7514>>$f(<<1211>>\begin<<10934>>tex2html_deferred<<10934>>\bf\end<<10935>>tex2html_deferred<<10935>>x<<1211>>)$\end<<7515>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7515>>
at \begin<<7516>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7516>>$<<1212>>\begin<<10936>>tex2html_deferred<<10936>>\bf\end<<10937>>tex2html_deferred<<10937>>x<<1212>>_n$\end<<7517>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7517>>. Substituting these back into the Taylor series above
we get:
\begin<<1213>>equation<<1213>> 
  f(<<1214>>\begin<<10938>>tex2html_deferred<<10938>>\bf\end<<10939>>tex2html_deferred<<10939>>x<<1214>>_n+\delta<<1215>>\begin<<10940>>tex2html_deferred<<10940>>\bf\end<<10941>>tex2html_deferred<<10941>>d<<1215>>_n)\approx 
  f(<<1216>>\begin<<10942>>tex2html_deferred<<10942>>\bf\end<<10943>>tex2html_deferred<<10943>>x<<1216>>_n)+\delta\,<<1217>>\begin<<10944>>tex2html_deferred<<10944>>\bf\end<<10945>>tex2html_deferred<<10945>>g<<1217>>^T_n\,<<1218>>\begin<<10946>>tex2html_deferred<<10946>>\bf\end<<10947>>tex2html_deferred<<10947>>d<<1218>>_n
  +\frac<<1219>>\delta^2<<1219>><<1220>>2<<1220>>\,<<1221>>\begin<<10948>>tex2html_deferred<<10948>>\bf\end<<10949>>tex2html_deferred<<10949>>d<<1221>>^T_n<<1222>>\begin<<10950>>tex2html_deferred<<10950>>\bf\end<<10951>>tex2html_deferred<<10951>>H<<1222>>_n\,<<1223>>\begin<<10952>>tex2html_deferred<<10952>>\bf\end<<10953>>tex2html_deferred<<10953>>d<<1223>>_n 
\end<<1224>>equation<<1224>>
To find \begin<<7518>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7518>>$\delta$\end<<7519>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7519>>\space that minimizes \begin<<7520>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7520>>$f(<<1225>>\begin<<10954>>tex2html_deferred<<10954>>\bf\end<<10955>>tex2html_deferred<<10955>>x<<1225>>_n+\delta<<1226>>\begin<<10956>>tex2html_deferred<<10956>>\bf\end<<10957>>tex2html_deferred<<10957>>d<<1226>>_n)$\end<<7521>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7521>>, we 
set its derivative with respect to \begin<<7522>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7522>>$\delta$\end<<7523>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7523>>\space to zero:
\begin<<1227>>equation<<1227>> 
  \frac<<1228>>d<<1228>><<1229>>d\delta<<1229>>f(<<1230>>\begin<<10958>>tex2html_deferred<<10958>>\bf\end<<10959>>tex2html_deferred<<10959>>x<<1230>>_n+\delta<<1231>>\begin<<10960>>tex2html_deferred<<10960>>\bf\end<<10961>>tex2html_deferred<<10961>>d<<1231>>_n)
  \approx\frac<<1232>>d<<1232>><<1233>>d\delta<<1233>>\left(
  f(<<1234>>\begin<<10962>>tex2html_deferred<<10962>>\bf\end<<10963>>tex2html_deferred<<10963>>x<<1234>>_n)+\delta<<1235>>\begin<<10964>>tex2html_deferred<<10964>>\bf\end<<10965>>tex2html_deferred<<10965>>g<<1235>>^T_n\,<<1236>>\begin<<10966>>tex2html_deferred<<10966>>\bf\end<<10967>>tex2html_deferred<<10967>>d<<1236>>_n
  +\frac<<1237>>\delta^2<<1237>><<1238>>2<<1238>><<1239>>\begin<<10968>>tex2html_deferred<<10968>>\bf\end<<10969>>tex2html_deferred<<10969>>d<<1239>>^T_n<<1240>>\begin<<10970>>tex2html_deferred<<10970>>\bf\end<<10971>>tex2html_deferred<<10971>>H<<1240>>_n\,<<1241>>\begin<<10972>>tex2html_deferred<<10972>>\bf\end<<10973>>tex2html_deferred<<10973>>d<<1241>>_n \right)
  =<<1242>>\begin<<10974>>tex2html_deferred<<10974>>\bf\end<<10975>>tex2html_deferred<<10975>>g<<1242>>^T_n\,<<1243>>\begin<<10976>>tex2html_deferred<<10976>>\bf\end<<10977>>tex2html_deferred<<10977>>d<<1243>>_n+\delta\,<<1244>>\begin<<10978>>tex2html_deferred<<10978>>\bf\end<<10979>>tex2html_deferred<<10979>>d<<1244>>^T_n<<1245>>\begin<<10980>>tex2html_deferred<<10980>>\bf\end<<10981>>tex2html_deferred<<10981>>H<<1245>>_n\,<<1246>>\begin<<10982>>tex2html_deferred<<10982>>\bf\end<<10983>>tex2html_deferred<<10983>>d<<1246>>_n=0 
  \label<<1247>>OptimalDelta1<<1247>>
\end<<1248>>equation<<1248>>
and solve the resulting equation for \begin<<7524>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7524>>$\delta$\end<<7525>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7525>>\space to get the optimal 
step size based on both \begin<<7526>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7526>>$<<1249>>\begin<<10984>>tex2html_deferred<<10984>>\bf\end<<10985>>tex2html_deferred<<10985>>g<<1249>>_n$\end<<7527>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7527>>\space and \begin<<7528>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7528>>$<<1250>>\begin<<10986>>tex2html_deferred<<10986>>\bf\end<<10987>>tex2html_deferred<<10987>>H<<1250>>_n$\end<<7529>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7529>>:
\begin<<1251>>equation<<1251>> 
  \delta_n=-\frac<<6529>><<1252>>\begin<<10988>>tex2html_deferred<<10988>>\bf\end<<10989>>tex2html_deferred<<10989>>g<<1252>>^T_n<<1253>>\begin<<10990>>tex2html_deferred<<10990>>\bf\end<<10991>>tex2html_deferred<<10991>>d<<1253>>_n<<6529>><<6530>><<1254>>\begin<<10992>>tex2html_deferred<<10992>>\bf\end<<10993>>tex2html_deferred<<10993>>d<<1254>>^T_n<<1255>>\begin<<10994>>tex2html_deferred<<10994>>\bf\end<<10995>>tex2html_deferred<<10995>>H<<1255>>_n<<1256>>\begin<<10996>>tex2html_deferred<<10996>>\bf\end<<10997>>tex2html_deferred<<10997>>d<<1256>>_n<<6530>> 
  \label<<1257>>OptimalDelta<<1257>>
\end<<1258>>equation<<1258>>
\begin<<10998>>tex2html_deferred<<10998>>\par\end<<10999>>tex2html_deferred<<10999>>
For example, consider the following two methods for minimization:
\begin<<11000>>tex2html_deferred<<11000>>\par\end<<11001>>tex2html_deferred<<11001>>
\begin<<1259>>itemize<<1259>>
\item <<1260>>\begin<<11002>>tex2html_deferred<<11002>>\bf\end<<11003>>tex2html_deferred<<11003>>Newton's method:<<1260>> 
\begin<<11004>>tex2html_deferred<<11004>>\par\end<<11005>>tex2html_deferred<<11005>>
The search direction is \begin<<7530>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7530>>$<<1261>>\begin<<11006>>tex2html_deferred<<11006>>\bf\end<<11007>>tex2html_deferred<<11007>>d<<1261>>_n=-<<1262>>\begin<<11008>>tex2html_deferred<<11008>>\bf\end<<11009>>tex2html_deferred<<11009>>H<<1262>>_n^<<1263>>-1<<1263>><<1264>>\begin<<11010>>tex2html_deferred<<11010>>\bf\end<<11011>>tex2html_deferred<<11011>>g<<1264>>_n$\end<<7531>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7531>>, and the 
  optimal step size is
  \begin<<1265>>equation<<1265>> 
    \delta_n=-\frac<<6531>><<1266>>\begin<<11012>>tex2html_deferred<<11012>>\bf\end<<11013>>tex2html_deferred<<11013>>g<<1266>>_n^T<<1267>>\begin<<11014>>tex2html_deferred<<11014>>\bf\end<<11015>>tex2html_deferred<<11015>>d<<1267>>_n<<6531>><<6532>><<1268>>\begin<<11016>>tex2html_deferred<<11016>>\bf\end<<11017>>tex2html_deferred<<11017>>d<<1268>>_n^T<<1269>>\begin<<11018>>tex2html_deferred<<11018>>\bf\end<<11019>>tex2html_deferred<<11019>>H<<1269>>_n<<1270>>\begin<<11020>>tex2html_deferred<<11020>>\bf\end<<11021>>tex2html_deferred<<11021>>d<<1270>>_n<<6532>> 
    =\frac<<6533>><<1271>>\begin<<11022>>tex2html_deferred<<11022>>\bf\end<<11023>>tex2html_deferred<<11023>>g<<1271>>^T_n(<<1272>>\begin<<11024>>tex2html_deferred<<11024>>\bf\end<<11025>>tex2html_deferred<<11025>>H<<1272>>_n^<<1273>>-1<<1273>><<1274>>\begin<<11026>>tex2html_deferred<<11026>>\bf\end<<11027>>tex2html_deferred<<11027>>g<<1274>>_n)<<6533>>
    <<6534>>(<<1275>>\begin<<11028>>tex2html_deferred<<11028>>\bf\end<<11029>>tex2html_deferred<<11029>>H<<1275>>_n^<<1276>>-1<<1276>><<1277>>\begin<<11030>>tex2html_deferred<<11030>>\bf\end<<11031>>tex2html_deferred<<11031>>g<<1277>>_n)^T<<1278>>\begin<<11032>>tex2html_deferred<<11032>>\bf\end<<11033>>tex2html_deferred<<11033>>H<<1278>>_n(<<1279>>\begin<<11034>>tex2html_deferred<<11034>>\bf\end<<11035>>tex2html_deferred<<11035>>H<<1279>>^<<1280>>-1<<1280>>_n<<1281>>\begin<<11036>>tex2html_deferred<<11036>>\bf\end<<11037>>tex2html_deferred<<11037>>g<<1281>>_n)<<6534>>\;
    =\frac<<6535>><<1282>>\begin<<11038>>tex2html_deferred<<11038>>\bf\end<<11039>>tex2html_deferred<<11039>>g<<1282>>^T_n(<<1283>>\begin<<11040>>tex2html_deferred<<11040>>\bf\end<<11041>>tex2html_deferred<<11041>>H<<1283>>_n^<<1284>>-1<<1284>><<1285>>\begin<<11042>>tex2html_deferred<<11042>>\bf\end<<11043>>tex2html_deferred<<11043>>g<<1285>>_n)<<6535>>
    <<6536>>(<<1286>>\begin<<11044>>tex2html_deferred<<11044>>\bf\end<<11045>>tex2html_deferred<<11045>>H<<1286>>_n^<<1287>>-1<<1287>><<1288>>\begin<<11046>>tex2html_deferred<<11046>>\bf\end<<11047>>tex2html_deferred<<11047>>g<<1288>>_n)^T<<1289>>\begin<<11048>>tex2html_deferred<<11048>>\bf\end<<11049>>tex2html_deferred<<11049>>g<<1289>>_n<<6536>>\;=1
  \end<<1290>>equation<<1290>>
  This is the iteration obtained before, which is indeed optimal:
  \begin<<1291>>equation<<1291>> 
    <<1292>>\begin<<11050>>tex2html_deferred<<11050>>\bf\end<<11051>>tex2html_deferred<<11051>>x<<1292>>_<<1293>>n+1<<1293>>=<<1294>>\begin<<11052>>tex2html_deferred<<11052>>\bf\end<<11053>>tex2html_deferred<<11053>>x<<1294>>_n+\delta_n<<1295>>\begin<<11054>>tex2html_deferred<<11054>>\bf\end<<11055>>tex2html_deferred<<11055>>d<<1295>>_n
    =x_n-\delta_n<<1296>>\begin<<11056>>tex2html_deferred<<11056>>\bf\end<<11057>>tex2html_deferred<<11057>>H<<1296>>^<<1297>>-1<<1297>>_n<<1298>>\begin<<11058>>tex2html_deferred<<11058>>\bf\end<<11059>>tex2html_deferred<<11059>>g<<1298>>_n=<<1299>>\begin<<11060>>tex2html_deferred<<11060>>\bf\end<<11061>>tex2html_deferred<<11061>>x<<1299>>_n-<<1300>>\begin<<11062>>tex2html_deferred<<11062>>\bf\end<<11063>>tex2html_deferred<<11063>>H<<1300>>^<<1301>>-1<<1301>>_n<<1302>>\begin<<11064>>tex2html_deferred<<11064>>\bf\end<<11065>>tex2html_deferred<<11065>>g<<1302>>_n
  \end<<1303>>equation<<1303>>
\begin<<11066>>tex2html_deferred<<11066>>\par\end<<11067>>tex2html_deferred<<11067>>
\item <<1304>>\begin<<11068>>tex2html_deferred<<11068>>\bf\end<<11069>>tex2html_deferred<<11069>>Gradient descent method:<<1304>> 
\begin<<11070>>tex2html_deferred<<11070>>\par\end<<11071>>tex2html_deferred<<11071>>
The search direction is \begin<<7532>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7532>>$<<1305>>\begin<<11072>>tex2html_deferred<<11072>>\bf\end<<11073>>tex2html_deferred<<11073>>d<<1305>>_n=-<<1306>>\begin<<11074>>tex2html_deferred<<11074>>\bf\end<<11075>>tex2html_deferred<<11075>>g<<1306>>_n$\end<<7533>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7533>>, we have
  \begin<<1307>>equation<<1307>>
    <<1308>>\begin<<11076>>tex2html_deferred<<11076>>\bf\end<<11077>>tex2html_deferred<<11077>>g<<1308>>^T_<<1309>>n+1<<1309>><<1310>>\begin<<11078>>tex2html_deferred<<11078>>\bf\end<<11079>>tex2html_deferred<<11079>>d<<1310>>_n=-<<1311>>\begin<<11080>>tex2html_deferred<<11080>>\bf\end<<11081>>tex2html_deferred<<11081>>g<<1311>>^T_<<1312>>n+1<<1312>><<1313>>\begin<<11082>>tex2html_deferred<<11082>>\bf\end<<11083>>tex2html_deferred<<11083>>g<<1313>>_n=0,
    \;\;\;\;\;\mbox<<1314>>i.e.,<<1314>>\;\;\;\;\;\; <<1315>>\begin<<11084>>tex2html_deferred<<11084>>\bf\end<<11085>>tex2html_deferred<<11085>>g<<1315>>_<<1316>>n+1<<1316>>\perp<<1317>>\begin<<11086>>tex2html_deferred<<11086>>\bf\end<<11087>>tex2html_deferred<<11087>>g<<1317>>_n
  \end<<1318>>equation<<1318>>
  i.e., the search direction \begin<<7534>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7534>>$<<1319>>\begin<<11088>>tex2html_deferred<<11088>>\bf\end<<11089>>tex2html_deferred<<11089>>d<<1319>>_<<1320>>n+1<<1320>>=-<<1321>>\begin<<11090>>tex2html_deferred<<11090>>\bf\end<<11091>>tex2html_deferred<<11091>>g<<1321>>_<<1322>>n+1<<1322>>$\end<<7535>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7535>>\space is always
  perpendicular to the previous one \begin<<7536>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7536>>$<<1323>>\begin<<11092>>tex2html_deferred<<11092>>\bf\end<<11093>>tex2html_deferred<<11093>>d<<1323>>_n=-<<1324>>\begin<<11094>>tex2html_deferred<<11094>>\bf\end<<11095>>tex2html_deferred<<11095>>g<<1324>>_n$\end<<7537>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7537>>, i.e., the
  iteration follows a zigzag path composed of a sequence of segments 
  from the initial guess to the final solution. The optimal step size 
  is
  \begin<<1325>>equation<<1325>> 
    \delta_n=-\frac<<6537>><<1326>>\begin<<11096>>tex2html_deferred<<11096>>\bf\end<<11097>>tex2html_deferred<<11097>>g<<1326>>_n^T<<1327>>\begin<<11098>>tex2html_deferred<<11098>>\bf\end<<11099>>tex2html_deferred<<11099>>d<<1327>>_n<<6537>><<6538>><<1328>>\begin<<11100>>tex2html_deferred<<11100>>\bf\end<<11101>>tex2html_deferred<<11101>>d<<1328>>_n^T<<1329>>\begin<<11102>>tex2html_deferred<<11102>>\bf\end<<11103>>tex2html_deferred<<11103>>H<<1329>>_n<<1330>>\begin<<11104>>tex2html_deferred<<11104>>\bf\end<<11105>>tex2html_deferred<<11105>>d<<1330>>_n<<6538>> 
    =\frac<<6539>><<1331>>\begin<<11106>>tex2html_deferred<<11106>>\bf\end<<11107>>tex2html_deferred<<11107>>g<<1331>>_n^T<<1332>>\begin<<11108>>tex2html_deferred<<11108>>\bf\end<<11109>>tex2html_deferred<<11109>>g<<1332>>_n<<6539>><<6540>><<1333>>\begin<<11110>>tex2html_deferred<<11110>>\bf\end<<11111>>tex2html_deferred<<11111>>g<<1333>>_n^T<<1334>>\begin<<11112>>tex2html_deferred<<11112>>\bf\end<<11113>>tex2html_deferred<<11113>>H<<1334>>_n<<1335>>\begin<<11114>>tex2html_deferred<<11114>>\bf\end<<11115>>tex2html_deferred<<11115>>g<<1335>>_n<<6540>> 
    =\frac<<6541>>||<<1336>>\begin<<11116>>tex2html_deferred<<11116>>\bf\end<<11117>>tex2html_deferred<<11117>>g<<1336>>_n||^2<<6541>><<6542>><<1337>>\begin<<11118>>tex2html_deferred<<11118>>\bf\end<<11119>>tex2html_deferred<<11119>>g<<1337>>_n^T<<1338>>\begin<<11120>>tex2html_deferred<<11120>>\bf\end<<11121>>tex2html_deferred<<11121>>H<<1338>>_n<<1339>>\begin<<11122>>tex2html_deferred<<11122>>\bf\end<<11123>>tex2html_deferred<<11123>>g<<1339>>_n<<6542>> 
    \label<<1340>>GradientStepSizeOptimal<<1340>>
  \end<<1341>>equation<<1341>>
\end<<1342>>itemize<<1342>>
\begin<<11124>>tex2html_deferred<<11124>>\par\end<<11125>>tex2html_deferred<<11125>>
However, as the Hessian \begin<<7538>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7538>>$<<1343>>\begin<<11126>>tex2html_deferred<<11126>>\bf\end<<11127>>tex2html_deferred<<11127>>H<<1343>>_n$\end<<7539>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7539>>\space is not assumed to be available in 
the gradient descent method, the optimal step size above cannot actually 
be computed. We can instead approximate \begin<<7540>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7540>>$f;SPMrdquo;(\delta)\big|_<<1344>>\delta=0<<1344>>$\end<<7541>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7541>>\space in 
the third term of Eq. (\ref<<1345>>OptimalStepTaylor<<1345>>) at two nearby points 
at \begin<<7542>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7542>>$\delta=0$\end<<7543>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7543>>\space and \begin<<7544>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7544>>$\delta=\sigma$\end<<7545>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7545>>, where \begin<<7546>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7546>>$\sigma$\end<<7547>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7547>>\space is a small value:
\begin<<1346>>eqnarray<<1346>>
  \left[\frac<<1347>>d^2<<1347>><<1348>>d\delta^2<<1348>> f(<<1349>>\begin<<11128>>tex2html_deferred<<11128>>\bf\end<<11129>>tex2html_deferred<<11129>>x<<1349>>+\delta<<1350>>\begin<<11130>>tex2html_deferred<<11130>>\bf\end<<11131>>tex2html_deferred<<11131>>d<<1350>>)\right]_<<1351>>\delta=0<<1351>>
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;\left[\frac<<1352>>d<<1352>><<1353>>d\delta<<1353>> f'(<<1354>>\begin<<11132>>tex2html_deferred<<11132>>\bf\end<<11133>>tex2html_deferred<<11133>>x<<1354>>+\delta<<1355>>\begin<<11134>>tex2html_deferred<<11134>>\bf\end<<11135>>tex2html_deferred<<11135>>d<<1355>>)\right]_<<1356>>\delta=0<<1356>>
=\lim_<<1357>>\sigma\rightarrow 0<<1357>>
  \frac<<6543>>f'(<<1358>>\begin<<11136>>tex2html_deferred<<11136>>\bf\end<<11137>>tex2html_deferred<<11137>>x<<1358>>+\sigma<<1359>>\begin<<11138>>tex2html_deferred<<11138>>\bf\end<<11139>>tex2html_deferred<<11139>>d<<1359>>)-f'(<<1360>>\begin<<11140>>tex2html_deferred<<11140>>\bf\end<<11141>>tex2html_deferred<<11141>>x<<1360>>)<<6543>><<1361>>\sigma<<1361>>
  \nonumber\\ 
  ;SPMamp;\approx ;SPMamp;\frac<<6544>><<1362>>\begin<<11142>>tex2html_deferred<<11142>>\bf\end<<11143>>tex2html_deferred<<11143>>g<<1362>>^T(<<1363>>\begin<<11144>>tex2html_deferred<<11144>>\bf\end<<11145>>tex2html_deferred<<11145>>x<<1363>>+\sigma<<1364>>\begin<<11146>>tex2html_deferred<<11146>>\bf\end<<11147>>tex2html_deferred<<11147>>d<<1364>>)\,<<1365>>\begin<<11148>>tex2html_deferred<<11148>>\bf\end<<11149>>tex2html_deferred<<11149>>d<<1365>>-<<1366>>\begin<<11150>>tex2html_deferred<<11150>>\bf\end<<11151>>tex2html_deferred<<11151>>g<<1366>>^T(<<1367>>\begin<<11152>>tex2html_deferred<<11152>>\bf\end<<11153>>tex2html_deferred<<11153>>x<<1367>>)\,<<1368>>\begin<<11154>>tex2html_deferred<<11154>>\bf\end<<11155>>tex2html_deferred<<11155>>d<<1368>><<6544>>
      <<1369>>\sigma<<1369>>
      =\frac<<6545>><<1370>>\begin<<11156>>tex2html_deferred<<11156>>\bf\end<<11157>>tex2html_deferred<<11157>>g<<1370>>^T_\sigma<<1371>>\begin<<11158>>tex2html_deferred<<11158>>\bf\end<<11159>>tex2html_deferred<<11159>>d<<1371>>-<<1372>>\begin<<11160>>tex2html_deferred<<11160>>\bf\end<<11161>>tex2html_deferred<<11161>>g<<1372>>^T<<1373>>\begin<<11162>>tex2html_deferred<<11162>>\bf\end<<11163>>tex2html_deferred<<11163>>d<<1373>><<6545>><<1374>>\sigma<<1374>>
\end<<1375>>eqnarray<<1375>>
where \begin<<7548>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7548>>$<<1376>>\begin<<11164>>tex2html_deferred<<11164>>\bf\end<<11165>>tex2html_deferred<<11165>>g<<1376>>=<<1377>>\begin<<11166>>tex2html_deferred<<11166>>\bf\end<<11167>>tex2html_deferred<<11167>>g<<1377>>(<<1378>>\begin<<11168>>tex2html_deferred<<11168>>\bf\end<<11169>>tex2html_deferred<<11169>>x<<1378>>)$\end<<7549>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7549>>\space and \begin<<7550>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7550>>$<<1379>>\begin<<11170>>tex2html_deferred<<11170>>\bf\end<<11171>>tex2html_deferred<<11171>>g<<1379>>_\sigma=<<1380>>\begin<<11172>>tex2html_deferred<<11172>>\bf\end<<11173>>tex2html_deferred<<11173>>g<<1380>>(<<1381>>\begin<<11174>>tex2html_deferred<<11174>>\bf\end<<11175>>tex2html_deferred<<11175>>x<<1381>>+\sigma<<1382>>\begin<<11176>>tex2html_deferred<<11176>>\bf\end<<11177>>tex2html_deferred<<11177>>d<<1382>>)$\end<<7551>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7551>>.
This approximation can be used to replace \begin<<7552>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7552>>$<<1383>>\begin<<11178>>tex2html_deferred<<11178>>\bf\end<<11179>>tex2html_deferred<<11179>>d<<1383>>_n^T<<1384>>\begin<<11180>>tex2html_deferred<<11180>>\bf\end<<11181>>tex2html_deferred<<11181>>H<<1384>>_n<<1385>>\begin<<11182>>tex2html_deferred<<11182>>\bf\end<<11183>>tex2html_deferred<<11183>>d<<1385>>_n$\end<<7553>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7553>> 
in Eq. (\ref<<1386>>OptimalDelta1<<1386>>) abve:
\begin<<1387>>equation<<1387>>
  \frac<<1388>>d<<1388>><<1389>>d\delta<<1389>>f(<<1390>>\begin<<11184>>tex2html_deferred<<11184>>\bf\end<<11185>>tex2html_deferred<<11185>>x<<1390>>_n+\delta<<1391>>\begin<<11186>>tex2html_deferred<<11186>>\bf\end<<11187>>tex2html_deferred<<11187>>d<<1391>>_n)
  \approx <<1392>>\begin<<11188>>tex2html_deferred<<11188>>\bf\end<<11189>>tex2html_deferred<<11189>>g<<1392>>_n^T\,<<1393>>\begin<<11190>>tex2html_deferred<<11190>>\bf\end<<11191>>tex2html_deferred<<11191>>d<<1393>>_n+\frac<<1394>>\delta<<1394>><<1395>>\sigma<<1395>>
  \left(<<1396>>\begin<<11192>>tex2html_deferred<<11192>>\bf\end<<11193>>tex2html_deferred<<11193>>g<<1396>>_<<1397>>\sigma n<<1397>>^T<<1398>>\begin<<11194>>tex2html_deferred<<11194>>\bf\end<<11195>>tex2html_deferred<<11195>>d<<1398>>_n-<<1399>>\begin<<11196>>tex2html_deferred<<11196>>\bf\end<<11197>>tex2html_deferred<<11197>>g<<1399>>_n^T<<1400>>\begin<<11198>>tex2html_deferred<<11198>>\bf\end<<11199>>tex2html_deferred<<11199>>d<<1400>>_n\right)=0
\end<<1401>>equation<<1401>>
Solving for \begin<<7554>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7554>>$\delta$\end<<7555>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7555>>\space we get the estimated optimal step size:
\begin<<1402>>equation<<1402>>
  \delta_n=-\frac<<6546>>\sigma\,<<1403>>\begin<<11200>>tex2html_deferred<<11200>>\bf\end<<11201>>tex2html_deferred<<11201>>g<<1403>>_n^T<<1404>>\begin<<11202>>tex2html_deferred<<11202>>\bf\end<<11203>>tex2html_deferred<<11203>>d<<1404>>_n<<6546>>
        <<6547>>(<<1405>>\begin<<11204>>tex2html_deferred<<11204>>\bf\end<<11205>>tex2html_deferred<<11205>>g<<1405>>_<<1406>>\sigma n<<1406>>^T<<1407>>\begin<<11206>>tex2html_deferred<<11206>>\bf\end<<11207>>tex2html_deferred<<11207>>d<<1407>>_n-<<1408>>\begin<<11208>>tex2html_deferred<<11208>>\bf\end<<11209>>tex2html_deferred<<11209>>g<<1408>>_n^T<<1409>>\begin<<11210>>tex2html_deferred<<11210>>\bf\end<<11211>>tex2html_deferred<<11211>>d<<1409>>_n)<<6547>> 
        =-\frac<<6548>>\sigma\,<<1410>>\begin<<11212>>tex2html_deferred<<11212>>\bf\end<<11213>>tex2html_deferred<<11213>>g<<1410>>_n^T<<1411>>\begin<<11214>>tex2html_deferred<<11214>>\bf\end<<11215>>tex2html_deferred<<11215>>d<<1411>>_n<<6548>><<6549>>(<<1412>>\begin<<11216>>tex2html_deferred<<11216>>\bf\end<<11217>>tex2html_deferred<<11217>>g<<1412>>_<<1413>>\sigma n<<1413>>-<<1414>>\begin<<11218>>tex2html_deferred<<11218>>\bf\end<<11219>>tex2html_deferred<<11219>>g<<1414>>_n)^T<<1415>>\begin<<11220>>tex2html_deferred<<11220>>\bf\end<<11221>>tex2html_deferred<<11221>>d<<1415>>_n<<6549>> 
\end<<1416>>equation<<1416>>
For example, in the gradient descent method, the search 
direction is \begin<<7556>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7556>>$<<1417>>\begin<<11222>>tex2html_deferred<<11222>>\bf\end<<11223>>tex2html_deferred<<11223>>d<<1417>>_n=-<<1418>>\begin<<11224>>tex2html_deferred<<11224>>\bf\end<<11225>>tex2html_deferred<<11225>>g<<1418>>_n$\end<<7557>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7557>>, and the optimal step size
\begin<<7558>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7558>>$\delta=||<<1419>>\begin<<11226>>tex2html_deferred<<11226>>\bf\end<<11227>>tex2html_deferred<<11227>>g<<1419>>_n||^2/<<1420>>\begin<<11228>>tex2html_deferred<<11228>>\bf\end<<11229>>tex2html_deferred<<11229>>g<<1420>>_n^T<<1421>>\begin<<11230>>tex2html_deferred<<11230>>\bf\end<<11231>>tex2html_deferred<<11231>>H<<1421>>_n<<1422>>\begin<<11232>>tex2html_deferred<<11232>>\bf\end<<11233>>tex2html_deferred<<11233>>g<<1422>>_n$\end<<7559>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7559>>\space depends on
\begin<<7560>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7560>>$<<1423>>\begin<<11234>>tex2html_deferred<<11234>>\bf\end<<11235>>tex2html_deferred<<11235>>H<<1423>>$\end<<7561>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7561>>, which is not assumed to be available. Therefore the 
secant method can be used to approximate the optimal step size:  
\begin<<1424>>equation<<1424>>
  \delta_n=-\frac<<6550>>\sigma\,<<1425>>\begin<<11236>>tex2html_deferred<<11236>>\bf\end<<11237>>tex2html_deferred<<11237>>g<<1425>>_n^T<<1426>>\begin<<11238>>tex2html_deferred<<11238>>\bf\end<<11239>>tex2html_deferred<<11239>>d<<1426>>_n<<6550>><<6551>>(<<1427>>\begin<<11240>>tex2html_deferred<<11240>>\bf\end<<11241>>tex2html_deferred<<11241>>g<<1427>>_<<1428>>\sigma n<<1428>>-<<1429>>\begin<<11242>>tex2html_deferred<<11242>>\bf\end<<11243>>tex2html_deferred<<11243>>g<<1429>>_n)^T<<1430>>\begin<<11244>>tex2html_deferred<<11244>>\bf\end<<11245>>tex2html_deferred<<11245>>d<<1430>>_n<<6551>> 
  =-\frac<<6552>>\sigma\,<<1431>>\begin<<11246>>tex2html_deferred<<11246>>\bf\end<<11247>>tex2html_deferred<<11247>>g<<1431>>_n^T<<1432>>\begin<<11248>>tex2html_deferred<<11248>>\bf\end<<11249>>tex2html_deferred<<11249>>g<<1432>>_n<<6552>><<6553>>(<<1433>>\begin<<11250>>tex2html_deferred<<11250>>\bf\end<<11251>>tex2html_deferred<<11251>>g<<1433>>_<<1434>>\sigma n<<1434>>-<<1435>>\begin<<11252>>tex2html_deferred<<11252>>\bf\end<<11253>>tex2html_deferred<<11253>>g<<1435>>_n)^T<<1436>>\begin<<11254>>tex2html_deferred<<11254>>\bf\end<<11255>>tex2html_deferred<<11255>>g<<1436>>_n<<6553>> 
  =\frac<<6554>>\sigma\,||<<1437>>\begin<<11256>>tex2html_deferred<<11256>>\bf\end<<11257>>tex2html_deferred<<11257>>g<<1437>>_n||^2<<6554>><<6555>>||<<1438>>\begin<<11258>>tex2html_deferred<<11258>>\bf\end<<11259>>tex2html_deferred<<11259>>g<<1438>>_n||^2-<<1439>>\begin<<11260>>tex2html_deferred<<11260>>\bf\end<<11261>>tex2html_deferred<<11261>>g<<1439>>_<<1440>>\sigma n<<1440>>^T<<1441>>\begin<<11262>>tex2html_deferred<<11262>>\bf\end<<11263>>tex2html_deferred<<11263>>g<<1441>>_n<<6555>> 
  \label<<1442>>GradientStepSizeSecant<<1442>>
\end<<1443>>equation<<1443>>
The iteration becomes
\begin<<1444>>equation<<1444>>
  <<1445>>\begin<<11264>>tex2html_deferred<<11264>>\bf\end<<11265>>tex2html_deferred<<11265>>x<<1445>>_<<1446>>n+1<<1446>>=<<1447>>\begin<<11266>>tex2html_deferred<<11266>>\bf\end<<11267>>tex2html_deferred<<11267>>x<<1447>>_n-\delta_n<<1448>>\begin<<11268>>tex2html_deferred<<11268>>\bf\end<<11269>>tex2html_deferred<<11269>>g<<1448>>_n
  =<<1449>>\begin<<11270>>tex2html_deferred<<11270>>\bf\end<<11271>>tex2html_deferred<<11271>>x<<1449>>_n+\frac<<6556>>\sigma\,||<<1450>>\begin<<11272>>tex2html_deferred<<11272>>\bf\end<<11273>>tex2html_deferred<<11273>>g<<1450>>_n||^2<<6556>><<6557>><<1451>>\begin<<11274>>tex2html_deferred<<11274>>\bf\end<<11275>>tex2html_deferred<<11275>>g<<1451>>_<<1452>>\sigma n<<1452>>^T<<1453>>\begin<<11276>>tex2html_deferred<<11276>>\bf\end<<11277>>tex2html_deferred<<11277>>g<<1453>>_n-||<<1454>>\begin<<11278>>tex2html_deferred<<11278>>\bf\end<<11279>>tex2html_deferred<<11279>>g<<1454>>_n||^2<<6557>>\,
  <<1455>>\begin<<11280>>tex2html_deferred<<11280>>\bf\end<<11281>>tex2html_deferred<<11281>>g<<1455>>_n
\end<<1456>>equation<<1456>>
\begin<<11282>>tex2html_deferred<<11282>>\par\end<<11283>>tex2html_deferred<<11283>>
<<1457>>\begin<<11284>>tex2html_deferred<<11284>>\bf\end<<11285>>tex2html_deferred<<11285>>Example: <<1457>> The gradient descent method applied to solve the same
three-variable equation system previously solved by Newton's method:
\begin<<1458>>equation<<1458>>
  \left\{\begin<<1459>>array<<1459>><<1460>>l<<1460>>
  f_1(x_1,\,x_2,\,x_3)=3x_1-(x_2x_3)^2-3/2\\ 
  f_2(x_1,\,x_2,\,x_3)=4x_1^2-625\,x_2^2+2x_2-1\\ 
  f_3(x_1,\,x_2,\,x_3)=exp(-x_1x_2)+20x_3+9\end<<1461>>array<<1461>>\right.
  \nonumber
\end<<1462>>equation<<1462>>
\begin<<11286>>tex2html_deferred<<11286>>\par\end<<11287>>tex2html_deferred<<11287>>
The step size \begin<<7562>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7562>>$\delta_n$\end<<7563>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7563>>\space is determined by the secant method with 
\begin<<7564>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7564>>$\sigma=10^<<1463>>-6<<1463>>$\end<<7565>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7565>>. The iteration from an initial guess \begin<<7566>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7566>>$<<1464>>\begin<<11288>>tex2html_deferred<<11288>>\bf\end<<11289>>tex2html_deferred<<11289>>x<<1464>>_0=<<1465>>\begin<<11290>>tex2html_deferred<<11290>>\bf\end<<11291>>tex2html_deferred<<11291>>0<<1465>>$\end<<7567>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7567>> 
is shown below: 
\begin<<1466>>equation<<1466>>
  \begin<<1467>>array<<1467>><<1468>>c||c|c<<1468>>\hline 
    n ;SPMamp; <<1469>>\begin<<11292>>tex2html_deferred<<11292>>\bf\end<<11293>>tex2html_deferred<<11293>>x<<1469>>=[x_1,\,x_2,\,x_3]  ;SPMamp; ||<<1470>>\begin<<11294>>tex2html_deferred<<11294>>\bf\end<<11295>>tex2html_deferred<<11295>>f<<1470>>(<<1471>>\begin<<11296>>tex2html_deferred<<11296>>\bf\end<<11297>>tex2html_deferred<<11297>>x<<1471>>)|| \\ \hline\hline
    0  ;SPMamp;	0.0000,\;\; 0.0000,\;\;  0.0000	;SPMamp;1.032500e+02 \\ \hline
    10 ;SPMamp;	0.4246,\;\;-0.0073,\;\;-0.5002	;SPMamp;1.535939e-01 \\ \hline
    20 ;SPMamp;	0.5015,\;\; 0.0064,\;\; -0.4998	;SPMamp;2.448241e-05 \\ \hline
    30 ;SPMamp;	0.5009,\;\; 0.0057,\;\; -0.4998	;SPMamp;9.178209e-06 \\ \hline
    40 ;SPMamp;	0.5006,\;\; 0.0052,\;\; -0.4998	;SPMamp;4.17587e-06 \\ \hline
    50 ;SPMamp;	0.5004,\;\; 0.0049,\;\; -0.4999	;SPMamp;2.122594e-06 \\ \hline
    60 ;SPMamp;	0.5003,\;\; 0.0047,\;\; -0.4999	;SPMamp;1.182466e-06 \\ \hline
    100;SPMamp;	0.5001,\;\; 0.0043,\;\; -0.4999	;SPMamp;1.805871e-07 \\ \hline
    150;SPMamp;	0.5000,\;\; 0.0041,\;\; -0.4999	;SPMamp;2.720744e-08 \\ \hline
    200;SPMamp;	0.5000,\;\; 0.0041,\;\; -0.4999	;SPMamp;4.934027e-09 \\ \hline
    250;SPMamp;	0.5000,\;\; 0.0040,\;\; -0.4999	;SPMamp;9.630085e-10 \\ \hline
    300;SPMamp;	0.5000,\;\; 0.0040,\;\; -0.4999	;SPMamp;1.939747e-10 \\ \hline
    350;SPMamp;	0.5000,\;\; 0.0040,\;\; -0.4999	;SPMamp;3.961646e-11 \\ \hline
    400;SPMamp;	0.5000,\;\; 0.0040,\;\; -0.4999	;SPMamp;8.140393e-12 \\ \hline
    450;SPMamp;	0.5000,\;\; 0.0040,\;\; -0.4999	;SPMamp;1.677968e-12 \\ \hline
    500;SPMamp;	0.5000,\;\; 0.0040,\;\; -0.4999	;SPMamp;3.462695e-13 \\ \hline
    550;SPMamp;	0.5000,\;\; 0.0040,\;\; -0.4999	;SPMamp;7.136628e-14 \\ \hline
    600;SPMamp;	0.5000,\;\; 0.0040,\;\; -0.4999	;SPMamp;1.474205e-14 \\ \hline
  \end<<1472>>array<<1472>>
  \nonumber
\end<<1473>>equation<<1473>>
We see that after the first 100 iterations the error is reduced
to about \begin<<7568>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7568>>$o(<<1474>>\begin<<11298>>tex2html_deferred<<11298>>\bf\end<<11299>>tex2html_deferred<<11299>>x<<1474>>)=||<<1475>>\begin<<11300>>tex2html_deferred<<11300>>\bf\end<<11301>>tex2html_deferred<<11301>>f<<1475>>(<<1476>>\begin<<11302>>tex2html_deferred<<11302>>\bf\end<<11303>>tex2html_deferred<<11303>>x<<1476>>^*)||^2\approx 10^<<1477>>-14<<1477>>$\end<<7569>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7569>>, and
With 500 additional iterations the algorithm converges to the 
following approximated solution with accuracy of 
\begin<<7570>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7570>>$o(<<1478>>\begin<<11304>>tex2html_deferred<<11304>>\bf\end<<11305>>tex2html_deferred<<11305>>x<<1478>>)\approx 10^<<1479>>-28<<1479>>$\end<<7571>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7571>>:
\begin<<1480>>equation<<1480>>
  <<1481>>\begin<<11306>>tex2html_deferred<<11306>>\bf\end<<11307>>tex2html_deferred<<11307>>x<<1481>>^*=\left[\begin<<1482>>array<<1482>><<1483>>r<<1483>>
      0.5000013623816102\\ 
      0.0040027495837189\\ 
     -0.4999000311539049\end<<1484>>array<<1484>>\right]
\end<<1485>>equation<<1485>>
Although the gradient descent method requires many more iterations
than Newton's method to converge, the computational cost in each 
iteration is much reduced, as no more matrix inversion is needed.
\begin<<11308>>tex2html_deferred<<11308>>\par\end<<11309>>tex2html_deferred<<11309>>
When it is difficult or too computationally costly to find the 
optimal step size along the search direction, some suboptimal 
step size may be acceptable, such as in the 
\htmladdnormallink<<1486>>\begin<<11310>>tex2html_deferred<<11310>>\em\end<<11311>>tex2html_deferred<<11311>>quasi-Newton methods<<1486>><<1487>>node8.html<<1487>>
for minimization problems. In this case, although the step size 
\begin<<7572>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7572>>$\delta$\end<<7573>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7573>>\space is no longer required to be such that the function value 
at the new position \begin<<7574>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7574>>$f(<<1488>>\begin<<11312>>tex2html_deferred<<11312>>\bf\end<<11313>>tex2html_deferred<<11313>>x<<1488>>_<<1489>>n+1<<1489>>)=f(<<1490>>\begin<<11314>>tex2html_deferred<<11314>>\bf\end<<11315>>tex2html_deferred<<11315>>x<<1490>>_n+\delta<<1491>>\begin<<11316>>tex2html_deferred<<11316>>\bf\end<<11317>>tex2html_deferred<<11317>>d<<1491>>_n)$\end<<7575>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7575>> 
is minimized along the search direction \begin<<7576>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7576>>$<<1492>>\begin<<11318>>tex2html_deferred<<11318>>\bf\end<<11319>>tex2html_deferred<<11319>>d<<1492>>_n$\end<<7577>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7577>>, the step size 
\begin<<7578>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7578>>$\delta$\end<<7579>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7579>>\space still has to satisfy the following
\htmladdnormallink<<1493>>\begin<<11320>>tex2html_deferred<<11320>>\em\end<<11321>>tex2html_deferred<<11321>>Wolfe conditions<<1493>><<1494>>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wolfe_conditions<<1494>>:
\begin<<1495>>itemize<<1495>>
\item <<1496>>\begin<<11322>>tex2html_deferred<<11322>>\em\end<<11323>>tex2html_deferred<<11323>>Sufficient decrease (Armijo rule):<<1496>>
  \begin<<1497>>equation<<1497>>
    f(<<1498>>\begin<<11324>>tex2html_deferred<<11324>>\bf\end<<11325>>tex2html_deferred<<11325>>x<<1498>>_<<1499>>n+1<<1499>>)=f(<<1500>>\begin<<11326>>tex2html_deferred<<11326>>\bf\end<<11327>>tex2html_deferred<<11327>>x<<1500>>_n+\delta<<1501>>\begin<<11328>>tex2html_deferred<<11328>>\bf\end<<11329>>tex2html_deferred<<11329>>d<<1501>>_n)
    \le f(<<1502>>\begin<<11330>>tex2html_deferred<<11330>>\bf\end<<11331>>tex2html_deferred<<11331>>x<<1502>>_n)+c_1\,\delta<<1503>>\begin<<11332>>tex2html_deferred<<11332>>\bf\end<<11333>>tex2html_deferred<<11333>>d<<1503>>^T <<1504>>\begin<<11334>>tex2html_deferred<<11334>>\bf\end<<11335>>tex2html_deferred<<11335>>g<<1504>>_n
  \end<<1505>>equation<<1505>>
\item <<1506>>\begin<<11336>>tex2html_deferred<<11336>>\em\end<<11337>>tex2html_deferred<<11337>>Curvature condition:<<1506>>
  \begin<<1507>>equation<<1507>>
    <<1508>>\begin<<11338>>tex2html_deferred<<11338>>\bf\end<<11339>>tex2html_deferred<<11339>>g<<1508>>_<<1509>>n+1<<1509>>^T <<1510>>\begin<<11340>>tex2html_deferred<<11340>>\bf\end<<11341>>tex2html_deferred<<11341>>d<<1510>>_n\ge c_2\;  <<1511>>\begin<<11342>>tex2html_deferred<<11342>>\bf\end<<11343>>tex2html_deferred<<11343>>g<<1511>>_n^T <<1512>>\begin<<11344>>tex2html_deferred<<11344>>\bf\end<<11345>>tex2html_deferred<<11345>>d<<1512>>_n
  \end<<1513>>equation<<1513>>
  As \begin<<7580>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7580>>$<<1514>>\begin<<11346>>tex2html_deferred<<11346>>\bf\end<<11347>>tex2html_deferred<<11347>>g<<1514>>_n^T<<1515>>\begin<<11348>>tex2html_deferred<<11348>>\bf\end<<11349>>tex2html_deferred<<11349>>d<<1515>>_n;SPMlt;0$\end<<7581>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7581>>, this condition can also be written 
  in the following alternative form:
  \begin<<1516>>equation<<1516>>
    |<<1517>>\begin<<11350>>tex2html_deferred<<11350>>\bf\end<<11351>>tex2html_deferred<<11351>>g<<1517>>_<<1518>>n+1<<1518>>^T <<1519>>\begin<<11352>>tex2html_deferred<<11352>>\bf\end<<11353>>tex2html_deferred<<11353>>d<<1519>>_n| ;SPMlt; |c_2\;<<1520>>\begin<<11354>>tex2html_deferred<<11354>>\bf\end<<11355>>tex2html_deferred<<11355>>g<<1520>>_n^T <<1521>>\begin<<11356>>tex2html_deferred<<11356>>\bf\end<<11357>>tex2html_deferred<<11357>>d<<1521>>_n|
  \end<<1522>>equation<<1522>>
\end<<1523>>itemize<<1523>>
Here the two constants \begin<<7582>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7582>>$c_1$\end<<7583>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7583>>\space and \begin<<7584>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7584>>$c_2$\end<<7585>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7585>>\space above satisfy \begin<<7586>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7586>>$0 ;SPMlt; c_1 ;SPMlt; c_2 ;SPMlt; 1$\end<<7587>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7587>>. 
\begin<<11358>>tex2html_deferred<<11358>>\par\end<<11359>>tex2html_deferred<<11359>>
In general, these conditions are motivated by the desired effect 
that after each iterative step, the function should have a shallower 
slope along \begin<<7588>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7588>>$<<1524>>\begin<<11360>>tex2html_deferred<<11360>>\bf\end<<11361>>tex2html_deferred<<11361>>d<<1524>>_n$\end<<7589>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7589>>, as well as a lower value, so that eventually 
the solution can be approached where \begin<<7590>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7590>>$f(<<1525>>\begin<<11362>>tex2html_deferred<<11362>>\bf\end<<11363>>tex2html_deferred<<11363>>x<<1525>>)$\end<<7591>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7591>>\space is minimum and 
the gradient is zero.
\begin<<11364>>tex2html_deferred<<11364>>\par\end<<11365>>tex2html_deferred<<11365>>
Specifically, to understand the first condition above, we represent
the function to be minimized as a single-variable function of the 
step size \begin<<7592>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7592>>$\phi(\delta)=f(<<1526>>\begin<<11366>>tex2html_deferred<<11366>>\bf\end<<11367>>tex2html_deferred<<11367>>x<<1526>>_n+\delta<<1527>>\begin<<11368>>tex2html_deferred<<11368>>\bf\end<<11369>>tex2html_deferred<<11369>>d<<1527>>_n)$\end<<7593>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7593>>, and its 
tangent line at the point \begin<<7594>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7594>>$\delta=0$\end<<7595>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7595>>\space as a linear function 
\begin<<7596>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7596>>$L_0(\delta)=a+b\delta$\end<<7597>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7597>>, where the intercept \begin<<7598>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7598>>$a$\end<<7599>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7599>>\space can be found
as \begin<<7600>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7600>>$a=L_0(0)=\phi(\delta)\big|_<<1528>>\delta=0<<1528>>=f(<<1529>>\begin<<11370>>tex2html_deferred<<11370>>\bf\end<<11371>>tex2html_deferred<<11371>>x<<1529>>_n)$\end<<7601>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7601>>, and the
slope \begin<<7602>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7602>>$b$\end<<7603>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7603>>\space can be found as the derivative of 
\begin<<7604>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7604>>$\phi(\delta)=f(<<1530>>\begin<<11372>>tex2html_deferred<<11372>>\bf\end<<11373>>tex2html_deferred<<11373>>x<<1530>>_n+\delta<<1531>>\begin<<11374>>tex2html_deferred<<11374>>\bf\end<<11375>>tex2html_deferred<<11375>>d<<1531>>_n)$\end<<7605>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7605>>\space at \begin<<7606>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7606>>$\delta=0$\end<<7607>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7607>>:
\begin<<1532>>equation<<1532>>
  b=\frac<<1533>>d<<1533>><<1534>>d\delta<<1534>>\;f(<<1535>>\begin<<11376>>tex2html_deferred<<11376>>\bf\end<<11377>>tex2html_deferred<<11377>>x<<1535>>_n+\delta<<1536>>\begin<<11378>>tex2html_deferred<<11378>>\bf\end<<11379>>tex2html_deferred<<11379>>d<<1536>>_n)\bigg|_<<1537>>\delta=0<<1537>>
  =<<1538>>\begin<<11380>>tex2html_deferred<<11380>>\bf\end<<11381>>tex2html_deferred<<11381>>g<<1538>>^T_n<<1539>>\begin<<11382>>tex2html_deferred<<11382>>\bf\end<<11383>>tex2html_deferred<<11383>>d<<1539>>_n;SPMlt;0
\end<<1540>>equation<<1540>>
which is required to be negative for the function value to be
reduced, \begin<<7608>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7608>>$f(<<1541>>\begin<<11384>>tex2html_deferred<<11384>>\bf\end<<11385>>tex2html_deferred<<11385>>x<<1541>>_n+\delta<<1542>>\begin<<11386>>tex2html_deferred<<11386>>\bf\end<<11387>>tex2html_deferred<<11387>>d<<1542>>_n);SPMlt;f(<<1543>>\begin<<11388>>tex2html_deferred<<11388>>\bf\end<<11389>>tex2html_deferred<<11389>>x<<1543>>_n)$\end<<7609>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7609>>. Now the
function of the tangent line can be written as
\begin<<1544>>equation<<1544>>
  L_0(\delta)=a+b\delta=f(<<1545>>\begin<<11390>>tex2html_deferred<<11390>>\bf\end<<11391>>tex2html_deferred<<11391>>x<<1545>>_n)+<<1546>>\begin<<11392>>tex2html_deferred<<11392>>\bf\end<<11393>>tex2html_deferred<<11393>>g<<1546>>^T_n<<1547>>\begin<<11394>>tex2html_deferred<<11394>>\bf\end<<11395>>tex2html_deferred<<11395>>d<<1547>>_n\delta
\end<<1548>>equation<<1548>>
Comparing this with a constant line \begin<<7610>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7610>>$L_1(\delta)=f(<<1549>>\begin<<11396>>tex2html_deferred<<11396>>\bf\end<<11397>>tex2html_deferred<<11397>>x<<1549>>_n)$\end<<7611>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7611>>\space of
slope zero, we see that any straight line between \begin<<7612>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7612>>$L_0(\delta)$\end<<7613>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7613>>
and \begin<<7614>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7614>>$L_1(\delta)$\end<<7615>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7615>>\space can be described by 
\begin<<7616>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7616>>$L(\delta)=f(<<1550>>\begin<<11398>>tex2html_deferred<<11398>>\bf\end<<11399>>tex2html_deferred<<11399>>x<<1550>>_n)+c_1\,<<1551>>\begin<<11400>>tex2html_deferred<<11400>>\bf\end<<11401>>tex2html_deferred<<11401>>g<<1551>>^T_n<<1552>>\begin<<11402>>tex2html_deferred<<11402>>\bf\end<<11403>>tex2html_deferred<<11403>>d<<1552>>_n\delta$\end<<7617>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7617>>\space with 
\begin<<7618>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7618>>$0;SPMlt;c_1;SPMlt;1$\end<<7619>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7619>>, with a slope \begin<<7620>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7620>>$0;SPMlt; c_1 <<1553>>\begin<<11404>>tex2html_deferred<<11404>>\bf\end<<11405>>tex2html_deferred<<11405>>g<<1553>>_n^T<<1554>>\begin<<11406>>tex2html_deferred<<11406>>\bf\end<<11407>>tex2html_deferred<<11407>>d<<1554>>_n;SPMlt; <<1555>>\begin<<11408>>tex2html_deferred<<11408>>\bf\end<<11409>>tex2html_deferred<<11409>>g<<1555>>_n^T<<1556>>\begin<<11410>>tex2html_deferred<<11410>>\bf\end<<11411>>tex2html_deferred<<11411>>d<<1556>>_n$\end<<7621>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7621>>.
The Armijo rule is to find any \begin<<7622>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7622>>$\delta;SPMgt;0$\end<<7623>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7623>>\space that satisfies
\begin<<1557>>equation<<1557>>
  f(<<1558>>\begin<<11412>>tex2html_deferred<<11412>>\bf\end<<11413>>tex2html_deferred<<11413>>x<<1558>>_<<1559>>n+1<<1559>>)=f(<<1560>>\begin<<11414>>tex2html_deferred<<11414>>\bf\end<<11415>>tex2html_deferred<<11415>>x<<1560>>_n+\delta<<1561>>\begin<<11416>>tex2html_deferred<<11416>>\bf\end<<11417>>tex2html_deferred<<11417>>d<<1561>>_n) 
  \le f(<<1562>>\begin<<11418>>tex2html_deferred<<11418>>\bf\end<<11419>>tex2html_deferred<<11419>>x<<1562>>_n)+c_1\,<<1563>>\begin<<11420>>tex2html_deferred<<11420>>\bf\end<<11421>>tex2html_deferred<<11421>>g<<1563>>^T_n<<1564>>\begin<<11422>>tex2html_deferred<<11422>>\bf\end<<11423>>tex2html_deferred<<11423>>d<<1564>>_n\delta ;SPMlt;f(<<1565>>\begin<<11424>>tex2html_deferred<<11424>>\bf\end<<11425>>tex2html_deferred<<11425>>x<<1565>>_n)
\end<<1566>>equation<<1566>>
We see that the value of \begin<<7624>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7624>>$f(<<1567>>\begin<<11426>>tex2html_deferred<<11426>>\bf\end<<11427>>tex2html_deferred<<11427>>x<<1567>>)$\end<<7625>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7625>>\space is guaranteed to be reduced.
\begin<<11428>>tex2html_deferred<<11428>>\par\end<<11429>>tex2html_deferred<<11429>>
The second condition requires that at the new position 
\begin<<7626>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7626>>$<<1568>>\begin<<11430>>tex2html_deferred<<11430>>\bf\end<<11431>>tex2html_deferred<<11431>>x<<1568>>_<<1569>>n+1<<1569>>$\end<<7627>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7627>>\space the slope of the gradient \begin<<7628>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7628>>$<<1570>>\begin<<11432>>tex2html_deferred<<11432>>\bf\end<<11433>>tex2html_deferred<<11433>>g<<1570>>_<<1571>>n+1<<1571>>$\end<<7629>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7629>>\space along 
the search direction \begin<<7630>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7630>>$<<1572>>\begin<<11434>>tex2html_deferred<<11434>>\bf\end<<11435>>tex2html_deferred<<11435>>d<<1572>>_n$\end<<7631>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7631>>\space be sufficiently reduced to be 
less than a specified value (determined by \begin<<7632>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7632>>$c_2$\end<<7633>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7633>>), in comparison 
to the slope at the old position \begin<<7634>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7634>>$<<1573>>\begin<<11436>>tex2html_deferred<<11436>>\bf\end<<11437>>tex2html_deferred<<11437>>x<<1573>>_n$\end<<7635>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7635>>. 
\begin<<11438>>tex2html_deferred<<11438>>\par\end<<11439>>tex2html_deferred<<11439>>
\htmladdimg<<1574>>figures/GradientDescent.png<<1574>>
\begin<<11440>>tex2html_deferred<<11440>>\par\end<<11441>>tex2html_deferred<<11441>>
The reason why \begin<<7636>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7636>>$<<1575>>\begin<<11442>>tex2html_deferred<<11442>>\bf\end<<11443>>tex2html_deferred<<11443>>g<<1575>>_<<1576>>n+1<<1576>>\perp<<1577>>\begin<<11444>>tex2html_deferred<<11444>>\bf\end<<11445>>tex2html_deferred<<11445>>g<<1577>>_n$\end<<7637>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7637>>\space can also be explained geometrically.
As shown in the figure the gradient vectors at various points along the direction 
of \begin<<7638>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7638>>$-<<1578>>\begin<<11446>>tex2html_deferred<<11446>>\bf\end<<11447>>tex2html_deferred<<11447>>g<<1578>>_n$\end<<7639>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7639>>\space are shown by the blue arrows, and their projections onto the direction
represent the slopes of the function \begin<<7640>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7640>>$f(\delta_n)=f(<<1579>>\begin<<11448>>tex2html_deferred<<11448>>\bf\end<<11449>>tex2html_deferred<<11449>>x<<1579>>_n-\delta_n<<1580>>\begin<<11450>>tex2html_deferred<<11450>>\bf\end<<11451>>tex2html_deferred<<11451>>g<<1580>>_n)$\end<<7641>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7641>>. 
Obviously at \begin<<7642>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7642>>$<<1581>>\begin<<11452>>tex2html_deferred<<11452>>\bf\end<<11453>>tex2html_deferred<<11453>>x<<1581>>_<<1582>>n+1<<1582>>$\end<<7643>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7643>>\space where \begin<<7644>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7644>>$f(\delta_n)$\end<<7645>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7645>>\space reaches its minimum, its slope 
is zero. In other words, the projection of the gradient \begin<<7646>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7646>>$<<1583>>\begin<<11454>>tex2html_deferred<<11454>>\bf\end<<11455>>tex2html_deferred<<11455>>g<<1583>>_<<1584>>n+1<<1584>>$\end<<7647>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7647>>\space onto the 
direction of \begin<<7648>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7648>>$-<<1585>>\begin<<11456>>tex2html_deferred<<11456>>\bf\end<<11457>>tex2html_deferred<<11457>>g<<1585>>_n$\end<<7649>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7649>>\space is zero, i.e., \begin<<7650>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7650>>$<<1586>>\begin<<11458>>tex2html_deferred<<11458>>\bf\end<<11459>>tex2html_deferred<<11459>>g<<1586>>_<<1587>>n+1<<1587>>\perp <<1588>>\begin<<11460>>tex2html_deferred<<11460>>\bf\end<<11461>>tex2html_deferred<<11461>>g<<1588>>_n$\end<<7651>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7651>>\space or
\begin<<7652>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7652>>$<<1589>>\begin<<11462>>tex2html_deferred<<11462>>\bf\end<<11463>>tex2html_deferred<<11463>>g<<1589>>_<<1590>>n+1<<1590>>^T<<1591>>\begin<<11464>>tex2html_deferred<<11464>>\bf\end<<11465>>tex2html_deferred<<11465>>g<<1591>>_n=0$\end<<7653>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7653>>.
\begin<<11466>>tex2html_deferred<<11466>>\par\end<<11467>>tex2html_deferred<<11467>>
The gradient descent method gradually approaches a solution \begin<<7654>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7654>>$<<1592>>\begin<<11468>>tex2html_deferred<<11468>>\bf\end<<11469>>tex2html_deferred<<11469>>x<<1592>>$\end<<7655>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7655>>\space of an N-D
minimization problem by moving from the initial guess \begin<<7656>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7656>>$<<1593>>\begin<<11470>>tex2html_deferred<<11470>>\bf\end<<11471>>tex2html_deferred<<11471>>x<<1593>>_0$\end<<7657>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7657>>\space along a zigzag 
path composed of a set of segments with any two consecutive segments
perpendicular to each other. The number of steps depends greatly on the initial 
guess. As illustrated in the example below in an N=2 dimensional case, the best 
possible case is that the solution happens to be on the gradient direction of the
initial guess, which could be reached in a single step, while the worst possible 
case is that the gradient direction of the initial guess happens to be 45 degrees
off from the gradient direction of the optimal case, and it takes many zigzag 
steps to go around the optimal path to reach the solution. Many of the steps 
are in the same direction as some of the previous steps. 
\begin<<11472>>tex2html_deferred<<11472>>\par\end<<11473>>tex2html_deferred<<11473>>
To improve the performance of the gradient descent method we can include in
the iteration a momentum term representing the search direction previously
traversed:
\begin<<1594>>equation<<1594>>
  <<1595>>\begin<<11474>>tex2html_deferred<<11474>>\bf\end<<11475>>tex2html_deferred<<11475>>x<<1595>>_<<1596>>n+1<<1596>>=<<1597>>\begin<<11476>>tex2html_deferred<<11476>>\bf\end<<11477>>tex2html_deferred<<11477>>x<<1597>>_n-\delta_n<<1598>>\begin<<11478>>tex2html_deferred<<11478>>\bf\end<<11479>>tex2html_deferred<<11479>>g<<1598>>_n+\alpha_n(<<1599>>\begin<<11480>>tex2html_deferred<<11480>>\bf\end<<11481>>tex2html_deferred<<11481>>x<<1599>>_n-<<1600>>\begin<<11482>>tex2html_deferred<<11482>>\bf\end<<11483>>tex2html_deferred<<11483>>x<<1600>>_<<1601>>n-1<<1601>>)
\end<<1602>>equation<<1602>>
Now two consecutive search directions are no longer perpendicular to each 
other and the resulting search path is smoother than the zigzag path  without
the momentum term. The parameter \begin<<7658>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7658>>$\alpha_m$\end<<7659>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7659>>\space controls how much momentum is to 
be added.
\begin<<11484>>tex2html_deferred<<11484>>\par\end<<11485>>tex2html_deferred<<11485>>
Obviously it is most desirable not to repeat any of the previous directions 
traveled so that the solution can be reached in N steps, each in a unique 
direction in the N-D space. In other words, the subsequent steps are independent 
of each other, never interfering with the results achieved in the previous steps.
Such a method will be discussed in the next section.
\begin<<11486>>tex2html_deferred<<11486>>\par\end<<11487>>tex2html_deferred<<11487>>
\htmladdimg<<1603>>figures/GradientDescent1.png<<1603>>
\begin<<11488>>tex2html_deferred<<11488>>\par\end<<11489>>tex2html_deferred<<11489>>
<<1604>>\begin<<11490>>tex2html_deferred<<11490>>\bf\end<<11491>>tex2html_deferred<<11491>>Example:<<1604>> The Rosenbrock function 
\begin<<1605>>equation<<1605>>
  f(x,y)=(a-x)^2+b(y-x^2)^2\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\mbox<<1606>>typically \begin<<7660>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7660>>$a=1,\;
    b=100$\end<<7661>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7661>><<1606>>
  \nonumber
\end<<1607>>equation<<1607>>
is a two-variable non-convex function with a global minimum 
\begin<<7662>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7662>>$f(1,\;1)=0$\end<<7663>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7663>>\space at the point \begin<<7664>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7664>>$(1,\;1)$\end<<7665>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7665>>, which is inside a long parabolic 
shaped valley as shown in the figure below. As the slope along the 
valley is very shallow, it is difficult for an algorithm to converge 
quickly to the minimum. For this reason, the Rosenbrock function is 
often used to test various minimization algorithms.
\begin<<11492>>tex2html_deferred<<11492>>\par\end<<11493>>tex2html_deferred<<11493>>
\htmladdimg<<1608>>figures/Rosenbrock.png<<1608>>
\begin<<11494>>tex2html_deferred<<11494>>\par\end<<11495>>tex2html_deferred<<11495>>
The figure below shows the search path of the gradient 
descent method based on the optimal step size given in Eq. 
(\ref<<1609>>GradientStepSizeOptimal<<1609>>). We see that the search path 
is composed a long sequence of 90 degree turns between consecutive 
segments.
\begin<<11496>>tex2html_deferred<<11496>>\par\end<<11497>>tex2html_deferred<<11497>>
\htmladdimg<<1610>>figures/RosenbrockGradient0.png<<1610>>
\begin<<11498>>tex2html_deferred<<11498>>\par\end<<11499>>tex2html_deferred<<11499>>
\htmladdimg<<1611>>figures/RosenbrockGradient01.png<<1611>>
\begin<<11500>>tex2html_deferred<<11500>>\par\end<<11501>>tex2html_deferred<<11501>>
When the Newton's method is applied to this minimization problem,
it takes only four iterations for the algorithm to converge to the
minimum, as shown in the figure below:
\begin<<11502>>tex2html_deferred<<11502>>\par\end<<11503>>tex2html_deferred<<11503>>
\htmladdimg<<1612>>figures/RosenbrockNewton.png<<1612>>
\begin<<11504>>tex2html_deferred<<11504>>\par\end<<11505>>tex2html_deferred<<11505>>
\subsection*<<1613>>Quasi-Newton Methods<<1613>>
\begin<<11506>>tex2html_deferred<<11506>>\par\end<<11507>>tex2html_deferred<<11507>>
As we have seen above, Newton's methods can be used to solve both 
nonlinear systems to find roots of a set of simultaneous equations,
and optimization problems to minimize a scalar-valued objective function
based on the iterations of the same form. Specifically, 
\begin<<1614>>itemize<<1614>>
\item Solving equations \begin<<7666>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7666>>$<<1615>>\begin<<11508>>tex2html_deferred<<11508>>\bf\end<<11509>>tex2html_deferred<<11509>>f<<1615>>(<<1616>>\begin<<11510>>tex2html_deferred<<11510>>\bf\end<<11511>>tex2html_deferred<<11511>>x<<1616>>)=<<1617>>\begin<<11512>>tex2html_deferred<<11512>>\bf\end<<11513>>tex2html_deferred<<11513>>0<<1617>>$\end<<7667>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7667>>:
  \begin<<1618>>equation<<1618>>
    <<1619>>\begin<<11514>>tex2html_deferred<<11514>>\bf\end<<11515>>tex2html_deferred<<11515>>x<<1619>>_<<1620>>n+1<<1620>>=<<1621>>\begin<<11516>>tex2html_deferred<<11516>>\bf\end<<11517>>tex2html_deferred<<11517>>x<<1621>>_n-\delta <<1622>>\begin<<11518>>tex2html_deferred<<11518>>\bf\end<<11519>>tex2html_deferred<<11519>>J<<1622>>(<<1623>>\begin<<11520>>tex2html_deferred<<11520>>\bf\end<<11521>>tex2html_deferred<<11521>>x<<1623>>_n)^<<1624>>-1<<1624>><<1625>>\begin<<11522>>tex2html_deferred<<11522>>\bf\end<<11523>>tex2html_deferred<<11523>>f<<1625>>(<<1626>>\begin<<11524>>tex2html_deferred<<11524>>\bf\end<<11525>>tex2html_deferred<<11525>>x<<1626>>_n) 
    =<<1627>>\begin<<11526>>tex2html_deferred<<11526>>\bf\end<<11527>>tex2html_deferred<<11527>>x<<1627>>_n-\delta\;<<1628>>\begin<<11528>>tex2html_deferred<<11528>>\bf\end<<11529>>tex2html_deferred<<11529>>J<<1628>>_n^<<1629>>-1<<1629>><<1630>>\begin<<11530>>tex2html_deferred<<11530>>\bf\end<<11531>>tex2html_deferred<<11531>>f<<1630>>_n
  \end<<1631>>equation<<1631>>
  where \begin<<7668>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7668>>$<<1632>>\begin<<11532>>tex2html_deferred<<11532>>\bf\end<<11533>>tex2html_deferred<<11533>>J<<1632>>_n=<<1633>>\begin<<11534>>tex2html_deferred<<11534>>\bf\end<<11535>>tex2html_deferred<<11535>>J<<1633>>(<<1634>>\begin<<11536>>tex2html_deferred<<11536>>\bf\end<<11537>>tex2html_deferred<<11537>>x<<1634>>_n)$\end<<7669>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7669>>\space is the Jacobian matrix of 
  \begin<<7670>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7670>>$<<1635>>\begin<<11538>>tex2html_deferred<<11538>>\bf\end<<11539>>tex2html_deferred<<11539>>f<<1635>>(<<1636>>\begin<<11540>>tex2html_deferred<<11540>>\bf\end<<11541>>tex2html_deferred<<11541>>x<<1636>>_n)$\end<<7671>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7671>>, 
\item Minimizing \begin<<7672>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7672>>$f(<<1637>>\begin<<11542>>tex2html_deferred<<11542>>\bf\end<<11543>>tex2html_deferred<<11543>>x<<1637>>)$\end<<7673>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7673>>:
  \begin<<1638>>equation<<1638>>
  <<1639>>\begin<<11544>>tex2html_deferred<<11544>>\bf\end<<11545>>tex2html_deferred<<11545>>x<<1639>>_<<1640>>n+1<<1640>>=<<1641>>\begin<<11546>>tex2html_deferred<<11546>>\bf\end<<11547>>tex2html_deferred<<11547>>x<<1641>>_n-\delta <<1642>>\begin<<11548>>tex2html_deferred<<11548>>\bf\end<<11549>>tex2html_deferred<<11549>>H<<1642>>(<<1643>>\begin<<11550>>tex2html_deferred<<11550>>\bf\end<<11551>>tex2html_deferred<<11551>>x<<1643>>_n)^<<1644>>-1<<1644>><<1645>>\begin<<11552>>tex2html_deferred<<11552>>\bf\end<<11553>>tex2html_deferred<<11553>>g<<1645>>(<<1646>>\begin<<11554>>tex2html_deferred<<11554>>\bf\end<<11555>>tex2html_deferred<<11555>>x<<1646>>_n)
  =<<1647>>\begin<<11556>>tex2html_deferred<<11556>>\bf\end<<11557>>tex2html_deferred<<11557>>x<<1647>>_n-\delta\;<<1648>>\begin<<11558>>tex2html_deferred<<11558>>\bf\end<<11559>>tex2html_deferred<<11559>>H<<1648>>_n^<<1649>>-1<<1649>><<1650>>\begin<<11560>>tex2html_deferred<<11560>>\bf\end<<11561>>tex2html_deferred<<11561>>g<<1650>>_n
  \end<<1651>>equation<<1651>>
  where \begin<<7674>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7674>>$<<1652>>\begin<<11562>>tex2html_deferred<<11562>>\bf\end<<11563>>tex2html_deferred<<11563>>g<<1652>>_n=<<1653>>\begin<<11564>>tex2html_deferred<<11564>>\bf\end<<11565>>tex2html_deferred<<11565>>g<<1653>>(<<1654>>\begin<<11566>>tex2html_deferred<<11566>>\bf\end<<11567>>tex2html_deferred<<11567>>x<<1654>>_n)$\end<<7675>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7675>>\space and 
  \begin<<7676>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7676>>$<<1655>>\begin<<11568>>tex2html_deferred<<11568>>\bf\end<<11569>>tex2html_deferred<<11569>>H<<1655>>_n=<<1656>>\begin<<11570>>tex2html_deferred<<11570>>\bf\end<<11571>>tex2html_deferred<<11571>>H<<1656>>(<<1657>>\begin<<11572>>tex2html_deferred<<11572>>\bf\end<<11573>>tex2html_deferred<<11573>>x<<1657>>_n)$\end<<7677>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7677>>\space are the gradient vector and 
  Hessian matrix of \begin<<7678>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7678>>$f(<<1658>>\begin<<11574>>tex2html_deferred<<11574>>\bf\end<<11575>>tex2html_deferred<<11575>>x<<1658>>)$\end<<7679>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7679>>\space at \begin<<7680>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7680>>$<<1659>>\begin<<11576>>tex2html_deferred<<11576>>\bf\end<<11577>>tex2html_deferred<<11577>>x<<1659>>_n$\end<<7681>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7681>>, respectively. 
\end<<1660>>itemize<<1660>>
\begin<<11578>>tex2html_deferred<<11578>>\par\end<<11579>>tex2html_deferred<<11579>>
If the Jacobian \begin<<7682>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7682>>$<<1661>>\begin<<11580>>tex2html_deferred<<11580>>\bf\end<<11581>>tex2html_deferred<<11581>>J<<1661>>(<<1662>>\begin<<11582>>tex2html_deferred<<11582>>\bf\end<<11583>>tex2html_deferred<<11583>>x<<1662>>)$\end<<7683>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7683>>\space or the Hessian matrix \begin<<7684>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7684>>$<<1663>>\begin<<11584>>tex2html_deferred<<11584>>\bf\end<<11585>>tex2html_deferred<<11585>>H<<1663>>(<<1664>>\begin<<11586>>tex2html_deferred<<11586>>\bf\end<<11587>>tex2html_deferred<<11587>>x<<1664>>)$\end<<7685>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7685>>
is not available, or if it is too computationally costly to calculate
its inverse (of complexity \begin<<7686>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7686>>$O(N^3)$\end<<7687>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7687>>), the quasi-Newton methods can be 
used to approximate the Hessian matrix or its inverse based only on 
the first order derivative, the gradient \begin<<7688>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7688>>$<<1665>>\begin<<11588>>tex2html_deferred<<11588>>\bf\end<<11589>>tex2html_deferred<<11589>>g<<1665>>$\end<<7689>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7689>>\space of \begin<<7690>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7690>>$f(<<1666>>\begin<<11590>>tex2html_deferred<<11590>>\bf\end<<11591>>tex2html_deferred<<11591>>x<<1666>>)$\end<<7691>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7691>> 
(with complexity \begin<<7692>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7692>>$O(N^2)$\end<<7693>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7693>>), similar to the Broyden's method considered 
\htmladdnormallink<<1667>>here<<1667>><<1668>>../ch2/node6.html<<1668>>.
\begin<<11592>>tex2html_deferred<<11592>>\par\end<<11593>>tex2html_deferred<<11593>>
In the following, we consider the minimization of a function \begin<<7694>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7694>>$f(<<1669>>\begin<<11594>>tex2html_deferred<<11594>>\bf\end<<11595>>tex2html_deferred<<11595>>x<<1669>>)$\end<<7695>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7695>>.
Its Taylor expansion around point \begin<<7696>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7696>>$<<1670>>\begin<<11596>>tex2html_deferred<<11596>>\bf\end<<11597>>tex2html_deferred<<11597>>x<<1670>>_<<1671>>n+1<<1671>>$\end<<7697>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7697>>\space is
\begin<<1672>>equation<<1672>>
  f(<<1673>>\begin<<11598>>tex2html_deferred<<11598>>\bf\end<<11599>>tex2html_deferred<<11599>>x<<1673>>)=f(<<1674>>\begin<<11600>>tex2html_deferred<<11600>>\bf\end<<11601>>tex2html_deferred<<11601>>x<<1674>>_<<1675>>n+1<<1675>>)+(<<1676>>\begin<<11602>>tex2html_deferred<<11602>>\bf\end<<11603>>tex2html_deferred<<11603>>x<<1676>>-<<1677>>\begin<<11604>>tex2html_deferred<<11604>>\bf\end<<11605>>tex2html_deferred<<11605>>x<<1677>>_<<1678>>n+1<<1678>>)^T <<1679>>\begin<<11606>>tex2html_deferred<<11606>>\bf\end<<11607>>tex2html_deferred<<11607>>g<<1679>>_<<1680>>n+1<<1680>>
  +\frac<<1681>>1<<1681>><<1682>>2<<1682>>(<<1683>>\begin<<11608>>tex2html_deferred<<11608>>\bf\end<<11609>>tex2html_deferred<<11609>>x<<1683>>-<<1684>>\begin<<11610>>tex2html_deferred<<11610>>\bf\end<<11611>>tex2html_deferred<<11611>>x<<1684>>_<<1685>>n+1<<1685>>)^T <<1686>>\begin<<11612>>tex2html_deferred<<11612>>\bf\end<<11613>>tex2html_deferred<<11613>>H<<1686>>_<<1687>>n+1<<1687>>
  (<<1688>>\begin<<11614>>tex2html_deferred<<11614>>\bf\end<<11615>>tex2html_deferred<<11615>>x<<1688>>-<<1689>>\begin<<11616>>tex2html_deferred<<11616>>\bf\end<<11617>>tex2html_deferred<<11617>>x<<1689>>_<<1690>>n+1<<1690>>)+O(||<<1691>>\begin<<11618>>tex2html_deferred<<11618>>\bf\end<<11619>>tex2html_deferred<<11619>>x<<1691>>-<<1692>>\begin<<11620>>tex2html_deferred<<11620>>\bf\end<<11621>>tex2html_deferred<<11621>>x<<1692>>_<<1693>>n+1<<1693>>||^3)
\end<<1694>>equation<<1694>>
Taking derivetive with respect to \begin<<7698>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7698>>$<<1695>>\begin<<11622>>tex2html_deferred<<11622>>\bf\end<<11623>>tex2html_deferred<<11623>>x<<1695>>$\end<<7699>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7699>>, we get
\begin<<1696>>equation<<1696>>
  \frac<<1697>>d<<1697>><<6558>>d<<1698>>\begin<<11624>>tex2html_deferred<<11624>>\bf\end<<11625>>tex2html_deferred<<11625>>x<<1698>><<6558>>f(<<1699>>\begin<<11626>>tex2html_deferred<<11626>>\bf\end<<11627>>tex2html_deferred<<11627>>x<<1699>>)=<<1700>>\begin<<11628>>tex2html_deferred<<11628>>\bf\end<<11629>>tex2html_deferred<<11629>>g<<1700>>(<<1701>>\begin<<11630>>tex2html_deferred<<11630>>\bf\end<<11631>>tex2html_deferred<<11631>>x<<1701>>)
  =<<1702>>\begin<<11632>>tex2html_deferred<<11632>>\bf\end<<11633>>tex2html_deferred<<11633>>g<<1702>>_<<1703>>n+1<<1703>>+<<1704>>\begin<<11634>>tex2html_deferred<<11634>>\bf\end<<11635>>tex2html_deferred<<11635>>H<<1704>>_<<1705>>n+1<<1705>> (<<1706>>\begin<<11636>>tex2html_deferred<<11636>>\bf\end<<11637>>tex2html_deferred<<11637>>x<<1706>>-<<1707>>\begin<<11638>>tex2html_deferred<<11638>>\bf\end<<11639>>tex2html_deferred<<11639>>x<<1707>>_<<1708>>n+1<<1708>>)
  +O(||<<1709>>\begin<<11640>>tex2html_deferred<<11640>>\bf\end<<11641>>tex2html_deferred<<11641>>x<<1709>>-<<1710>>\begin<<11642>>tex2html_deferred<<11642>>\bf\end<<11643>>tex2html_deferred<<11643>>x<<1710>>_<<1711>>n+1<<1711>>||^2)
\end<<1712>>equation<<1712>>
Evaluating at \begin<<7700>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7700>>$<<1713>>\begin<<11644>>tex2html_deferred<<11644>>\bf\end<<11645>>tex2html_deferred<<11645>>x<<1713>>=<<1714>>\begin<<11646>>tex2html_deferred<<11646>>\bf\end<<11647>>tex2html_deferred<<11647>>x<<1714>>_n$\end<<7701>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7701>>, we have \begin<<7702>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7702>>$<<1715>>\begin<<11648>>tex2html_deferred<<11648>>\bf\end<<11649>>tex2html_deferred<<11649>>g<<1715>>(<<1716>>\begin<<11650>>tex2html_deferred<<11650>>\bf\end<<11651>>tex2html_deferred<<11651>>x<<1716>>_n)=<<1717>>\begin<<11652>>tex2html_deferred<<11652>>\bf\end<<11653>>tex2html_deferred<<11653>>g<<1717>>_n$\end<<7703>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7703>>, 
and the above can be written as
\begin<<1718>>eqnarray<<1718>>
  <<1719>>\begin<<11654>>tex2html_deferred<<11654>>\bf\end<<11655>>tex2html_deferred<<11655>>g<<1719>>_<<1720>>n+1<<1720>>-<<1721>>\begin<<11656>>tex2html_deferred<<11656>>\bf\end<<11657>>tex2html_deferred<<11657>>g<<1721>>_n;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;<<1722>>\begin<<11658>>tex2html_deferred<<11658>>\bf\end<<11659>>tex2html_deferred<<11659>>H<<1722>>_<<1723>>n+1<<1723>>(<<1724>>\begin<<11660>>tex2html_deferred<<11660>>\bf\end<<11661>>tex2html_deferred<<11661>>x<<1724>>_<<1725>>n+1<<1725>>-<<1726>>\begin<<11662>>tex2html_deferred<<11662>>\bf\end<<11663>>tex2html_deferred<<11663>>x<<1726>>_n)
  +O(||<<1727>>\begin<<11664>>tex2html_deferred<<11664>>\bf\end<<11665>>tex2html_deferred<<11665>>x<<1727>>_<<1728>>n+1<<1728>>-<<1729>>\begin<<11666>>tex2html_deferred<<11666>>\bf\end<<11667>>tex2html_deferred<<11667>>x<<1729>>_n||^2)  
  \nonumber\\ 
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;<<1730>>\begin<<11668>>tex2html_deferred<<11668>>\bf\end<<11669>>tex2html_deferred<<11669>>B<<1730>>_<<1731>>n+1<<1731>>(<<1732>>\begin<<11670>>tex2html_deferred<<11670>>\bf\end<<11671>>tex2html_deferred<<11671>>x<<1732>>_<<1733>>n+1<<1733>>-<<1734>>\begin<<11672>>tex2html_deferred<<11672>>\bf\end<<11673>>tex2html_deferred<<11673>>x<<1734>>_n)
\end<<1735>>eqnarray<<1735>>
where matrix \begin<<7704>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7704>>$<<1736>>\begin<<11674>>tex2html_deferred<<11674>>\bf\end<<11675>>tex2html_deferred<<11675>>B<<1736>>_n$\end<<7705>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7705>>\space is the secant approximation of the Hessian
matrix \begin<<7706>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7706>>$<<1737>>\begin<<11676>>tex2html_deferred<<11676>>\bf\end<<11677>>tex2html_deferred<<11677>>H<<1737>>_n$\end<<7707>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7707>>, and the last eqality is called the 
<<1738>>\begin<<11678>>tex2html_deferred<<11678>>\em\end<<11679>>tex2html_deferred<<11679>>secant equation<<1738>>. For convenience, we further define:
\begin<<1739>>equation<<1739>>
<<1740>>\begin<<11680>>tex2html_deferred<<11680>>\bf\end<<11681>>tex2html_deferred<<11681>>s<<1740>>_n=<<1741>>\begin<<11682>>tex2html_deferred<<11682>>\bf\end<<11683>>tex2html_deferred<<11683>>x<<1741>>_<<1742>>n+1<<1742>>-<<1743>>\begin<<11684>>tex2html_deferred<<11684>>\bf\end<<11685>>tex2html_deferred<<11685>>x<<1743>>_n,\;\;\;\;\;\;
<<1744>>\begin<<11686>>tex2html_deferred<<11686>>\bf\end<<11687>>tex2html_deferred<<11687>>y<<1744>>_n=<<1745>>\begin<<11688>>tex2html_deferred<<11688>>\bf\end<<11689>>tex2html_deferred<<11689>>g<<1745>>_<<1746>>n+1<<1746>>-<<1747>>\begin<<11690>>tex2html_deferred<<11690>>\bf\end<<11691>>tex2html_deferred<<11691>>g<<1747>>_n
\end<<1748>>equation<<1748>>
so that the equation above can be written as
\begin<<1749>>equation<<1749>>
  <<1750>>\begin<<11692>>tex2html_deferred<<11692>>\bf\end<<11693>>tex2html_deferred<<11693>>B<<1750>>_<<1751>>n+1<<1751>><<1752>>\begin<<11694>>tex2html_deferred<<11694>>\bf\end<<11695>>tex2html_deferred<<11695>>s<<1752>>_n=<<1753>>\begin<<11696>>tex2html_deferred<<11696>>\bf\end<<11697>>tex2html_deferred<<11697>>y<<1753>>_n,\;\;\;\;\;\mbox<<1754>>or<<1754>>\;\;\;\;\;
  <<1755>>\begin<<11698>>tex2html_deferred<<11698>>\bf\end<<11699>>tex2html_deferred<<11699>>B<<1755>>_<<1756>>n+1<<1756>>^<<1757>>-1<<1757>><<1758>>\begin<<11700>>tex2html_deferred<<11700>>\bf\end<<11701>>tex2html_deferred<<11701>>y<<1758>>_n=<<1759>>\begin<<11702>>tex2html_deferred<<11702>>\bf\end<<11703>>tex2html_deferred<<11703>>s<<1759>>_n
\end<<1760>>equation<<1760>>
This is the <<1761>>\begin<<11704>>tex2html_deferred<<11704>>\em\end<<11705>>tex2html_deferred<<11705>>quasi-Newton equation<<1761>>, which is the 
<<1762>>\begin<<11706>>tex2html_deferred<<11706>>\em\end<<11707>>tex2html_deferred<<11707>>secant condition<<1762>> that must be satisfied by matrix 
\begin<<7708>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7708>>$<<1763>>\begin<<11708>>tex2html_deferred<<11708>>\bf\end<<11709>>tex2html_deferred<<11709>>B<<1763>>_n$\end<<7709>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7709>>, or its inverse \begin<<7710>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7710>>$<<1764>>\begin<<11710>>tex2html_deferred<<11710>>\bf\end<<11711>>tex2html_deferred<<11711>>B<<1764>>_n^<<1765>>-1<<1765>>$\end<<7711>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7711>>, in any of the 
quasi-Newton algorithms, all taking the follow general steps:
\begin<<1766>>enumerate<<1766>>
\item Initialize \begin<<7712>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7712>>$<<1767>>\begin<<11712>>tex2html_deferred<<11712>>\bf\end<<11713>>tex2html_deferred<<11713>>x<<1767>>_0$\end<<7713>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7713>>\space and \begin<<7714>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7714>>$<<1768>>\begin<<11714>>tex2html_deferred<<11714>>\bf\end<<11715>>tex2html_deferred<<11715>>B<<1768>>_0$\end<<7715>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7715>>, set \begin<<7716>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7716>>$n=0$\end<<7717>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7717>>; 
\item Compute gradient \begin<<7718>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7718>>$<<1769>>\begin<<11716>>tex2html_deferred<<11716>>\bf\end<<11717>>tex2html_deferred<<11717>>g<<1769>>_n$\end<<7719>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7719>>\space and the search direction 
  \begin<<7720>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7720>>$<<1770>>\begin<<11718>>tex2html_deferred<<11718>>\bf\end<<11719>>tex2html_deferred<<11719>>d<<1770>>_n=-<<1771>>\begin<<11720>>tex2html_deferred<<11720>>\bf\end<<11721>>tex2html_deferred<<11721>>B<<1771>>_n^<<1772>>-1<<1772>><<1773>>\begin<<11722>>tex2html_deferred<<11722>>\bf\end<<11723>>tex2html_deferred<<11723>>g<<1773>>_n$\end<<7721>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7721>>;
\item Get \begin<<7722>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7722>>$<<1774>>\begin<<11724>>tex2html_deferred<<11724>>\bf\end<<11725>>tex2html_deferred<<11725>>x<<1774>>_<<1775>>n+1<<1775>>=<<1776>>\begin<<11726>>tex2html_deferred<<11726>>\bf\end<<11727>>tex2html_deferred<<11727>>x<<1776>>_n+\delta <<1777>>\begin<<11728>>tex2html_deferred<<11728>>\bf\end<<11729>>tex2html_deferred<<11729>>d<<1777>>_n$\end<<7723>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7723>>\space with step
  size \begin<<7724>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7724>>$\delta$\end<<7725>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7725>>\space satisfying the 
  \htmladdnormallink<<1778>>Wolfe conditions<<1778>><<1779>>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wolfe_conditions<<1779>>.
\item update \begin<<7726>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7726>>$<<1780>>\begin<<11730>>tex2html_deferred<<11730>>\bf\end<<11731>>tex2html_deferred<<11731>>B<<1780>>_<<1781>>n+1<<1781>>=<<1782>>\begin<<11732>>tex2html_deferred<<11732>>\bf\end<<11733>>tex2html_deferred<<11733>>B<<1782>>_n+\Delta<<1783>>\begin<<11734>>tex2html_deferred<<11734>>\bf\end<<11735>>tex2html_deferred<<11735>>B<<1783>>_n$\end<<7727>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7727>>\space or
  \begin<<7728>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7728>>$<<1784>>\begin<<11736>>tex2html_deferred<<11736>>\bf\end<<11737>>tex2html_deferred<<11737>>B<<1784>>_<<1785>>n+1<<1785>>^<<1786>>-1<<1786>>=<<1787>>\begin<<11738>>tex2html_deferred<<11738>>\bf\end<<11739>>tex2html_deferred<<11739>>B<<1787>>_n^<<1788>>-1<<1788>>+\Delta<<1789>>\begin<<11740>>tex2html_deferred<<11740>>\bf\end<<11741>>tex2html_deferred<<11741>>B<<1789>>_n^<<1790>>-1<<1790>>$\end<<7729>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7729>>,
  that satisfies the quasi-Newton equation;
\item If termination condition is not satisfied, \begin<<7730>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7730>>$n=n+1$\end<<7731>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7731>>, go back 
  to second step.
\end<<1791>>enumerate<<1791>>
For this iteration to converge to a local minimum of \begin<<7732>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7732>>$f(<<1792>>\begin<<11742>>tex2html_deferred<<11742>>\bf\end<<11743>>tex2html_deferred<<11743>>x<<1792>>)$\end<<7733>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7733>>,
\begin<<7734>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7734>>$<<1793>>\begin<<11744>>tex2html_deferred<<11744>>\bf\end<<11745>>tex2html_deferred<<11745>>B<<1793>>_n$\end<<7735>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7735>>\space must be positive definite matrix, same as the Hessian
matrix \begin<<7736>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7736>>$<<1794>>\begin<<11746>>tex2html_deferred<<11746>>\bf\end<<11747>>tex2html_deferred<<11747>>H<<1794>>$\end<<7737>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7737>>\space it approximates. Specially, if \begin<<7738>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7738>>$<<1795>>\begin<<11748>>tex2html_deferred<<11748>>\bf\end<<11749>>tex2html_deferred<<11749>>B<<1795>>_n=<<1796>>\begin<<11750>>tex2html_deferred<<11750>>\bf\end<<11751>>tex2html_deferred<<11751>>I<<1796>>$\end<<7739>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7739>>, 
then \begin<<7740>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7740>>$<<1797>>\begin<<11752>>tex2html_deferred<<11752>>\bf\end<<11753>>tex2html_deferred<<11753>>d<<1797>>_n=-<<1798>>\begin<<11754>>tex2html_deferred<<11754>>\bf\end<<11755>>tex2html_deferred<<11755>>g<<1798>>_n$\end<<7741>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7741>>, the algorithm becomes the gradient 
descent method; also, if \begin<<7742>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7742>>$<<1799>>\begin<<11756>>tex2html_deferred<<11756>>\bf\end<<11757>>tex2html_deferred<<11757>>B<<1799>>_n=<<1800>>\begin<<11758>>tex2html_deferred<<11758>>\bf\end<<11759>>tex2html_deferred<<11759>>H<<1800>>_n$\end<<7743>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7743>>\space is the Hessian matrix, 
then the algorithm becomes the Newton's method.
\begin<<11760>>tex2html_deferred<<11760>>\par\end<<11761>>tex2html_deferred<<11761>>
In a quasi-Newton method, we can choose to update either \begin<<7744>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7744>>$<<1801>>\begin<<11762>>tex2html_deferred<<11762>>\bf\end<<11763>>tex2html_deferred<<11763>>B<<1801>>_n$\end<<7745>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7745>> 
or its inverse \begin<<7746>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7746>>$<<1802>>\begin<<11764>>tex2html_deferred<<11764>>\bf\end<<11765>>tex2html_deferred<<11765>>B<<1802>>_n^<<1803>>-1<<1803>>$\end<<7747>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7747>>\space based on one of the two forms of 
the quasi-Newton equation. We note that there is a dual relationship 
between the two ways to update, i.e., by swapping \begin<<7748>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7748>>$<<1804>>\begin<<11766>>tex2html_deferred<<11766>>\bf\end<<11767>>tex2html_deferred<<11767>>y<<1804>>_n$\end<<7749>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7749>>\space and 
\begin<<7750>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7750>>$<<1805>>\begin<<11768>>tex2html_deferred<<11768>>\bf\end<<11769>>tex2html_deferred<<11769>>s<<1805>>_m$\end<<7751>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7751>>, an update formula for \begin<<7752>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7752>>$<<1806>>\begin<<11770>>tex2html_deferred<<11770>>\bf\end<<11771>>tex2html_deferred<<11771>>B<<1806>>_n$\end<<7753>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7753>>\space can be directly 
applied to its inverse and vice versa.
\begin<<11772>>tex2html_deferred<<11772>>\par\end<<11773>>tex2html_deferred<<11773>>
\begin<<1807>>itemize<<1807>>
\item The <<1808>>\begin<<11774>>tex2html_deferred<<11774>>\em\end<<11775>>tex2html_deferred<<11775>>Symmetric Rank 1 (SR1)<<1808>> Algorithm
\begin<<11776>>tex2html_deferred<<11776>>\par\end<<11777>>tex2html_deferred<<11777>>
Here matrix \begin<<7754>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7754>>$<<1809>>\begin<<11778>>tex2html_deferred<<11778>>\bf\end<<11779>>tex2html_deferred<<11779>>B<<1809>>_n$\end<<7755>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7755>>\space is updated by an additional term:
  \begin<<1810>>equation<<1810>>
    <<1811>>\begin<<11780>>tex2html_deferred<<11780>>\bf\end<<11781>>tex2html_deferred<<11781>>B<<1811>>_<<1812>>n+1<<1812>>=<<1813>>\begin<<11782>>tex2html_deferred<<11782>>\bf\end<<11783>>tex2html_deferred<<11783>>B<<1813>>_n+<<1814>>\begin<<11784>>tex2html_deferred<<11784>>\bf\end<<11785>>tex2html_deferred<<11785>>uu<<1814>>^T
  \end<<1815>>equation<<1815>>
  where \begin<<7756>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7756>>$<<1816>>\begin<<11786>>tex2html_deferred<<11786>>\bf\end<<11787>>tex2html_deferred<<11787>>u<<1816>>$\end<<7757>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7757>>\space a vector and \begin<<7758>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7758>>$<<1817>>\begin<<11788>>tex2html_deferred<<11788>>\bf\end<<11789>>tex2html_deferred<<11789>>uu<<1817>>^T$\end<<7759>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7759>>\space is a matrix of rank 1.
  Imposing the secant condition, we get
  \begin<<1818>>equation<<1818>>
    <<1819>>\begin<<11790>>tex2html_deferred<<11790>>\bf\end<<11791>>tex2html_deferred<<11791>>B<<1819>>_<<1820>>n+1<<1820>><<1821>>\begin<<11792>>tex2html_deferred<<11792>>\bf\end<<11793>>tex2html_deferred<<11793>>s<<1821>>_n
    =<<1822>>\begin<<11794>>tex2html_deferred<<11794>>\bf\end<<11795>>tex2html_deferred<<11795>>B<<1822>>_n<<1823>>\begin<<11796>>tex2html_deferred<<11796>>\bf\end<<11797>>tex2html_deferred<<11797>>s<<1823>>_n+<<1824>>\begin<<11798>>tex2html_deferred<<11798>>\bf\end<<11799>>tex2html_deferred<<11799>>uu<<1824>>^T<<1825>>\begin<<11800>>tex2html_deferred<<11800>>\bf\end<<11801>>tex2html_deferred<<11801>>s<<1825>>_n=<<1826>>\begin<<11802>>tex2html_deferred<<11802>>\bf\end<<11803>>tex2html_deferred<<11803>>y<<1826>>_n,
    \;\;\;\;\mbox<<1827>>i.e.,<<1827>>\;\;\;\;\;
    <<1828>>\begin<<11804>>tex2html_deferred<<11804>>\bf\end<<11805>>tex2html_deferred<<11805>>u<<1828>>(<<1829>>\begin<<11806>>tex2html_deferred<<11806>>\bf\end<<11807>>tex2html_deferred<<11807>>u<<1829>>^T<<1830>>\begin<<11808>>tex2html_deferred<<11808>>\bf\end<<11809>>tex2html_deferred<<11809>>s<<1830>>_n)=<<1831>>\begin<<11810>>tex2html_deferred<<11810>>\bf\end<<11811>>tex2html_deferred<<11811>>y<<1831>>_n-<<1832>>\begin<<11812>>tex2html_deferred<<11812>>\bf\end<<11813>>tex2html_deferred<<11813>>B<<1832>>_n<<1833>>\begin<<11814>>tex2html_deferred<<11814>>\bf\end<<11815>>tex2html_deferred<<11815>>s<<1833>>_n
  \end<<1834>>equation<<1834>>
  This equation indicats \begin<<7760>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7760>>$<<1835>>\begin<<11816>>tex2html_deferred<<11816>>\bf\end<<11817>>tex2html_deferred<<11817>>u<<1835>>$\end<<7761>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7761>>\space is in the same direction as 
  \begin<<7762>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7762>>$<<1836>>\begin<<11818>>tex2html_deferred<<11818>>\bf\end<<11819>>tex2html_deferred<<11819>>w<<1836>>=<<1837>>\begin<<11820>>tex2html_deferred<<11820>>\bf\end<<11821>>tex2html_deferred<<11821>>y<<1837>>_n-<<1838>>\begin<<11822>>tex2html_deferred<<11822>>\bf\end<<11823>>tex2html_deferred<<11823>>B<<1838>>_n<<1839>>\begin<<11824>>tex2html_deferred<<11824>>\bf\end<<11825>>tex2html_deferred<<11825>>s<<1839>>_n$\end<<7763>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7763>>, and can therefore
  be written as \begin<<7764>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7764>>$<<1840>>\begin<<11826>>tex2html_deferred<<11826>>\bf\end<<11827>>tex2html_deferred<<11827>>u<<1840>>=c <<1841>>\begin<<11828>>tex2html_deferred<<11828>>\bf\end<<11829>>tex2html_deferred<<11829>>w<<1841>>$\end<<7765>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7765>>. Substituting this back we get
  \begin<<1842>>equation<<1842>>
    <<1843>>\begin<<11830>>tex2html_deferred<<11830>>\bf\end<<11831>>tex2html_deferred<<11831>>u<<1843>><<1844>>\begin<<11832>>tex2html_deferred<<11832>>\bf\end<<11833>>tex2html_deferred<<11833>>u<<1844>>^T<<1845>>\begin<<11834>>tex2html_deferred<<11834>>\bf\end<<11835>>tex2html_deferred<<11835>>s<<1845>>_n=c^2<<1846>>\begin<<11836>>tex2html_deferred<<11836>>\bf\end<<11837>>tex2html_deferred<<11837>>w<<1846>><<1847>>\begin<<11838>>tex2html_deferred<<11838>>\bf\end<<11839>>tex2html_deferred<<11839>>w<<1847>>^T<<1848>>\begin<<11840>>tex2html_deferred<<11840>>\bf\end<<11841>>tex2html_deferred<<11841>>s<<1848>>_n=<<1849>>\begin<<11842>>tex2html_deferred<<11842>>\bf\end<<11843>>tex2html_deferred<<11843>>w<<1849>>
  \end<<1850>>equation<<1850>>
  Solving this we get \begin<<7766>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7766>>$c =1/(<<1851>>\begin<<11844>>tex2html_deferred<<11844>>\bf\end<<11845>>tex2html_deferred<<11845>>w<<1851>>^T <<1852>>\begin<<11846>>tex2html_deferred<<11846>>\bf\end<<11847>>tex2html_deferred<<11847>>s<<1852>>_n)^<<1853>>1/2<<1853>>$\end<<7767>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7767>>,
  \begin<<1854>>equation<<1854>>
    <<1855>>\begin<<11848>>tex2html_deferred<<11848>>\bf\end<<11849>>tex2html_deferred<<11849>>u<<1855>>=c<<1856>>\begin<<11850>>tex2html_deferred<<11850>>\bf\end<<11851>>tex2html_deferred<<11851>>w<<1856>>=\frac<<6559>><<1857>>\begin<<11852>>tex2html_deferred<<11852>>\bf\end<<11853>>tex2html_deferred<<11853>>y<<1857>>_n-<<1858>>\begin<<11854>>tex2html_deferred<<11854>>\bf\end<<11855>>tex2html_deferred<<11855>>B<<1858>>_n<<1859>>\begin<<11856>>tex2html_deferred<<11856>>\bf\end<<11857>>tex2html_deferred<<11857>>s<<1859>>_n<<6559>><<6560>>(<<1860>>\begin<<11858>>tex2html_deferred<<11858>>\bf\end<<11859>>tex2html_deferred<<11859>>w<<1860>>^T<<1861>>\begin<<11860>>tex2html_deferred<<11860>>\bf\end<<11861>>tex2html_deferred<<11861>>s<<1861>>_n)^<<1862>>1/2<<1862>><<6560>>
    =\frac<<6561>><<1863>>\begin<<11862>>tex2html_deferred<<11862>>\bf\end<<11863>>tex2html_deferred<<11863>>y<<1863>>_n-<<1864>>\begin<<11864>>tex2html_deferred<<11864>>\bf\end<<11865>>tex2html_deferred<<11865>>B<<1864>>_n<<1865>>\begin<<11866>>tex2html_deferred<<11866>>\bf\end<<11867>>tex2html_deferred<<11867>>s<<1865>>_n<<6561>><<6562>>( (<<1866>>\begin<<11868>>tex2html_deferred<<11868>>\bf\end<<11869>>tex2html_deferred<<11869>>y<<1866>>_n-<<1867>>\begin<<11870>>tex2html_deferred<<11870>>\bf\end<<11871>>tex2html_deferred<<11871>>B<<1867>>_n<<1868>>\begin<<11872>>tex2html_deferred<<11872>>\bf\end<<11873>>tex2html_deferred<<11873>>s<<1868>>_n)^T<<1869>>\begin<<11874>>tex2html_deferred<<11874>>\bf\end<<11875>>tex2html_deferred<<11875>>s<<1869>>_n)^<<1870>>1/2<<1870>><<6562>>
  \end<<1871>>equation<<1871>>
  and the iteration of \begin<<7768>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7768>>$<<1872>>\begin<<11876>>tex2html_deferred<<11876>>\bf\end<<11877>>tex2html_deferred<<11877>>B<<1872>>_n$\end<<7769>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7769>>\space becomes
  \begin<<1873>>equation<<1873>>
    <<1874>>\begin<<11878>>tex2html_deferred<<11878>>\bf\end<<11879>>tex2html_deferred<<11879>>B<<1874>>_<<1875>>n+1<<1875>>=<<1876>>\begin<<11880>>tex2html_deferred<<11880>>\bf\end<<11881>>tex2html_deferred<<11881>>B<<1876>>_n+<<1877>>\begin<<11882>>tex2html_deferred<<11882>>\bf\end<<11883>>tex2html_deferred<<11883>>uu<<1877>>^T
    =<<1878>>\begin<<11884>>tex2html_deferred<<11884>>\bf\end<<11885>>tex2html_deferred<<11885>>B<<1878>>_n
    +\frac<<6563>> (<<1879>>\begin<<11886>>tex2html_deferred<<11886>>\bf\end<<11887>>tex2html_deferred<<11887>>y<<1879>>_n-<<1880>>\begin<<11888>>tex2html_deferred<<11888>>\bf\end<<11889>>tex2html_deferred<<11889>>B<<1880>>_n<<1881>>\begin<<11890>>tex2html_deferred<<11890>>\bf\end<<11891>>tex2html_deferred<<11891>>s<<1881>>_n)(<<1882>>\begin<<11892>>tex2html_deferred<<11892>>\bf\end<<11893>>tex2html_deferred<<11893>>y<<1882>>_n-<<1883>>\begin<<11894>>tex2html_deferred<<11894>>\bf\end<<11895>>tex2html_deferred<<11895>>B<<1883>>_n<<1884>>\begin<<11896>>tex2html_deferred<<11896>>\bf\end<<11897>>tex2html_deferred<<11897>>s<<1884>>_n)^T <<6563>>
    <<6564>> (<<1885>>\begin<<11898>>tex2html_deferred<<11898>>\bf\end<<11899>>tex2html_deferred<<11899>>y<<1885>>_n-<<1886>>\begin<<11900>>tex2html_deferred<<11900>>\bf\end<<11901>>tex2html_deferred<<11901>>B<<1886>>_n<<1887>>\begin<<11902>>tex2html_deferred<<11902>>\bf\end<<11903>>tex2html_deferred<<11903>>s<<1887>>_n)^T <<1888>>\begin<<11904>>tex2html_deferred<<11904>>\bf\end<<11905>>tex2html_deferred<<11905>>s<<1888>>_n <<6564>>
  \end<<1889>>equation<<1889>>
  Applying the
  \htmladdnormallink<<1890>>Sherman-Morrison formula<<1890>><<1891>>../appendices/node7.html<<1891>>,
  we can further get the inverse \begin<<7770>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7770>>$<<1892>>\begin<<11906>>tex2html_deferred<<11906>>\bf\end<<11907>>tex2html_deferred<<11907>>B<<1892>>_<<1893>>n+1<<1893>>$\end<<7771>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7771>>:
  \begin<<1894>>eqnarray<<1894>>
    <<1895>>\begin<<11908>>tex2html_deferred<<11908>>\bf\end<<11909>>tex2html_deferred<<11909>>B<<1895>>_<<1896>>n+1<<1896>>^<<1897>>-1<<1897>>;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;\left( <<1898>>\begin<<11910>>tex2html_deferred<<11910>>\bf\end<<11911>>tex2html_deferred<<11911>>B<<1898>>_n+<<1899>>\begin<<11912>>tex2html_deferred<<11912>>\bf\end<<11913>>tex2html_deferred<<11913>>uu<<1899>>^T \right)^<<1900>>-1<<1900>>
    =<<1901>>\begin<<11914>>tex2html_deferred<<11914>>\bf\end<<11915>>tex2html_deferred<<11915>>B<<1901>>_n^<<1902>>-1<<1902>>-\frac<<6565>> <<1903>>\begin<<11916>>tex2html_deferred<<11916>>\bf\end<<11917>>tex2html_deferred<<11917>>B<<1903>>_n^<<1904>>-1<<1904>><<1905>>\begin<<11918>>tex2html_deferred<<11918>>\bf\end<<11919>>tex2html_deferred<<11919>>uu<<1905>>^T<<1906>>\begin<<11920>>tex2html_deferred<<11920>>\bf\end<<11921>>tex2html_deferred<<11921>>B<<1906>>_n^<<1907>>-1<<1907>><<6565>><<6566>>1+<<1908>>\begin<<11922>>tex2html_deferred<<11922>>\bf\end<<11923>>tex2html_deferred<<11923>>u<<1908>>^T<<1909>>\begin<<11924>>tex2html_deferred<<11924>>\bf\end<<11925>>tex2html_deferred<<11925>>B<<1909>>_n^<<1910>>-1<<1910>><<1911>>\begin<<11926>>tex2html_deferred<<11926>>\bf\end<<11927>>tex2html_deferred<<11927>>u<<1911>><<6566>>
    \nonumber\\ 
    ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;<<1912>>\begin<<11928>>tex2html_deferred<<11928>>\bf\end<<11929>>tex2html_deferred<<11929>>B<<1912>>_n^<<1913>>-1<<1913>>
    +\frac<<6567>> (<<1914>>\begin<<11930>>tex2html_deferred<<11930>>\bf\end<<11931>>tex2html_deferred<<11931>>s<<1914>>_n-<<1915>>\begin<<11932>>tex2html_deferred<<11932>>\bf\end<<11933>>tex2html_deferred<<11933>>B<<1915>>_n^<<1916>>-1<<1916>><<1917>>\begin<<11934>>tex2html_deferred<<11934>>\bf\end<<11935>>tex2html_deferred<<11935>>y<<1917>>_n)(<<1918>>\begin<<11936>>tex2html_deferred<<11936>>\bf\end<<11937>>tex2html_deferred<<11937>>s<<1918>>_n-<<1919>>\begin<<11938>>tex2html_deferred<<11938>>\bf\end<<11939>>tex2html_deferred<<11939>>B<<1919>>_n^<<1920>>-1<<1920>><<1921>>\begin<<11940>>tex2html_deferred<<11940>>\bf\end<<11941>>tex2html_deferred<<11941>>y<<1921>>_n)^T <<6567>>
    <<6568>> (<<1922>>\begin<<11942>>tex2html_deferred<<11942>>\bf\end<<11943>>tex2html_deferred<<11943>>s<<1922>>_n-<<1923>>\begin<<11944>>tex2html_deferred<<11944>>\bf\end<<11945>>tex2html_deferred<<11945>>B<<1923>>_n^<<1924>>-1<<1924>><<1925>>\begin<<11946>>tex2html_deferred<<11946>>\bf\end<<11947>>tex2html_deferred<<11947>>y<<1925>>_n)^T <<1926>>\begin<<11948>>tex2html_deferred<<11948>>\bf\end<<11949>>tex2html_deferred<<11949>>y<<1926>>_n <<6568>>
  \end<<1927>>eqnarray<<1927>>
  We note that this equation is dual to the previous one, and it
  can also be obtained based on the duality between the secant 
  conditions for \begin<<7772>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7772>>$<<1928>>\begin<<11950>>tex2html_deferred<<11950>>\bf\end<<11951>>tex2html_deferred<<11951>>B<<1928>>_n$\end<<7773>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7773>>\space and \begin<<7774>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7774>>$<<1929>>\begin<<11952>>tex2html_deferred<<11952>>\bf\end<<11953>>tex2html_deferred<<11953>>B<<1929>>_n^<<1930>>-1<<1930>>$\end<<7775>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7775>>. Specifically, 
  same as above, we impose the secant condition for the inverse 
  \begin<<7776>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7776>>$<<1931>>\begin<<11954>>tex2html_deferred<<11954>>\bf\end<<11955>>tex2html_deferred<<11955>>B<<1931>>_<<1932>>n+1<<1932>>^<<1933>>-1<<1933>>$\end<<7777>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7777>>\space of the following form
  \begin<<1934>>equation<<1934>>
    <<1935>>\begin<<11956>>tex2html_deferred<<11956>>\bf\end<<11957>>tex2html_deferred<<11957>>B<<1935>>_<<1936>>n+1<<1936>>^<<1937>>-1<<1937>>=<<1938>>\begin<<11958>>tex2html_deferred<<11958>>\bf\end<<11959>>tex2html_deferred<<11959>>B<<1938>>_n^<<1939>>-1<<1939>>+<<1940>>\begin<<11960>>tex2html_deferred<<11960>>\bf\end<<11961>>tex2html_deferred<<11961>>uu<<1940>>^T
  \end<<1941>>equation<<1941>>
  and get
  \begin<<1942>>equation<<1942>>
    <<1943>>\begin<<11962>>tex2html_deferred<<11962>>\bf\end<<11963>>tex2html_deferred<<11963>>B<<1943>>_<<1944>>n+1<<1944>>^<<1945>>-1<<1945>><<1946>>\begin<<11964>>tex2html_deferred<<11964>>\bf\end<<11965>>tex2html_deferred<<11965>>y<<1946>>_n
    =<<1947>>\begin<<11966>>tex2html_deferred<<11966>>\bf\end<<11967>>tex2html_deferred<<11967>>B<<1947>>_n^<<1948>>-1<<1948>><<1949>>\begin<<11968>>tex2html_deferred<<11968>>\bf\end<<11969>>tex2html_deferred<<11969>>y<<1949>>_n+<<1950>>\begin<<11970>>tex2html_deferred<<11970>>\bf\end<<11971>>tex2html_deferred<<11971>>uu<<1950>>^T<<1951>>\begin<<11972>>tex2html_deferred<<11972>>\bf\end<<11973>>tex2html_deferred<<11973>>y<<1951>>_n=<<1952>>\begin<<11974>>tex2html_deferred<<11974>>\bf\end<<11975>>tex2html_deferred<<11975>>s<<1952>>_n,
  \end<<1953>>equation<<1953>>
  Then by repeating the same process above, we get the same update
  formula for \begin<<7778>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7778>>$<<1954>>\begin<<11976>>tex2html_deferred<<11976>>\bf\end<<11977>>tex2html_deferred<<11977>>B<<1954>>_n^<<1955>>-1<<1955>>$\end<<7779>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7779>>.
\begin<<11978>>tex2html_deferred<<11978>>\par\end<<11979>>tex2html_deferred<<11979>>
This is the formula for directly updating \begin<<7780>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7780>>$<<1956>>\begin<<11980>>tex2html_deferred<<11980>>\bf\end<<11981>>tex2html_deferred<<11981>>B<<1956>>_n^<<1957>>-1<<1957>>$\end<<7781>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7781>>. 
  For the iteration to converge to a local minimum, matrix 
  \begin<<7782>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7782>>$<<1958>>\begin<<11982>>tex2html_deferred<<11982>>\bf\end<<11983>>tex2html_deferred<<11983>>B<<1958>>_<<1959>>n+1<<1959>>^<<1960>>-1<<1960>>$\end<<7783>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7783>>\space needs to be positive definite as well as 
  \begin<<7784>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7784>>$<<1961>>\begin<<11984>>tex2html_deferred<<11984>>\bf\end<<11985>>tex2html_deferred<<11985>>B<<1961>>_n^<<1962>>-1<<1962>>$\end<<7785>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7785>>, we therefore require
  \begin<<1963>>equation<<1963>>
  <<1964>>\begin<<11986>>tex2html_deferred<<11986>>\bf\end<<11987>>tex2html_deferred<<11987>>w<<1964>>^T<<1965>>\begin<<11988>>tex2html_deferred<<11988>>\bf\end<<11989>>tex2html_deferred<<11989>>y<<1965>>_n=(<<1966>>\begin<<11990>>tex2html_deferred<<11990>>\bf\end<<11991>>tex2html_deferred<<11991>>s<<1966>>_n-<<1967>>\begin<<11992>>tex2html_deferred<<11992>>\bf\end<<11993>>tex2html_deferred<<11993>>B<<1967>>_n^<<1968>>-1<<1968>><<1969>>\begin<<11994>>tex2html_deferred<<11994>>\bf\end<<11995>>tex2html_deferred<<11995>>y<<1969>>_n)^T <<1970>>\begin<<11996>>tex2html_deferred<<11996>>\bf\end<<11997>>tex2html_deferred<<11997>>y<<1970>>_n 
  =<<1971>>\begin<<11998>>tex2html_deferred<<11998>>\bf\end<<11999>>tex2html_deferred<<11999>>s<<1971>>_n^T<<1972>>\begin<<12000>>tex2html_deferred<<12000>>\bf\end<<12001>>tex2html_deferred<<12001>>y<<1972>>_n -<<1973>>\begin<<12002>>tex2html_deferred<<12002>>\bf\end<<12003>>tex2html_deferred<<12003>>y<<1973>>_n^T <<1974>>\begin<<12004>>tex2html_deferred<<12004>>\bf\end<<12005>>tex2html_deferred<<12005>>B<<1974>>_n^<<1975>>-1<<1975>><<1976>>\begin<<12006>>tex2html_deferred<<12006>>\bf\end<<12007>>tex2html_deferred<<12007>>y<<1976>>_n ;SPMgt;0
  \end<<1977>>equation<<1977>>
  It may be difficult to maintain this requirement through out the
  iteration. This problem can be avoided in the following DFP and 
  BFGS methods.
\begin<<12008>>tex2html_deferred<<12008>>\par\end<<12009>>tex2html_deferred<<12009>>
\item The <<1978>>\begin<<12010>>tex2html_deferred<<12010>>\em\end<<12011>>tex2html_deferred<<12011>>BFGS (Broyden-Fletcher-Goldfarb-Shanno)<<1978>> algorithm
\begin<<12012>>tex2html_deferred<<12012>>\par\end<<12013>>tex2html_deferred<<12013>>
This is a rank 2 algorithm in which matrix \begin<<7786>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7786>>$<<1979>>\begin<<12014>>tex2html_deferred<<12014>>\bf\end<<12015>>tex2html_deferred<<12015>>B<<1979>>_n$\end<<7787>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7787>>\space is updated 
  by two rank-1 terms:
  \begin<<1980>>equation<<1980>>
    <<1981>>\begin<<12016>>tex2html_deferred<<12016>>\bf\end<<12017>>tex2html_deferred<<12017>>B<<1981>>_<<1982>>n+1<<1982>>=<<1983>>\begin<<12018>>tex2html_deferred<<12018>>\bf\end<<12019>>tex2html_deferred<<12019>>B<<1983>>_n+\alpha<<1984>>\begin<<12020>>tex2html_deferred<<12020>>\bf\end<<12021>>tex2html_deferred<<12021>>uu<<1984>>^T+\beta<<1985>>\begin<<12022>>tex2html_deferred<<12022>>\bf\end<<12023>>tex2html_deferred<<12023>>vv<<1985>>^T
  \end<<1986>>equation<<1986>>
  Imposing the secant condition for \begin<<7788>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7788>>$<<1987>>\begin<<12024>>tex2html_deferred<<12024>>\bf\end<<12025>>tex2html_deferred<<12025>>B<<1987>>_n$\end<<7789>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7789>>, we get
  \begin<<1988>>equation<<1988>>
    <<1989>>\begin<<12026>>tex2html_deferred<<12026>>\bf\end<<12027>>tex2html_deferred<<12027>>B<<1989>>_<<1990>>n+1<<1990>> <<1991>>\begin<<12028>>tex2html_deferred<<12028>>\bf\end<<12029>>tex2html_deferred<<12029>>s<<1991>>_n
    =(<<1992>>\begin<<12030>>tex2html_deferred<<12030>>\bf\end<<12031>>tex2html_deferred<<12031>>B<<1992>>_n+\alpha<<1993>>\begin<<12032>>tex2html_deferred<<12032>>\bf\end<<12033>>tex2html_deferred<<12033>>uu<<1993>>^T+\beta<<1994>>\begin<<12034>>tex2html_deferred<<12034>>\bf\end<<12035>>tex2html_deferred<<12035>>vv<<1994>>^T)<<1995>>\begin<<12036>>tex2html_deferred<<12036>>\bf\end<<12037>>tex2html_deferred<<12037>>s<<1995>>_n
    =<<1996>>\begin<<12038>>tex2html_deferred<<12038>>\bf\end<<12039>>tex2html_deferred<<12039>>B<<1996>>_n<<1997>>\begin<<12040>>tex2html_deferred<<12040>>\bf\end<<12041>>tex2html_deferred<<12041>>s<<1997>>_n+<<1998>>\begin<<12042>>tex2html_deferred<<12042>>\bf\end<<12043>>tex2html_deferred<<12043>>u<<1998>>(\alpha<<1999>>\begin<<12044>>tex2html_deferred<<12044>>\bf\end<<12045>>tex2html_deferred<<12045>>u<<1999>>^T<<2000>>\begin<<12046>>tex2html_deferred<<12046>>\bf\end<<12047>>tex2html_deferred<<12047>>s<<2000>>_n)
    +<<2001>>\begin<<12048>>tex2html_deferred<<12048>>\bf\end<<12049>>tex2html_deferred<<12049>>v<<2001>>(\beta<<2002>>\begin<<12050>>tex2html_deferred<<12050>>\bf\end<<12051>>tex2html_deferred<<12051>>v<<2002>>^T<<2003>>\begin<<12052>>tex2html_deferred<<12052>>\bf\end<<12053>>tex2html_deferred<<12053>>s<<2003>>_n)=<<2004>>\begin<<12054>>tex2html_deferred<<12054>>\bf\end<<12055>>tex2html_deferred<<12055>>y<<2004>>_n  
  \end<<2005>>equation<<2005>>
  or
  \begin<<2006>>equation<<2006>>
    <<2007>>\begin<<12056>>tex2html_deferred<<12056>>\bf\end<<12057>>tex2html_deferred<<12057>>u<<2007>>(\alpha<<2008>>\begin<<12058>>tex2html_deferred<<12058>>\bf\end<<12059>>tex2html_deferred<<12059>>u<<2008>>^T<<2009>>\begin<<12060>>tex2html_deferred<<12060>>\bf\end<<12061>>tex2html_deferred<<12061>>s<<2009>>_n)
    +<<2010>>\begin<<12062>>tex2html_deferred<<12062>>\bf\end<<12063>>tex2html_deferred<<12063>>v<<2010>>(\beta<<2011>>\begin<<12064>>tex2html_deferred<<12064>>\bf\end<<12065>>tex2html_deferred<<12065>>v<<2011>>^T<<2012>>\begin<<12066>>tex2html_deferred<<12066>>\bf\end<<12067>>tex2html_deferred<<12067>>s<<2012>>_n)=<<2013>>\begin<<12068>>tex2html_deferred<<12068>>\bf\end<<12069>>tex2html_deferred<<12069>>y<<2013>>_n-<<2014>>\begin<<12070>>tex2html_deferred<<12070>>\bf\end<<12071>>tex2html_deferred<<12071>>B<<2014>>_n<<2015>>\begin<<12072>>tex2html_deferred<<12072>>\bf\end<<12073>>tex2html_deferred<<12073>>s<<2015>>_n
  \end<<2016>>equation<<2016>>
  which can be satisfied if we let
  \begin<<2017>>equation<<2017>>
    <<2018>>\begin<<12074>>tex2html_deferred<<12074>>\bf\end<<12075>>tex2html_deferred<<12075>>u<<2018>>=<<2019>>\begin<<12076>>tex2html_deferred<<12076>>\bf\end<<12077>>tex2html_deferred<<12077>>y<<2019>>_n,\;\;\;\;\;\;\alpha=\frac<<2020>>1<<2020>><<6569>><<2021>>\begin<<12078>>tex2html_deferred<<12078>>\bf\end<<12079>>tex2html_deferred<<12079>>s<<2021>>_n^T<<2022>>\begin<<12080>>tex2html_deferred<<12080>>\bf\end<<12081>>tex2html_deferred<<12081>>y<<2022>>_n<<6569>>,
    \;\;\;\;\;<<2023>>\begin<<12082>>tex2html_deferred<<12082>>\bf\end<<12083>>tex2html_deferred<<12083>>v<<2023>>=<<2024>>\begin<<12084>>tex2html_deferred<<12084>>\bf\end<<12085>>tex2html_deferred<<12085>>B<<2024>>_n<<2025>>\begin<<12086>>tex2html_deferred<<12086>>\bf\end<<12087>>tex2html_deferred<<12087>>s<<2025>>_n,\;\;\;\;\;
    \beta=-\frac<<2026>>1<<2026>><<6570>><<2027>>\begin<<12088>>tex2html_deferred<<12088>>\bf\end<<12089>>tex2html_deferred<<12089>>v<<2027>>^T<<2028>>\begin<<12090>>tex2html_deferred<<12090>>\bf\end<<12091>>tex2html_deferred<<12091>>s<<2028>>_n<<6570>>=-\frac<<2029>>1<<2029>><<6571>><<2030>>\begin<<12092>>tex2html_deferred<<12092>>\bf\end<<12093>>tex2html_deferred<<12093>>s<<2030>>_n^T<<2031>>\begin<<12094>>tex2html_deferred<<12094>>\bf\end<<12095>>tex2html_deferred<<12095>>B<<2031>>_n<<2032>>\begin<<12096>>tex2html_deferred<<12096>>\bf\end<<12097>>tex2html_deferred<<12097>>s<<2032>>_n<<6571>>
  \end<<2033>>equation<<2033>>
  Substituting these into 
  \begin<<7790>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7790>>$<<2034>>\begin<<12098>>tex2html_deferred<<12098>>\bf\end<<12099>>tex2html_deferred<<12099>>B<<2034>>_<<2035>>n+1<<2035>>=<<2036>>\begin<<12100>>tex2html_deferred<<12100>>\bf\end<<12101>>tex2html_deferred<<12101>>B<<2036>>_n+\alpha<<2037>>\begin<<12102>>tex2html_deferred<<12102>>\bf\end<<12103>>tex2html_deferred<<12103>>uu<<2037>>^T+\beta<<2038>>\begin<<12104>>tex2html_deferred<<12104>>\bf\end<<12105>>tex2html_deferred<<12105>>vv<<2038>>^T$\end<<7791>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7791>>
  we get
  \begin<<2039>>equation<<2039>>
    <<2040>>\begin<<12106>>tex2html_deferred<<12106>>\bf\end<<12107>>tex2html_deferred<<12107>>B<<2040>>_<<2041>>n+1<<2041>>=<<2042>>\begin<<12108>>tex2html_deferred<<12108>>\bf\end<<12109>>tex2html_deferred<<12109>>B<<2042>>_n+\alpha<<2043>>\begin<<12110>>tex2html_deferred<<12110>>\bf\end<<12111>>tex2html_deferred<<12111>>uu<<2043>>^T+\beta<<2044>>\begin<<12112>>tex2html_deferred<<12112>>\bf\end<<12113>>tex2html_deferred<<12113>>vv<<2044>>^T
    =<<2045>>\begin<<12114>>tex2html_deferred<<12114>>\bf\end<<12115>>tex2html_deferred<<12115>>B<<2045>>_n+\frac<<6572>><<2046>>\begin<<12116>>tex2html_deferred<<12116>>\bf\end<<12117>>tex2html_deferred<<12117>>y<<2046>>_n<<2047>>\begin<<12118>>tex2html_deferred<<12118>>\bf\end<<12119>>tex2html_deferred<<12119>>y<<2047>>_n^T<<6572>><<6573>><<2048>>\begin<<12120>>tex2html_deferred<<12120>>\bf\end<<12121>>tex2html_deferred<<12121>>y<<2048>>_n^T<<2049>>\begin<<12122>>tex2html_deferred<<12122>>\bf\end<<12123>>tex2html_deferred<<12123>>s<<2049>>_n<<6573>>
    -\frac<<6574>><<2050>>\begin<<12124>>tex2html_deferred<<12124>>\bf\end<<12125>>tex2html_deferred<<12125>>B<<2050>>_n<<2051>>\begin<<12126>>tex2html_deferred<<12126>>\bf\end<<12127>>tex2html_deferred<<12127>>s<<2051>>_n<<2052>>\begin<<12128>>tex2html_deferred<<12128>>\bf\end<<12129>>tex2html_deferred<<12129>>s<<2052>>_n^T<<2053>>\begin<<12130>>tex2html_deferred<<12130>>\bf\end<<12131>>tex2html_deferred<<12131>>B<<2053>>_n<<6574>><<6575>><<2054>>\begin<<12132>>tex2html_deferred<<12132>>\bf\end<<12133>>tex2html_deferred<<12133>>s<<2054>>_n^T<<2055>>\begin<<12134>>tex2html_deferred<<12134>>\bf\end<<12135>>tex2html_deferred<<12135>>B<<2055>>_n<<2056>>\begin<<12136>>tex2html_deferred<<12136>>\bf\end<<12137>>tex2html_deferred<<12137>>s<<2056>>_n<<6575>>
    \label<<2057>>BFGSupdateB<<2057>>
  \end<<2058>>equation<<2058>>
  Given this update formula for \begin<<7792>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7792>>$<<2059>>\begin<<12138>>tex2html_deferred<<12138>>\bf\end<<12139>>tex2html_deferred<<12139>>B<<2059>>_n$\end<<7793>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7793>>, we can further find its
  inverse \begin<<7794>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7794>>$<<2060>>\begin<<12140>>tex2html_deferred<<12140>>\bf\end<<12141>>tex2html_deferred<<12141>>B<<2060>>_n^<<2061>>-1<<2061>>$\end<<7795>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7795>>\space and then the search direction 
  \begin<<7796>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7796>>$<<2062>>\begin<<12142>>tex2html_deferred<<12142>>\bf\end<<12143>>tex2html_deferred<<12143>>d<<2062>>_n=-<<2063>>\begin<<12144>>tex2html_deferred<<12144>>\bf\end<<12145>>tex2html_deferred<<12145>>B<<2063>>_n^<<2064>>-1<<2064>><<2065>>\begin<<12146>>tex2html_deferred<<12146>>\bf\end<<12147>>tex2html_deferred<<12147>>g<<2065>>_n$\end<<7797>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7797>>.
\begin<<12148>>tex2html_deferred<<12148>>\par\end<<12149>>tex2html_deferred<<12149>>
Alternatively, given \begin<<7798>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7798>>$<<2066>>\begin<<12150>>tex2html_deferred<<12150>>\bf\end<<12151>>tex2html_deferred<<12151>>B<<2066>>_n$\end<<7799>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7799>>, we can further derive an update 
  formula directly for the inverse matrix \begin<<7800>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7800>>$<<2067>>\begin<<12152>>tex2html_deferred<<12152>>\bf\end<<12153>>tex2html_deferred<<12153>>B<<2067>>_n^<<2068>>-1<<2068>>$\end<<7801>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7801>>, so that 
  the search direction \begin<<7802>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7802>>$<<2069>>\begin<<12154>>tex2html_deferred<<12154>>\bf\end<<12155>>tex2html_deferred<<12155>>d<<2069>>_n$\end<<7803>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7803>>\space can be obtained without carrying 
  out the inversion computation. Specifically, we first define 
  \begin<<7804>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7804>>$<<2070>>\begin<<12156>>tex2html_deferred<<12156>>\bf\end<<12157>>tex2html_deferred<<12157>>U<<2070>>=[<<2071>>\begin<<12158>>tex2html_deferred<<12158>>\bf\end<<12159>>tex2html_deferred<<12159>>u<<2071>>_1\;<<2072>>\begin<<12160>>tex2html_deferred<<12160>>\bf\end<<12161>>tex2html_deferred<<12161>>u<<2072>>_2]$\end<<7805>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7805>>\space and \begin<<7806>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7806>>$<<2073>>\begin<<12162>>tex2html_deferred<<12162>>\bf\end<<12163>>tex2html_deferred<<12163>>V<<2073>>=[<<2074>>\begin<<12164>>tex2html_deferred<<12164>>\bf\end<<12165>>tex2html_deferred<<12165>>v<<2074>>_1\;<<2075>>\begin<<12166>>tex2html_deferred<<12166>>\bf\end<<12167>>tex2html_deferred<<12167>>v<<2075>>_2]$\end<<7807>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7807>>,
  where
  \begin<<2076>>equation<<2076>>
    <<2077>>\begin<<12168>>tex2html_deferred<<12168>>\bf\end<<12169>>tex2html_deferred<<12169>>u<<2077>>_1=<<2078>>\begin<<12170>>tex2html_deferred<<12170>>\bf\end<<12171>>tex2html_deferred<<12171>>v<<2078>>_1=\frac<<6576>><<2079>>\begin<<12172>>tex2html_deferred<<12172>>\bf\end<<12173>>tex2html_deferred<<12173>>y<<2079>>_n<<6576>><<6577>>(<<2080>>\begin<<12174>>tex2html_deferred<<12174>>\bf\end<<12175>>tex2html_deferred<<12175>>s<<2080>>_n^T<<2081>>\begin<<12176>>tex2html_deferred<<12176>>\bf\end<<12177>>tex2html_deferred<<12177>>y<<2081>>_n)^<<2082>>1/2<<2082>><<6577>>,
    \;\;\;\;\;\;
