\begin<<13086>>tex2html_deferred<<13086>>\par\end<<13087>>tex2html_deferred<<13087>>
\subsection*<<2784>>Conjugate gradient method<<2784>>
\begin<<13088>>tex2html_deferred<<13088>>\par\end<<13089>>tex2html_deferred<<13089>>
\htmladdnormallink<<2785>>reference<<2785>><<2786>>http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~quake-papers/painless-conjugate-gradient.pdf<<2786>>
\begin<<13090>>tex2html_deferred<<13090>>\par\end<<13091>>tex2html_deferred<<13091>>
The gradient descent method can be used to solve the minimization problem
when the Hessian matrix of the objective function is not available. However, 
this method may not be efficient if it gets into a zigzag search pattern and 
repeat the same search directions many times. This problem can be avoided 
in the <<2787>>\begin<<13092>>tex2html_deferred<<13092>>\em\end<<13093>>tex2html_deferred<<13093>>conjugate gradient (CG)<<2787>> method. If the objective function is
quadratic, the CG method converges to the solution in \begin<<7878>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7878>>$N$\end<<7879>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7879>>\space iterations without 
repeating any of the directions previously traversed. If the objective function 
is not quadratic, the CG method can still significantly improve the performance
in comparison to the gradient descent method. 
\begin<<13094>>tex2html_deferred<<13094>>\par\end<<13095>>tex2html_deferred<<13095>>
Here we will first assume the function \begin<<7880>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7880>>$f(<<2788>>\begin<<13096>>tex2html_deferred<<13096>>\bf\end<<13097>>tex2html_deferred<<13097>>x<<2788>>)$\end<<7881>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7881>>\space to be minimized is quadratic:
\begin<<2789>>equation<<2789>> 
  f(<<2790>>\begin<<13098>>tex2html_deferred<<13098>>\bf\end<<13099>>tex2html_deferred<<13099>>x<<2790>>)=\frac<<2791>>1<<2791>><<2792>>2<<2792>><<2793>>\begin<<13100>>tex2html_deferred<<13100>>\bf\end<<13101>>tex2html_deferred<<13101>>x<<2793>>^T<<2794>>\begin<<13102>>tex2html_deferred<<13102>>\bf\end<<13103>>tex2html_deferred<<13103>>A<<2794>><<2795>>\begin<<13104>>tex2html_deferred<<13104>>\bf\end<<13105>>tex2html_deferred<<13105>>x<<2795>>-<<2796>>\begin<<13106>>tex2html_deferred<<13106>>\bf\end<<13107>>tex2html_deferred<<13107>>b<<2796>>^T<<2797>>\begin<<13108>>tex2html_deferred<<13108>>\bf\end<<13109>>tex2html_deferred<<13109>>x<<2797>>+c
\end<<2798>>equation<<2798>>
where \begin<<7882>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7882>>$<<2799>>\begin<<13110>>tex2html_deferred<<13110>>\bf\end<<13111>>tex2html_deferred<<13111>>A<<2799>>=<<2800>>\begin<<13112>>tex2html_deferred<<13112>>\bf\end<<13113>>tex2html_deferred<<13113>>A<<2800>>^T$\end<<7883>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7883>>\space is symmetric. Later we will relax the condition 
for \begin<<7884>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7884>>$f(<<2801>>\begin<<13114>>tex2html_deferred<<13114>>\bf\end<<13115>>tex2html_deferred<<13115>>x<<2801>>)$\end<<7885>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7885>>\space and consider the minimization of arbitrary functions, which
can be approximated by the first three terms of it Taylor expansion, with 
the symmetric Hessian matrix in the third term.
\begin<<13116>>tex2html_deferred<<13116>>\par\end<<13117>>tex2html_deferred<<13117>>
The gradient and Hessian of the quadratic function given above are respectively:
\begin<<2802>>equation<<2802>> 
  <<2803>>\begin<<13118>>tex2html_deferred<<13118>>\bf\end<<13119>>tex2html_deferred<<13119>>g<<2803>>(<<2804>>\begin<<13120>>tex2html_deferred<<13120>>\bf\end<<13121>>tex2html_deferred<<13121>>x<<2804>>)=\frac<<2805>>d<<2805>><<6654>>d<<2806>>\begin<<13122>>tex2html_deferred<<13122>>\bf\end<<13123>>tex2html_deferred<<13123>>x<<2806>><<6654>>f(<<2807>>\begin<<13124>>tex2html_deferred<<13124>>\bf\end<<13125>>tex2html_deferred<<13125>>x<<2807>>)
  =\frac<<2808>>d<<2808>><<6655>>d<<2809>>\begin<<13126>>tex2html_deferred<<13126>>\bf\end<<13127>>tex2html_deferred<<13127>>x<<2809>><<6655>>\left(\frac<<2810>>1<<2810>><<2811>>2<<2811>><<2812>>\begin<<13128>>tex2html_deferred<<13128>>\bf\end<<13129>>tex2html_deferred<<13129>>x<<2812>>^T<<2813>>\begin<<13130>>tex2html_deferred<<13130>>\bf\end<<13131>>tex2html_deferred<<13131>>A<<2813>><<2814>>\begin<<13132>>tex2html_deferred<<13132>>\bf\end<<13133>>tex2html_deferred<<13133>>x<<2814>>
  -<<2815>>\begin<<13134>>tex2html_deferred<<13134>>\bf\end<<13135>>tex2html_deferred<<13135>>b<<2815>>^T<<2816>>\begin<<13136>>tex2html_deferred<<13136>>\bf\end<<13137>>tex2html_deferred<<13137>>x<<2816>>+c\right)  =<<2817>>\begin<<13138>>tex2html_deferred<<13138>>\bf\end<<13139>>tex2html_deferred<<13139>>A<<2817>><<2818>>\begin<<13140>>tex2html_deferred<<13140>>\bf\end<<13141>>tex2html_deferred<<13141>>x<<2818>>-<<2819>>\begin<<13142>>tex2html_deferred<<13142>>\bf\end<<13143>>tex2html_deferred<<13143>>b<<2819>>
\end<<2820>>equation<<2820>>
and 
\begin<<2821>>equation<<2821>>
  <<2822>>\begin<<13144>>tex2html_deferred<<13144>>\bf\end<<13145>>tex2html_deferred<<13145>>H<<2822>>(<<2823>>\begin<<13146>>tex2html_deferred<<13146>>\bf\end<<13147>>tex2html_deferred<<13147>>x<<2823>>)=\frac<<2824>>d^2<<2824>><<6656>>d<<2825>>\begin<<13148>>tex2html_deferred<<13148>>\bf\end<<13149>>tex2html_deferred<<13149>>x<<2825>>^2<<6656>>f(<<2826>>\begin<<13150>>tex2html_deferred<<13150>>\bf\end<<13151>>tex2html_deferred<<13151>>x<<2826>>)=\frac<<2827>>d<<2827>><<6657>>d<<2828>>\begin<<13152>>tex2html_deferred<<13152>>\bf\end<<13153>>tex2html_deferred<<13153>>x<<2828>><<6657>><<2829>>\begin<<13154>>tex2html_deferred<<13154>>\bf\end<<13155>>tex2html_deferred<<13155>>g<<2829>>
  =\frac<<2830>>d<<2830>><<6658>>d<<2831>>\begin<<13156>>tex2html_deferred<<13156>>\bf\end<<13157>>tex2html_deferred<<13157>>x<<2831>><<6658>>(<<2832>>\begin<<13158>>tex2html_deferred<<13158>>\bf\end<<13159>>tex2html_deferred<<13159>>Ax<<2832>>-<<2833>>\begin<<13160>>tex2html_deferred<<13160>>\bf\end<<13161>>tex2html_deferred<<13161>>b<<2833>>)=<<2834>>\begin<<13162>>tex2html_deferred<<13162>>\bf\end<<13163>>tex2html_deferred<<13163>>A<<2834>>
\end<<2835>>equation<<2835>>
We further assume the Hessian matrix is positive definite, so that \begin<<7886>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7886>>$f(<<2836>>\begin<<13164>>tex2html_deferred<<13164>>\bf\end<<13165>>tex2html_deferred<<13165>>x<<2836>>)$\end<<7887>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7887>> 
has a minimum. 
\begin<<13166>>tex2html_deferred<<13166>>\par\end<<13167>>tex2html_deferred<<13167>>
Solving \begin<<7888>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7888>>$<<2837>>\begin<<13168>>tex2html_deferred<<13168>>\bf\end<<13169>>tex2html_deferred<<13169>>g<<2837>>(<<2838>>\begin<<13170>>tex2html_deferred<<13170>>\bf\end<<13171>>tex2html_deferred<<13171>>x<<2838>>)=<<2839>>\begin<<13172>>tex2html_deferred<<13172>>\bf\end<<13173>>tex2html_deferred<<13173>>A<<2839>><<2840>>\begin<<13174>>tex2html_deferred<<13174>>\bf\end<<13175>>tex2html_deferred<<13175>>x<<2840>>-<<2841>>\begin<<13176>>tex2html_deferred<<13176>>\bf\end<<13177>>tex2html_deferred<<13177>>b<<2841>>=<<2842>>\begin<<13178>>tex2html_deferred<<13178>>\bf\end<<13179>>tex2html_deferred<<13179>>0<<2842>>$\end<<7889>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7889>>, we get the
solution \begin<<7890>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7890>>$<<2843>>\begin<<13180>>tex2html_deferred<<13180>>\bf\end<<13181>>tex2html_deferred<<13181>>x<<2843>>^*=<<2844>>\begin<<13182>>tex2html_deferred<<13182>>\bf\end<<13183>>tex2html_deferred<<13183>>A<<2844>>^<<2845>>-1<<2845>><<2846>>\begin<<13184>>tex2html_deferred<<13184>>\bf\end<<13185>>tex2html_deferred<<13185>>b<<2846>>$\end<<7891>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7891>>, at which the function is minimized 
to 
\begin<<2847>>equation<<2847>>
  f(<<2848>>\begin<<13186>>tex2html_deferred<<13186>>\bf\end<<13187>>tex2html_deferred<<13187>>x<<2848>>^*)=\frac<<2849>>1<<2849>><<2850>>2<<2850>>(<<2851>>\begin<<13188>>tex2html_deferred<<13188>>\bf\end<<13189>>tex2html_deferred<<13189>>A<<2851>>^<<2852>>-1<<2852>><<2853>>\begin<<13190>>tex2html_deferred<<13190>>\bf\end<<13191>>tex2html_deferred<<13191>>b<<2853>>)^T<<2854>>\begin<<13192>>tex2html_deferred<<13192>>\bf\end<<13193>>tex2html_deferred<<13193>>A<<2854>>(<<2855>>\begin<<13194>>tex2html_deferred<<13194>>\bf\end<<13195>>tex2html_deferred<<13195>>A<<2855>>^<<2856>>-1<<2856>><<2857>>\begin<<13196>>tex2html_deferred<<13196>>\bf\end<<13197>>tex2html_deferred<<13197>>b<<2857>>)
  -<<2858>>\begin<<13198>>tex2html_deferred<<13198>>\bf\end<<13199>>tex2html_deferred<<13199>>b<<2858>>^T(<<2859>>\begin<<13200>>tex2html_deferred<<13200>>\bf\end<<13201>>tex2html_deferred<<13201>>A<<2859>>^<<2860>>-1<<2860>><<2861>>\begin<<13202>>tex2html_deferred<<13202>>\bf\end<<13203>>tex2html_deferred<<13203>>b<<2861>>)+c=-\frac<<2862>>1<<2862>><<2863>>2<<2863>><<2864>>\begin<<13204>>tex2html_deferred<<13204>>\bf\end<<13205>>tex2html_deferred<<13205>>b<<2864>>^T<<2865>>\begin<<13206>>tex2html_deferred<<13206>>\bf\end<<13207>>tex2html_deferred<<13207>>A<<2865>>^<<2866>>-1<<2866>><<2867>>\begin<<13208>>tex2html_deferred<<13208>>\bf\end<<13209>>tex2html_deferred<<13209>>b<<2867>>+c
\end<<2868>>equation<<2868>>
\begin<<13210>>tex2html_deferred<<13210>>\par\end<<13211>>tex2html_deferred<<13211>>
At the solution \begin<<7892>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7892>>$<<2869>>\begin<<13212>>tex2html_deferred<<13212>>\bf\end<<13213>>tex2html_deferred<<13213>>x<<2869>>^*$\end<<7893>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7893>>\space that minimizes \begin<<7894>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7894>>$f(<<2870>>\begin<<13214>>tex2html_deferred<<13214>>\bf\end<<13215>>tex2html_deferred<<13215>>x<<2870>>)$\end<<7895>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7895>>, its gradient
\begin<<7896>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7896>>$<<2871>>\begin<<13216>>tex2html_deferred<<13216>>\bf\end<<13217>>tex2html_deferred<<13217>>g<<2871>>(<<2872>>\begin<<13218>>tex2html_deferred<<13218>>\bf\end<<13219>>tex2html_deferred<<13219>>x<<2872>>^*)=<<2873>>\begin<<13220>>tex2html_deferred<<13220>>\bf\end<<13221>>tex2html_deferred<<13221>>A<<2873>><<2874>>\begin<<13222>>tex2html_deferred<<13222>>\bf\end<<13223>>tex2html_deferred<<13223>>x<<2874>>^*-<<2875>>\begin<<13224>>tex2html_deferred<<13224>>\bf\end<<13225>>tex2html_deferred<<13225>>b<<2875>>=<<2876>>\begin<<13226>>tex2html_deferred<<13226>>\bf\end<<13227>>tex2html_deferred<<13227>>0<<2876>>$\end<<7897>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7897>>. At the nth estimate 
\begin<<7898>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7898>>$<<2877>>\begin<<13228>>tex2html_deferred<<13228>>\bf\end<<13229>>tex2html_deferred<<13229>>x<<2877>>_n$\end<<7899>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7899>>\space the gradient \begin<<7900>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7900>>$<<2878>>\begin<<13230>>tex2html_deferred<<13230>>\bf\end<<13231>>tex2html_deferred<<13231>>g<<2878>>_n=<<2879>>\begin<<13232>>tex2html_deferred<<13232>>\bf\end<<13233>>tex2html_deferred<<13233>>g<<2879>>(<<2880>>\begin<<13234>>tex2html_deferred<<13234>>\bf\end<<13235>>tex2html_deferred<<13235>>x<<2880>>_n)$\end<<7901>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7901>>\space can be considered 
as the residual of the nth iteration, and \begin<<7902>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7902>>$\varepsilon=||<<2881>>\begin<<13236>>tex2html_deferred<<13236>>\bf\end<<13237>>tex2html_deferred<<13237>>g<<2881>>_n||^2$\end<<7903>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7903>>\space can 
be used as an error measurement representing how close \begin<<7904>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7904>>$<<2882>>\begin<<13238>>tex2html_deferred<<13238>>\bf\end<<13239>>tex2html_deferred<<13239>>x<<2882>>_n$\end<<7905>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7905>>\space is to 
the true solution \begin<<7906>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7906>>$<<2883>>\begin<<13240>>tex2html_deferred<<13240>>\bf\end<<13241>>tex2html_deferred<<13241>>x<<2883>>^*$\end<<7907>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7907>>. 
\begin<<13242>>tex2html_deferred<<13242>>\par\end<<13243>>tex2html_deferred<<13243>>
We also see that the minimization of the quadratic function \begin<<7908>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7908>>$f(<<2884>>\begin<<13244>>tex2html_deferred<<13244>>\bf\end<<13245>>tex2html_deferred<<13245>>x<<2884>>)$\end<<7909>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7909>> 
is equivalent to solving a linear equation \begin<<7910>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7910>>$<<2885>>\begin<<13246>>tex2html_deferred<<13246>>\bf\end<<13247>>tex2html_deferred<<13247>>A<<2885>><<2886>>\begin<<13248>>tex2html_deferred<<13248>>\bf\end<<13249>>tex2html_deferred<<13249>>x<<2886>>=<<2887>>\begin<<13250>>tex2html_deferred<<13250>>\bf\end<<13251>>tex2html_deferred<<13251>>b<<2887>>$\end<<7911>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7911>>\space with 
a symmetric positive definite coefficient matrix \begin<<7912>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7912>>$<<2888>>\begin<<13252>>tex2html_deferred<<13252>>\bf\end<<13253>>tex2html_deferred<<13253>>A<<2888>>$\end<<7913>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7913>>. The CG method 
considered here can therefore be used for solving both problems. 
\begin<<13254>>tex2html_deferred<<13254>>\par\end<<13255>>tex2html_deferred<<13255>>
<<2889>>\begin<<13256>>tex2html_deferred<<13256>>\bf\end<<13257>>tex2html_deferred<<13257>>Conjugate basis vectors<<2889>>
\begin<<13258>>tex2html_deferred<<13258>>\par\end<<13259>>tex2html_deferred<<13259>>
Before continuing to discuss the CG algorithm, we first review the concept of 
\htmladdnormallink<<2890>>conjugate vectors<<2890>><<2891>>http://fourier.eng.hmc.edu/e176/lectures/algebra/node2.html<<2891>>,
which is the key to the CG method. Two vectors \begin<<7914>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7914>>$<<2892>>\begin<<13260>>tex2html_deferred<<13260>>\bf\end<<13261>>tex2html_deferred<<13261>>u<<2892>>$\end<<7915>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7915>>\space and \begin<<7916>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7916>>$<<2893>>\begin<<13262>>tex2html_deferred<<13262>>\bf\end<<13263>>tex2html_deferred<<13263>>v<<2893>>$\end<<7917>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7917>>\space are
<<2894>>\begin<<13264>>tex2html_deferred<<13264>>\em\end<<13265>>tex2html_deferred<<13265>>mutually conjugate<<2894>> (or A-orthogonal or A-conjugate) to each other 
with respect to a symmetric matrix \begin<<7918>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7918>>$<<2895>>\begin<<13266>>tex2html_deferred<<13266>>\bf\end<<13267>>tex2html_deferred<<13267>>A<<2895>>=<<2896>>\begin<<13268>>tex2html_deferred<<13268>>\bf\end<<13269>>tex2html_deferred<<13269>>A<<2896>>^T$\end<<7919>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7919>>, if they satisfy:
\begin<<2897>>equation<<2897>>
  <<2898>>\begin<<13270>>tex2html_deferred<<13270>>\bf\end<<13271>>tex2html_deferred<<13271>>u<<2898>>^T<<2899>>\begin<<13272>>tex2html_deferred<<13272>>\bf\end<<13273>>tex2html_deferred<<13273>>A<<2899>><<2900>>\begin<<13274>>tex2html_deferred<<13274>>\bf\end<<13275>>tex2html_deferred<<13275>>v<<2900>>=(<<2901>>\begin<<13276>>tex2html_deferred<<13276>>\bf\end<<13277>>tex2html_deferred<<13277>>A<<2901>><<2902>>\begin<<13278>>tex2html_deferred<<13278>>\bf\end<<13279>>tex2html_deferred<<13279>>v<<2902>>)^T<<2903>>\begin<<13280>>tex2html_deferred<<13280>>\bf\end<<13281>>tex2html_deferred<<13281>>u<<2903>>
  =<<2904>>\begin<<13282>>tex2html_deferred<<13282>>\bf\end<<13283>>tex2html_deferred<<13283>>v<<2904>>^T<<2905>>\begin<<13284>>tex2html_deferred<<13284>>\bf\end<<13285>>tex2html_deferred<<13285>>A<<2905>><<2906>>\begin<<13286>>tex2html_deferred<<13286>>\bf\end<<13287>>tex2html_deferred<<13287>>u<<2906>>=0
\end<<2907>>equation<<2907>>
Specially, if \begin<<7920>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7920>>$<<2908>>\begin<<13288>>tex2html_deferred<<13288>>\bf\end<<13289>>tex2html_deferred<<13289>>A<<2908>>=<<2909>>\begin<<13290>>tex2html_deferred<<13290>>\bf\end<<13291>>tex2html_deferred<<13291>>I<<2909>>$\end<<7921>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7921>>, the two conjugate vectors become orthogonal 
to each other, i.e., \begin<<7922>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7922>>$<<2910>>\begin<<13292>>tex2html_deferred<<13292>>\bf\end<<13293>>tex2html_deferred<<13293>>v<<2910>>^T<<2911>>\begin<<13294>>tex2html_deferred<<13294>>\bf\end<<13295>>tex2html_deferred<<13295>>u<<2911>>=0$\end<<7923>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7923>>.
\begin<<13296>>tex2html_deferred<<13296>>\par\end<<13297>>tex2html_deferred<<13297>>
Similar to a set of \begin<<7924>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7924>>$N$\end<<7925>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7925>>\space orthogonal vectors that can be used as the basis 
spanning an N-D space, a set of \begin<<7926>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7926>>$N$\end<<7927>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7927>>\space mutually conjugate vectors 
\begin<<7928>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7928>>$\{<<2912>>\begin<<13298>>tex2html_deferred<<13298>>\bf\end<<13299>>tex2html_deferred<<13299>>d<<2912>>_0,\cdots,<<2913>>\begin<<13300>>tex2html_deferred<<13300>>\bf\end<<13301>>tex2html_deferred<<13301>>d<<2913>>_<<2914>>N-1<<2914>>\}$\end<<7929>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7929>>\space satisfying \begin<<7930>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7930>>$<<2915>>\begin<<13302>>tex2html_deferred<<13302>>\bf\end<<13303>>tex2html_deferred<<13303>>d<<2915>>_i^T<<2916>>\begin<<13304>>tex2html_deferred<<13304>>\bf\end<<13305>>tex2html_deferred<<13305>>A<<2916>><<2917>>\begin<<13306>>tex2html_deferred<<13306>>\bf\end<<13307>>tex2html_deferred<<13307>>d<<2917>>_j=0$\end<<7931>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7931>>
(\begin<<7932>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7932>>$i\ne j$\end<<7933>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7933>>) can also be used as a basis to span the N-D space. Any vector in 
the space can be expressed as a linear combination of these basis vectors.
\begin<<13308>>tex2html_deferred<<13308>>\par\end<<13309>>tex2html_deferred<<13309>>
Also we note that any set of \begin<<7934>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7934>>$N$\end<<7935>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7935>>\space independent vectors can be converted by the
\htmladdnormallink<<2918>>Gram-Schmidt process<<2918>><<2919>>http://fourier.eng.hmc.edu/e176/lectures/algebra/node2.html<<2919>> 
to a set of \begin<<7936>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7936>>$N$\end<<7937>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7937>>\space basis vectors that are either orthogonal or A-orthogonal.
\begin<<13310>>tex2html_deferred<<13310>>\par\end<<13311>>tex2html_deferred<<13311>>
<<2920>>\begin<<13312>>tex2html_deferred<<13312>>\bf\end<<13313>>tex2html_deferred<<13313>>Example:<<2920>>  Given two independent basis vectors of the 2-D space, and
a positive-definite matrix:
\begin<<2921>>equation<<2921>>
  <<2922>>\begin<<13314>>tex2html_deferred<<13314>>\bf\end<<13315>>tex2html_deferred<<13315>>v<<2922>>_1=\left[\begin<<2923>>array<<2923>><<2924>>r<<2924>>1\\ 0\end<<2925>>array<<2925>>\right],\;\;\;\;\;
  <<2926>>\begin<<13316>>tex2html_deferred<<13316>>\bf\end<<13317>>tex2html_deferred<<13317>>v<<2926>>_2=\left[\begin<<2927>>array<<2927>><<2928>>r<<2928>>0\\ 1\end<<2929>>array<<2929>>\right],\;\;\;\;\;
  <<2930>>\begin<<13318>>tex2html_deferred<<13318>>\bf\end<<13319>>tex2html_deferred<<13319>>A<<2930>>=\left[\begin<<2931>>array<<2931>><<2932>>rr<<2932>>3;SPMamp;1\\ 1;SPMamp;2\end<<2933>>array<<2933>>\right]
  \nonumber
\end<<2934>>equation<<2934>>
we can construct two A-orthogonal basis vectors by the Gram-Schmidt method:
\begin<<2935>>equation<<2935>>
  <<2936>>\begin<<13320>>tex2html_deferred<<13320>>\bf\end<<13321>>tex2html_deferred<<13321>>u<<2936>>_1=<<2937>>\begin<<13322>>tex2html_deferred<<13322>>\bf\end<<13323>>tex2html_deferred<<13323>>v<<2937>>_1=\left[\begin<<2938>>array<<2938>><<2939>>r<<2939>>1\\ 0\end<<2940>>array<<2940>>\right],
  \;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;
  <<2941>>\begin<<13324>>tex2html_deferred<<13324>>\bf\end<<13325>>tex2html_deferred<<13325>>u<<2941>>_2=<<2942>>\begin<<13326>>tex2html_deferred<<13326>>\bf\end<<13327>>tex2html_deferred<<13327>>v<<2942>>_2-\frac<<6659>><<2943>>\begin<<13328>>tex2html_deferred<<13328>>\bf\end<<13329>>tex2html_deferred<<13329>>u<<2943>>_1^T<<2944>>\begin<<13330>>tex2html_deferred<<13330>>\bf\end<<13331>>tex2html_deferred<<13331>>A<<2944>><<2945>>\begin<<13332>>tex2html_deferred<<13332>>\bf\end<<13333>>tex2html_deferred<<13333>>v<<2945>>_2<<6659>><<6660>><<2946>>\begin<<13334>>tex2html_deferred<<13334>>\bf\end<<13335>>tex2html_deferred<<13335>>u<<2946>>_1^T<<2947>>\begin<<13336>>tex2html_deferred<<13336>>\bf\end<<13337>>tex2html_deferred<<13337>>A<<2947>><<2948>>\begin<<13338>>tex2html_deferred<<13338>>\bf\end<<13339>>tex2html_deferred<<13339>>u<<2948>>_1<<6660>><<2949>>\begin<<13340>>tex2html_deferred<<13340>>\bf\end<<13341>>tex2html_deferred<<13341>>u<<2949>>_1
  =\left[\begin<<2950>>array<<2950>><<2951>>c<<2951>>-1/3\\ 1\end<<2952>>array<<2952>>\right]
  \nonumber
\end<<2953>>equation<<2953>>
The projections of a vector \begin<<7938>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7938>>$<<2954>>\begin<<13342>>tex2html_deferred<<13342>>\bf\end<<13343>>tex2html_deferred<<13343>>x<<2954>>=[2,\;3]^T$\end<<7939>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7939>>\space onto \begin<<7940>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7940>>$<<2955>>\begin<<13344>>tex2html_deferred<<13344>>\bf\end<<13345>>tex2html_deferred<<13345>>v<<2955>>_1$\end<<7941>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7941>>\space and \begin<<7942>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7942>>$<<2956>>\begin<<13346>>tex2html_deferred<<13346>>\bf\end<<13347>>tex2html_deferred<<13347>>v<<2956>>_2$\end<<7943>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7943>> 
are:
\begin<<2957>>equation<<2957>>
  <<2958>>\begin<<13348>>tex2html_deferred<<13348>>\bf\end<<13349>>tex2html_deferred<<13349>>p<<2958>>_<<6661>><<2959>>\begin<<13350>>tex2html_deferred<<13350>>\bf\end<<13351>>tex2html_deferred<<13351>>v<<2959>>_1<<6661>>(<<2960>>\begin<<13352>>tex2html_deferred<<13352>>\bf\end<<13353>>tex2html_deferred<<13353>>x<<2960>>)=\frac<<6662>><<2961>>\begin<<13354>>tex2html_deferred<<13354>>\bf\end<<13355>>tex2html_deferred<<13355>>v<<2961>>_1^T<<2962>>\begin<<13356>>tex2html_deferred<<13356>>\bf\end<<13357>>tex2html_deferred<<13357>>x<<2962>><<6662>><<6663>><<2963>>\begin<<13358>>tex2html_deferred<<13358>>\bf\end<<13359>>tex2html_deferred<<13359>>v<<2963>>_1^T<<2964>>\begin<<13360>>tex2html_deferred<<13360>>\bf\end<<13361>>tex2html_deferred<<13361>>v<<2964>>_1<<6663>><<2965>>\begin<<13362>>tex2html_deferred<<13362>>\bf\end<<13363>>tex2html_deferred<<13363>>v<<2965>>_1
  =2\left[\begin<<2966>>array<<2966>><<2967>>c<<2967>>1\\ 0\end<<2968>>array<<2968>>\right]
  =\left[\begin<<2969>>array<<2969>><<2970>>c<<2970>>2\\ 0\end<<2971>>array<<2971>>\right],\;\;\;\;\;
  <<2972>>\begin<<13364>>tex2html_deferred<<13364>>\bf\end<<13365>>tex2html_deferred<<13365>>p<<2972>>_<<6664>><<2973>>\begin<<13366>>tex2html_deferred<<13366>>\bf\end<<13367>>tex2html_deferred<<13367>>v<<2973>>_2<<6664>>(<<2974>>\begin<<13368>>tex2html_deferred<<13368>>\bf\end<<13369>>tex2html_deferred<<13369>>x<<2974>>)=\frac<<6665>><<2975>>\begin<<13370>>tex2html_deferred<<13370>>\bf\end<<13371>>tex2html_deferred<<13371>>v<<2975>>_2^T<<2976>>\begin<<13372>>tex2html_deferred<<13372>>\bf\end<<13373>>tex2html_deferred<<13373>>x<<2976>><<6665>><<6666>><<2977>>\begin<<13374>>tex2html_deferred<<13374>>\bf\end<<13375>>tex2html_deferred<<13375>>v<<2977>>_2^T<<2978>>\begin<<13376>>tex2html_deferred<<13376>>\bf\end<<13377>>tex2html_deferred<<13377>>v<<2978>>_2<<6666>><<2979>>\begin<<13378>>tex2html_deferred<<13378>>\bf\end<<13379>>tex2html_deferred<<13379>>v<<2979>>_2
  =3\left[\begin<<2980>>array<<2980>><<2981>>c<<2981>>0\\ 1\end<<2982>>array<<2982>>\right]
  =\left[\begin<<2983>>array<<2983>><<2984>>c<<2984>>0\\ 3\end<<2985>>array<<2985>>\right]
  \nonumber
\end<<2986>>equation<<2986>>
The A-projections of the same vector \begin<<7944>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7944>>$<<2987>>\begin<<13380>>tex2html_deferred<<13380>>\bf\end<<13381>>tex2html_deferred<<13381>>x<<2987>>$\end<<7945>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7945>>\space onto \begin<<7946>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7946>>$<<2988>>\begin<<13382>>tex2html_deferred<<13382>>\bf\end<<13383>>tex2html_deferred<<13383>>u<<2988>>_1$\end<<7947>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7947>>\space and \begin<<7948>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7948>>$<<2989>>\begin<<13384>>tex2html_deferred<<13384>>\bf\end<<13385>>tex2html_deferred<<13385>>u<<2989>>_2$\end<<7949>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7949>>
are:
\begin<<2990>>equation<<2990>>
  <<2991>>\begin<<13386>>tex2html_deferred<<13386>>\bf\end<<13387>>tex2html_deferred<<13387>>p<<2991>>_<<6667>><<2992>>\begin<<13388>>tex2html_deferred<<13388>>\bf\end<<13389>>tex2html_deferred<<13389>>u<<2992>>_1<<6667>>(<<2993>>\begin<<13390>>tex2html_deferred<<13390>>\bf\end<<13391>>tex2html_deferred<<13391>>x<<2993>>)=\frac<<6668>><<2994>>\begin<<13392>>tex2html_deferred<<13392>>\bf\end<<13393>>tex2html_deferred<<13393>>u<<2994>>_1^T<<2995>>\begin<<13394>>tex2html_deferred<<13394>>\bf\end<<13395>>tex2html_deferred<<13395>>A<<2995>><<2996>>\begin<<13396>>tex2html_deferred<<13396>>\bf\end<<13397>>tex2html_deferred<<13397>>x<<2996>><<6668>>
  <<6669>><<2997>>\begin<<13398>>tex2html_deferred<<13398>>\bf\end<<13399>>tex2html_deferred<<13399>>u<<2997>>_1^T<<2998>>\begin<<13400>>tex2html_deferred<<13400>>\bf\end<<13401>>tex2html_deferred<<13401>>A<<2998>><<2999>>\begin<<13402>>tex2html_deferred<<13402>>\bf\end<<13403>>tex2html_deferred<<13403>>u<<2999>>_1<<6669>><<3000>>\begin<<13404>>tex2html_deferred<<13404>>\bf\end<<13405>>tex2html_deferred<<13405>>u<<3000>>_1
  =3\left[\begin<<3001>>array<<3001>><<3002>>c<<3002>>1\\ 0\end<<3003>>array<<3003>>\right]
  =\left[\begin<<3004>>array<<3004>><<3005>>c<<3005>>3\\ 0\end<<3006>>array<<3006>>\right],
  \;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;
  <<3007>>\begin<<13406>>tex2html_deferred<<13406>>\bf\end<<13407>>tex2html_deferred<<13407>>p<<3007>>_<<6670>><<3008>>\begin<<13408>>tex2html_deferred<<13408>>\bf\end<<13409>>tex2html_deferred<<13409>>u<<3008>>_2<<6670>>(<<3009>>\begin<<13410>>tex2html_deferred<<13410>>\bf\end<<13411>>tex2html_deferred<<13411>>x<<3009>>)=\frac<<6671>><<3010>>\begin<<13412>>tex2html_deferred<<13412>>\bf\end<<13413>>tex2html_deferred<<13413>>u<<3010>>_2^T<<3011>>\begin<<13414>>tex2html_deferred<<13414>>\bf\end<<13415>>tex2html_deferred<<13415>>A<<3011>><<3012>>\begin<<13416>>tex2html_deferred<<13416>>\bf\end<<13417>>tex2html_deferred<<13417>>x<<3012>><<6671>>
  <<6672>><<3013>>\begin<<13418>>tex2html_deferred<<13418>>\bf\end<<13419>>tex2html_deferred<<13419>>u<<3013>>_2^T<<3014>>\begin<<13420>>tex2html_deferred<<13420>>\bf\end<<13421>>tex2html_deferred<<13421>>A<<3014>><<3015>>\begin<<13422>>tex2html_deferred<<13422>>\bf\end<<13423>>tex2html_deferred<<13423>>u<<3015>>_2<<6672>><<3016>>\begin<<13424>>tex2html_deferred<<13424>>\bf\end<<13425>>tex2html_deferred<<13425>>u<<3016>>_2
  =3\left[\begin<<3017>>array<<3017>><<3018>>c<<3018>>-1/3\\ 1\end<<3019>>array<<3019>>\right]
  =\left[\begin<<3020>>array<<3020>><<3021>>c<<3021>>-1\\ 3\end<<3022>>array<<3022>>\right]
  \nonumber
\end<<3023>>equation<<3023>>
The original vector \begin<<7950>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7950>>$<<3024>>\begin<<13426>>tex2html_deferred<<13426>>\bf\end<<13427>>tex2html_deferred<<13427>>x<<3024>>$\end<<7951>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7951>>\space can be represented in either of the two bases:
\begin<<3025>>eqnarray<<3025>>
  <<3026>>\begin<<13428>>tex2html_deferred<<13428>>\bf\end<<13429>>tex2html_deferred<<13429>>x<<3026>>=\left[\begin<<3027>>array<<3027>><<3028>>c<<3028>>2\\ 3\end<<3029>>array<<3029>>\right]
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;2\left[\begin<<3030>>array<<3030>><<3031>>c<<3031>>1\\ 0\end<<3032>>array<<3032>>\right]
  +3\left[\begin<<3033>>array<<3033>><<3034>>c<<3034>>0\\ 1\end<<3035>>array<<3035>>\right]
  =2<<3036>>\begin<<13430>>tex2html_deferred<<13430>>\bf\end<<13431>>tex2html_deferred<<13431>>v<<3036>>_1+3<<3037>>\begin<<13432>>tex2html_deferred<<13432>>\bf\end<<13433>>tex2html_deferred<<13433>>v<<3037>>_2
  =<<3038>>\begin<<13434>>tex2html_deferred<<13434>>\bf\end<<13435>>tex2html_deferred<<13435>>p<<3038>>_<<6673>><<3039>>\begin<<13436>>tex2html_deferred<<13436>>\bf\end<<13437>>tex2html_deferred<<13437>>v<<3039>>_1<<6673>>(<<3040>>\begin<<13438>>tex2html_deferred<<13438>>\bf\end<<13439>>tex2html_deferred<<13439>>x<<3040>>)+<<3041>>\begin<<13440>>tex2html_deferred<<13440>>\bf\end<<13441>>tex2html_deferred<<13441>>p<<3041>>_<<6674>><<3042>>\begin<<13442>>tex2html_deferred<<13442>>\bf\end<<13443>>tex2html_deferred<<13443>>v<<3042>>_2<<6674>>(<<3043>>\begin<<13444>>tex2html_deferred<<13444>>\bf\end<<13445>>tex2html_deferred<<13445>>x<<3043>>)
  \nonumber \\ 
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;3\left[\begin<<3044>>array<<3044>><<3045>>c<<3045>>1\\ 0\end<<3046>>array<<3046>>\right]
  +3\left[\begin<<3047>>array<<3047>><<3048>>c<<3048>>-1/3\\ 1\end<<3049>>array<<3049>>\right]
  =3<<3050>>\begin<<13446>>tex2html_deferred<<13446>>\bf\end<<13447>>tex2html_deferred<<13447>>u<<3050>>_1+3<<3051>>\begin<<13448>>tex2html_deferred<<13448>>\bf\end<<13449>>tex2html_deferred<<13449>>u<<3051>>_2
  =<<3052>>\begin<<13450>>tex2html_deferred<<13450>>\bf\end<<13451>>tex2html_deferred<<13451>>p<<3052>>_<<6675>><<3053>>\begin<<13452>>tex2html_deferred<<13452>>\bf\end<<13453>>tex2html_deferred<<13453>>u<<3053>>_1<<6675>>(<<3054>>\begin<<13454>>tex2html_deferred<<13454>>\bf\end<<13455>>tex2html_deferred<<13455>>x<<3054>>)+<<3055>>\begin<<13456>>tex2html_deferred<<13456>>\bf\end<<13457>>tex2html_deferred<<13457>>p<<3055>>_<<6676>><<3056>>\begin<<13458>>tex2html_deferred<<13458>>\bf\end<<13459>>tex2html_deferred<<13459>>u<<3056>>_2<<6676>>(<<3057>>\begin<<13460>>tex2html_deferred<<13460>>\bf\end<<13461>>tex2html_deferred<<13461>>x<<3057>>)
  \nonumber 
\end<<3058>>eqnarray<<3058>>
\begin<<13462>>tex2html_deferred<<13462>>\par\end<<13463>>tex2html_deferred<<13463>>
\htmladdimg<<3059>>figures/Aorthogonal.png<<3059>>
\begin<<13464>>tex2html_deferred<<13464>>\par\end<<13465>>tex2html_deferred<<13465>>
<<3060>>\begin<<13466>>tex2html_deferred<<13466>>\bf\end<<13467>>tex2html_deferred<<13467>>Search along a conjugate basis<<3060>>
\begin<<13468>>tex2html_deferred<<13468>>\par\end<<13469>>tex2html_deferred<<13469>>
Similar to the gradient descent method, which iteratively improves 
the estimated solution by following a sequence of orthogonal search 
directions \begin<<7952>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7952>>$\{ -<<3061>>\begin<<13470>>tex2html_deferred<<13470>>\bf\end<<13471>>tex2html_deferred<<13471>>g<<3061>>_0,\cdots,-<<3062>>\begin<<13472>>tex2html_deferred<<13472>>\bf\end<<13473>>tex2html_deferred<<13473>>g<<3062>>_n,\cdots\}$\end<<7953>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7953>>, the CG method
also follows a sequence of search directions \begin<<7954>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7954>>$\{<<3063>>\begin<<13474>>tex2html_deferred<<13474>>\bf\end<<13475>>tex2html_deferred<<13475>>d<<3063>>_0,\cdots,
<<3064>>\begin<<13476>>tex2html_deferred<<13476>>\bf\end<<13477>>tex2html_deferred<<13477>>d<<3064>>_<<3065>>N-1<<3065>>\}$\end<<7955>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7955>>\space A-orthogonal to each other, i.e., 
\begin<<7956>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7956>>$<<3066>>\begin<<13478>>tex2html_deferred<<13478>>\bf\end<<13479>>tex2html_deferred<<13479>>d<<3066>>_i^T<<3067>>\begin<<13480>>tex2html_deferred<<13480>>\bf\end<<13481>>tex2html_deferred<<13481>>Ad<<3067>>_j=0\;(i\ne j)$\end<<7957>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7957>>:
\begin<<3068>>equation<<3068>>
  <<3069>>\begin<<13482>>tex2html_deferred<<13482>>\bf\end<<13483>>tex2html_deferred<<13483>>x<<3069>>_<<3070>>n+1<<3070>>=<<3071>>\begin<<13484>>tex2html_deferred<<13484>>\bf\end<<13485>>tex2html_deferred<<13485>>x<<3071>>_n+\delta_n<<3072>>\begin<<13486>>tex2html_deferred<<13486>>\bf\end<<13487>>tex2html_deferred<<13487>>d<<3072>>_n
  =\cdots =<<3073>>\begin<<13488>>tex2html_deferred<<13488>>\bf\end<<13489>>tex2html_deferred<<13489>>x<<3073>>_0+\sum_<<3074>>i=0<<3074>>^n \delta_i<<3075>>\begin<<13490>>tex2html_deferred<<13490>>\bf\end<<13491>>tex2html_deferred<<13491>>d<<3075>>_i
  \label<<3076>>CGiteration<<3076>>
\end<<3077>>equation<<3077>>
Subtracting \begin<<7958>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7958>>$<<3078>>\begin<<13492>>tex2html_deferred<<13492>>\bf\end<<13493>>tex2html_deferred<<13493>>x<<3078>>^*=<<3079>>\begin<<13494>>tex2html_deferred<<13494>>\bf\end<<13495>>tex2html_deferred<<13495>>x<<3079>>_<<3080>>n+1<<3080>>-<<3081>>\begin<<13496>>tex2html_deferred<<13496>>\bf\end<<13497>>tex2html_deferred<<13497>>e<<3081>>_<<3082>>n+1<<3082>>=<<3083>>\begin<<13498>>tex2html_deferred<<13498>>\bf\end<<13499>>tex2html_deferred<<13499>>x<<3083>>_n-<<3084>>\begin<<13500>>tex2html_deferred<<13500>>\bf\end<<13501>>tex2html_deferred<<13501>>e<<3084>>_n$\end<<7959>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7959>>
from both sides, we get the iteration in terms of the errors:
\begin<<3085>>equation<<3085>>
  <<3086>>\begin<<13502>>tex2html_deferred<<13502>>\bf\end<<13503>>tex2html_deferred<<13503>>e<<3086>>_<<3087>>n+1<<3087>>=<<3088>>\begin<<13504>>tex2html_deferred<<13504>>\bf\end<<13505>>tex2html_deferred<<13505>>e<<3088>>_n+\delta_n<<3089>>\begin<<13506>>tex2html_deferred<<13506>>\bf\end<<13507>>tex2html_deferred<<13507>>d<<3089>>_n
  =\cdots=<<3090>>\begin<<13508>>tex2html_deferred<<13508>>\bf\end<<13509>>tex2html_deferred<<13509>>e<<3090>>_0+\sum_<<3091>>i=0<<3091>>^n \delta_i<<3092>>\begin<<13510>>tex2html_deferred<<13510>>\bf\end<<13511>>tex2html_deferred<<13511>>d<<3092>>_i
  \label<<3093>>CGerror<<3093>>
\end<<3094>>equation<<3094>>
\begin<<13512>>tex2html_deferred<<13512>>\par\end<<13513>>tex2html_deferred<<13513>>
As it is assumed that the function to be minimized is quadratic 
\begin<<7960>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7960>>$f(<<3095>>\begin<<13514>>tex2html_deferred<<13514>>\bf\end<<13515>>tex2html_deferred<<13515>>x<<3095>>)=<<3096>>\begin<<13516>>tex2html_deferred<<13516>>\bf\end<<13517>>tex2html_deferred<<13517>>x<<3096>>^T<<3097>>\begin<<13518>>tex2html_deferred<<13518>>\bf\end<<13519>>tex2html_deferred<<13519>>Ax<<3097>>/2-<<3098>>\begin<<13520>>tex2html_deferred<<13520>>\bf\end<<13521>>tex2html_deferred<<13521>>b<<3098>>^T<<3099>>\begin<<13522>>tex2html_deferred<<13522>>\bf\end<<13523>>tex2html_deferred<<13523>>x<<3099>>+c$\end<<7961>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7961>>, its
gradient at \begin<<7962>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7962>>$<<3100>>\begin<<13524>>tex2html_deferred<<13524>>\bf\end<<13525>>tex2html_deferred<<13525>>x<<3100>>_i$\end<<7963>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7963>>\space is:
\begin<<3101>>equation<<3101>> 
  <<3102>>\begin<<13526>>tex2html_deferred<<13526>>\bf\end<<13527>>tex2html_deferred<<13527>>g<<3102>>_i=f'(<<3103>>\begin<<13528>>tex2html_deferred<<13528>>\bf\end<<13529>>tex2html_deferred<<13529>>x<<3103>>_i)
  =<<3104>>\begin<<13530>>tex2html_deferred<<13530>>\bf\end<<13531>>tex2html_deferred<<13531>>A<<3104>><<3105>>\begin<<13532>>tex2html_deferred<<13532>>\bf\end<<13533>>tex2html_deferred<<13533>>x<<3105>>_i-<<3106>>\begin<<13534>>tex2html_deferred<<13534>>\bf\end<<13535>>tex2html_deferred<<13535>>b<<3106>>=<<3107>>\begin<<13536>>tex2html_deferred<<13536>>\bf\end<<13537>>tex2html_deferred<<13537>>A<<3107>>(<<3108>>\begin<<13538>>tex2html_deferred<<13538>>\bf\end<<13539>>tex2html_deferred<<13539>>x<<3108>>^*+<<3109>>\begin<<13540>>tex2html_deferred<<13540>>\bf\end<<13541>>tex2html_deferred<<13541>>e<<3109>>_i)-<<3110>>\begin<<13542>>tex2html_deferred<<13542>>\bf\end<<13543>>tex2html_deferred<<13543>>b<<3110>>
  =<<3111>>\begin<<13544>>tex2html_deferred<<13544>>\bf\end<<13545>>tex2html_deferred<<13545>>A<<3111>><<3112>>\begin<<13546>>tex2html_deferred<<13546>>\bf\end<<13547>>tex2html_deferred<<13547>>x<<3112>>^*-<<3113>>\begin<<13548>>tex2html_deferred<<13548>>\bf\end<<13549>>tex2html_deferred<<13549>>b<<3113>>+<<3114>>\begin<<13550>>tex2html_deferred<<13550>>\bf\end<<13551>>tex2html_deferred<<13551>>A<<3114>><<3115>>\begin<<13552>>tex2html_deferred<<13552>>\bf\end<<13553>>tex2html_deferred<<13553>>e<<3115>>_i=<<3116>>\begin<<13554>>tex2html_deferred<<13554>>\bf\end<<13555>>tex2html_deferred<<13555>>A<<3116>><<3117>>\begin<<13556>>tex2html_deferred<<13556>>\bf\end<<13557>>tex2html_deferred<<13557>>e<<3117>>_i
\end<<3118>>equation<<3118>>
where \begin<<7964>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7964>>$<<3119>>\begin<<13558>>tex2html_deferred<<13558>>\bf\end<<13559>>tex2html_deferred<<13559>>x<<3119>>^*$\end<<7965>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7965>>\space is the solution satisfying
\begin<<7966>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7966>>$<<3120>>\begin<<13560>>tex2html_deferred<<13560>>\bf\end<<13561>>tex2html_deferred<<13561>>g<<3120>>(<<3121>>\begin<<13562>>tex2html_deferred<<13562>>\bf\end<<13563>>tex2html_deferred<<13563>>x<<3121>>^*)=<<3122>>\begin<<13564>>tex2html_deferred<<13564>>\bf\end<<13565>>tex2html_deferred<<13565>>A<<3122>><<3123>>\begin<<13566>>tex2html_deferred<<13566>>\bf\end<<13567>>tex2html_deferred<<13567>>x<<3123>>^*-<<3124>>\begin<<13568>>tex2html_deferred<<13568>>\bf\end<<13569>>tex2html_deferred<<13569>>b<<3124>>=<<3125>>\begin<<13570>>tex2html_deferred<<13570>>\bf\end<<13571>>tex2html_deferred<<13571>>0<<3125>>$\end<<7967>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<7967>>. The optimal 
step size in Eq. (\ref<<3126>>OptimalDelta<<3126>>) can be written as
\begin<<3127>>eqnarray<<3127>>
  \delta_i;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;-\frac<<6677>><<3128>>\begin<<13572>>tex2html_deferred<<13572>>\bf\end<<13573>>tex2html_deferred<<13573>>g<<3128>>_i^T<<3129>>\begin<<13574>>tex2html_deferred<<13574>>\bf\end<<13575>>tex2html_deferred<<13575>>d<<3129>>_i<<6677>><<6678>><<3130>>\begin<<13576>>tex2html_deferred<<13576>>\bf\end<<13577>>tex2html_deferred<<13577>>d<<3130>>_i^T<<3131>>\begin<<13578>>tex2html_deferred<<13578>>\bf\end<<13579>>tex2html_deferred<<13579>>A<<3131>><<3132>>\begin<<13580>>tex2html_deferred<<13580>>\bf\end<<13581>>tex2html_deferred<<13581>>d<<3132>>_i<<6678>>
