Pre-multiplying \begin<<8074>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8074>>$<<3473>>\begin<<14068>>tex2html_deferred<<14068>>\bf\end<<14069>>tex2html_deferred<<14069>>g<<3473>>_n^T$\end<<8075>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8075>>\space with \begin<<8076>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8076>>$n;SPMgt;m$\end<<8077>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8077>>\space on both sides we get
\begin<<3474>>equation<<3474>> 
  <<3475>>\begin<<14070>>tex2html_deferred<<14070>>\bf\end<<14071>>tex2html_deferred<<14071>>g<<3475>>_n^T<<3476>>\begin<<14072>>tex2html_deferred<<14072>>\bf\end<<14073>>tex2html_deferred<<14073>>g<<3476>>_<<3477>>m+1<<3477>>=<<3478>>\begin<<14074>>tex2html_deferred<<14074>>\bf\end<<14075>>tex2html_deferred<<14075>>g<<3478>>_n^T<<3479>>\begin<<14076>>tex2html_deferred<<14076>>\bf\end<<14077>>tex2html_deferred<<14077>>g<<3479>>_m+\delta_m<<3480>>\begin<<14078>>tex2html_deferred<<14078>>\bf\end<<14079>>tex2html_deferred<<14079>>g<<3480>>_n^T<<3481>>\begin<<14080>>tex2html_deferred<<14080>>\bf\end<<14081>>tex2html_deferred<<14081>>A<<3481>><<3482>>\begin<<14082>>tex2html_deferred<<14082>>\bf\end<<14083>>tex2html_deferred<<14083>>d<<3482>>_m 
  =\delta_m<<3483>>\begin<<14084>>tex2html_deferred<<14084>>\bf\end<<14085>>tex2html_deferred<<14085>>g<<3483>>_n^T<<3484>>\begin<<14086>>tex2html_deferred<<14086>>\bf\end<<14087>>tex2html_deferred<<14087>>A<<3484>><<3485>>\begin<<14088>>tex2html_deferred<<14088>>\bf\end<<14089>>tex2html_deferred<<14089>>d<<3485>>_m 
\end<<3486>>equation<<3486>>
where \begin<<8078>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8078>>$<<3487>>\begin<<14090>>tex2html_deferred<<14090>>\bf\end<<14091>>tex2html_deferred<<14091>>g<<3487>>_n^T<<3488>>\begin<<14092>>tex2html_deferred<<14092>>\bf\end<<14093>>tex2html_deferred<<14093>>g<<3488>>_m=0$\end<<8079>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8079>>\space (\begin<<8080>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8080>>$m\ne n$\end<<8081>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8081>>). Solving for \begin<<8082>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8082>>$<<3489>>\begin<<14094>>tex2html_deferred<<14094>>\bf\end<<14095>>tex2html_deferred<<14095>>g<<3489>>_n^T<<3490>>\begin<<14096>>tex2html_deferred<<14096>>\bf\end<<14097>>tex2html_deferred<<14097>>A<<3490>><<3491>>\begin<<14098>>tex2html_deferred<<14098>>\bf\end<<14099>>tex2html_deferred<<14099>>d<<3491>>_m$\end<<8083>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8083>> 
we get
\begin<<3492>>equation<<3492>> 
  <<3493>>\begin<<14100>>tex2html_deferred<<14100>>\bf\end<<14101>>tex2html_deferred<<14101>>g<<3493>>_n^T<<3494>>\begin<<14102>>tex2html_deferred<<14102>>\bf\end<<14103>>tex2html_deferred<<14103>>A<<3494>><<3495>>\begin<<14104>>tex2html_deferred<<14104>>\bf\end<<14105>>tex2html_deferred<<14105>>d<<3495>>_m
  =\frac<<3496>>1<<3496>><<3497>>\delta_m<<3497>> <<3498>>\begin<<14106>>tex2html_deferred<<14106>>\bf\end<<14107>>tex2html_deferred<<14107>>g<<3498>>_n^T<<3499>>\begin<<14108>>tex2html_deferred<<14108>>\bf\end<<14109>>tex2html_deferred<<14109>>g<<3499>>_<<3500>>m+1<<3500>>
  =\left\{\begin<<3501>>array<<3501>><<3502>>cl<<3502>>
  ||<<3503>>\begin<<14110>>tex2html_deferred<<14110>>\bf\end<<14111>>tex2html_deferred<<14111>>g<<3503>>_n||^2/\delta_<<3504>>n-1<<3504>>;SPMamp;m=n-1\\   0;SPMamp;m;SPMlt;n-1\end<<3505>>array<<3505>>\right.
\end<<3506>>equation<<3506>>
Substituting this into Eq. (\ref<<3507>>GSbeta<<3507>>) we get
\begin<<3508>>equation<<3508>>
  \beta_<<3509>>nm<<3509>>=-\frac<<6713>><<3510>>\begin<<14112>>tex2html_deferred<<14112>>\bf\end<<14113>>tex2html_deferred<<14113>>d<<3510>>_m^T<<3511>>\begin<<14114>>tex2html_deferred<<14114>>\bf\end<<14115>>tex2html_deferred<<14115>>A<<3511>><<3512>>\begin<<14116>>tex2html_deferred<<14116>>\bf\end<<14117>>tex2html_deferred<<14117>>g<<3512>>_n<<6713>><<6714>><<3513>>\begin<<14118>>tex2html_deferred<<14118>>\bf\end<<14119>>tex2html_deferred<<14119>>d<<3513>>^T_m<<3514>>\begin<<14120>>tex2html_deferred<<14120>>\bf\end<<14121>>tex2html_deferred<<14121>>A<<3514>><<3515>>\begin<<14122>>tex2html_deferred<<14122>>\bf\end<<14123>>tex2html_deferred<<14123>>d<<3515>>_m<<6714>>
  =\left\{\begin<<3516>>array<<3516>><<3517>>cl<<3517>>-||<<3518>>\begin<<14124>>tex2html_deferred<<14124>>\bf\end<<14125>>tex2html_deferred<<14125>>g<<3518>>_n||^2/\delta_<<3519>>n-1<<3519>><<3520>>\begin<<14126>>tex2html_deferred<<14126>>\bf\end<<14127>>tex2html_deferred<<14127>>d<<3520>>_<<3521>>n-1<<3521>>^T<<3522>>\begin<<14128>>tex2html_deferred<<14128>>\bf\end<<14129>>tex2html_deferred<<14129>>A<<3522>><<3523>>\begin<<14130>>tex2html_deferred<<14130>>\bf\end<<14131>>tex2html_deferred<<14131>>d<<3523>>_<<3524>>n-1<<3524>>
;SPMamp;m=n-1
  \\ 0;SPMamp;m;SPMlt;n-1\end<<3525>>array<<3525>>\right.
\end<<3526>>equation<<3526>>
\begin<<14132>>tex2html_deferred<<14132>>\par\end<<14133>>tex2html_deferred<<14133>>
which is non-zero only when \begin<<8084>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8084>>$m=n-1$\end<<8085>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8085>>, i.e., there is only one non-zero term
in the summation of the Gram-Schmidt formula for \begin<<8086>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8086>>$<<3527>>\begin<<14134>>tex2html_deferred<<14134>>\bf\end<<14135>>tex2html_deferred<<14135>>d<<3527>>_n$\end<<8087>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8087>>. This is the 
reason why we choose \begin<<8088>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8088>>$<<3528>>\begin<<14136>>tex2html_deferred<<14136>>\bf\end<<14137>>tex2html_deferred<<14137>>v<<3528>>_n=-<<3529>>\begin<<14138>>tex2html_deferred<<14138>>\bf\end<<14139>>tex2html_deferred<<14139>>g<<3529>>_n$\end<<8089>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8089>>. We can now drop the second 
subscript \begin<<8090>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8090>>$m$\end<<8091>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8091>>\space in \begin<<8092>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8092>>$\beta_<<3530>>nm<<3530>>$\end<<8093>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8093>>. Substituting the step size
\begin<<8094>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8094>>$\delta_<<3531>>n-1<<3531>>=||<<3532>>\begin<<14140>>tex2html_deferred<<14140>>\bf\end<<14141>>tex2html_deferred<<14141>>g<<3532>>_<<3533>>n-1<<3533>>||^2/<<3534>>\begin<<14142>>tex2html_deferred<<14142>>\bf\end<<14143>>tex2html_deferred<<14143>>d<<3534>>_<<3535>>n-1<<3535>>^T<<3536>>\begin<<14144>>tex2html_deferred<<14144>>\bf\end<<14145>>tex2html_deferred<<14145>>A<<3536>><<3537>>\begin<<14146>>tex2html_deferred<<14146>>\bf\end<<14147>>tex2html_deferred<<14147>>d<<3537>>_<<3538>>n-1<<3538>>$\end<<8095>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8095>> 
(Eq. (\ref<<3539>>CGstepsize<<3539>>)) into the above expression for \begin<<8096>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8096>>$\beta_<<3540>>nm<<3540>>=\beta_m$\end<<8097>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8097>>,
we get
\begin<<3541>>equation<<3541>> 
  \beta_n=-\frac<<6715>>||<<3542>>\begin<<14148>>tex2html_deferred<<14148>>\bf\end<<14149>>tex2html_deferred<<14149>>g<<3542>>_n||^2<<6715>><<6716>>||<<3543>>\begin<<14150>>tex2html_deferred<<14150>>\bf\end<<14151>>tex2html_deferred<<14151>>g<<3543>>_<<3544>>n-1<<3544>>||^2<<6716>> 
\end<<3545>>equation<<3545>>
We note that matrix \begin<<8098>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8098>>$<<3546>>\begin<<14152>>tex2html_deferred<<14152>>\bf\end<<14153>>tex2html_deferred<<14153>>A<<3546>>$\end<<8099>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8099>>\space no longer appears in the expression.
\begin<<14154>>tex2html_deferred<<14154>>\par\end<<14155>>tex2html_deferred<<14155>>
<<3547>>\begin<<14156>>tex2html_deferred<<14156>>\bf\end<<14157>>tex2html_deferred<<14157>>The CG algorithm<<3547>>
\begin<<14158>>tex2html_deferred<<14158>>\par\end<<14159>>tex2html_deferred<<14159>>
In summary here are the steps of the conjugate gradient algorithm:
\begin<<3548>>enumerate<<3548>>
\item Set \begin<<8100>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8100>>$n=0$\end<<8101>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8101>>\space and initialize the search direction (same as gradient descent):
  \begin<<3549>>equation<<3549>> 
    <<3550>>\begin<<14160>>tex2html_deferred<<14160>>\bf\end<<14161>>tex2html_deferred<<14161>>d<<3550>>_0=-<<3551>>\begin<<14162>>tex2html_deferred<<14162>>\bf\end<<14163>>tex2html_deferred<<14163>>g<<3551>>_0
  \end<<3552>>equation<<3552>>
\item Terminate if the error \begin<<8102>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8102>>$\varepsilon=||<<3553>>\begin<<14164>>tex2html_deferred<<14164>>\bf\end<<14165>>tex2html_deferred<<14165>>g<<3553>>_n||^2$\end<<8103>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8103>>\space is smaller 
  than a preset threshold. Otherwise, continue with the following:
\item Find optimal step size and step forward:
  \begin<<3554>>equation<<3554>>
  \delta_n=\frac<<6717>>||<<3555>>\begin<<14166>>tex2html_deferred<<14166>>\bf\end<<14167>>tex2html_deferred<<14167>>g<<3555>>_n||^2<<6717>><<6718>><<3556>>\begin<<14168>>tex2html_deferred<<14168>>\bf\end<<14169>>tex2html_deferred<<14169>>d<<3556>>_n^T<<3557>>\begin<<14170>>tex2html_deferred<<14170>>\bf\end<<14171>>tex2html_deferred<<14171>>A<<3557>><<3558>>\begin<<14172>>tex2html_deferred<<14172>>\bf\end<<14173>>tex2html_deferred<<14173>>d<<3558>>_n<<6718>>,
  \;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;
  <<3559>>\begin<<14174>>tex2html_deferred<<14174>>\bf\end<<14175>>tex2html_deferred<<14175>>x<<3559>>_<<3560>>n+1<<3560>>=<<3561>>\begin<<14176>>tex2html_deferred<<14176>>\bf\end<<14177>>tex2html_deferred<<14177>>x<<3561>>_n+\delta_n<<3562>>\begin<<14178>>tex2html_deferred<<14178>>\bf\end<<14179>>tex2html_deferred<<14179>>d<<3562>>_n 
  \end<<3563>>equation<<3563>>
\item Update gradient:
  \begin<<3564>>equation<<3564>>
  <<3565>>\begin<<14180>>tex2html_deferred<<14180>>\bf\end<<14181>>tex2html_deferred<<14181>>g<<3565>>_<<3566>>n+1<<3566>>=\frac<<3567>>d<<3567>><<6719>>d<<3568>>\begin<<14182>>tex2html_deferred<<14182>>\bf\end<<14183>>tex2html_deferred<<14183>>x<<3568>><<6719>>f(<<3569>>\begin<<14184>>tex2html_deferred<<14184>>\bf\end<<14185>>tex2html_deferred<<14185>>x<<3569>>_<<3570>>n+1<<3570>>)
  \end<<3571>>equation<<3571>>
\item Find coefficient for the Gram-Schmidt process:
  \begin<<3572>>equation<<3572>>
  \beta_<<3573>>n+1<<3573>>=\frac<<6720>>||<<3574>>\begin<<14186>>tex2html_deferred<<14186>>\bf\end<<14187>>tex2html_deferred<<14187>>g<<3574>>_<<3575>>n+1<<3575>>||^2<<6720>><<6721>>||<<3576>>\begin<<14188>>tex2html_deferred<<14188>>\bf\end<<14189>>tex2html_deferred<<14189>>g<<3576>>_n||^2<<6721>> 
\end<<3577>>equation<<3577>>
\item Update search direction:
  \begin<<3578>>equation<<3578>> 
    <<3579>>\begin<<14190>>tex2html_deferred<<14190>>\bf\end<<14191>>tex2html_deferred<<14191>>d<<3579>>_<<3580>>n+1<<3580>>=-<<3581>>\begin<<14192>>tex2html_deferred<<14192>>\bf\end<<14193>>tex2html_deferred<<14193>>g<<3581>>_<<3582>>n+1<<3582>>+\beta_<<3583>>n+1<<3583>><<3584>>\begin<<14194>>tex2html_deferred<<14194>>\bf\end<<14195>>tex2html_deferred<<14195>>d<<3584>>_n 
\end<<3585>>equation<<3585>>
  Set \begin<<8104>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8104>>$n=n+1$\end<<8105>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8105>>\space and go back to step 2.
\end<<3586>>enumerate<<3586>>
\begin<<14196>>tex2html_deferred<<14196>>\par\end<<14197>>tex2html_deferred<<14197>>
The algorithm above assumes the objective function \begin<<8106>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8106>>$f(<<3587>>\begin<<14198>>tex2html_deferred<<14198>>\bf\end<<14199>>tex2html_deferred<<14199>>x<<3587>>)$\end<<8107>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8107>>\space to be quadratic 
with known \begin<<8108>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8108>>$<<3588>>\begin<<14200>>tex2html_deferred<<14200>>\bf\end<<14201>>tex2html_deferred<<14201>>A<<3588>>$\end<<8109>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8109>>. But when \begin<<8110>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8110>>$f(<<3589>>\begin<<14202>>tex2html_deferred<<14202>>\bf\end<<14203>>tex2html_deferred<<14203>>x<<3589>>)$\end<<8111>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8111>>\space is not quadratic, \begin<<8112>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8112>>$<<3590>>\begin<<14204>>tex2html_deferred<<14204>>\bf\end<<14205>>tex2html_deferred<<14205>>A<<3590>>$\end<<8113>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8113>>\space is no 
longer available, and the Hessian \begin<<8114>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8114>>$<<3591>>\begin<<14206>>tex2html_deferred<<14206>>\bf\end<<14207>>tex2html_deferred<<14207>>H<<3591>>$\end<<8115>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8115>>\space may not be a good approximation of 
\begin<<8116>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8116>>$<<3592>>\begin<<14208>>tex2html_deferred<<14208>>\bf\end<<14209>>tex2html_deferred<<14209>>A<<3592>>$\end<<8117>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8117>>. However, we can still assume that \begin<<8118>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8118>>$f(<<3593>>\begin<<14210>>tex2html_deferred<<14210>>\bf\end<<14211>>tex2html_deferred<<14211>>x<<3593>>)$\end<<8119>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8119>>\space can be approximated 
as a quadratic function in the neighborhood of its minimum. In this case, the 
algorithm can be modified so that it does not depend on \begin<<8120>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8120>>$<<3594>>\begin<<14212>>tex2html_deferred<<14212>>\bf\end<<14213>>tex2html_deferred<<14213>>A<<3594>>$\end<<8121>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8121>>. Specifically,
in step 3 above, the optimal step size \begin<<8122>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8122>>$\delta_n$\end<<8123>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8123>>\space is calculated based on \begin<<8124>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8124>>$<<3595>>\begin<<14214>>tex2html_deferred<<14214>>\bf\end<<14215>>tex2html_deferred<<14215>>A<<3595>>$\end<<8125>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8125>>.
When \begin<<8126>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8126>>$<<3596>>\begin<<14216>>tex2html_deferred<<14216>>\bf\end<<14217>>tex2html_deferred<<14217>>A<<3596>>$\end<<8127>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8127>>\space is unavailable, \begin<<8128>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8128>>$\delta$\end<<8129>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8129>>\space can also be found by line minimization
based on any suitable algorithms for 1-D optimization. 
\begin<<14218>>tex2html_deferred<<14218>>\par\end<<14219>>tex2html_deferred<<14219>>
If it is known that the current \begin<<8130>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8130>>$<<3597>>\begin<<14220>>tex2html_deferred<<14220>>\bf\end<<14221>>tex2html_deferred<<14221>>x<<3597>>_n$\end<<8131>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8131>>\space is close enough to the solution 
\begin<<8132>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8132>>$<<3598>>\begin<<14222>>tex2html_deferred<<14222>>\bf\end<<14223>>tex2html_deferred<<14223>>x<<3598>>^*$\end<<8133>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8133>>, we can approximate \begin<<8134>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8134>>$f(<<3599>>\begin<<14224>>tex2html_deferred<<14224>>\bf\end<<14225>>tex2html_deferred<<14225>>x<<3599>>)$\end<<8135>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8135>>\space as a quadratic function, and
its Hessian matrix \begin<<8136>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8136>>$<<3600>>\begin<<14226>>tex2html_deferred<<14226>>\bf\end<<14227>>tex2html_deferred<<14227>>H<<3600>>$\end<<8137>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8137>>\space can be used to approximate \begin<<8138>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8138>>$<<3601>>\begin<<14228>>tex2html_deferred<<14228>>\bf\end<<14229>>tex2html_deferred<<14229>>A<<3601>>$\end<<8139>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8139>>\space so that the 
original algorithm may still be used. 
\begin<<14230>>tex2html_deferred<<14230>>\par\end<<14231>>tex2html_deferred<<14231>>
<<3602>>\begin<<14232>>tex2html_deferred<<14232>>\bf\end<<14233>>tex2html_deferred<<14233>>Example 1:<<3602>> 
To compare the conjugate method and the gradient descent method, consider a very 
simple 2-D quadratic function
\begin<<3603>>equation<<3603>>
  f(x,y)=<<3604>>\begin<<14234>>tex2html_deferred<<14234>>\bf\end<<14235>>tex2html_deferred<<14235>>x<<3604>>^T<<3605>>\begin<<14236>>tex2html_deferred<<14236>>\bf\end<<14237>>tex2html_deferred<<14237>>A<<3605>><<3606>>\begin<<14238>>tex2html_deferred<<14238>>\bf\end<<14239>>tex2html_deferred<<14239>>x<<3606>>
  =[x_1,\,x_2]\left[\begin<<3607>>array<<3607>><<3608>>cc<<3608>>3;SPMamp;1\\ 1;SPMamp;2\end<<3609>>array<<3609>>\right]
  \left[\begin<<3610>>array<<3610>><<3611>>c<<3611>>x_1\\ x_2\end<<3612>>array<<3612>>\right]
  \nonumber
\end<<3613>>equation<<3613>>
The performance of the gradient descent method depends significantly on
the initial guess. For the specific initial guess of \begin<<8140>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8140>>$<<3614>>\begin<<14240>>tex2html_deferred<<14240>>\bf\end<<14241>>tex2html_deferred<<14241>>x<<3614>>_0=[1.5,\;-0.75]^T$\end<<8141>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8141>>,
the iteration gets into a zigzag pattern and the convergence is very slow,
as shown below:
\begin<<14242>>tex2html_deferred<<14242>>\par\end<<14243>>tex2html_deferred<<14243>>
\begin<<3615>>equation<<3615>>
\begin<<3616>>array<<3616>><<3617>>c|c|c<<3617>>\hline
    n ;SPMamp; <<3618>>\begin<<14244>>tex2html_deferred<<14244>>\bf\end<<14245>>tex2html_deferred<<14245>>x<<3618>>=[x_1,\,x_2] ;SPMamp; f(<<3619>>\begin<<14246>>tex2html_deferred<<14246>>\bf\end<<14247>>tex2html_deferred<<14247>>x<<3619>>) \\ \hline
    0 ;SPMamp; 1.500000, -0.750000 ;SPMamp; 2.812500 \\ 
    1 ;SPMamp; 0.250000, -0.750000 ;SPMamp; 0.468750e-01 \\ 
    2 ;SPMamp; 0.250000, -0.125000 ;SPMamp; 7.812500e-02 \\ 
    3 ;SPMamp; 0.041667, -0.125000 ;SPMamp; 1.302083e-02 \\ 
    4 ;SPMamp; 0.041667, -0.020833 ;SPMamp; 2.170139e-03 \\ 
    5 ;SPMamp; 0.006944, -0.020833 ;SPMamp; 3.616898e-04 \\ 
    6 ;SPMamp; 0.006944, -0.003472 ;SPMamp; 6.028164e-05 \\ 
    7 ;SPMamp; 0.001157, -0.003472 ;SPMamp; 1.004694e-05 \\ 	
    8 ;SPMamp; 0.001157, -0.000579 ;SPMamp; 1.674490e-06 \\ 
    9 ;SPMamp; 0.000193, -0.000579 ;SPMamp; 2.790816e-07 \\ 	
    10 ;SPMamp; 0.000193, -0.000096 ;SPMamp; 4.651361e-08 \\ 	
    11 ;SPMamp; 0.000032, -0.000096 ;SPMamp; 7.752268e-09 \\ 
    12 ;SPMamp; 0.000032, -0.000016 ;SPMamp; 1.292045e-09 \\ 
    13 ;SPMamp; 0.000005, -0.000016 ;SPMamp; 2.153408e-10 \\ \hline
  \end<<3620>>array<<3620>>
  \nonumber
\end<<3621>>equation<<3621>>
However, as expected, the conjugate gradient method takes exactly
\begin<<8142>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8142>>$N=2$\end<<8143>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8143>>\space steps from any initial guess to reach at the solution:
\begin<<14248>>tex2html_deferred<<14248>>\par\end<<14249>>tex2html_deferred<<14249>>
\begin<<3622>>equation<<3622>>
  \begin<<3623>>array<<3623>><<3624>>c|c|c<<3624>>\hline
    n ;SPMamp; <<3625>>\begin<<14250>>tex2html_deferred<<14250>>\bf\end<<14251>>tex2html_deferred<<14251>>x<<3625>>=[x_1,\,x_2] ;SPMamp; f(<<3626>>\begin<<14252>>tex2html_deferred<<14252>>\bf\end<<14253>>tex2html_deferred<<14253>>x<<3626>>) \\ \hline
    0 ;SPMamp; 1.500000, -0.750000 ;SPMamp; 2.812500e+00 \\ 
    1 ;SPMamp; 0.250000, -0.750000 ;SPMamp; 4.687500e-01 \\ 
    2 ;SPMamp; 0.000000, -0.000000 ;SPMamp; 1.155558e-33 \\ \hline
  \end<<3627>>array<<3627>>
  \nonumber
\end<<3628>>equation<<3628>>
\begin<<14254>>tex2html_deferred<<14254>>\par\end<<14255>>tex2html_deferred<<14255>>
\htmladdimg<<3629>>figures/GDvsCG2.png<<3629>>
\begin<<14256>>tex2html_deferred<<14256>>\par\end<<14257>>tex2html_deferred<<14257>>
For an \begin<<8144>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8144>>$N=3$\end<<8145>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8145>>\space example of \begin<<8146>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8146>>$f(<<3630>>\begin<<14258>>tex2html_deferred<<14258>>\bf\end<<14259>>tex2html_deferred<<14259>>x<<3630>>)=<<3631>>\begin<<14260>>tex2html_deferred<<14260>>\bf\end<<14261>>tex2html_deferred<<14261>>x<<3631>>^T<<3632>>\begin<<14262>>tex2html_deferred<<14262>>\bf\end<<14263>>tex2html_deferred<<14263>>A<<3632>><<3633>>\begin<<14264>>tex2html_deferred<<14264>>\bf\end<<14265>>tex2html_deferred<<14265>>x<<3633>>$\end<<8147>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8147>>\space with
\begin<<3634>>equation<<3634>>
  <<3635>>\begin<<14266>>tex2html_deferred<<14266>>\bf\end<<14267>>tex2html_deferred<<14267>>A<<3635>>=\left[\begin<<3636>>array<<3636>><<3637>>ccc<<3637>>5 ;SPMamp; 3 ;SPMamp; 1\\ 3 ;SPMamp; 4 ;SPMamp; 2\\ 1 ;SPMamp; 2 ;SPMamp; 3
    \end<<3638>>array<<3638>>\right]
  \nonumber
\end<<3639>>equation<<3639>>
from an initial guess \begin<<8148>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8148>>$<<3640>>\begin<<14268>>tex2html_deferred<<14268>>\bf\end<<14269>>tex2html_deferred<<14269>>x<<3640>>_0=[1,\;2,\;3]^T$\end<<8149>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8149>>, it takes the gradient 
descent method 41 iterations to reach 
\begin<<8150>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8150>>$<<3641>>\begin<<14270>>tex2html_deferred<<14270>>\bf\end<<14271>>tex2html_deferred<<14271>>x<<3641>>_<<3642>>41<<3642>>=[3.5486e-06,\;-7.4471e-06,\;4.6180e-06]^T$\end<<8151>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8151>>\space corresponding
to \begin<<8152>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8152>>$f(<<3643>>\begin<<14272>>tex2html_deferred<<14272>>\bf\end<<14273>>tex2html_deferred<<14273>>x<<3643>>)=8.5429e-11$\end<<8153>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8153>>. From the same initial guess, it takes the 
conjugate gradient method only \begin<<8154>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8154>>$N=3$\end<<8155>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8155>>\space iterations to converge to the 
solution:
\begin<<14274>>tex2html_deferred<<14274>>\par\end<<14275>>tex2html_deferred<<14275>>
\begin<<3644>>equation<<3644>>
  \begin<<3645>>array<<3645>><<3646>>c|c|c<<3646>>\hline
    n ;SPMamp; <<3647>>\begin<<14276>>tex2html_deferred<<14276>>\bf\end<<14277>>tex2html_deferred<<14277>>x<<3647>>=[x_1,\,x_2,\,x_3] ;SPMamp; f(<<3648>>\begin<<14278>>tex2html_deferred<<14278>>\bf\end<<14279>>tex2html_deferred<<14279>>x<<3648>>) \\ \hline
    0 ;SPMamp;  1.000000,  2.000000, 3.000000 ;SPMamp; 4.500000e+01 \\ 
    1 ;SPMamp; -0.734716, -0.106441, 1.265284 ;SPMamp; 2.809225e+00 \\ 
    2 ;SPMamp;  0.123437, -0.209498, 0.136074 ;SPMamp; 3.584736e-02 \\ 
    3 ;SPMamp; -0.000000,  0.000000, 0.000000 ;SPMamp; 3.949119e-31 \\ \hline
  \end<<3649>>array<<3649>>
  \nonumber
\end<<3650>>equation<<3650>>
\begin<<14280>>tex2html_deferred<<14280>>\par\end<<14281>>tex2html_deferred<<14281>>
For an \begin<<8156>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8156>>$N=9$\end<<8157>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8157>>\space example, it takes over 4000 iterations for the gradient
descent method to converge with \begin<<8158>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8158>>$||<<3651>>\begin<<14282>>tex2html_deferred<<14282>>\bf\end<<14283>>tex2html_deferred<<14283>>e<<3651>>||\approx 10^<<3652>>-10<<3652>>$\end<<8159>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8159>>, but exactly 9
iterations for the CG method to converge with \begin<<8160>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8160>>$||<<3653>>\begin<<14284>>tex2html_deferred<<14284>>\bf\end<<14285>>tex2html_deferred<<14285>>e<<3653>>||\approx 10^<<3654>>-16<<3654>>$\end<<8161>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8161>>.
\begin<<14286>>tex2html_deferred<<14286>>\par\end<<14287>>tex2html_deferred<<14287>>
<<3655>>\begin<<14288>>tex2html_deferred<<14288>>\bf\end<<14289>>tex2html_deferred<<14289>>Example 2:<<3655>> 
\begin<<14290>>tex2html_deferred<<14290>>\par\end<<14291>>tex2html_deferred<<14291>>
The figure below shows the search path of the conjugate gradient method
applied to the minimization of the Rosenbrock function:
\begin<<14292>>tex2html_deferred<<14292>>\par\end<<14293>>tex2html_deferred<<14293>>
\htmladdimg<<3656>>figures/RosenbrockCG.png<<3656>>
\begin<<14294>>tex2html_deferred<<14294>>\par\end<<14295>>tex2html_deferred<<14295>>
<<3657>>\begin<<14296>>tex2html_deferred<<14296>>\bf\end<<14297>>tex2html_deferred<<14297>>Example 3:<<3657>> 
\begin<<14298>>tex2html_deferred<<14298>>\par\end<<14299>>tex2html_deferred<<14299>>
Solve the following \begin<<8162>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8162>>$N=3$\end<<8163>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8163>>\space non-linear equation system by the CG method:
\begin<<3658>>equation<<3658>>
  \left\{\begin<<3659>>array<<3659>><<3660>>l<<3660>>
  f_1(x_1,\,x_2,\,x_3)=3x_1-(x_2x_3)^2-3/2\\ 
  f_2(x_1,\,x_2,\,x_3)=4x_1^2-625\,x_2^2+2x_2-1\\ 
  f_3(x_1,\,x_2,\,x_3)=exp(-x_1x_2)+20x_3+9\end<<3661>>array<<3661>>\right.
  \nonumber
\end<<3662>>equation<<3662>>
The solution is known to be \begin<<8164>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8164>>$x_1=0.5,\;x_2=0,\;x_3=-0.5$\end<<8165>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8165>>.
\begin<<14300>>tex2html_deferred<<14300>>\par\end<<14301>>tex2html_deferred<<14301>>
This equation system can be represented in vector form as \begin<<8166>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8166>>$<<3663>>\begin<<14302>>tex2html_deferred<<14302>>\bf\end<<14303>>tex2html_deferred<<14303>>f<<3663>>(<<3664>>\begin<<14304>>tex2html_deferred<<14304>>\bf\end<<14305>>tex2html_deferred<<14305>>x<<3664>>)=<<3665>>\begin<<14306>>tex2html_deferred<<14306>>\bf\end<<14307>>tex2html_deferred<<14307>>0<<3665>>$\end<<8167>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8167>>
and the objective function is \begin<<8168>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8168>>$o(<<3666>>\begin<<14308>>tex2html_deferred<<14308>>\bf\end<<14309>>tex2html_deferred<<14309>>x<<3666>>)=<<3667>>\begin<<14310>>tex2html_deferred<<14310>>\bf\end<<14311>>tex2html_deferred<<14311>>f<<3667>>^T(<<3668>>\begin<<14312>>tex2html_deferred<<14312>>\bf\end<<14313>>tex2html_deferred<<14313>>x<<3668>>)<<3669>>\begin<<14314>>tex2html_deferred<<14314>>\bf\end<<14315>>tex2html_deferred<<14315>>f<<3669>>(<<3670>>\begin<<14316>>tex2html_deferred<<14316>>\bf\end<<14317>>tex2html_deferred<<14317>>x<<3670>>)$\end<<8169>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8169>>. 
The iteration of the CG method with an initial guess \begin<<8170>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8170>>$<<3671>>\begin<<14318>>tex2html_deferred<<14318>>\bf\end<<14319>>tex2html_deferred<<14319>>x<<3671>>_0=<<3672>>\begin<<14320>>tex2html_deferred<<14320>>\bf\end<<14321>>tex2html_deferred<<14321>>0<<3672>>$\end<<8171>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8171>>\space is 
shown below:
\begin<<3673>>equation<<3673>>
  \begin<<3674>>array<<3674>><<3675>>c|c|c<<3675>>\hline
    n ;SPMamp; <<3676>>\begin<<14322>>tex2html_deferred<<14322>>\bf\end<<14323>>tex2html_deferred<<14323>>x<<3676>>=[x_1,\,x_2,\,x_3] ;SPMamp; o(<<3677>>\begin<<14324>>tex2html_deferred<<14324>>\bf\end<<14325>>tex2html_deferred<<14325>>x<<3677>>) \\ \hline
    0 ;SPMamp;	0.0000,  0.0000,  0.0000 ;SPMamp;	1.032500e+02 \\ 
    1 ;SPMamp;	0.0113,  0.0050, -0.5001 ;SPMamp;	3.160163e+00 \\ 
    2 ;SPMamp;	0.0188, -0.0021, -0.5004 ;SPMamp;	3.095894e+00 \\ 
    3 ;SPMamp;	0.5009, -0.0018, -0.5004 ;SPMamp;	7.268252e-05 \\ 
    4 ;SPMamp;	0.5009, -0.0017, -0.5000 ;SPMamp;	1.051537e-05 \\ 
    5 ;SPMamp;	0.5008, -0.0012, -0.5000 ;SPMamp;	6.511151e-06 \\ 
    6 ;SPMamp;	0.5001, -0.0005, -0.5000 ;SPMamp;	6.365321e-07 \\ 
    7 ;SPMamp;	0.5001, -0.0005, -0.5000 ;SPMamp;	5.667357e-07 \\ 
    8 ;SPMamp;	0.5002, -0.0004, -0.5000 ;SPMamp;	2.675128e-07 \\ 
    9 ;SPMamp;	0.5001, -0.0003, -0.5000 ;SPMamp;	1.344218e-07 \\ 
    10;SPMamp;	0.5001, -0.0002, -0.5000 ;SPMamp;	1.241196e-07 \\ 
    11;SPMamp;	0.5000, -0.0001, -0.5000 ;SPMamp;	2.120969e-08 \\ 
    12;SPMamp;	0.5000, -0.0001, -0.5000 ;SPMamp;	1.541814e-08 \\ 
    13;SPMamp;	0.5000, -0.0001, -0.5000 ;SPMamp;	7.282025e-09 \\ 
    14;SPMamp;	0.5000, -0.0001, -0.5000 ;SPMamp;	4.801781e-09 \\ 
    15;SPMamp;	0.5000, -0.0000, -0.5000 ;SPMamp;	4.463926e-09 \\ \hline
  \end<<3678>>array<<3678>>
  \nonumber
\end<<3679>>equation<<3679>>
\begin<<14326>>tex2html_deferred<<14326>>\par\end<<14327>>tex2html_deferred<<14327>>
In comparison, the gradient descent method would need to take over 200 
iterations (with much reduced complexity though) to reach this level of 
error. 
\begin<<14328>>tex2html_deferred<<14328>>\par\end<<14329>>tex2html_deferred<<14329>>
<<3680>>\begin<<14330>>tex2html_deferred<<14330>>\bf\end<<14331>>tex2html_deferred<<14331>>Conjugate gradient method used for solving linear equation systems:<<3680>>
\begin<<14332>>tex2html_deferred<<14332>>\par\end<<14333>>tex2html_deferred<<14333>>
As discussed before, if \begin<<8172>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8172>>$<<3681>>\begin<<14334>>tex2html_deferred<<14334>>\bf\end<<14335>>tex2html_deferred<<14335>>x<<3681>>$\end<<8173>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8173>>\space is the solution that minimizes the 
quadratic function \begin<<8174>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8174>>$f(<<3682>>\begin<<14336>>tex2html_deferred<<14336>>\bf\end<<14337>>tex2html_deferred<<14337>>x<<3682>>)=<<3683>>\begin<<14338>>tex2html_deferred<<14338>>\bf\end<<14339>>tex2html_deferred<<14339>>x<<3683>>^T<<3684>>\begin<<14340>>tex2html_deferred<<14340>>\bf\end<<14341>>tex2html_deferred<<14341>>A<<3684>><<3685>>\begin<<14342>>tex2html_deferred<<14342>>\bf\end<<14343>>tex2html_deferred<<14343>>x<<3685>>/2-<<3686>>\begin<<14344>>tex2html_deferred<<14344>>\bf\end<<14345>>tex2html_deferred<<14345>>b<<3686>>^T<<3687>>\begin<<14346>>tex2html_deferred<<14346>>\bf\end<<14347>>tex2html_deferred<<14347>>x<<3687>>+c$\end<<8175>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8175>>, 
with \begin<<8176>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8176>>$<<3688>>\begin<<14348>>tex2html_deferred<<14348>>\bf\end<<14349>>tex2html_deferred<<14349>>A<<3688>>=<<3689>>\begin<<14350>>tex2html_deferred<<14350>>\bf\end<<14351>>tex2html_deferred<<14351>>A<<3689>>^T$\end<<8177>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8177>>\space being symmetric and positive definite, it also satisfies
\begin<<8178>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8178>>$d\,f(<<3690>>\begin<<14352>>tex2html_deferred<<14352>>\bf\end<<14353>>tex2html_deferred<<14353>>x<<3690>>)/d<<3691>>\begin<<14354>>tex2html_deferred<<14354>>\bf\end<<14355>>tex2html_deferred<<14355>>x<<3691>>=<<3692>>\begin<<14356>>tex2html_deferred<<14356>>\bf\end<<14357>>tex2html_deferred<<14357>>A<<3692>><<3693>>\begin<<14358>>tex2html_deferred<<14358>>\bf\end<<14359>>tex2html_deferred<<14359>>x<<3693>>-<<3694>>\begin<<14360>>tex2html_deferred<<14360>>\bf\end<<14361>>tex2html_deferred<<14361>>b<<3694>>=<<3695>>\begin<<14362>>tex2html_deferred<<14362>>\bf\end<<14363>>tex2html_deferred<<14363>>0<<3695>>$\end<<8179>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8179>>. In other words, the 
optimization problem is equivalent to the problem of solving the linear system 
\begin<<8180>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8180>>$<<3696>>\begin<<14364>>tex2html_deferred<<14364>>\bf\end<<14365>>tex2html_deferred<<14365>>A<<3696>><<3697>>\begin<<14366>>tex2html_deferred<<14366>>\bf\end<<14367>>tex2html_deferred<<14367>>x<<3697>>-<<3698>>\begin<<14368>>tex2html_deferred<<14368>>\bf\end<<14369>>tex2html_deferred<<14369>>b<<3698>>=<<3699>>\begin<<14370>>tex2html_deferred<<14370>>\bf\end<<14371>>tex2html_deferred<<14371>>0<<3699>>$\end<<8181>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8181>>, both can be solved by the conjugate gradient 
method.
\begin<<14372>>tex2html_deferred<<14372>>\par\end<<14373>>tex2html_deferred<<14373>>
Now consider solving the linear system \begin<<8182>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8182>>$<<3700>>\begin<<14374>>tex2html_deferred<<14374>>\bf\end<<14375>>tex2html_deferred<<14375>>A<<3700>><<3701>>\begin<<14376>>tex2html_deferred<<14376>>\bf\end<<14377>>tex2html_deferred<<14377>>x<<3701>>=<<3702>>\begin<<14378>>tex2html_deferred<<14378>>\bf\end<<14379>>tex2html_deferred<<14379>>b<<3702>>$\end<<8183>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8183>>\space with 
\begin<<8184>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8184>>$<<3703>>\begin<<14380>>tex2html_deferred<<14380>>\bf\end<<14381>>tex2html_deferred<<14381>>A<<3703>>=<<3704>>\begin<<14382>>tex2html_deferred<<14382>>\bf\end<<14383>>tex2html_deferred<<14383>>A<<3704>>^T$\end<<8185>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8185>>. Let \begin<<8186>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8186>>$<<3705>>\begin<<14384>>tex2html_deferred<<14384>>\bf\end<<14385>>tex2html_deferred<<14385>>d<<3705>>_i,\;(i=1,\cdots,N)$\end<<8187>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8187>>\space be a set of \begin<<8188>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8188>>$N$\end<<8189>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8189>> 
A-orthogonal vectors satisfying \begin<<8190>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8190>>$<<3706>>\begin<<14386>>tex2html_deferred<<14386>>\bf\end<<14387>>tex2html_deferred<<14387>>d<<3706>>_i^T<<3707>>\begin<<14388>>tex2html_deferred<<14388>>\bf\end<<14389>>tex2html_deferred<<14389>>A<<3707>><<3708>>\begin<<14390>>tex2html_deferred<<14390>>\bf\end<<14391>>tex2html_deferred<<14391>>d<<3708>>_j=0\;(i\ne j)$\end<<8191>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8191>>,
which can be generated based on any \begin<<8192>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8192>>$N$\end<<8193>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8193>>\space independent vectors, such as the
standard basis vectors, by the Gram-Smidth method. The solution \begin<<8194>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8194>>$<<3709>>\begin<<14392>>tex2html_deferred<<14392>>\bf\end<<14393>>tex2html_deferred<<14393>>x<<3709>>$\end<<8195>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8195>>
of the equation \begin<<8196>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8196>>$<<3710>>\begin<<14394>>tex2html_deferred<<14394>>\bf\end<<14395>>tex2html_deferred<<14395>>A<<3710>><<3711>>\begin<<14396>>tex2html_deferred<<14396>>\bf\end<<14397>>tex2html_deferred<<14397>>x<<3711>>=<<3712>>\begin<<14398>>tex2html_deferred<<14398>>\bf\end<<14399>>tex2html_deferred<<14399>>b<<3712>>$\end<<8197>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8197>>\space can be represented by these \begin<<8198>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8198>>$N$\end<<8199>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8199>> 
vectors as
\begin<<3713>>equation<<3713>> 
  <<3714>>\begin<<14400>>tex2html_deferred<<14400>>\bf\end<<14401>>tex2html_deferred<<14401>>x<<3714>>=\sum_<<3715>>i=1<<3715>>^N c_i<<3716>>\begin<<14402>>tex2html_deferred<<14402>>\bf\end<<14403>>tex2html_deferred<<14403>>d<<3716>>_i
\end<<3717>>equation<<3717>>
Now we have
\begin<<3718>>equation<<3718>>
  <<3719>>\begin<<14404>>tex2html_deferred<<14404>>\bf\end<<14405>>tex2html_deferred<<14405>>b<<3719>>=<<3720>>\begin<<14406>>tex2html_deferred<<14406>>\bf\end<<14407>>tex2html_deferred<<14407>>A<<3720>><<3721>>\begin<<14408>>tex2html_deferred<<14408>>\bf\end<<14409>>tex2html_deferred<<14409>>x<<3721>>=<<3722>>\begin<<14410>>tex2html_deferred<<14410>>\bf\end<<14411>>tex2html_deferred<<14411>>A<<3722>>\left[\sum_<<3723>>i=1<<3723>>^N c_i<<3724>>\begin<<14412>>tex2html_deferred<<14412>>\bf\end<<14413>>tex2html_deferred<<14413>>d<<3724>>_i\right]
=\sum_<<3725>>i=1<<3725>>^N c_i<<3726>>\begin<<14414>>tex2html_deferred<<14414>>\bf\end<<14415>>tex2html_deferred<<14415>>A<<3726>><<3727>>\begin<<14416>>tex2html_deferred<<14416>>\bf\end<<14417>>tex2html_deferred<<14417>>d<<3727>>_i
\end<<3728>>equation<<3728>>
Pre-multiplying \begin<<8200>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8200>>$<<3729>>\begin<<14418>>tex2html_deferred<<14418>>\bf\end<<14419>>tex2html_deferred<<14419>>d<<3729>>_j^T$\end<<8201>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8201>>\space on both sides we get
\begin<<3730>>equation<<3730>>
  <<3731>>\begin<<14420>>tex2html_deferred<<14420>>\bf\end<<14421>>tex2html_deferred<<14421>>d<<3731>>_j^T<<3732>>\begin<<14422>>tex2html_deferred<<14422>>\bf\end<<14423>>tex2html_deferred<<14423>>b<<3732>>=\sum_<<3733>>i=1<<3733>>^N c_i<<3734>>\begin<<14424>>tex2html_deferred<<14424>>\bf\end<<14425>>tex2html_deferred<<14425>>d<<3734>>_j^T<<3735>>\begin<<14426>>tex2html_deferred<<14426>>\bf\end<<14427>>tex2html_deferred<<14427>>A<<3735>><<3736>>\begin<<14428>>tex2html_deferred<<14428>>\bf\end<<14429>>tex2html_deferred<<14429>>d<<3736>>_i=c_j<<3737>>\begin<<14430>>tex2html_deferred<<14430>>\bf\end<<14431>>tex2html_deferred<<14431>>d<<3737>>_j^T<<3738>>\begin<<14432>>tex2html_deferred<<14432>>\bf\end<<14433>>tex2html_deferred<<14433>>A<<3738>><<3739>>\begin<<14434>>tex2html_deferred<<14434>>\bf\end<<14435>>tex2html_deferred<<14435>>d<<3739>>_j
\end<<3740>>equation<<3740>>
Solving for \begin<<8202>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8202>>$c_j$\end<<8203>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8203>>\space we get
\begin<<3741>>equation<<3741>>
c_j=\frac<<6722>><<3742>>\begin<<14436>>tex2html_deferred<<14436>>\bf\end<<14437>>tex2html_deferred<<14437>>d<<3742>>_j^T<<3743>>\begin<<14438>>tex2html_deferred<<14438>>\bf\end<<14439>>tex2html_deferred<<14439>>b<<3743>><<6722>><<6723>><<3744>>\begin<<14440>>tex2html_deferred<<14440>>\bf\end<<14441>>tex2html_deferred<<14441>>d<<3744>>_j^T<<3745>>\begin<<14442>>tex2html_deferred<<14442>>\bf\end<<14443>>tex2html_deferred<<14443>>A<<3745>><<3746>>\begin<<14444>>tex2html_deferred<<14444>>\bf\end<<14445>>tex2html_deferred<<14445>>d<<3746>>_j<<6723>>
\end<<3747>>equation<<3747>>
Substituting this back into the expression for \begin<<8204>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8204>>$<<3748>>\begin<<14446>>tex2html_deferred<<14446>>\bf\end<<14447>>tex2html_deferred<<14447>>x<<3748>>$\end<<8205>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8205>>\space we get the solution
of the equation:
\begin<<3749>>equation<<3749>> 
  <<3750>>\begin<<14448>>tex2html_deferred<<14448>>\bf\end<<14449>>tex2html_deferred<<14449>>x<<3750>>=\sum_<<3751>>i=1<<3751>>^N c_i<<3752>>\begin<<14450>>tex2html_deferred<<14450>>\bf\end<<14451>>tex2html_deferred<<14451>>d<<3752>>_i
  =\sum_<<3753>>i=1<<3753>>^N \left(\frac<<6724>><<3754>>\begin<<14452>>tex2html_deferred<<14452>>\bf\end<<14453>>tex2html_deferred<<14453>>d<<3754>>_i^T<<3755>>\begin<<14454>>tex2html_deferred<<14454>>\bf\end<<14455>>tex2html_deferred<<14455>>b<<3755>><<6724>><<6725>><<3756>>\begin<<14456>>tex2html_deferred<<14456>>\bf\end<<14457>>tex2html_deferred<<14457>>d<<3756>>_i^T<<3757>>\begin<<14458>>tex2html_deferred<<14458>>\bf\end<<14459>>tex2html_deferred<<14459>>A<<3757>><<3758>>\begin<<14460>>tex2html_deferred<<14460>>\bf\end<<14461>>tex2html_deferred<<14461>>d<<3758>>_i<<6725>>\right)
  <<3759>>\begin<<14462>>tex2html_deferred<<14462>>\bf\end<<14463>>tex2html_deferred<<14463>>d<<3759>>_i
\end<<3760>>equation<<3760>>
Also note that as \begin<<8206>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8206>>$<<3761>>\begin<<14464>>tex2html_deferred<<14464>>\bf\end<<14465>>tex2html_deferred<<14465>>b<<3761>>=<<3762>>\begin<<14466>>tex2html_deferred<<14466>>\bf\end<<14467>>tex2html_deferred<<14467>>A<<3762>><<3763>>\begin<<14468>>tex2html_deferred<<14468>>\bf\end<<14469>>tex2html_deferred<<14469>>x<<3763>>$\end<<8207>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8207>>, the ith term of the summation above
is simply the A-projection of \begin<<8208>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8208>>$<<3764>>\begin<<14470>>tex2html_deferred<<14470>>\bf\end<<14471>>tex2html_deferred<<14471>>x<<3764>>$\end<<8209>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8209>>\space onto the ith direction \begin<<8210>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8210>>$<<3765>>\begin<<14472>>tex2html_deferred<<14472>>\bf\end<<14473>>tex2html_deferred<<14473>>d<<3765>>_i$\end<<8211>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8211>>:
\begin<<3766>>equation<<3766>>
<<3767>>\begin<<14474>>tex2html_deferred<<14474>>\bf\end<<14475>>tex2html_deferred<<14475>>p<<3767>>_<<6726>><<3768>>\begin<<14476>>tex2html_deferred<<14476>>\bf\end<<14477>>tex2html_deferred<<14477>>d<<3768>>_i<<6726>>(<<3769>>\begin<<14478>>tex2html_deferred<<14478>>\bf\end<<14479>>tex2html_deferred<<14479>>x<<3769>>)
=\left(\frac<<6727>><<3770>>\begin<<14480>>tex2html_deferred<<14480>>\bf\end<<14481>>tex2html_deferred<<14481>>d<<3770>>_i^T<<3771>>\begin<<14482>>tex2html_deferred<<14482>>\bf\end<<14483>>tex2html_deferred<<14483>>A<<3771>><<3772>>\begin<<14484>>tex2html_deferred<<14484>>\bf\end<<14485>>tex2html_deferred<<14485>>x<<3772>><<6727>><<6728>><<3773>>\begin<<14486>>tex2html_deferred<<14486>>\bf\end<<14487>>tex2html_deferred<<14487>>d<<3773>>_i^T<<3774>>\begin<<14488>>tex2html_deferred<<14488>>\bf\end<<14489>>tex2html_deferred<<14489>>A<<3774>><<3775>>\begin<<14490>>tex2html_deferred<<14490>>\bf\end<<14491>>tex2html_deferred<<14491>>d<<3775>>_i<<6728>>\right)<<3776>>\begin<<14492>>tex2html_deferred<<14492>>\bf\end<<14493>>tex2html_deferred<<14493>>d<<3776>>_i
\end<<3777>>equation<<3777>>
\begin<<14494>>tex2html_deferred<<14494>>\par\end<<14495>>tex2html_deferred<<14495>>
One application of the conjugate gradient method is to solve the normal 
equation to find the least-square solution of an over-constrained equation 
system \begin<<8212>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8212>>$<<3778>>\begin<<14496>>tex2html_deferred<<14496>>\bf\end<<14497>>tex2html_deferred<<14497>>A<<3778>><<3779>>\begin<<14498>>tex2html_deferred<<14498>>\bf\end<<14499>>tex2html_deferred<<14499>>x<<3779>>=<<3780>>\begin<<14500>>tex2html_deferred<<14500>>\bf\end<<14501>>tex2html_deferred<<14501>>b<<3780>>$\end<<8213>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8213>>, where the coefficient matrix \begin<<8214>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8214>>$<<3781>>\begin<<14502>>tex2html_deferred<<14502>>\bf\end<<14503>>tex2html_deferred<<14503>>A<<3781>>$\end<<8215>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8215>>\space is \begin<<8216>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8216>>$M$\end<<8217>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8217>> 
by \begin<<8218>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8218>>$N$\end<<8219>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8219>>\space with rank \begin<<8220>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8220>>$R=N;SPMlt;M$\end<<8221>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8221>>. As discussed previously, the normal equation of this 
system is
\begin<<3782>>equation<<3782>>
  <<3783>>\begin<<14504>>tex2html_deferred<<14504>>\bf\end<<14505>>tex2html_deferred<<14505>>A<<3783>>^T<<3784>>\begin<<14506>>tex2html_deferred<<14506>>\bf\end<<14507>>tex2html_deferred<<14507>>A<<3784>><<3785>>\begin<<14508>>tex2html_deferred<<14508>>\bf\end<<14509>>tex2html_deferred<<14509>>x<<3785>>=<<3786>>\begin<<14510>>tex2html_deferred<<14510>>\bf\end<<14511>>tex2html_deferred<<14511>>A<<3786>>^T<<3787>>\begin<<14512>>tex2html_deferred<<14512>>\bf\end<<14513>>tex2html_deferred<<14513>>b<<3787>> 
\end<<3788>>equation<<3788>>
Here \begin<<8222>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8222>>$<<3789>>\begin<<14514>>tex2html_deferred<<14514>>\bf\end<<14515>>tex2html_deferred<<14515>>A<<3789>>^T<<3790>>\begin<<14516>>tex2html_deferred<<14516>>\bf\end<<14517>>tex2html_deferred<<14517>>A<<3790>>$\end<<8223>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8223>>\space is an \begin<<8224>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8224>>$N$\end<<8225>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8225>>\space by \begin<<8226>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8226>>$N$\end<<8227>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8227>>\space symmetric, positive definite matrix.
This normal equation can be solved by the conjugate gradient method.
\begin<<14518>>tex2html_deferred<<14518>>\par\end<<14519>>tex2html_deferred<<14519>>
\subsection*<<3791>>Issues of Local/Global Minimum<<3791>>
\begin<<14520>>tex2html_deferred<<14520>>\par\end<<14521>>tex2html_deferred<<14521>>
A main concern in optimization problems is whether the solution obtained by 
the algorithm is a local minimum or a global one. The simulated annealing
(SA) algorithm is typically used to search for the global minimum in a 
high-dimensional space, by allowing up-hill moves in the iteration to avoid
getting stuck by a local minimum. SA mimics the annealing process in metallurgy,
in which the temperature is carefully controlled to decrease slowly so that the
material reaches a state with minimum free energy. 
\begin<<14522>>tex2html_deferred<<14522>>\par\end<<14523>>tex2html_deferred<<14523>>
The way the SA method avoids getting stuck at a local minimum is to allow the 
iteration steps to go up-hill. Specifically, the objective function \begin<<8228>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8228>>$f(<<3792>>\begin<<14524>>tex2html_deferred<<14524>>\bf\end<<14525>>tex2html_deferred<<14525>>x<<3792>>)$\end<<8229>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8229>> 
evaluated at \begin<<8230>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8230>>$<<3793>>\begin<<14526>>tex2html_deferred<<14526>>\bf\end<<14527>>tex2html_deferred<<14527>>x<<3793>>_n$\end<<8231>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8231>>\space is treated as the energy at \begin<<8232>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8232>>$<<3794>>\begin<<14528>>tex2html_deferred<<14528>>\bf\end<<14529>>tex2html_deferred<<14529>>x<<3794>>_n$\end<<8233>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8233>>, and an up-hill 
move corresponding to an energy increase \begin<<8234>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8234>>$\Delta E=f(<<3795>>\begin<<14530>>tex2html_deferred<<14530>>\bf\end<<14531>>tex2html_deferred<<14531>>x<<3795>>_<<3796>>n+1<<3796>>)-f(<<3797>>\begin<<14532>>tex2html_deferred<<14532>>\bf\end<<14533>>tex2html_deferred<<14533>>x<<3797>>_n)_0$\end<<8235>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8235>> 
can be accepted if some probability function is greater than a random threshold 
value \begin<<8236>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8236>>$Th$\end<<8237>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8237>>\space within a certain range comparable with \begin<<8238>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8238>>$P$\end<<8239>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8239>>:
\begin<<3798>>equation<<3798>> 
P(\Delta E, T)=e^<<3799>>-\Delta E/T<<3799>>  ;SPMgt; Th
\end<<3800>>equation<<3800>>
Obviously smaller \begin<<8240>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8240>>$\Delta E$\end<<8241>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8241>>\space and higher \begin<<8242>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8242>>$T$\end<<8243>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8243>>\space will cause higher \begin<<8244>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8244>>$P$\end<<8245>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8245>>, it is more
probable for a move to be accepted.
\begin<<14534>>tex2html_deferred<<14534>>\par\end<<14535>>tex2html_deferred<<14535>>
During the entire search process, the temperature \begin<<8246>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8246>>$T$\end<<8247>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8247>>\space gradually reduces so that 
the probability of accepting an up-hill move also gradually reduces. In the early
stage of the search, it is more probable to go up-hill, thereby getting out of a
local minimum; but toward the later part of the search process, such a move is
less likely to happen, as presumably in this late stage of the search, the energy
level is already low, not likely to be at a local minimum with high energy level.
Through out the search, the best result corresponding to he lowest energy level
is always updated, to be returned as the final solution at the end of the process.
\begin<<14536>>tex2html_deferred<<14536>>\par\end<<14537>>tex2html_deferred<<14537>>
Further information can be found at 
\htmladdnormallink<<3801>>wikipedia<<3801>><<3802>>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simulated_annealing<<3802>>
and
\htmladdnormallink<<3803>>mathworld<<3803>><<3804>>http://mathworld.wolfram.com/SimulatedAnnealing.html<<3804>>.
\begin<<14538>>tex2html_deferred<<14538>>\par\end<<14539>>tex2html_deferred<<14539>>
A c program for AS can be found 
\htmladdnormallink<<3805>>here<<3805>><<3806>>http://fourier.eng.hmc.edu/e176/lectures/siman.c<<3806>>.
\begin<<14540>>tex2html_deferred<<14540>>\par\end<<14541>>tex2html_deferred<<14541>>
\section*<<3807>>Constrained Optimization<<3807>>
\begin<<14542>>tex2html_deferred<<14542>>\par\end<<14543>>tex2html_deferred<<14543>>
An optimization problem is more complicated if it is constrained, i.e.,
the arguments \begin<<8248>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8248>>$<<3808>>\begin<<14544>>tex2html_deferred<<14544>>\bf\end<<14545>>tex2html_deferred<<14545>>x<<3808>>=[x_1,\cdots,x_N]^T$\end<<8249>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8249>>\space of the objective function 
\begin<<8250>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8250>>$f(<<3809>>\begin<<14546>>tex2html_deferred<<14546>>\bf\end<<14547>>tex2html_deferred<<14547>>x<<3809>>)$\end<<8251>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8251>>\space are subject to certain equality or inequality constraints
in terms of what values they can take. Such a constrained optimization
problem can be formulated as:
\begin<<3810>>equation<<3810>>
  \begin<<3811>>array<<3811>><<3812>>ll<<3812>>
    \mbox<<3813>>optimize<<3813>> ;SPMamp; f(<<3814>>\begin<<14548>>tex2html_deferred<<14548>>\bf\end<<14549>>tex2html_deferred<<14549>>x<<3814>>)=f(x_1,\cdots,x_N) \\ 
    \;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\\ 
    \mbox<<3815>>subject to:<<3815>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{ \begin<<3816>>array<<3816>><<3817>>l<<3817>> 
      h_i(<<3818>>\begin<<14550>>tex2html_deferred<<14550>>\bf\end<<14551>>tex2html_deferred<<14551>>x<<3818>>)=0,\;\;\;\;\;(i=1,\cdots m)\\ 
      g_j(<<3819>>\begin<<14552>>tex2html_deferred<<14552>>\bf\end<<14553>>tex2html_deferred<<14553>>x<<3819>>)\le 0,\;\;\;\;\;(j=1,\cdots n)
    \end<<3820>>array<<3820>> \right.
  \end<<3821>>array<<3821>>
\end<<3822>>equation<<3822>>
The set of all \begin<<8252>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8252>>$<<3823>>\begin<<14554>>tex2html_deferred<<14554>>\bf\end<<14555>>tex2html_deferred<<14555>>x<<3823>>$\end<<8253>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8253>>\space satisfying the \begin<<8254>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8254>>$m+n$\end<<8255>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8255>>\space constraints is called
the feasible region of the problem. The goal is to find a point
\begin<<8256>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8256>>$<<3824>>\begin<<14556>>tex2html_deferred<<14556>>\bf\end<<14557>>tex2html_deferred<<14557>>x<<3824>>^*$\end<<8257>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8257>>\space in the feasible region at which \begin<<8258>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8258>>$f(<<3825>>\begin<<14558>>tex2html_deferred<<14558>>\bf\end<<14559>>tex2html_deferred<<14559>>x<<3825>>^*)$\end<<8259>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8259>>\space is an 
extremum. 
\begin<<14560>>tex2html_deferred<<14560>>\par\end<<14561>>tex2html_deferred<<14561>>
In the most general case where the objective function \begin<<8260>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8260>>$f(<<3826>>\begin<<14562>>tex2html_deferred<<14562>>\bf\end<<14563>>tex2html_deferred<<14563>>x<<3826>>)$\end<<8261>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8261>> 
and the constraint functions \begin<<8262>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8262>>$g_i(<<3827>>\begin<<14564>>tex2html_deferred<<14564>>\bf\end<<14565>>tex2html_deferred<<14565>>x<<3827>>)$\end<<8263>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8263>>\space and \begin<<8264>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8264>>$h_j(<<3828>>\begin<<14566>>tex2html_deferred<<14566>>\bf\end<<14567>>tex2html_deferred<<14567>>x<<3828>>)$\end<<8265>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8265>>\space are 
nonlinear, the process of solving this nonlinear optimization problem 
is called <<3829>>\begin<<14568>>tex2html_deferred<<14568>>\em\end<<14569>>tex2html_deferred<<14569>>nonlinear programming (NLP)<<3829>>. Specially, if the 
objective function is quadratic while the constraints are linear, 
(the feasible region is a polytope), the process is called 
<<3830>>\begin<<14570>>tex2html_deferred<<14570>>\em\end<<14571>>tex2html_deferred<<14571>>quadratic programming (QP)<<3830>>. More specially, if the objective 
function is linear as well as the constraints, the process is called 
<<3831>>\begin<<14572>>tex2html_deferred<<14572>>\em\end<<14573>>tex2html_deferred<<14573>>linear programming (LP)<<3831>>. In the following, we will first 
consider the NLP in general, and then discuss more specifically 
QP and LP.
\begin<<14574>>tex2html_deferred<<14574>>\par\end<<14575>>tex2html_deferred<<14575>>
\subsection*<<3832>>Optimization with Equality Constraints<<3832>>
\begin<<14576>>tex2html_deferred<<14576>>\par\end<<14577>>tex2html_deferred<<14577>>
The optimization problems subject to equality constraints can be
generally formulated as:
\begin<<3833>>equation<<3833>>
  \begin<<3834>>array<<3834>><<3835>>ll<<3835>>
    \mbox<<3836>>maximize/minimize<<3836>> ;SPMamp; f(<<3837>>\begin<<14578>>tex2html_deferred<<14578>>\bf\end<<14579>>tex2html_deferred<<14579>>x<<3837>>)=f(x_1,\cdots,x_N) \\ 
    \mbox<<3838>>subject to:<<3838>> ;SPMamp; h_i(<<3839>>\begin<<14580>>tex2html_deferred<<14580>>\bf\end<<14581>>tex2html_deferred<<14581>>x<<3839>>)=h_i(x_1,\cdots,x_N)=0,
    \;\;\;\;\;(i=1,\cdots m)\\ 
  \end<<3840>>array<<3840>>
\end<<3841>>equation<<3841>>
where \begin<<8266>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8266>>$f(<<3842>>\begin<<14582>>tex2html_deferred<<14582>>\bf\end<<14583>>tex2html_deferred<<14583>>x<<3842>>)$\end<<8267>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8267>>\space is the objective function and \begin<<8268>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8268>>$h_i(<<3843>>\begin<<14584>>tex2html_deferred<<14584>>\bf\end<<14585>>tex2html_deferred<<14585>>x<<3843>>)=0$\end<<8269>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8269>>
is the ith constraint. Here \begin<<8270>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8270>>$m\le N$\end<<8271>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8271>>, as in general there does not
exist a solution that satisfies more than \begin<<8272>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8272>>$N$\end<<8273>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8273>>\space equations in the N-D 
space.
\begin<<14586>>tex2html_deferred<<14586>>\par\end<<14587>>tex2html_deferred<<14587>>
To visualize the problem, we first consider the special case with 
\begin<<8274>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8274>>$N=2$\end<<8275>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8275>>\space and \begin<<8276>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8276>>$m=1$\end<<8277>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8277>>. In this case, both \begin<<8278>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8278>>$f(<<3844>>\begin<<14588>>tex2html_deferred<<14588>>\bf\end<<14589>>tex2html_deferred<<14589>>x<<3844>>)$\end<<8279>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8279>>\space and \begin<<8280>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8280>>$h(<<3845>>\begin<<14590>>tex2html_deferred<<14590>>\bf\end<<14591>>tex2html_deferred<<14591>>x<<3845>>)$\end<<8281>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8281>> 
are surfaces defined over the 2-D space spanned by \begin<<8282>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8282>>$x_1$\end<<8283>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8283>>\space and \begin<<8284>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8284>>$x_2$\end<<8285>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8285>>, 
and \begin<<8286>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8286>>$h(<<3846>>\begin<<14592>>tex2html_deferred<<14592>>\bf\end<<14593>>tex2html_deferred<<14593>>x<<3846>>)=0$\end<<8287>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8287>>\space is the contour line of \begin<<8288>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8288>>$h(<<3847>>\begin<<14594>>tex2html_deferred<<14594>>\bf\end<<14595>>tex2html_deferred<<14595>>x<<3847>>)$\end<<8289>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8289>>\space on the 2-D 
plane. The solution \begin<<8290>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8290>>$<<3848>>\begin<<14596>>tex2html_deferred<<14596>>\bf\end<<14597>>tex2html_deferred<<14597>>x<<3848>>^*$\end<<8291>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8291>>\space must satisfy the following two 
conditions:
\begin<<3849>>itemize<<3849>> 
\item \begin<<8292>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8292>>$<<3850>>\begin<<14598>>tex2html_deferred<<14598>>\bf\end<<14599>>tex2html_deferred<<14599>>x<<3850>>^*$\end<<8293>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8293>>\space is on the contour line \begin<<8294>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8294>>$h(<<3851>>\begin<<14600>>tex2html_deferred<<14600>>\bf\end<<14601>>tex2html_deferred<<14601>>x<<3851>>)=0$\end<<8295>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8295>>;
\item \begin<<8296>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8296>>$<<3852>>\begin<<14602>>tex2html_deferred<<14602>>\bf\end<<14603>>tex2html_deferred<<14603>>x<<3852>>^*$\end<<8297>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8297>>\space is on the contour line \begin<<8298>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8298>>$f(<<3853>>\begin<<14604>>tex2html_deferred<<14604>>\bf\end<<14605>>tex2html_deferred<<14605>>x<<3853>>)=d$\end<<8299>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8299>>\space (for some 
  \begin<<8300>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8300>>$d$\end<<8301>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8301>>\space as shown in the figure), so that \begin<<8302>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8302>>$f(<<3854>>\begin<<14606>>tex2html_deferred<<14606>>\bf\end<<14607>>tex2html_deferred<<14607>>x<<3854>>^*)$\end<<8303>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8303>>\space is an extremum,
  it does not increase/decrease in the neighborhood of \begin<<8304>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8304>>$<<3855>>\begin<<14608>>tex2html_deferred<<14608>>\bf\end<<14609>>tex2html_deferred<<14609>>x<<3855>>^*$\end<<8305>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8305>>
  along the contour line.
\end<<3856>>itemize<<3856>>
In other words, the two contours \begin<<8306>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8306>>$h(<<3857>>\begin<<14610>>tex2html_deferred<<14610>>\bf\end<<14611>>tex2html_deferred<<14611>>x<<3857>>)=0$\end<<8307>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8307>>\space and \begin<<8308>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8308>>$f(<<3858>>\begin<<14612>>tex2html_deferred<<14612>>\bf\end<<14613>>tex2html_deferred<<14613>>x<<3858>>)=d$\end<<8309>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8309>>
must coincide at \begin<<8310>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8310>>$<<3859>>\begin<<14614>>tex2html_deferred<<14614>>\bf\end<<14615>>tex2html_deferred<<14615>>x<<3859>>^*$\end<<8311>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8311>>, i.e., they must have the same tangents
and therefore parallel gradients (perpendicular to the tangents):
\begin<<3860>>equation<<3860>>
  \bigtriangledown_<<3861>>\begin<<14616>>tex2html_deferred<<14616>>\bf\end<<14617>>tex2html_deferred<<14617>>x<<3861>>f(<<3862>>\begin<<14618>>tex2html_deferred<<14618>>\bf\end<<14619>>tex2html_deferred<<14619>>x<<3862>>^*)
  =\lambda^*\,\bigtriangledown_<<3863>>\begin<<14620>>tex2html_deferred<<14620>>\bf\end<<14621>>tex2html_deferred<<14621>>x<<3863>> h(<<3864>>\begin<<14622>>tex2html_deferred<<14622>>\bf\end<<14623>>tex2html_deferred<<14623>>x<<3864>>^*)
\end<<3865>>equation<<3865>>
where the constant scaling factor \begin<<8312>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8312>>$\lambda^*$\end<<8313>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8313>>\space is positive if the
two gradients are in the same direction or negative if they are
in opposite directions. As here we are only interested in whether
the two curves coincide or not, the sign of \begin<<8314>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8314>>$\lambda^*$\end<<8315>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8315>>\space is of no
concern.
\begin<<14624>>tex2html_deferred<<14624>>\par\end<<14625>>tex2html_deferred<<14625>>
\htmladdimg<<3866>>figures/Lagrange.png<<3866>>
\begin<<14626>>tex2html_deferred<<14626>>\par\end<<14627>>tex2html_deferred<<14627>>
To find such a point \begin<<8316>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8316>>$<<3867>>\begin<<14628>>tex2html_deferred<<14628>>\bf\end<<14629>>tex2html_deferred<<14629>>x<<3867>>^*$\end<<8317>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8317>>, we first construct a new objective 
function, called the <<3868>>\begin<<14630>>tex2html_deferred<<14630>>\em\end<<14631>>tex2html_deferred<<14631>>Lagrange function<<3868>> (or simply 
<<3869>>\begin<<14632>>tex2html_deferred<<14632>>\em\end<<14633>>tex2html_deferred<<14633>>Lagrangian<<3869>>):
\begin<<3870>>equation<<3870>>
  L(<<3871>>\begin<<14634>>tex2html_deferred<<14634>>\bf\end<<14635>>tex2html_deferred<<14635>>x<<3871>>,\lambda)=f(<<3872>>\begin<<14636>>tex2html_deferred<<14636>>\bf\end<<14637>>tex2html_deferred<<14637>>x<<3872>>)-\lambda\, h(<<3873>>\begin<<14638>>tex2html_deferred<<14638>>\bf\end<<14639>>tex2html_deferred<<14639>>x<<3873>>)
\end<<3874>>equation<<3874>>
where \begin<<8318>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8318>>$\lambda$\end<<8319>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8319>>\space is the <<3875>>\begin<<14640>>tex2html_deferred<<14640>>\em\end<<14641>>tex2html_deferred<<14641>>Lagrange multiplier<<3875>>, which can be 
either positive or negative (the sign in front of \begin<<8320>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8320>>$\lambda$\end<<8321>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8321>>\space can 
be either plus or minus), and then set the gradient of this 
objective function with respect to \begin<<8322>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8322>>$\lambda$\end<<8323>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8323>>\space as well as \begin<<8324>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8324>>$<<3876>>\begin<<14642>>tex2html_deferred<<14642>>\bf\end<<14643>>tex2html_deferred<<14643>>x<<3876>>$\end<<8325>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8325>> 
to zero:
\begin<<3877>>equation<<3877>>
  \bigtriangledown_<<6729>><<3878>>\begin<<14644>>tex2html_deferred<<14644>>\bf\end<<14645>>tex2html_deferred<<14645>>x<<3878>>,\lambda<<6729>> L(<<3879>>\begin<<14646>>tex2html_deferred<<14646>>\bf\end<<14647>>tex2html_deferred<<14647>>x<<3879>>,\lambda)
  =\bigtriangledown_<<6730>><<3880>>\begin<<14648>>tex2html_deferred<<14648>>\bf\end<<14649>>tex2html_deferred<<14649>>x<<3880>>,\lambda<<6730>> [ f(<<3881>>\begin<<14650>>tex2html_deferred<<14650>>\bf\end<<14651>>tex2html_deferred<<14651>>x<<3881>>)-\lambda\, h(<<3882>>\begin<<14652>>tex2html_deferred<<14652>>\bf\end<<14653>>tex2html_deferred<<14653>>x<<3882>>) ]
  =<<3883>>\begin<<14654>>tex2html_deferred<<14654>>\bf\end<<14655>>tex2html_deferred<<14655>>0<<3883>>
\end<<3884>>equation<<3884>>
This equation contains two parts:
\begin<<3885>>equation<<3885>>
  \left\{\begin<<3886>>array<<3886>><<3887>>l<<3887>>
  \bigtriangledown_<<3888>>\begin<<14656>>tex2html_deferred<<14656>>\bf\end<<14657>>tex2html_deferred<<14657>>x<<3888>> f(<<3889>>\begin<<14658>>tex2html_deferred<<14658>>\bf\end<<14659>>tex2html_deferred<<14659>>x<<3889>>)=\lambda\bigtriangledown_<<3890>>\begin<<14660>>tex2html_deferred<<14660>>\bf\end<<14661>>tex2html_deferred<<14661>>x<<3890>> h(<<3891>>\begin<<14662>>tex2html_deferred<<14662>>\bf\end<<14663>>tex2html_deferred<<14663>>x<<3891>>)\\ 
  \bigtriangledown_\lambda L(<<3892>>\begin<<14664>>tex2html_deferred<<14664>>\bf\end<<14665>>tex2html_deferred<<14665>>x<<3892>>,\lambda)=\partial L(<<3893>>\begin<<14666>>tex2html_deferred<<14666>>\bf\end<<14667>>tex2html_deferred<<14667>>x<<3893>>,\lambda)/\partial \lambda
  =-h(<<3894>>\begin<<14668>>tex2html_deferred<<14668>>\bf\end<<14669>>tex2html_deferred<<14669>>x<<3894>>)=0
  \end<<3895>>array<<3895>>\right.
\end<<3896>>equation<<3896>>
This is an equation system containing \begin<<8326>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8326>>$N+m=2+1=3$\end<<8327>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8327>>\space equations for 
the same number of unknowns \begin<<8328>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8328>>$x_1,\,x_2,\,\lambda$\end<<8329>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8329>>:
\begin<<3897>>equation<<3897>>
  \frac<<6731>>\partial f(<<3898>>\begin<<14670>>tex2html_deferred<<14670>>\bf\end<<14671>>tex2html_deferred<<14671>>x<<3898>>)<<6731>><<3899>>\partial x_i<<3899>>
  =\lambda \frac<<6732>>\partial h(<<3900>>\begin<<14672>>tex2html_deferred<<14672>>\bf\end<<14673>>tex2html_deferred<<14673>>x<<3900>>)<<6732>><<3901>>\partial x_i<<3901>>\;\;\;(i=1,2),
  \;\;\;\;\;h(<<3902>>\begin<<14674>>tex2html_deferred<<14674>>\bf\end<<14675>>tex2html_deferred<<14675>>x<<3902>>)=0
\end<<3903>>equation<<3903>>
The solution \begin<<8330>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8330>>$<<3904>>\begin<<14676>>tex2html_deferred<<14676>>\bf\end<<14677>>tex2html_deferred<<14677>>x<<3904>>^*=[x_1^*,\,x_2^*]^T$\end<<8331>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8331>>\space and \begin<<8332>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8332>>$\lambda^*$\end<<8333>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8333>>\space (either
positive or negative) of this equation system happens to satisfy 
the desired relationships: (a) 
\begin<<8334>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8334>>$\bigtriangledown_<<3905>>\begin<<14678>>tex2html_deferred<<14678>>\bf\end<<14679>>tex2html_deferred<<14679>>x<<3905>>f(<<3906>>\begin<<14680>>tex2html_deferred<<14680>>\bf\end<<14681>>tex2html_deferred<<14681>>x<<3906>>^*)=\lambda^*\bigtriangledown_<<3907>>\begin<<14682>>tex2html_deferred<<14682>>\bf\end<<14683>>tex2html_deferred<<14683>>x<<3907>>h(<<3908>>\begin<<14684>>tex2html_deferred<<14684>>\bf\end<<14685>>tex2html_deferred<<14685>>x<<3908>>^*)$\end<<8335>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8335>>,
i.e., the two curves \begin<<8336>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8336>>$f(<<3909>>\begin<<14686>>tex2html_deferred<<14686>>\bf\end<<14687>>tex2html_deferred<<14687>>x<<3909>>)=d$\end<<8337>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8337>>\space and \begin<<8338>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8338>>$h(<<3910>>\begin<<14688>>tex2html_deferred<<14688>>\bf\end<<14689>>tex2html_deferred<<14689>>x<<3910>>)=0$\end<<8339>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8339>>\space do coincide 
at \begin<<8340>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8340>>$<<3911>>\begin<<14690>>tex2html_deferred<<14690>>\bf\end<<14691>>tex2html_deferred<<14691>>x<<3911>>^*$\end<<8341>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8341>>, and (b) \begin<<8342>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8342>>$h(<<3912>>\begin<<14692>>tex2html_deferred<<14692>>\bf\end<<14693>>tex2html_deferred<<14693>>x<<3912>>^*)=0$\end<<8343>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8343>>, i.e., \begin<<8344>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8344>>$<<3913>>\begin<<14694>>tex2html_deferred<<14694>>\bf\end<<14695>>tex2html_deferred<<14695>>x<<3913>>^*$\end<<8345>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8345>>\space does 
indeed satisfy the equality constraints. 
\begin<<14696>>tex2html_deferred<<14696>>\par\end<<14697>>tex2html_deferred<<14697>>
Specially, consider the following two possible cases:
\begin<<3914>>itemize<<3914>>
\item If \begin<<8346>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8346>>$\lambda^*=0$\end<<8347>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8347>>, then 
  \begin<<8348>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8348>>$\bigtriangledown_<<3915>>\begin<<14698>>tex2html_deferred<<14698>>\bf\end<<14699>>tex2html_deferred<<14699>>x<<3915>>f(<<3916>>\begin<<14700>>tex2html_deferred<<14700>>\bf\end<<14701>>tex2html_deferred<<14701>>x<<3916>>^*)=\lambda^*\bigtriangledown_<<3917>>\begin<<14702>>tex2html_deferred<<14702>>\bf\end<<14703>>tex2html_deferred<<14703>>x<<3917>>h(<<3918>>\begin<<14704>>tex2html_deferred<<14704>>\bf\end<<14705>>tex2html_deferred<<14705>>x<<3918>>^*)=0$\end<<8349>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8349>>, 
  indicating \begin<<8350>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8350>>$f(<<3919>>\begin<<14706>>tex2html_deferred<<14706>>\bf\end<<14707>>tex2html_deferred<<14707>>x<<3919>>^*)$\end<<8351>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8351>>\space is an extremum independent of the constraint,
  i.e., the constraint \begin<<8352>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8352>>$h(<<3920>>\begin<<14708>>tex2html_deferred<<14708>>\bf\end<<14709>>tex2html_deferred<<14709>>x<<3920>>)=0$\end<<8353>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8353>>\space is inactive, and the optimization 
  is unconstrained. 
\item If \begin<<8354>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8354>>$\lambda^*\ne 0$\end<<8355>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8355>>, then \begin<<8356>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8356>>$\bigtriangledown_<<3921>>\begin<<14710>>tex2html_deferred<<14710>>\bf\end<<14711>>tex2html_deferred<<14711>>x<<3921>>f(<<3922>>\begin<<14712>>tex2html_deferred<<14712>>\bf\end<<14713>>tex2html_deferred<<14713>>x<<3922>>^*)\ne 0$\end<<8357>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8357>>
  (as in general \begin<<8358>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8358>>$\bigtriangledown_<<3923>>\begin<<14714>>tex2html_deferred<<14714>>\bf\end<<14715>>tex2html_deferred<<14715>>x<<3923>>h(<<3924>>\begin<<14716>>tex2html_deferred<<14716>>\bf\end<<14717>>tex2html_deferred<<14717>>x<<3924>>^*)\ne<<3925>>\begin<<14718>>tex2html_deferred<<14718>>\bf\end<<14719>>tex2html_deferred<<14719>>0<<3925>>$\end<<8359>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8359>>),
  indicating \begin<<8360>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8360>>$f(<<3926>>\begin<<14720>>tex2html_deferred<<14720>>\bf\end<<14721>>tex2html_deferred<<14721>>x<<3926>>^*)$\end<<8361>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8361>>\space is not an extremum without the constraint, 
  i.e., the constraint is active, and the optimization is indeed
  constrained.
\end<<3927>>itemize<<3927>>
\begin<<14722>>tex2html_deferred<<14722>>\par\end<<14723>>tex2html_deferred<<14723>>
The discussion above can be generalized from 2-D to an \begin<<8362>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8362>>$N;SPMgt;2$\end<<8363>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8363>>\space dimensional
space, in which the optimal solution \begin<<8364>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8364>>$<<3928>>\begin<<14724>>tex2html_deferred<<14724>>\bf\end<<14725>>tex2html_deferred<<14725>>x<<3928>>^*$\end<<8365>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8365>>\space is to be found to
extremize the objective \begin<<8366>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8366>>$f(<<3929>>\begin<<14726>>tex2html_deferred<<14726>>\bf\end<<14727>>tex2html_deferred<<14727>>x<<3929>>)$\end<<8367>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8367>>\space subject to \begin<<8368>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8368>>$m$\end<<8369>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8369>>\space equality 
constraints \begin<<8370>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8370>>$h_i(<<3930>>\begin<<14728>>tex2html_deferred<<14728>>\bf\end<<14729>>tex2html_deferred<<14729>>x<<3930>>)=0\;(i=1,\cdots,m)$\end<<8371>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8371>>, each representing a 
contour surface in the N-D space. The solution \begin<<8372>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8372>>$<<3931>>\begin<<14730>>tex2html_deferred<<14730>>\bf\end<<14731>>tex2html_deferred<<14731>>x<<3931>>^*$\end<<8373>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8373>>\space must 
satisfy the following two conditions:
\begin<<3932>>itemize<<3932>>
\item \begin<<8374>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8374>>$<<3933>>\begin<<14732>>tex2html_deferred<<14732>>\bf\end<<14733>>tex2html_deferred<<14733>>x<<3933>>^*$\end<<8375>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8375>>\space is on all \begin<<8376>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8376>>$m$\end<<8377>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8377>>\space contour surfaces so that
  \begin<<8378>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8378>>$h_1(<<3934>>\begin<<14734>>tex2html_deferred<<14734>>\bf\end<<14735>>tex2html_deferred<<14735>>x<<3934>>^*)=\cdots=h_m(<<3935>>\begin<<14736>>tex2html_deferred<<14736>>\bf\end<<14737>>tex2html_deferred<<14737>>x<<3935>>^*)=0$\end<<8379>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8379>>, i.e., it is on the 
  intersection of these surfaces, a curve in the space (e.g.,
  the intersection of two surfaces in 3-D space is a curve);
\item \begin<<8380>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8380>>$<<3936>>\begin<<14738>>tex2html_deferred<<14738>>\bf\end<<14739>>tex2html_deferred<<14739>>x<<3936>>^*$\end<<8381>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8381>>\space is on a contour surface \begin<<8382>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8382>>$f(<<3937>>\begin<<14740>>tex2html_deferred<<14740>>\bf\end<<14741>>tex2html_deferred<<14741>>x<<3937>>^*)=d$\end<<8383>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8383>>
  (for some value \begin<<8384>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8384>>$d$\end<<8385>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8385>>) so that \begin<<8386>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8386>>$f(<<3938>>\begin<<14742>>tex2html_deferred<<14742>>\bf\end<<14743>>tex2html_deferred<<14743>>x<<3938>>^*)$\end<<8387>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8387>>\space is an extremum,
  i.e., it does not increase or degrease in the neighborhood of 
  \begin<<8388>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8388>>$<<3939>>\begin<<14744>>tex2html_deferred<<14744>>\bf\end<<14745>>tex2html_deferred<<14745>>x<<3939>>^*$\end<<8389>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8389>>\space along the curve.
\end<<3940>>itemize<<3940>>
Combining these conditions, we see that the intersection curve 
of the \begin<<8390>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8390>>$m$\end<<8391>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8391>>\space surfaces \begin<<8392>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8392>>$h_i(<<3941>>\begin<<14746>>tex2html_deferred<<14746>>\bf\end<<14747>>tex2html_deferred<<14747>>x<<3941>>)=0$\end<<8393>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8393>>\space must coincide with the contour
surface \begin<<8394>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8394>>$f(<<3942>>\begin<<14748>>tex2html_deferred<<14748>>\bf\end<<14749>>tex2html_deferred<<14749>>x<<3942>>)=d$\end<<8395>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8395>>\space at \begin<<8396>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8396>>$<<3943>>\begin<<14750>>tex2html_deferred<<14750>>\bf\end<<14751>>tex2html_deferred<<14751>>x<<3943>>^*$\end<<8397>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8397>>, i.e., the intersection of 
the tangent surfaces of \begin<<8398>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8398>>$h_i(<<3944>>\begin<<14752>>tex2html_deferred<<14752>>\bf\end<<14753>>tex2html_deferred<<14753>>x<<3944>>)=0$\end<<8399>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8399>>\space through \begin<<8400>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8400>>$<<3945>>\begin<<14754>>tex2html_deferred<<14754>>\bf\end<<14755>>tex2html_deferred<<14755>>x<<3945>>^*$\end<<8401>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8401>>\space must
lie on the tangent surface of \begin<<8402>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8402>>$f(<<3946>>\begin<<14756>>tex2html_deferred<<14756>>\bf\end<<14757>>tex2html_deferred<<14757>>x<<3946>>)=d$\end<<8403>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8403>>\space at \begin<<8404>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8404>>$<<3947>>\begin<<14758>>tex2html_deferred<<14758>>\bf\end<<14759>>tex2html_deferred<<14759>>x<<3947>>^*$\end<<8405>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8405>>,
therefore the gradient \begin<<8406>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8406>>$\bigtriangledown f(<<3948>>\begin<<14760>>tex2html_deferred<<14760>>\bf\end<<14761>>tex2html_deferred<<14761>>x<<3948>>^*)$\end<<8407>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8407>>\space must 
be a linear combination of the \begin<<8408>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8408>>$m$\end<<8409>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8409>>\space gradients 
\begin<<8410>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8410>>$\bigtriangledown h_i(<<3949>>\begin<<14762>>tex2html_deferred<<14762>>\bf\end<<14763>>tex2html_deferred<<14763>>x<<3949>>^*)$\end<<8411>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8411>>:
\begin<<3950>>equation<<3950>>
\bigtriangledown_<<3951>>\begin<<14764>>tex2html_deferred<<14764>>\bf\end<<14765>>tex2html_deferred<<14765>>x<<3951>>f(<<3952>>\begin<<14766>>tex2html_deferred<<14766>>\bf\end<<14767>>tex2html_deferred<<14767>>x<<3952>>^*)
=\sum_<<3953>>i=1<<3953>>^m \lambda_i^* \bigtriangledown_<<3954>>\begin<<14768>>tex2html_deferred<<14768>>\bf\end<<14769>>tex2html_deferred<<14769>>x<<3954>> h_i(<<3955>>\begin<<14770>>tex2html_deferred<<14770>>\bf\end<<14771>>tex2html_deferred<<14771>>x<<3955>>^*)
\end<<3956>>equation<<3956>>
\begin<<14772>>tex2html_deferred<<14772>>\par\end<<14773>>tex2html_deferred<<14773>>
\htmladdimg<<3957>>figures/Lagrange1.png<<3957>>
\begin<<14774>>tex2html_deferred<<14774>>\par\end<<14775>>tex2html_deferred<<14775>>
To find such a solution \begin<<8412>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8412>>$<<3958>>\begin<<14776>>tex2html_deferred<<14776>>\bf\end<<14777>>tex2html_deferred<<14777>>x<<3958>>^*$\end<<8413>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8413>>\space of the optimization problem, 
we first construct the Lagrange function:
\begin<<3959>>equation<<3959>>
  L(<<3960>>\begin<<14778>>tex2html_deferred<<14778>>\bf\end<<14779>>tex2html_deferred<<14779>>x<<3960>>,<<3961>>\begin<<14780>>tex2html_deferred<<14780>>\bf\end<<14781>>tex2html_deferred<<14781>>\lambda<<3961>>)=f(<<3962>>\begin<<14782>>tex2html_deferred<<14782>>\bf\end<<14783>>tex2html_deferred<<14783>>x<<3962>>)-\sum_<<3963>>i=1<<3963>>^m\lambda_i h_i(<<3964>>\begin<<14784>>tex2html_deferred<<14784>>\bf\end<<14785>>tex2html_deferred<<14785>>x<<3964>>)
\end<<3965>>equation<<3965>>
where \begin<<8414>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8414>>$<<3966>>\begin<<14786>>tex2html_deferred<<14786>>\bf\end<<14787>>tex2html_deferred<<14787>>\lambda<<3966>>=[\lambda_1,\cdots,\lambda_m]^T$\end<<8415>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8415>>\space is a vector
for \begin<<8416>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8416>>$m$\end<<8417>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8417>>\space <<3967>>\begin<<14788>>tex2html_deferred<<14788>>\em\end<<14789>>tex2html_deferred<<14789>>Lagrange multipliers<<3967>>, and then set its gradient to 
zero: 
\begin<<3968>>equation<<3968>>
  \bigtriangledown_<<6733>><<3969>>\begin<<14790>>tex2html_deferred<<14790>>\bf\end<<14791>>tex2html_deferred<<14791>>x<<3969>>,<<3970>>\begin<<14792>>tex2html_deferred<<14792>>\bf\end<<14793>>tex2html_deferred<<14793>>\lambda<<3970>><<6733>> L(<<3971>>\begin<<14794>>tex2html_deferred<<14794>>\bf\end<<14795>>tex2html_deferred<<14795>>x<<3971>>,<<3972>>\begin<<14796>>tex2html_deferred<<14796>>\bf\end<<14797>>tex2html_deferred<<14797>>\lambda<<3972>>)
  =\bigtriangledown_<<6734>><<3973>>\begin<<14798>>tex2html_deferred<<14798>>\bf\end<<14799>>tex2html_deferred<<14799>>x<<3973>>,<<3974>>\begin<<14800>>tex2html_deferred<<14800>>\bf\end<<14801>>tex2html_deferred<<14801>>\lambda<<3974>><<6734>>
  \left[ f(<<3975>>\begin<<14802>>tex2html_deferred<<14802>>\bf\end<<14803>>tex2html_deferred<<14803>>x<<3975>>)-\sum_<<3976>>i=1<<3976>>^m \lambda_i h_i(<<3977>>\begin<<14804>>tex2html_deferred<<14804>>\bf\end<<14805>>tex2html_deferred<<14805>>x<<3977>>) \right]
  =<<3978>>\begin<<14806>>tex2html_deferred<<14806>>\bf\end<<14807>>tex2html_deferred<<14807>>0<<3978>>
\end<<3979>>equation<<3979>>
to get the following two equation systems of \begin<<8418>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8418>>$N$\end<<8419>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8419>>\space and \begin<<8420>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8420>>$m$\end<<8421>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8421>>\space equations 
repectively:
\begin<<3980>>equation<<3980>>
  \bigtriangledown_<<3981>>\begin<<14808>>tex2html_deferred<<14808>>\bf\end<<14809>>tex2html_deferred<<14809>>x<<3981>> f(<<3982>>\begin<<14810>>tex2html_deferred<<14810>>\bf\end<<14811>>tex2html_deferred<<14811>>x<<3982>>)
  =\sum_<<3983>>i=1<<3983>>^m \lambda_i \bigtriangledown_<<3984>>\begin<<14812>>tex2html_deferred<<14812>>\bf\end<<14813>>tex2html_deferred<<14813>>x<<3984>> h_i(<<3985>>\begin<<14814>>tex2html_deferred<<14814>>\bf\end<<14815>>tex2html_deferred<<14815>>x<<3985>>)
  \;\;\;\;\mbox<<3986>>i.e.<<3986>>\;\;\;\;
  \frac<<6735>>\partial f(<<3987>>\begin<<14816>>tex2html_deferred<<14816>>\bf\end<<14817>>tex2html_deferred<<14817>>x<<3987>>)<<6735>><<3988>>\partial x_j<<3988>>
  =\sum_<<3989>>i=1<<3989>>^m\lambda_i \frac<<6736>>\partial h_i(<<3990>>\begin<<14818>>tex2html_deferred<<14818>>\bf\end<<14819>>tex2html_deferred<<14819>>x<<3990>>)<<6736>><<3991>>\partial x_j<<3991>>
  \;\;\;(j=1,\cdots,N),
\end<<3992>>equation<<3992>>
and
\begin<<3993>>equation<<3993>>
  \frac<<6737>>\partial L(<<3994>>\begin<<14820>>tex2html_deferred<<14820>>\bf\end<<14821>>tex2html_deferred<<14821>>x<<3994>>,<<3995>>\begin<<14822>>tex2html_deferred<<14822>>\bf\end<<14823>>tex2html_deferred<<14823>>\lambda<<3995>>)<<6737>><<3996>>\partial \lambda_i<<3996>>
  =h_i(<<3997>>\begin<<14824>>tex2html_deferred<<14824>>\bf\end<<14825>>tex2html_deferred<<14825>>x<<3997>>)=0\;\;\;\;(i=1,\cdots,m)
\end<<3998>>equation<<3998>>
The first set of \begin<<8422>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8422>>$N$\end<<8423>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8423>>\space equations indicates that the gradient 
\begin<<8424>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8424>>$\bigtriangledown_<<3999>>\begin<<14826>>tex2html_deferred<<14826>>\bf\end<<14827>>tex2html_deferred<<14827>>x<<3999>>f(<<4000>>\begin<<14828>>tex2html_deferred<<14828>>\bf\end<<14829>>tex2html_deferred<<14829>>x<<4000>>^*)$\end<<8425>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8425>>\space at \begin<<8426>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8426>>$<<4001>>\begin<<14830>>tex2html_deferred<<14830>>\bf\end<<14831>>tex2html_deferred<<14831>>x<<4001>>^*$\end<<8427>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8427>>\space is a 
linear combination of the \begin<<8428>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8428>>$m$\end<<8429>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8429>>\space gradients 
\begin<<8430>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8430>>$\bigtriangledown_<<4002>>\begin<<14832>>tex2html_deferred<<14832>>\bf\end<<14833>>tex2html_deferred<<14833>>x<<4002>> h_i(<<4003>>\begin<<14834>>tex2html_deferred<<14834>>\bf\end<<14835>>tex2html_deferred<<14835>>x<<4003>>^*)$\end<<8431>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8431>>, while the second 
set of \begin<<8432>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8432>>$m$\end<<8433>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8433>>\space equations guarantees that \begin<<8434>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8434>>$<<4004>>\begin<<14836>>tex2html_deferred<<14836>>\bf\end<<14837>>tex2html_deferred<<14837>>x<<4004>>^*$\end<<8435>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8435>>\space also satisfy
the \begin<<8436>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8436>>$m$\end<<8437>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8437>>\space equality constraints. Solving these equations we get 
the desired soluton \begin<<8438>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8438>>$<<4005>>\begin<<14838>>tex2html_deferred<<14838>>\bf\end<<14839>>tex2html_deferred<<14839>>x<<4005>>^*$\end<<8439>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8439>>\space together with the Lagrange
multipliers \begin<<8440>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8440>>$\lambda_1,\cdots,\lambda_m$\end<<8441>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8441>>. This is the 
<<4006>>\begin<<14840>>tex2html_deferred<<14840>>\em\end<<14841>>tex2html_deferred<<14841>>Lagrange multiplier method<<4006>>.
\begin<<14842>>tex2html_deferred<<14842>>\par\end<<14843>>tex2html_deferred<<14843>>
Specially, if \begin<<8442>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8442>>$\lambda_i=0$\end<<8443>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8443>>, then the ith constraint is not active. 
More specially if \begin<<8444>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8444>>$\lambda_i=0$\end<<8445>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8445>>\space for all \begin<<8446>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8446>>$i=1,\cdots,m$\end<<8447>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8447>>, then 
\begin<<4007>>equation<<4007>>
  \bigtriangledown_<<4008>>\begin<<14844>>tex2html_deferred<<14844>>\bf\end<<14845>>tex2html_deferred<<14845>>x<<4008>> f(<<4009>>\begin<<14846>>tex2html_deferred<<14846>>\bf\end<<14847>>tex2html_deferred<<14847>>x<<4009>>^*)
  =\sum_<<4010>>i=1<<4010>>^m \lambda_i \bigtriangledown_<<4011>>\begin<<14848>>tex2html_deferred<<14848>>\bf\end<<14849>>tex2html_deferred<<14849>>x<<4011>> h_i(<<4012>>\begin<<14850>>tex2html_deferred<<14850>>\bf\end<<14851>>tex2html_deferred<<14851>>x<<4012>>)=<<4013>>\begin<<14852>>tex2html_deferred<<14852>>\bf\end<<14853>>tex2html_deferred<<14853>>0<<4013>>
\end<<4014>>equation<<4014>>
indicating \begin<<8448>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8448>>$f(<<4015>>\begin<<14854>>tex2html_deferred<<14854>>\bf\end<<14855>>tex2html_deferred<<14855>>x<<4015>>^*)$\end<<8449>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8449>>\space is an extremum independent of any of
the constraints, i.e., \begin<<8450>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8450>>$<<4016>>\begin<<14856>>tex2html_deferred<<14856>>\bf\end<<14857>>tex2html_deferred<<14857>>x<<4016>>^*$\end<<8451>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8451>>\space is an unconstrained solution, 
and the optimization problem is unconstrained.
\begin<<14858>>tex2html_deferred<<14858>>\par\end<<14859>>tex2html_deferred<<14859>>
\subsection*<<4017>>Optimization with Inequality Constraints<<4017>>
\begin<<14860>>tex2html_deferred<<14860>>\par\end<<14861>>tex2html_deferred<<14861>>
The optimization problems subject to inequality constraints can
be generally formulated as:
\begin<<4018>>equation<<4018>>
  \begin<<4019>>array<<4019>><<4020>>ll<<4020>>
    \mbox<<4021>>maximize/minimize<<4021>> ;SPMamp; f(<<4022>>\begin<<14862>>tex2html_deferred<<14862>>\bf\end<<14863>>tex2html_deferred<<14863>>x<<4022>>)=f(x_1,\cdots,x_N) \\ 
    \mbox<<4023>>subject to:<<4023>> ;SPMamp; 
      g_j(<<4024>>\begin<<14864>>tex2html_deferred<<14864>>\bf\end<<14865>>tex2html_deferred<<14865>>x<<4024>>)=g_j(x_1,\cdots,x_N)\le \;\mbox<<4025>>or<<4025>>\;\;
\ge 0,\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;(j=1,\cdots n)
  \end<<4026>>array<<4026>>
\end<<4027>>equation<<4027>>
Again, to visualize the problem we first consider an example with 
\begin<<8452>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8452>>$N=2$\end<<8453>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8453>>\space and \begin<<8454>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8454>>$n=1$\end<<8455>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8455>>, as shown in the figure below for the minimization 
(left) and maximization (right) of \begin<<8456>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8456>>$f(<<4028>>\begin<<14866>>tex2html_deferred<<14866>>\bf\end<<14867>>tex2html_deferred<<14867>>x<<4028>>)$\end<<8457>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8457>>\space subject to 
\begin<<8458>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8458>>$g(<<4029>>\begin<<14868>>tex2html_deferred<<14868>>\bf\end<<14869>>tex2html_deferred<<14869>>x<<4029>>) ;SPMgt; 0$\end<<8459>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8459>>. The constrained solution \begin<<8460>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8460>>$<<4030>>\begin<<14870>>tex2html_deferred<<14870>>\bf\end<<14871>>tex2html_deferred<<14871>>x<<4030>>^*=[x^*_1,\,x^*_2]^T$\end<<8461>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8461>> 
is on the boundary of the feasible region satisfying \begin<<8462>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8462>>$g(x^*_1,x^*_2)=0$\end<<8463>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8463>>, 
while the unconstrained extremum is outside the feasible region.
\begin<<14872>>tex2html_deferred<<14872>>\par\end<<14873>>tex2html_deferred<<14873>>
\htmladdimg<<4031>>figures/KKT0a.png<<4031>>
\begin<<14874>>tex2html_deferred<<14874>>\par\end<<14875>>tex2html_deferred<<14875>>
Consider the following two possible cases.
\begin<<4032>>itemize<<4032>>
\item First, if the unconstrained extremum at which 
  \begin<<8464>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8464>>$\bigtriangledown_<<4033>>\begin<<14876>>tex2html_deferred<<14876>>\bf\end<<14877>>tex2html_deferred<<14877>>x<<4033>> f(<<4034>>\begin<<14878>>tex2html_deferred<<14878>>\bf\end<<14879>>tex2html_deferred<<14879>>x<<4034>>)=0$\end<<8465>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8465>>\space is outside the feasible
  region, i.e., the inequality constraint is active, then the 
  constrained solution \begin<<8466>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8466>>$<<4035>>\begin<<14880>>tex2html_deferred<<14880>>\bf\end<<14881>>tex2html_deferred<<14881>>x<<4035>>^*$\end<<8467>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8467>>\space must be
  \begin<<4036>>itemize<<4036>>
  \item on the boundary of the feasible region, i.e., \begin<<8468>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8468>>$g(<<4037>>\begin<<14882>>tex2html_deferred<<14882>>\bf\end<<14883>>tex2html_deferred<<14883>>x<<4037>>^*)=0$\end<<8469>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8469>>,
  \item different from the unconstrained solution, i.e., 
    \begin<<8470>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8470>>$\bigtriangledown_<<4038>>\begin<<14884>>tex2html_deferred<<14884>>\bf\end<<14885>>tex2html_deferred<<14885>>x<<4038>> f(<<4039>>\begin<<14886>>tex2html_deferred<<14886>>\bf\end<<14887>>tex2html_deferred<<14887>>x<<4039>>^*)\ne<<4040>>\begin<<14888>>tex2html_deferred<<14888>>\bf\end<<14889>>tex2html_deferred<<14889>>0<<4040>>$\end<<8471>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8471>>;
  \end<<4041>>itemize<<4041>>
  The problem becomes the same as an equality constrained problem 
  considered before, which requires the objective function \begin<<8472>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8472>>$f(<<4042>>\begin<<14890>>tex2html_deferred<<14890>>\bf\end<<14891>>tex2html_deferred<<14891>>x<<4042>>)$\end<<8473>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8473>>
  and the constraining function \begin<<8474>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8474>>$g(<<4043>>\begin<<14892>>tex2html_deferred<<14892>>\bf\end<<14893>>tex2html_deferred<<14893>>x<<4043>>)$\end<<8475>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8475>>\space to have the same tangent
  at \begin<<8476>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8476>>$<<4044>>\begin<<14894>>tex2html_deferred<<14894>>\bf\end<<14895>>tex2html_deferred<<14895>>x<<4044>>^*$\end<<8477>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8477>>, or parallel gradients: 
  \begin<<4045>>equation<<4045>>
    \bigtriangledown_<<4046>>\begin<<14896>>tex2html_deferred<<14896>>\bf\end<<14897>>tex2html_deferred<<14897>>x<<4046>> f(<<4047>>\begin<<14898>>tex2html_deferred<<14898>>\bf\end<<14899>>tex2html_deferred<<14899>>x<<4047>>^*)=\mu^*\;\bigtriangledown_<<4048>>\begin<<14900>>tex2html_deferred<<14900>>\bf\end<<14901>>tex2html_deferred<<14901>>x<<4048>> g(<<4049>>\begin<<14902>>tex2html_deferred<<14902>>\bf\end<<14903>>tex2html_deferred<<14903>>x<<4049>>^*)
    \;\;\;\;\mbox<<4050>>or<<4050>>\;\;\;\;
    \bigtriangledown_<<4051>>\begin<<14904>>tex2html_deferred<<14904>>\bf\end<<14905>>tex2html_deferred<<14905>>x<<4051>> f(<<4052>>\begin<<14906>>tex2html_deferred<<14906>>\bf\end<<14907>>tex2html_deferred<<14907>>x<<4052>>^*)-\mu^*\;\bigtriangledown_<<4053>>\begin<<14908>>tex2html_deferred<<14908>>\bf\end<<14909>>tex2html_deferred<<14909>>x<<4053>> g(<<4054>>\begin<<14910>>tex2html_deferred<<14910>>\bf\end<<14911>>tex2html_deferred<<14911>>x<<4054>>^*)=0
  \end<<4055>>equation<<4055>>
  However, different from before, now we are also concerned with whether
  the two gradients have the same or opposite directions, corresponding to 
  \begin<<8478>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8478>>$\mu;SPMgt;0$\end<<8479>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8479>>\space or \begin<<8480>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8480>>$\mu;SPMlt;0$\end<<8481>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8481>>, respectively, as illustrated in the 1-D examples in 
  the figure below:
\begin<<14912>>tex2html_deferred<<14912>>\par\end<<14913>>tex2html_deferred<<14913>>
\htmladdimg<<4056>>figures/KKT1a.png<<4056>>
\begin<<14914>>tex2html_deferred<<14914>>\par\end<<14915>>tex2html_deferred<<14915>>
Depending on whether \begin<<8482>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8482>>$f(<<4057>>\begin<<14916>>tex2html_deferred<<14916>>\bf\end<<14917>>tex2html_deferred<<14917>>x<<4057>>)$\end<<8483>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8483>>\space is to be maximized or minimized, 
  and whether the constraint is \begin<<8484>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8484>>$g(<<4058>>\begin<<14918>>tex2html_deferred<<14918>>\bf\end<<14919>>tex2html_deferred<<14919>>x<<4058>>)\ge 0$\end<<8485>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8485>>\space or \begin<<8486>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8486>>$g(<<4059>>\begin<<14920>>tex2html_deferred<<14920>>\bf\end<<14921>>tex2html_deferred<<14921>>x<<4059>>)\le 0$\end<<8487>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8487>>,
  there exist four possible cases in terms of the sign of \begin<<8488>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8488>>$\mu$\end<<8489>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8489>>, as 
  summarized in the table below: 
\begin<<14922>>tex2html_deferred<<14922>>\par\end<<14923>>tex2html_deferred<<14923>>
\begin<<4060>>equation<<4060>>
    \begin<<4061>>array<<4061>><<4062>>c||c|c<<4062>>\hline 
      ;SPMamp; g(<<4063>>\begin<<14924>>tex2html_deferred<<14924>>\bf\end<<14925>>tex2html_deferred<<14925>>x<<4063>>)\ge 0 ;SPMamp; g(<<4064>>\begin<<14926>>tex2html_deferred<<14926>>\bf\end<<14927>>tex2html_deferred<<14927>>x<<4064>>)\le 0 \\ \hline\hline
      \max\; f(<<4065>>\begin<<14928>>tex2html_deferred<<14928>>\bf\end<<14929>>tex2html_deferred<<14929>>x<<4065>>) ;SPMamp;\bigtriangledown f(<<4066>>\begin<<14930>>tex2html_deferred<<14930>>\bf\end<<14931>>tex2html_deferred<<14931>>x<<4066>>_1)=\mu\,\bigtriangledown g(<<4067>>\begin<<14932>>tex2html_deferred<<14932>>\bf\end<<14933>>tex2html_deferred<<14933>>x<<4067>>_1),\;\mu;SPMlt;0 ;SPMamp; 
      \bigtriangledown f(<<4068>>\begin<<14934>>tex2html_deferred<<14934>>\bf\end<<14935>>tex2html_deferred<<14935>>x<<4068>>_3)=\mu\,\bigtriangledown g(<<4069>>\begin<<14936>>tex2html_deferred<<14936>>\bf\end<<14937>>tex2html_deferred<<14937>>x<<4069>>_3),\;\mu;SPMgt;0 \\ \hline
      \min\; f(<<4070>>\begin<<14938>>tex2html_deferred<<14938>>\bf\end<<14939>>tex2html_deferred<<14939>>x<<4070>>) ;SPMamp; \bigtriangledown f(<<4071>>\begin<<14940>>tex2html_deferred<<14940>>\bf\end<<14941>>tex2html_deferred<<14941>>x<<4071>>_2)=\mu\,\bigtriangledown g(<<4072>>\begin<<14942>>tex2html_deferred<<14942>>\bf\end<<14943>>tex2html_deferred<<14943>>x<<4072>>_2),\;\mu;SPMgt;0 ;SPMamp; 
      \bigtriangledown f(<<4073>>\begin<<14944>>tex2html_deferred<<14944>>\bf\end<<14945>>tex2html_deferred<<14945>>x<<4073>>_4)=\mu \,\bigtriangledown g(<<4074>>\begin<<14946>>tex2html_deferred<<14946>>\bf\end<<14947>>tex2html_deferred<<14947>>x<<4074>>_4),\;\mu;SPMlt;0 \\ \hline
    \end<<4075>>array<<4075>>
    \label<<4076>>PolarityTable<<4076>>
  \end<<4077>>equation<<4077>>
  These cases can also be summarized in terms of the product of
  the coeficient \begin<<8490>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8490>>$\mu$\end<<8491>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8491>>\space and the constraining function \begin<<8492>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8492>>$g(<<4078>>\begin<<14948>>tex2html_deferred<<14948>>\bf\end<<14949>>tex2html_deferred<<14949>>x<<4078>>)$\end<<8493>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8493>>:
  \begin<<4079>>equation<<4079>>
    \mu\, g(<<4080>>\begin<<14950>>tex2html_deferred<<14950>>\bf\end<<14951>>tex2html_deferred<<14951>>x<<4080>>)\;\left\{\begin<<4081>>array<<4081>><<4082>>ll<<4082>> 
    \le 0 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<4083>>for maximization<<4083>>\\  \ge 0 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<4084>>for minimization<<4084>>
    \end<<4085>>array<<4085>>\right.
    \label<<4086>>mugminmax<<4086>>
  \end<<4087>>equation<<4087>>
\begin<<14952>>tex2html_deferred<<14952>>\par\end<<14953>>tex2html_deferred<<14953>>
\item Second, if the unconstrained extremum is inside the feasible 
  region, i.e., the inequality constraint is inactive, then the problem 
  is actually unconstrained and its solution \begin<<8494>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8494>>$<<4088>>\begin<<14954>>tex2html_deferred<<14954>>\bf\end<<14955>>tex2html_deferred<<14955>>x<<4088>>^*$\end<<8495>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8495>>\space is 
  \begin<<4089>>itemize<<4089>>
  \item the same as the unconstrained solution, i.e.,
    \begin<<8496>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8496>>$\bigtriangledown_<<4090>>\begin<<14956>>tex2html_deferred<<14956>>\bf\end<<14957>>tex2html_deferred<<14957>>x<<4090>> f(<<4091>>\begin<<14958>>tex2html_deferred<<14958>>\bf\end<<14959>>tex2html_deferred<<14959>>x<<4091>>^*)=<<4092>>\begin<<14960>>tex2html_deferred<<14960>>\bf\end<<14961>>tex2html_deferred<<14961>>0<<4092>>$\end<<8497>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8497>>;
  \item not on the boundary of the feasible region, i.e., 
    \begin<<8498>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8498>>$g(<<4093>>\begin<<14962>>tex2html_deferred<<14962>>\bf\end<<14963>>tex2html_deferred<<14963>>x<<4093>>^*)\ne 0$\end<<8499>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8499>>;
  \end<<4094>>itemize<<4094>>
  This solution can still be found by solving the same equation 
  \begin<<8500>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8500>>$\bigtriangledown_<<4095>>\begin<<14964>>tex2html_deferred<<14964>>\bf\end<<14965>>tex2html_deferred<<14965>>x<<4095>> f(<<4096>>\begin<<14966>>tex2html_deferred<<14966>>\bf\end<<14967>>tex2html_deferred<<14967>>x<<4096>>)
  =\mu\,\bigtriangledown_<<4097>>\begin<<14968>>tex2html_deferred<<14968>>\bf\end<<14969>>tex2html_deferred<<14969>>x<<4097>> g(<<4098>>\begin<<14970>>tex2html_deferred<<14970>>\bf\end<<14971>>tex2html_deferred<<14971>>x<<4098>>)=<<4099>>\begin<<14972>>tex2html_deferred<<14972>>\bf\end<<14973>>tex2html_deferred<<14973>>0<<4099>>$\end<<8501>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8501>>\space with \begin<<8502>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8502>>$\mu=0$\end<<8503>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8503>>. 
\end<<4100>>itemize<<4100>>
\begin<<14974>>tex2html_deferred<<14974>>\par\end<<14975>>tex2html_deferred<<14975>>
Summarizing the two cases above, we see that \begin<<8504>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8504>>$g(<<4101>>\begin<<14976>>tex2html_deferred<<14976>>\bf\end<<14977>>tex2html_deferred<<14977>>x<<4101>>^*)=0$\end<<8505>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8505>>\space but
\begin<<8506>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8506>>$\mu^*\ne 0$\end<<8507>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8507>>\space in the first case, \begin<<8508>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8508>>$g(<<4102>>\begin<<14978>>tex2html_deferred<<14978>>\bf\end<<14979>>tex2html_deferred<<14979>>x<<4102>>^*)\ne 0$\end<<8509>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8509>>\space but \begin<<8510>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8510>>$\mu^*=0$\end<<8511>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8511>>
in the second case, i.e., the following holds in either case:
\begin<<4103>>equation<<4103>>
  \mu^*\,g(<<4104>>\begin<<14980>>tex2html_deferred<<14980>>\bf\end<<14981>>tex2html_deferred<<14981>>x<<4104>>^*)=0
  \label<<4105>>mugeqz<<4105>>
\end<<4106>>equation<<4106>>
\begin<<14982>>tex2html_deferred<<14982>>\par\end<<14983>>tex2html_deferred<<14983>>
The discussion above can be generalized from 2-D to \begin<<8512>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8512>>$N;SPMgt;2$\end<<8513>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8513>>\space dimensional
space, in which the optimal solution \begin<<8514>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8514>>$<<4107>>\begin<<14984>>tex2html_deferred<<14984>>\bf\end<<14985>>tex2html_deferred<<14985>>x<<4107>>^*$\end<<8515>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8515>>\space is to be found 
to extremize the objective \begin<<8516>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8516>>$f(<<4108>>\begin<<14986>>tex2html_deferred<<14986>>\bf\end<<14987>>tex2html_deferred<<14987>>x<<4108>>)$\end<<8517>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8517>>\space subject to \begin<<8518>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8518>>$n$\end<<8519>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8519>>\space inequality 
constraints \begin<<8520>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8520>>$g_i(<<4109>>\begin<<14988>>tex2html_deferred<<14988>>\bf\end<<14989>>tex2html_deferred<<14989>>x<<4109>>)=0\;(i=1,\cdots,n)$\end<<8521>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8521>>. To solve this inequality
constrained optimization problem, we first construct the Lagrangian:
\begin<<4110>>equation<<4110>>
  L(<<4111>>\begin<<14990>>tex2html_deferred<<14990>>\bf\end<<14991>>tex2html_deferred<<14991>>x<<4111>>,<<4112>>\begin<<14992>>tex2html_deferred<<14992>>\bf\end<<14993>>tex2html_deferred<<14993>>\mu<<4112>>)=f(<<4113>>\begin<<14994>>tex2html_deferred<<14994>>\bf\end<<14995>>tex2html_deferred<<14995>>x<<4113>>)-\sum_<<4114>>i=1<<4114>>^n\mu_i\,g_i(<<4115>>\begin<<14996>>tex2html_deferred<<14996>>\bf\end<<14997>>tex2html_deferred<<14997>>x<<4115>>)
\end<<4116>>equation<<4116>>
Here we note that in some literatures, a plus sign is used in front of 
the summation of the second term. This is equivalent to our discussion
here so long as the sign of \begin<<8522>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8522>>$\mu$\end<<8523>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8523>>\space indicated in Table \ref<<4117>>PolarityTable<<4117>>
is negated. 
\begin<<14998>>tex2html_deferred<<14998>>\par\end<<14999>>tex2html_deferred<<14999>>
We now set the gradient of the Lagrangian to zero: 
\begin<<4118>>equation<<4118>>
  \bigtriangledown_<<6738>><<4119>>\begin<<15000>>tex2html_deferred<<15000>>\bf\end<<15001>>tex2html_deferred<<15001>>x<<4119>>,<<4120>>\begin<<15002>>tex2html_deferred<<15002>>\bf\end<<15003>>tex2html_deferred<<15003>>\mu<<4120>><<6738>> L(<<4121>>\begin<<15004>>tex2html_deferred<<15004>>\bf\end<<15005>>tex2html_deferred<<15005>>x<<4121>>,<<4122>>\begin<<15006>>tex2html_deferred<<15006>>\bf\end<<15007>>tex2html_deferred<<15007>>\mu<<4122>>)
  =\bigtriangledown_<<6739>><<4123>>\begin<<15008>>tex2html_deferred<<15008>>\bf\end<<15009>>tex2html_deferred<<15009>>x<<4123>>,<<4124>>\begin<<15010>>tex2html_deferred<<15010>>\bf\end<<15011>>tex2html_deferred<<15011>>\mu<<4124>><<6739>>\left[f(<<4125>>\begin<<15012>>tex2html_deferred<<15012>>\bf\end<<15013>>tex2html_deferred<<15013>>x<<4125>>)-\sum_<<4126>>i=1<<4126>>^n\mu_i\,g_i(<<4127>>\begin<<15014>>tex2html_deferred<<15014>>\bf\end<<15015>>tex2html_deferred<<15015>>x<<4127>>)\right]
  =<<4128>>\begin<<15016>>tex2html_deferred<<15016>>\bf\end<<15017>>tex2html_deferred<<15017>>0<<4128>>
\end<<4129>>equation<<4129>>
and get two equation systems of \begin<<8524>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8524>>$N$\end<<8525>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8525>>\space and \begin<<8526>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8526>>$n$\end<<8527>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8527>>\space equations,
respectively:
\begin<<4130>>equation<<4130>>
  \bigtriangledown_<<4131>>\begin<<15018>>tex2html_deferred<<15018>>\bf\end<<15019>>tex2html_deferred<<15019>>x<<4131>>f(<<4132>>\begin<<15020>>tex2html_deferred<<15020>>\bf\end<<15021>>tex2html_deferred<<15021>>x<<4132>>)
  =\sum_<<4133>>i=1<<4133>>^n\mu_i \bigtriangledown_<<4134>>\begin<<15022>>tex2html_deferred<<15022>>\bf\end<<15023>>tex2html_deferred<<15023>>x<<4134>> g_i(<<4135>>\begin<<15024>>tex2html_deferred<<15024>>\bf\end<<15025>>tex2html_deferred<<15025>>x<<4135>>)
\end<<4136>>equation<<4136>>
and
\begin<<4137>>equation<<4137>>
  \frac<<6740>>\partial L(<<4138>>\begin<<15026>>tex2html_deferred<<15026>>\bf\end<<15027>>tex2html_deferred<<15027>>x<<4138>>,<<4139>>\begin<<15028>>tex2html_deferred<<15028>>\bf\end<<15029>>tex2html_deferred<<15029>>\mu<<4139>>)<<6740>><<4140>>\partial\mu_i<<4140>>
  =g_i(<<4141>>\begin<<15030>>tex2html_deferred<<15030>>\bf\end<<15031>>tex2html_deferred<<15031>>x<<4141>>)=0\;\;\;\;(i=1,\cdots,n)
\end<<4142>>equation<<4142>>
\begin<<15032>>tex2html_deferred<<15032>>\par\end<<15033>>tex2html_deferred<<15033>>
The result above for the inequality constrained problems is the same 
as that for the equality constrained problems considered before. However,
we note that there is an additional requirement regarding the sign of the
scaling coifficients. For an equality constrained problem, the direction 
of the gradient \begin<<8528>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8528>>$\bigtriangledown g(<<4143>>\begin<<15034>>tex2html_deferred<<15034>>\bf\end<<15035>>tex2html_deferred<<15035>>x<<4143>>)$\end<<8529>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8529>>\space is of no concern, i.e., the
sign of \begin<<8530>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8530>>$\lambda$\end<<8531>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8531>>\space is unrestricted; but here for an inequality constrained 
problem, \begin<<8532>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8532>>$\mu$\end<<8533>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8533>>\space is required to be either positive or negative, depending
on whether the gradients of \begin<<8534>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8534>>$f(<<4144>>\begin<<15036>>tex2html_deferred<<15036>>\bf\end<<15037>>tex2html_deferred<<15037>>x<<4144>>^*)$\end<<8535>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8535>>\space and \begin<<8536>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8536>>$g(<<4145>>\begin<<15038>>tex2html_deferred<<15038>>\bf\end<<15039>>tex2html_deferred<<15039>>x<<4145>>^*)$\end<<8537>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8537>>\space are in the
same or opposite directions, as shown in Table \ref<<4146>>PolarityTable<<4146>>. For 
example, to minimize \begin<<8538>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8538>>$f(<<4147>>\begin<<15040>>tex2html_deferred<<15040>>\bf\end<<15041>>tex2html_deferred<<15041>>x<<4147>>)$\end<<8539>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8539>>\space subject to \begin<<8540>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8540>>$g(<<4148>>\begin<<15042>>tex2html_deferred<<15042>>\bf\end<<15043>>tex2html_deferred<<15043>>x<<4148>>)\ge 0$\end<<8541>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8541>>, \begin<<8542>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8542>>$\mu^*$\end<<8543>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8543>> 
needs to be positive, but to maximize \begin<<8544>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8544>>$f(<<4149>>\begin<<15044>>tex2html_deferred<<15044>>\bf\end<<15045>>tex2html_deferred<<15045>>x<<4149>>)$\end<<8545>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8545>>\space subject to 
\begin<<8546>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8546>>$g(<<4150>>\begin<<15046>>tex2html_deferred<<15046>>\bf\end<<15047>>tex2html_deferred<<15047>>x<<4150>>)\ge 0$\end<<8547>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8547>>, \begin<<8548>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8548>>$\mu^*$\end<<8549>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8549>>\space needs to be negative.
\begin<<15048>>tex2html_deferred<<15048>>\par\end<<15049>>tex2html_deferred<<15049>>
In principle, we can find the solution \begin<<8550>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8550>>$<<4151>>\begin<<15050>>tex2html_deferred<<15050>>\bf\end<<15051>>tex2html_deferred<<15051>>x<<4151>>^*$\end<<8551>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8551>>\space that optimizes 
\begin<<8552>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8552>>$f(<<4152>>\begin<<15052>>tex2html_deferred<<15052>>\bf\end<<15053>>tex2html_deferred<<15053>>x<<4152>>)$\end<<8553>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8553>>\space while also satisfying the inequality constraints by
solving the equation system above for \begin<<8554>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8554>>$<<4153>>\begin<<15054>>tex2html_deferred<<15054>>\bf\end<<15055>>tex2html_deferred<<15055>>x<<4153>>$\end<<8555>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8555>>\space as well as \begin<<8556>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8556>>$<<4154>>\begin<<15056>>tex2html_deferred<<15056>>\bf\end<<15057>>tex2html_deferred<<15057>>\mu<<4154>>$\end<<8557>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8557>>
with the required sign.
\begin<<15058>>tex2html_deferred<<15058>>\par\end<<15059>>tex2html_deferred<<15059>>
We can now address the general optimization of an N-D objective function
\begin<<8558>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8558>>$f(<<4155>>\begin<<15060>>tex2html_deferred<<15060>>\bf\end<<15061>>tex2html_deferred<<15061>>x<<4155>>)$\end<<8559>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8559>>\space subject to multiple constraints of both equalities and 
inequalities:
\begin<<4156>>equation<<4156>>
  \begin<<4157>>array<<4157>><<4158>>ll<<4158>>
    \mbox<<4159>>maximize/minimize<<4159>> ;SPMamp; f(<<4160>>\begin<<15062>>tex2html_deferred<<15062>>\bf\end<<15063>>tex2html_deferred<<15063>>x<<4160>>)=f(x_1,\cdots,x_N) \\ 
    \mbox<<4161>>subject to:<<4161>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{ \begin<<4162>>array<<4162>><<4163>>l<<4163>> 
      h_i(<<4164>>\begin<<15064>>tex2html_deferred<<15064>>\bf\end<<15065>>tex2html_deferred<<15065>>x<<4164>>)=0,\;\;\;\;\;(i=1,\cdots m)\\ 
      g_j(<<4165>>\begin<<15066>>tex2html_deferred<<15066>>\bf\end<<15067>>tex2html_deferred<<15067>>x<<4165>>)\le 0\;\;\mbox<<4166>>or<<4166>>\;\;
      g_j(<<4167>>\begin<<15068>>tex2html_deferred<<15068>>\bf\end<<15069>>tex2html_deferred<<15069>>x<<4167>>)\ge 0,\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;(j=1,\cdots n)\\ 
    \end<<4168>>array<<4168>> \right.
  \end<<4169>>array<<4169>>
\end<<4170>>equation<<4170>>
For notational convenience, we represent the \begin<<8560>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8560>>$m+n$\end<<8561>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8561>>\space equality and 
inequality constraints in vector form as: 
\begin<<4171>>equation<<4171>>
  \begin<<4172>>array<<4172>><<4173>>ll<<4173>>
    \mbox<<4174>>maximize/minimize<<4174>> ;SPMamp; f(<<4175>>\begin<<15070>>tex2html_deferred<<15070>>\bf\end<<15071>>tex2html_deferred<<15071>>x<<4175>>)\\ 
    \mbox<<4176>>subject to:<<4176>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{ \begin<<4177>>array<<4177>><<4178>>l<<4178>> 
      <<4179>>\begin<<15072>>tex2html_deferred<<15072>>\bf\end<<15073>>tex2html_deferred<<15073>>h<<4179>>(<<4180>>\begin<<15074>>tex2html_deferred<<15074>>\bf\end<<15075>>tex2html_deferred<<15075>>x<<4180>>)=<<4181>>\begin<<15076>>tex2html_deferred<<15076>>\bf\end<<15077>>tex2html_deferred<<15077>>0<<4181>>\\ 
      <<4182>>\begin<<15078>>tex2html_deferred<<15078>>\bf\end<<15079>>tex2html_deferred<<15079>>g<<4182>>(<<4183>>\begin<<15080>>tex2html_deferred<<15080>>\bf\end<<15081>>tex2html_deferred<<15081>>x<<4183>>)\le<<4184>>\begin<<15082>>tex2html_deferred<<15082>>\bf\end<<15083>>tex2html_deferred<<15083>>0<<4184>>\;\;\mbox<<4185>>or<<4185>>\;\;<<4186>>\begin<<15084>>tex2html_deferred<<15084>>\bf\end<<15085>>tex2html_deferred<<15085>>g<<4186>>(<<4187>>\begin<<15086>>tex2html_deferred<<15086>>\bf\end<<15087>>tex2html_deferred<<15087>>x<<4187>>)\ge<<4188>>\begin<<15088>>tex2html_deferred<<15088>>\bf\end<<15089>>tex2html_deferred<<15089>>0<<4188>>
    \end<<4189>>array<<4189>> \right.
  \end<<4190>>array<<4190>>
\end<<4191>>equation<<4191>>
where \begin<<8562>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8562>>$<<4192>>\begin<<15090>>tex2html_deferred<<15090>>\bf\end<<15091>>tex2html_deferred<<15091>>h<<4192>>(<<4193>>\begin<<15092>>tex2html_deferred<<15092>>\bf\end<<15093>>tex2html_deferred<<15093>>x<<4193>>)=[h_1(<<4194>>\begin<<15094>>tex2html_deferred<<15094>>\bf\end<<15095>>tex2html_deferred<<15095>>x<<4194>>),\cdots,h_m(<<4195>>\begin<<15096>>tex2html_deferred<<15096>>\bf\end<<15097>>tex2html_deferred<<15097>>x<<4195>>)]^T$\end<<8563>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8563>>\space and 
\begin<<8564>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8564>>$<<4196>>\begin<<15098>>tex2html_deferred<<15098>>\bf\end<<15099>>tex2html_deferred<<15099>>g<<4196>>(<<4197>>\begin<<15100>>tex2html_deferred<<15100>>\bf\end<<15101>>tex2html_deferred<<15101>>x<<4197>>)=[g_1(<<4198>>\begin<<15102>>tex2html_deferred<<15102>>\bf\end<<15103>>tex2html_deferred<<15103>>x<<4198>>),\cdots,g_n(<<4199>>\begin<<15104>>tex2html_deferred<<15104>>\bf\end<<15105>>tex2html_deferred<<15105>>x<<4199>>)]^T$\end<<8565>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8565>>.
\begin<<15106>>tex2html_deferred<<15106>>\par\end<<15107>>tex2html_deferred<<15107>>
To solve this optimization problem, we first construct the Lagrangian
\begin<<4200>>equation<<4200>>
  L(<<4201>>\begin<<15108>>tex2html_deferred<<15108>>\bf\end<<15109>>tex2html_deferred<<15109>>x<<4201>>,<<4202>>\begin<<15110>>tex2html_deferred<<15110>>\bf\end<<15111>>tex2html_deferred<<15111>>\lambda<<4202>>,<<4203>>\begin<<15112>>tex2html_deferred<<15112>>\bf\end<<15113>>tex2html_deferred<<15113>>\mu<<4203>>)
  =f(<<4204>>\begin<<15114>>tex2html_deferred<<15114>>\bf\end<<15115>>tex2html_deferred<<15115>>x<<4204>>)-\sum_<<4205>>i=1<<4205>>^m\lambda_i h_i(<<4206>>\begin<<15116>>tex2html_deferred<<15116>>\bf\end<<15117>>tex2html_deferred<<15117>>x<<4206>>)-\sum_<<4207>>j=1<<4207>>^n\mu_j g_j(<<4208>>\begin<<15118>>tex2html_deferred<<15118>>\bf\end<<15119>>tex2html_deferred<<15119>>x<<4208>>)
  =f(<<4209>>\begin<<15120>>tex2html_deferred<<15120>>\bf\end<<15121>>tex2html_deferred<<15121>>x<<4209>>)-<<4210>>\begin<<15122>>tex2html_deferred<<15122>>\bf\end<<15123>>tex2html_deferred<<15123>>\lambda<<4210>>^T <<4211>>\begin<<15124>>tex2html_deferred<<15124>>\bf\end<<15125>>tex2html_deferred<<15125>>h<<4211>>(<<4212>>\begin<<15126>>tex2html_deferred<<15126>>\bf\end<<15127>>tex2html_deferred<<15127>>x<<4212>>)-<<4213>>\begin<<15128>>tex2html_deferred<<15128>>\bf\end<<15129>>tex2html_deferred<<15129>>\mu<<4213>>^T<<4214>>\begin<<15130>>tex2html_deferred<<15130>>\bf\end<<15131>>tex2html_deferred<<15131>>g<<4214>>(<<4215>>\begin<<15132>>tex2html_deferred<<15132>>\bf\end<<15133>>tex2html_deferred<<15133>>x<<4215>>)
\end<<4216>>equation<<4216>>
where the Lagrange multipliers in \begin<<8566>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8566>>$<<4217>>\begin<<15134>>tex2html_deferred<<15134>>\bf\end<<15135>>tex2html_deferred<<15135>>\lambda<<4217>>=[\lambda_1,\cdots,\lambda_m]^T$\end<<8567>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8567>> 
and \begin<<8568>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8568>>$<<4218>>\begin<<15136>>tex2html_deferred<<15136>>\bf\end<<15137>>tex2html_deferred<<15137>>\mu<<4218>>=[\mu_1,\cdots,\mu_n]^T$\end<<8569>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8569>>\space are for the \begin<<8570>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8570>>$m$\end<<8571>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8571>>\space equality and \begin<<8572>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8572>>$n$\end<<8573>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8573>> 
non-negative constraints, respectively, and then set its gradient with 
respect to both \begin<<8574>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8574>>$<<4219>>\begin<<15138>>tex2html_deferred<<15138>>\bf\end<<15139>>tex2html_deferred<<15139>>\lambda<<4219>>$\end<<8575>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8575>>\space and \begin<<8576>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8576>>$<<4220>>\begin<<15140>>tex2html_deferred<<15140>>\bf\end<<15141>>tex2html_deferred<<15141>>\mu<<4220>>$\end<<8577>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8577>>\space as well as \begin<<8578>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8578>>$<<4221>>\begin<<15142>>tex2html_deferred<<15142>>\bf\end<<15143>>tex2html_deferred<<15143>>x<<4221>>$\end<<8579>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8579>>\space to 
zero. The solution \begin<<8580>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8580>>$<<4222>>\begin<<15144>>tex2html_deferred<<15144>>\bf\end<<15145>>tex2html_deferred<<15145>>x<<4222>>^*$\end<<8581>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8581>>\space can then be obtained by solving the 
resulting equation system, with \begin<<8582>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8582>>$\mu_j$\end<<8583>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8583>>\space taking the proper sign depending
on whether \begin<<8584>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8584>>$f(<<4223>>\begin<<15146>>tex2html_deferred<<15146>>\bf\end<<15147>>tex2html_deferred<<15147>>x<<4223>>)$\end<<8585>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8585>>\space is to be maximized or minimized, and whether the
inequality constraints are \begin<<8586>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8586>>$g_j(<<4224>>\begin<<15148>>tex2html_deferred<<15148>>\bf\end<<15149>>tex2html_deferred<<15149>>x<<4224>>)\le 0$\end<<8587>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8587>>\space or \begin<<8588>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8588>>$g_j(<<4225>>\begin<<15150>>tex2html_deferred<<15150>>\bf\end<<15151>>tex2html_deferred<<15151>>x<<4225>>)\ge 0$\end<<8589>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8589>>, 
as specified in Table \ref<<4226>>PolarityTable<<4226>>. Also, the solution \begin<<8590>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8590>>$<<4227>>\begin<<15152>>tex2html_deferred<<15152>>\bf\end<<15153>>tex2html_deferred<<15153>>x<<4227>>^*$\end<<8591>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8591>>
should satisfy the generalized version of Eq. (\ref<<4228>>mugeqz<<4228>>):
\begin<<4229>>equation<<4229>>
  \mu_j\,g_j(<<4230>>\begin<<15154>>tex2html_deferred<<15154>>\bf\end<<15155>>tex2html_deferred<<15155>>x<<4230>>^*)=0,\;\;\;\;\;\;(j=1,\cdots,n)
  \label<<4231>>mugeqz1<<4231>>
\end<<4232>>equation<<4232>>
\begin<<15156>>tex2html_deferred<<15156>>\par\end<<15157>>tex2html_deferred<<15157>>
<<4233>>\begin<<15158>>tex2html_deferred<<15158>>\bf\end<<15159>>tex2html_deferred<<15159>>Example<<4233>> 
\begin<<15160>>tex2html_deferred<<15160>>\par\end<<15161>>tex2html_deferred<<15161>>
Find the extremum of \begin<<8592>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8592>>$f(x_1,x_2)=x^2_1+x^2_2$\end<<8593>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8593>>\space subject to each of 
the three different constraints: \begin<<8594>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8594>>$x_1+x_2=1$\end<<8595>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8595>>, \begin<<8596>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8596>>$x_1+x_2\le 1$\end<<8597>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8597>>, and 
\begin<<8598>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8598>>$x_1+x_2\ge 1$\end<<8599>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8599>>. 
\begin<<4234>>itemize<<4234>>
\item \begin<<8600>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8600>>$h(x_1,x_2)=x_1+x_2-1=0$\end<<8601>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8601>>:
  \begin<<4235>>equation<<4235>>
    \begin<<4236>>array<<4236>><<4237>>ll<<4237>>
      \mbox<<4238>>minimize/maximize:<<4238>>\;\;\;\;\;\;f(x_1,x_2)=x^2_1+x^2_2\\ 
      \mbox<<4239>>subject to:<<4239>>\;\;\;\;\;\;h(x_1,x_2)=x_1+x_2-1=0\\ 
    \end<<4240>>array<<4240>>
    \nonumber
  \end<<4241>>equation<<4241>>
  The Lagrangian is:
  \begin<<4242>>equation<<4242>>
    L(x_1,x_2,\lambda)=f(x_1,x_2)-\lambda g(x_1,x_2)
    =x^2_1+x^2_2-\lambda(x_1+x_2-1)
    \nonumber
  \end<<4243>>equation<<4243>>
  Solving the following equations 
  \begin<<4244>>equation<<4244>>
    \frac<<4245>>\partial L<<4245>><<4246>>\partial x_1<<4246>>=2x_1-\lambda=0,\;\;\;
    \frac<<4247>>\partial L<<4247>><<4248>>\partial x_2<<4248>>=2x_2-\lambda=0,\;\;\;
    \frac<<4249>>\partial L<<4249>><<4250>>\partial \lambda<<4250>>=x_1+x_2-1=0
    \nonumber
  \end<<4251>>equation<<4251>>
  we get \begin<<8602>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8602>>$\lambda^*=1$\end<<8603>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8603>>\space and the optimal solution \begin<<8604>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8604>>$x_1^*=x_2^*=0.5$\end<<8605>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8605>> 
  (satisfying \begin<<8606>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8606>>$x_1^*+x_2^*=1$\end<<8607>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8607>>), at which the function is minimized to 
  be \begin<<8608>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8608>>$f(0.5,\,0.5)=0.5$\end<<8609>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8609>>. We also note that \begin<<8610>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8610>>$f(x_1,x_2)$\end<<8611>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8611>>\space and \begin<<8612>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8612>>$g(x_1,x_2)$\end<<8613>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8613>> 
  have the same gradients
  \begin<<4252>>equation<<4252>>
    \bigtriangledown f(0.5,0.5)=\bigtriangledown h(0.5,0.5)=[1,1]^T
    \nonumber
  \end<<4253>>equation<<4253>>
\item The following two problems
  \begin<<4254>>equation<<4254>>
    \begin<<4255>>array<<4255>><<4256>>ll<<4256>>
      \mbox<<4257>>minimize:<<4257>> ;SPMamp; f(x_1,x_2)=x^2_1+x^2_2\\ 
      \mbox<<4258>>subject to:<<4258>> ;SPMamp; g(x_1,x_2)=x_1+x_2-1\ge 0
    \end<<4259>>array<<4259>>
    \nonumber
  \end<<4260>>equation<<4260>>
  and
  \begin<<4261>>equation<<4261>>
    \begin<<4262>>array<<4262>><<4263>>ll<<4263>>
      \mbox<<4264>>maximize:<<4264>> ;SPMamp; f(x_1,x_2)=x^2_1+x^2_2\\ 
      \mbox<<4265>>subject to:<<4265>> ;SPMamp; g(x_1,x_2)=x_1+x_2-1\le 0
    \end<<4266>>array<<4266>>
    \nonumber
  \end<<4267>>equation<<4267>>
  have the same Lagrangian:
  \begin<<4268>>equation<<4268>>
    L(x_1,x_2,\mu)=f(x_1,x_2)-\mu\, g(x_1,x_2)=x^2_1+x^2_2-\mu(x_1+x_2-1)
  \end<<4269>>equation<<4269>>
  Solving the following equations 
  \begin<<4270>>equation<<4270>>
    \frac<<4271>>\partial L<<4271>><<4272>>\partial x_1<<4272>>=2x_1-\mu=0,\;\;\;
    \frac<<4273>>\partial L<<4273>><<4274>>\partial x_2<<4274>>=2x_2-\mu=0,\;\;\;
    \frac<<4275>>\partial L<<4275>><<4276>>\partial \mu<<4276>>=x_1+x_2-1=0
    \nonumber
  \end<<4277>>equation<<4277>>
  we still get the same results \begin<<8614>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8614>>$\mu^*=1;SPMgt;0$\end<<8615>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8615>>\space and \begin<<8616>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8616>>$x_1^*=x_2^*=\mu^*/2=0.5$\end<<8617>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8617>>, 
  at which the function reaches minimum or maximum \begin<<8618>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8618>>$f(0.5,\,0.5)=0.5$\end<<8619>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8619>> 
  subject to the corresponding constraint \begin<<8620>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8620>>$x_1+x_2\ge 1$\end<<8621>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8621>>\space or 
  \begin<<8622>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8622>>$x_1+x_2\le 1$\end<<8623>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8623>>.
\item We could also consider the following two problems:
  \begin<<4278>>equation<<4278>>
    \begin<<4279>>array<<4279>><<4280>>ll<<4280>>
      \mbox<<4281>>minimize:<<4281>> ;SPMamp; f(x_1,x_2)=x^2_1+x^2_2\\ 
      \mbox<<4282>>subject to:<<4282>> ;SPMamp; g(x_1,x_2)=x_1+x_2-1\le 0
    \end<<4283>>array<<4283>>
    \nonumber
  \end<<4284>>equation<<4284>>  
  and
  \begin<<4285>>equation<<4285>>
    \begin<<4286>>array<<4286>><<4287>>ll<<4287>>
      \mbox<<4288>>maximize:<<4288>> ;SPMamp; f(x_1,x_2)=x^2_1+x^2_2\\ 
      \mbox<<4289>>subject to:<<4289>> ;SPMamp; g(x_1,x_2)=x_1+x_2-1\ge 0
    \end<<4290>>array<<4290>>
    \nonumber
  \end<<4291>>equation<<4291>>
  The Lagrangian is the same as before, however, now we need to
  consider the case where \begin<<8624>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8624>>$\mu^*=0$\end<<8625>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8625>>\space and
  \begin<<4292>>equation<<4292>>
    \frac<<4293>>\partial L<<4293>><<4294>>\partial x_1<<4294>>=2x_1=0,\;\;\;
    \frac<<4295>>\partial L<<4295>><<4296>>\partial x_2<<4296>>=2x_2=0
    \nonumber
  \end<<4297>>equation<<4297>>
  Solving these we get \begin<<8626>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8626>>$x_1^*=x_2^*=0$\end<<8627>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8627>>, corresponding to the solution
  for the first problem, the absolute minimum of \begin<<8628>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8628>>$f(0,\,0)=0$\end<<8629>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8629>>,
  independent of any constraint, i.e, the minimization problem is 
  unconstrained. However, as the function is not bounded from above,
  its maximum does not exist, i.e., the second problem has no
  solution.
\end<<4298>>itemize<<4298>>
\begin<<15162>>tex2html_deferred<<15162>>\par\end<<15163>>tex2html_deferred<<15163>>
\subsection*<<4299>>Duality and KKT Conditions<<4299>>
\begin<<15164>>tex2html_deferred<<15164>>\par\end<<15165>>tex2html_deferred<<15165>>
For a given optimization problem, now called the <<4300>>\begin<<15166>>tex2html_deferred<<15166>>\em\end<<15167>>tex2html_deferred<<15167>>primal problem<<4300>>,
there exists a <<4301>>\begin<<15168>>tex2html_deferred<<15168>>\em\end<<15169>>tex2html_deferred<<15169>>dual problem<<4301>>. To see this, consider the following
problem:
\begin<<4302>>equation<<4302>>
  \begin<<4303>>array<<4303>><<4304>>ll<<4304>>
    \mbox<<4305>>minimize<<4305>> ;SPMamp; f_p(<<4306>>\begin<<15170>>tex2html_deferred<<15170>>\bf\end<<15171>>tex2html_deferred<<15171>>x<<4306>>)\\ 
    \mbox<<4307>>subject to:<<4307>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{ \begin<<4308>>array<<4308>><<4309>>l<<4309>> 
      <<4310>>\begin<<15172>>tex2html_deferred<<15172>>\bf\end<<15173>>tex2html_deferred<<15173>>h<<4310>>(<<4311>>\begin<<15174>>tex2html_deferred<<15174>>\bf\end<<15175>>tex2html_deferred<<15175>>x<<4311>>)=<<4312>>\begin<<15176>>tex2html_deferred<<15176>>\bf\end<<15177>>tex2html_deferred<<15177>>0<<4312>>\\ 
      <<4313>>\begin<<15178>>tex2html_deferred<<15178>>\bf\end<<15179>>tex2html_deferred<<15179>>g<<4313>>(<<4314>>\begin<<15180>>tex2html_deferred<<15180>>\bf\end<<15181>>tex2html_deferred<<15181>>x<<4314>>)\le<<4315>>\begin<<15182>>tex2html_deferred<<15182>>\bf\end<<15183>>tex2html_deferred<<15183>>0<<4315>>\;\;\mbox<<4316>>or<<4316>>\;\;<<4317>>\begin<<15184>>tex2html_deferred<<15184>>\bf\end<<15185>>tex2html_deferred<<15185>>g<<4317>>(<<4318>>\begin<<15186>>tex2html_deferred<<15186>>\bf\end<<15187>>tex2html_deferred<<15187>>x<<4318>>)\ge<<4319>>\begin<<15188>>tex2html_deferred<<15188>>\bf\end<<15189>>tex2html_deferred<<15189>>0<<4319>>
    \end<<4320>>array<<4320>> \right.
  \end<<4321>>array<<4321>>
\end<<4322>>equation<<4322>>
with its Lagrangian:
\begin<<4323>>equation<<4323>>
  L(<<4324>>\begin<<15190>>tex2html_deferred<<15190>>\bf\end<<15191>>tex2html_deferred<<15191>>x<<4324>>,<<4325>>\begin<<15192>>tex2html_deferred<<15192>>\bf\end<<15193>>tex2html_deferred<<15193>>\lambda<<4325>>,<<4326>>\begin<<15194>>tex2html_deferred<<15194>>\bf\end<<15195>>tex2html_deferred<<15195>>\mu<<4326>>)
  =f_p(<<4327>>\begin<<15196>>tex2html_deferred<<15196>>\bf\end<<15197>>tex2html_deferred<<15197>>x<<4327>>)-<<4328>>\begin<<15198>>tex2html_deferred<<15198>>\bf\end<<15199>>tex2html_deferred<<15199>>\lambda<<4328>>^T<<4329>>\begin<<15200>>tex2html_deferred<<15200>>\bf\end<<15201>>tex2html_deferred<<15201>>h<<4329>>(<<4330>>\begin<<15202>>tex2html_deferred<<15202>>\bf\end<<15203>>tex2html_deferred<<15203>>x<<4330>>)-<<4331>>\begin<<15204>>tex2html_deferred<<15204>>\bf\end<<15205>>tex2html_deferred<<15205>>\mu<<4331>>^T<<4332>>\begin<<15206>>tex2html_deferred<<15206>>\bf\end<<15207>>tex2html_deferred<<15207>>g<<4332>>(<<4333>>\begin<<15208>>tex2html_deferred<<15208>>\bf\end<<15209>>tex2html_deferred<<15209>>x<<4333>>)
\end<<4334>>equation<<4334>>
As this is a minimization problem, here \begin<<8630>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8630>>$\mu^T g(<<4335>>\begin<<15210>>tex2html_deferred<<15210>>\bf\end<<15211>>tex2html_deferred<<15211>>x<<4335>>)\ge 0$\end<<8631>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8631>>\space as
indicated in Table \ref<<4336>>PolarityTable<<4336>>.
\begin<<15212>>tex2html_deferred<<15212>>\par\end<<15213>>tex2html_deferred<<15213>>
We now consider the <<4337>>\begin<<15214>>tex2html_deferred<<15214>>\em\end<<15215>>tex2html_deferred<<15215>>dual function<<4337>> defined as the infimum 
(lower bound) of the Lagrangian over \begin<<8632>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8632>>$<<4338>>\begin<<15216>>tex2html_deferred<<15216>>\bf\end<<15217>>tex2html_deferred<<15217>>x<<4338>>$\end<<8633>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8633>>:
\begin<<4339>>equation<<4339>>
  f_d(<<4340>>\begin<<15218>>tex2html_deferred<<15218>>\bf\end<<15219>>tex2html_deferred<<15219>>\lambda<<4340>>,<<4341>>\begin<<15220>>tex2html_deferred<<15220>>\bf\end<<15221>>tex2html_deferred<<15221>>\mu<<4341>>)
  =\inf_<<4342>>\begin<<15222>>tex2html_deferred<<15222>>\bf\end<<15223>>tex2html_deferred<<15223>>x<<4342>> L(<<4343>>\begin<<15224>>tex2html_deferred<<15224>>\bf\end<<15225>>tex2html_deferred<<15225>>x<<4343>>,<<4344>>\begin<<15226>>tex2html_deferred<<15226>>\bf\end<<15227>>tex2html_deferred<<15227>>\lambda<<4344>>,<<4345>>\begin<<15228>>tex2html_deferred<<15228>>\bf\end<<15229>>tex2html_deferred<<15229>>\mu<<4345>>)
  =\inf_<<4346>>\begin<<15230>>tex2html_deferred<<15230>>\bf\end<<15231>>tex2html_deferred<<15231>>x<<4346>>\left[ f_p(<<4347>>\begin<<15232>>tex2html_deferred<<15232>>\bf\end<<15233>>tex2html_deferred<<15233>>x<<4347>>)-<<4348>>\begin<<15234>>tex2html_deferred<<15234>>\bf\end<<15235>>tex2html_deferred<<15235>>\lambda<<4348>>^T<<4349>>\begin<<15236>>tex2html_deferred<<15236>>\bf\end<<15237>>tex2html_deferred<<15237>>h<<4349>>(<<4350>>\begin<<15238>>tex2html_deferred<<15238>>\bf\end<<15239>>tex2html_deferred<<15239>>x<<4350>>)
    -<<4351>>\begin<<15240>>tex2html_deferred<<15240>>\bf\end<<15241>>tex2html_deferred<<15241>>\mu<<4351>>^T<<4352>>\begin<<15242>>tex2html_deferred<<15242>>\bf\end<<15243>>tex2html_deferred<<15243>>g<<4352>>(<<4353>>\begin<<15244>>tex2html_deferred<<15244>>\bf\end<<15245>>tex2html_deferred<<15245>>x<<4353>>)\right]
\end<<4354>>equation<<4354>>
which can be obtained by solving the equation
\begin<<8634>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8634>>$\bigtriangledown_<<4355>>\begin<<15246>>tex2html_deferred<<15246>>\bf\end<<15247>>tex2html_deferred<<15247>>x<<4355>>L(<<4356>>\begin<<15248>>tex2html_deferred<<15248>>\bf\end<<15249>>tex2html_deferred<<15249>>x<<4356>>,<<4357>>\begin<<15250>>tex2html_deferred<<15250>>\bf\end<<15251>>tex2html_deferred<<15251>>\lambda<<4357>>,<<4358>>\begin<<15252>>tex2html_deferred<<15252>>\bf\end<<15253>>tex2html_deferred<<15253>>\mu<<4358>>)=<<4359>>\begin<<15254>>tex2html_deferred<<15254>>\bf\end<<15255>>tex2html_deferred<<15255>>0<<4359>>$\end<<8635>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8635>>\space to 
get \begin<<8636>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8636>>$<<4360>>\begin<<15256>>tex2html_deferred<<15256>>\bf\end<<15257>>tex2html_deferred<<15257>>x<<4360>>$\end<<8637>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8637>>\space that minimizes the Lagrangian, and then substituting 
it back into the Lagrangian. Moreover, in order to obtain the 
tightest lower bound, the supremum (upper bound) of the dual function 
\begin<<8638>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8638>>$f_d(<<4361>>\begin<<15258>>tex2html_deferred<<15258>>\bf\end<<15259>>tex2html_deferred<<15259>>\lambda<<4361>>,<<4362>>\begin<<15260>>tex2html_deferred<<15260>>\bf\end<<15261>>tex2html_deferred<<15261>>\mu<<4362>>)$\end<<8639>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8639>>\space over all possible values for its variables
\begin<<8640>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8640>>$<<4363>>\begin<<15262>>tex2html_deferred<<15262>>\bf\end<<15263>>tex2html_deferred<<15263>>\lambda<<4363>>$\end<<8641>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8641>>\space and \begin<<8642>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8642>>$<<4364>>\begin<<15264>>tex2html_deferred<<15264>>\bf\end<<15265>>tex2html_deferred<<15265>>\mu<<4364>>$\end<<8643>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8643>>, we need to solve the following optimization
problem:
\begin<<4365>>equation<<4365>>
  \begin<<4366>>array<<4366>><<4367>>ll<<4367>>
    \mbox<<4368>>maximize<<4368>> ;SPMamp; f_d(<<4369>>\begin<<15266>>tex2html_deferred<<15266>>\bf\end<<15267>>tex2html_deferred<<15267>>\lambda<<4369>>,<<4370>>\begin<<15268>>tex2html_deferred<<15268>>\bf\end<<15269>>tex2html_deferred<<15269>>\mu<<4370>>)
    =\inf_<<4371>>\begin<<15270>>tex2html_deferred<<15270>>\bf\end<<15271>>tex2html_deferred<<15271>>x<<4371>>L(<<4372>>\begin<<15272>>tex2html_deferred<<15272>>\bf\end<<15273>>tex2html_deferred<<15273>>x<<4372>>,<<4373>>\begin<<15274>>tex2html_deferred<<15274>>\bf\end<<15275>>tex2html_deferred<<15275>>\lambda<<4373>>,<<4374>>\begin<<15276>>tex2html_deferred<<15276>>\bf\end<<15277>>tex2html_deferred<<15277>>\mu<<4374>>)\\ 
    \mbox<<4375>>subject to:<<4375>> ;SPMamp; <<4376>>\begin<<15278>>tex2html_deferred<<15278>>\bf\end<<15279>>tex2html_deferred<<15279>>\mu<<4376>>\le<<4377>>\begin<<15280>>tex2html_deferred<<15280>>\bf\end<<15281>>tex2html_deferred<<15281>>0<<4377>>\;\;\mbox<<4378>>or<<4378>>\;\;
    <<4379>>\begin<<15282>>tex2html_deferred<<15282>>\bf\end<<15283>>tex2html_deferred<<15283>>\mu<<4379>>\ge<<4380>>\begin<<15284>>tex2html_deferred<<15284>>\bf\end<<15285>>tex2html_deferred<<15285>>0<<4380>>
  \end<<4381>>array<<4381>>
\end<<4382>>equation<<4382>>
This is the <<4383>>\begin<<15286>>tex2html_deferred<<15286>>\em\end<<15287>>tex2html_deferred<<15287>>dual problem<<4383>> of the original primal problem.
Note that which of the two inequalities of the dual problem is used 
depends on which of the two inequalities of the primal problem is 
used, as indicated in Table \ref<<4384>>PolarityTable<<4384>>. Specifically, for 
this minimization primal problem, \begin<<8644>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8644>>$<<4385>>\begin<<15288>>tex2html_deferred<<15288>>\bf\end<<15289>>tex2html_deferred<<15289>>\mu<<4385>>^T<<4386>>\begin<<15290>>tex2html_deferred<<15290>>\bf\end<<15291>>tex2html_deferred<<15291>>g<<4386>>(<<4387>>\begin<<15292>>tex2html_deferred<<15292>>\bf\end<<15293>>tex2html_deferred<<15293>>x<<4387>>)\ge 0$\end<<8645>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8645>>
(Eq. (\ref<<4388>>mugminmax<<4388>>)), i.e., the inequality constraints of both
the primal and dual problems should be either greater or smaller than 
zero.
\begin<<15294>>tex2html_deferred<<15294>>\par\end<<15295>>tex2html_deferred<<15295>>
For any \begin<<8646>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8646>>$<<4389>>\begin<<15296>>tex2html_deferred<<15296>>\bf\end<<15297>>tex2html_deferred<<15297>>x<<4389>>$\end<<8647>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8647>>, including the solutions \begin<<8648>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8648>>$<<4390>>\begin<<15298>>tex2html_deferred<<15298>>\bf\end<<15299>>tex2html_deferred<<15299>>x<<4390>>^*$\end<<8649>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8649>>, in the 
feasible regions defined by \begin<<8650>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8650>>$<<4391>>\begin<<15300>>tex2html_deferred<<15300>>\bf\end<<15301>>tex2html_deferred<<15301>>h<<4391>>(<<4392>>\begin<<15302>>tex2html_deferred<<15302>>\bf\end<<15303>>tex2html_deferred<<15303>>x<<4392>>)=<<4393>>\begin<<15304>>tex2html_deferred<<15304>>\bf\end<<15305>>tex2html_deferred<<15305>>0<<4393>>$\end<<8651>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8651>>\space and 
\begin<<8652>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8652>>$<<4394>>\begin<<15306>>tex2html_deferred<<15306>>\bf\end<<15307>>tex2html_deferred<<15307>>g<<4394>>(<<4395>>\begin<<15308>>tex2html_deferred<<15308>>\bf\end<<15309>>tex2html_deferred<<15309>>x<<4395>>)\ge<<4396>>\begin<<15310>>tex2html_deferred<<15310>>\bf\end<<15311>>tex2html_deferred<<15311>>0<<4396>>$\end<<8653>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8653>>, the following holds
\begin<<4397>>equation<<4397>>
  f_d(<<4398>>\begin<<15312>>tex2html_deferred<<15312>>\bf\end<<15313>>tex2html_deferred<<15313>>\lambda<<4398>>,<<4399>>\begin<<15314>>tex2html_deferred<<15314>>\bf\end<<15315>>tex2html_deferred<<15315>>\mu<<4399>>)\le L(<<4400>>\begin<<15316>>tex2html_deferred<<15316>>\bf\end<<15317>>tex2html_deferred<<15317>>x<<4400>>,<<4401>>\begin<<15318>>tex2html_deferred<<15318>>\bf\end<<15319>>tex2html_deferred<<15319>>\lambda<<4401>>,<<4402>>\begin<<15320>>tex2html_deferred<<15320>>\bf\end<<15321>>tex2html_deferred<<15321>>\mu<<4402>>)
  =f_p(<<4403>>\begin<<15322>>tex2html_deferred<<15322>>\bf\end<<15323>>tex2html_deferred<<15323>>x<<4403>>)-<<4404>>\begin<<15324>>tex2html_deferred<<15324>>\bf\end<<15325>>tex2html_deferred<<15325>>\lambda<<4404>>^T<<4405>>\begin<<15326>>tex2html_deferred<<15326>>\bf\end<<15327>>tex2html_deferred<<15327>>h<<4405>>(<<4406>>\begin<<15328>>tex2html_deferred<<15328>>\bf\end<<15329>>tex2html_deferred<<15329>>x<<4406>>)-<<4407>>\begin<<15330>>tex2html_deferred<<15330>>\bf\end<<15331>>tex2html_deferred<<15331>>\mu<<4407>>^T<<4408>>\begin<<15332>>tex2html_deferred<<15332>>\bf\end<<15333>>tex2html_deferred<<15333>>g<<4408>>(<<4409>>\begin<<15334>>tex2html_deferred<<15334>>\bf\end<<15335>>tex2html_deferred<<15335>>x<<4409>>)
  \le f_p(<<4410>>\begin<<15336>>tex2html_deferred<<15336>>\bf\end<<15337>>tex2html_deferred<<15337>>x<<4410>>)-<<4411>>\begin<<15338>>tex2html_deferred<<15338>>\bf\end<<15339>>tex2html_deferred<<15339>>\mu<<4411>>^T<<4412>>\begin<<15340>>tex2html_deferred<<15340>>\bf\end<<15341>>tex2html_deferred<<15341>>g<<4412>>(<<4413>>\begin<<15342>>tex2html_deferred<<15342>>\bf\end<<15343>>tex2html_deferred<<15343>>x<<4413>>) \le f_p(<<4414>>\begin<<15344>>tex2html_deferred<<15344>>\bf\end<<15345>>tex2html_deferred<<15345>>x<<4414>>)
\end<<4415>>equation<<4415>>
We further define \begin<<8654>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8654>>$d^*=f_d(<<4416>>\begin<<15346>>tex2html_deferred<<15346>>\bf\end<<15347>>tex2html_deferred<<15347>>\lambda<<4416>>^*,<<4417>>\begin<<15348>>tex2html_deferred<<15348>>\bf\end<<15349>>tex2html_deferred<<15349>>\mu<<4417>>^*)$\end<<8655>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8655>>\space and 
\begin<<8656>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8656>>$f_p(<<4418>>\begin<<15350>>tex2html_deferred<<15350>>\bf\end<<15351>>tex2html_deferred<<15351>>x<<4418>>^*)=p^*$\end<<8657>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8657>>, and get
\begin<<4419>>equation<<4419>>
  d^*=f_d(<<4420>>\begin<<15352>>tex2html_deferred<<15352>>\bf\end<<15353>>tex2html_deferred<<15353>>\lambda<<4420>>^*,<<4421>>\begin<<15354>>tex2html_deferred<<15354>>\bf\end<<15355>>tex2html_deferred<<15355>>\mu<<4421>>^*)\le L(<<4422>>\begin<<15356>>tex2html_deferred<<15356>>\bf\end<<15357>>tex2html_deferred<<15357>>x<<4422>>,<<4423>>\begin<<15358>>tex2html_deferred<<15358>>\bf\end<<15359>>tex2html_deferred<<15359>>\lambda<<4423>>,<<4424>>\begin<<15360>>tex2html_deferred<<15360>>\bf\end<<15361>>tex2html_deferred<<15361>>\mu<<4424>>)
  \le f_p(<<4425>>\begin<<15362>>tex2html_deferred<<15362>>\bf\end<<15363>>tex2html_deferred<<15363>>x<<4425>>^*)=p^*
\end<<4426>>equation<<4426>>
\begin<<15364>>tex2html_deferred<<15364>>\par\end<<15365>>tex2html_deferred<<15365>>
Similarly, we can also show that a primal maximization problem with
solution \begin<<8658>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8658>>$<<4427>>\begin<<15366>>tex2html_deferred<<15366>>\bf\end<<15367>>tex2html_deferred<<15367>>x<<4427>>^*$\end<<8659>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8659>>\space that satisfies \begin<<8660>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8660>>$p^*=f(<<4428>>\begin<<15368>>tex2html_deferred<<15368>>\bf\end<<15369>>tex2html_deferred<<15369>>x<<4428>>^*)\ge f(<<4429>>\begin<<15370>>tex2html_deferred<<15370>>\bf\end<<15371>>tex2html_deferred<<15371>>x<<4429>>)$\end<<8661>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8661>>\space has
a dual minimization problem with solution \begin<<8662>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8662>>$<<4430>>\begin<<15372>>tex2html_deferred<<15372>>\bf\end<<15373>>tex2html_deferred<<15373>>\lambda<<4430>>^*,\;<<4431>>\begin<<15374>>tex2html_deferred<<15374>>\bf\end<<15375>>tex2html_deferred<<15375>>\mu<<4431>>^*$\end<<8663>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8663>>
that satisfies
\begin<<4432>>equation<<4432>>
  d^*=f_d(<<4433>>\begin<<15376>>tex2html_deferred<<15376>>\bf\end<<15377>>tex2html_deferred<<15377>>\lambda<<4433>>^*,\;<<4434>>\begin<<15378>>tex2html_deferred<<15378>>\bf\end<<15379>>tex2html_deferred<<15379>>\mu<<4434>>^*)\ge f_p(<<4435>>\begin<<15380>>tex2html_deferred<<15380>>\bf\end<<15381>>tex2html_deferred<<15381>>x<<4435>>^*)=p^*
\end<<4436>>equation<<4436>>
\begin<<15382>>tex2html_deferred<<15382>>\par\end<<15383>>tex2html_deferred<<15383>>
We can therefore conclude that the solution of the dual problem always 
provides the tightest bound for the solution of the primal problem. The 
difference \begin<<8664>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8664>>$p^*-d^*\ge 0$\end<<8665>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8665>>\space for the minimization primal problem or 
\begin<<8666>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8666>>$d^*-p^*\ge 0$\end<<8667>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8667>>\space for the maximization primal problem is called the 
<<4437>>\begin<<15384>>tex2html_deferred<<15384>>\em\end<<15385>>tex2html_deferred<<15385>>duality gap<<4437>>. If the duality gap is non-zero, i.e., \begin<<8668>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8668>>$d^*\ne p^*$\end<<8669>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8669>>, 
the dual relationship is a <<4438>>\begin<<15386>>tex2html_deferred<<15386>>\em\end<<15387>>tex2html_deferred<<15387>>weak duality<<4438>>, otherwise it is a 
<<4439>>\begin<<15388>>tex2html_deferred<<15388>>\em\end<<15389>>tex2html_deferred<<15389>>strong duality<<4439>>, for which the following holds:
\begin<<4440>>eqnarray<<4440>>
  d^*;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;f_d(<<4441>>\begin<<15390>>tex2html_deferred<<15390>>\bf\end<<15391>>tex2html_deferred<<15391>>\lambda<<4441>>^*,<<4442>>\begin<<15392>>tex2html_deferred<<15392>>\bf\end<<15393>>tex2html_deferred<<15393>>\mu<<4442>>^*)= L(<<4443>>\begin<<15394>>tex2html_deferred<<15394>>\bf\end<<15395>>tex2html_deferred<<15395>>x<<4443>>^*,<<4444>>\begin<<15396>>tex2html_deferred<<15396>>\bf\end<<15397>>tex2html_deferred<<15397>>\lambda<<4444>>^*,<<4445>>\begin<<15398>>tex2html_deferred<<15398>>\bf\end<<15399>>tex2html_deferred<<15399>>\mu<<4445>>^*)
  =f_p(<<4446>>\begin<<15400>>tex2html_deferred<<15400>>\bf\end<<15401>>tex2html_deferred<<15401>>x<<4446>>^*)-<<4447>>\begin<<15402>>tex2html_deferred<<15402>>\bf\end<<15403>>tex2html_deferred<<15403>>\lambda<<4447>>^<<4448>>*T<<4448>><<4449>>\begin<<15404>>tex2html_deferred<<15404>>\bf\end<<15405>>tex2html_deferred<<15405>>h<<4449>>(<<4450>>\begin<<15406>>tex2html_deferred<<15406>>\bf\end<<15407>>tex2html_deferred<<15407>>x<<4450>>^*)-<<4451>>\begin<<15408>>tex2html_deferred<<15408>>\bf\end<<15409>>tex2html_deferred<<15409>>\mu<<4451>>^<<4452>>*T<<4452>><<4453>>\begin<<15410>>tex2html_deferred<<15410>>\bf\end<<15411>>tex2html_deferred<<15411>>g<<4453>>(<<4454>>\begin<<15412>>tex2html_deferred<<15412>>\bf\end<<15413>>tex2html_deferred<<15413>>x<<4454>>^*)
  \nonumber\\ 
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;f_p(<<4455>>\begin<<15414>>tex2html_deferred<<15414>>\bf\end<<15415>>tex2html_deferred<<15415>>x<<4455>>^*)-<<4456>>\begin<<15416>>tex2html_deferred<<15416>>\bf\end<<15417>>tex2html_deferred<<15417>>\mu<<4456>>^<<4457>>*T<<4457>><<4458>>\begin<<15418>>tex2html_deferred<<15418>>\bf\end<<15419>>tex2html_deferred<<15419>>g<<4458>>(<<4459>>\begin<<15420>>tex2html_deferred<<15420>>\bf\end<<15421>>tex2html_deferred<<15421>>x<<4459>>^*) =f_p(<<4460>>\begin<<15422>>tex2html_deferred<<15422>>\bf\end<<15423>>tex2html_deferred<<15423>>x<<4460>>^*)=p^*
  \nonumber
\end<<4461>>eqnarray<<4461>>
which further implies all following equations must hold:
\begin<<4462>>equation<<4462>>
  \left\{\begin<<4463>>array<<4463>><<4464>>ll<<4464>>
  \bigtriangledown_<<4465>>\begin<<15424>>tex2html_deferred<<15424>>\bf\end<<15425>>tex2html_deferred<<15425>>x<<4465>> L(<<4466>>\begin<<15426>>tex2html_deferred<<15426>>\bf\end<<15427>>tex2html_deferred<<15427>>x<<4466>>^*,<<4467>>\begin<<15428>>tex2html_deferred<<15428>>\bf\end<<15429>>tex2html_deferred<<15429>>\lambda<<4467>>,<<4468>>\begin<<15430>>tex2html_deferred<<15430>>\bf\end<<15431>>tex2html_deferred<<15431>>\mu<<4468>>)
  =\bigtriangledown_<<4469>>\begin<<15432>>tex2html_deferred<<15432>>\bf\end<<15433>>tex2html_deferred<<15433>>x<<4469>> f(<<4470>>\begin<<15434>>tex2html_deferred<<15434>>\bf\end<<15435>>tex2html_deferred<<15435>>x<<4470>>^*)
  -\sum_<<4471>>i=1<<4471>>^m\lambda_i \bigtriangledown_<<4472>>\begin<<15436>>tex2html_deferred<<15436>>\bf\end<<15437>>tex2html_deferred<<15437>>x<<4472>> h_i(<<4473>>\begin<<15438>>tex2html_deferred<<15438>>\bf\end<<15439>>tex2html_deferred<<15439>>x<<4473>>^*)
  -\sum_<<4474>>j=1<<4474>>^n\mu_j     \bigtriangledown_<<4475>>\begin<<15440>>tex2html_deferred<<15440>>\bf\end<<15441>>tex2html_deferred<<15441>>x<<4475>> g_j(<<4476>>\begin<<15442>>tex2html_deferred<<15442>>\bf\end<<15443>>tex2html_deferred<<15443>>x<<4476>>^*)=<<4477>>\begin<<15444>>tex2html_deferred<<15444>>\bf\end<<15445>>tex2html_deferred<<15445>>0<<4477>>
  ;SPMamp; \mbox<<4478>>(stationarity)<<4478>>  \\ 
  \left\{\begin<<4479>>array<<4479>><<4480>>l<<4480>>
  h_i(<<4481>>\begin<<15446>>tex2html_deferred<<15446>>\bf\end<<15447>>tex2html_deferred<<15447>>x<<4481>>^*)=0,\;\;\;\;\;(i=1,\cdots,m)\\ 
  g_j(<<4482>>\begin<<15448>>tex2html_deferred<<15448>>\bf\end<<15449>>tex2html_deferred<<15449>>x<<4482>>^*)\le 0\;\;\mbox<<4483>>or<<4483>>\;\; g_j(<<4484>>\begin<<15450>>tex2html_deferred<<15450>>\bf\end<<15451>>tex2html_deferred<<15451>>x<<4484>>^*)\ge 0,\;\;\;
  (j=1,\cdots,n)
  \end<<4485>>array<<4485>>\right.;SPMamp;\mbox<<4486>>(primal feasibility)<<4486>>  \\ 
  \mu_j^*\le 0,\;\;\mbox<<4487>>or<<4487>>\;\;\mu_j^*\ge 0,\;\;\;\;(j=1,\cdots,n);SPMamp;
  \mbox<<4488>>(dual feasibility)<<4488>> \\ 
  \mu_j^*\,g_j(<<4489>>\begin<<15452>>tex2html_deferred<<15452>>\bf\end<<15453>>tex2html_deferred<<15453>>x<<4489>>^*)=0,\;\;\;\;\;(j=1,\cdots,n) ;SPMamp; 
  \mbox<<4490>>(complementarity)<<4490>>
  \end<<4491>>array<<4491>>\right.
  \label<<4492>>KKTConditions<<4492>>
\end<<4493>>equation<<4493>>
\begin<<15454>>tex2html_deferred<<15454>>\par\end<<15455>>tex2html_deferred<<15455>>
These are called the <<4494>>\begin<<15456>>tex2html_deferred<<15456>>\em\end<<15457>>tex2html_deferred<<15457>>Karush-Kuhn-Tucker (KKT) conditions<<4494>>, the 
necessary conditions for the solution of a constrained optimization 
problem, i.e., for any \begin<<8670>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8670>>$<<4495>>\begin<<15458>>tex2html_deferred<<15458>>\bf\end<<15459>>tex2html_deferred<<15459>>x<<4495>>$\end<<8671>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8671>>\space to be a solution, it must satisfy
all of the following:
\begin<<4496>>itemize<<4496>>
\item Stationarity: \begin<<8672>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8672>>$<<4497>>\begin<<15460>>tex2html_deferred<<15460>>\bf\end<<15461>>tex2html_deferred<<15461>>x<<4497>>$\end<<8673>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8673>>\space maximizes or minimizes the Lagrangian, 
  i.e., \begin<<8674>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8674>>$\bigtriangledown_<<4498>>\begin<<15462>>tex2html_deferred<<15462>>\bf\end<<15463>>tex2html_deferred<<15463>>x<<4498>>L(<<4499>>\begin<<15464>>tex2html_deferred<<15464>>\bf\end<<15465>>tex2html_deferred<<15465>>x<<4499>>,<<4500>>\begin<<15466>>tex2html_deferred<<15466>>\bf\end<<15467>>tex2html_deferred<<15467>>\lambda<<4500>>,<<4501>>\begin<<15468>>tex2html_deferred<<15468>>\bf\end<<15469>>tex2html_deferred<<15469>>\mu<<4501>>)=<<4502>>\begin<<15470>>tex2html_deferred<<15470>>\bf\end<<15471>>tex2html_deferred<<15471>>0<<4502>>$\end<<8675>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8675>>;
\item Primal feasibility: \begin<<8676>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8676>>$<<4503>>\begin<<15472>>tex2html_deferred<<15472>>\bf\end<<15473>>tex2html_deferred<<15473>>x<<4503>>$\end<<8677>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8677>>\space must be inside the feasible region;
\item Dual feasibility: all multipliers \begin<<8678>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8678>>$\mu_j$\end<<8679>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8679>>\space for the inequalities 
  must take the proper sign as specified by Table \ref<<4504>>PolarityTable<<4504>>;
\item Complementarity: one of \begin<<8680>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8680>>$\mu_j^*$\end<<8681>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8681>>\space and \begin<<8682>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8682>>$g_j(<<4505>>\begin<<15474>>tex2html_deferred<<15474>>\bf\end<<15475>>tex2html_deferred<<15475>>x<<4505>>^*)$\end<<8683>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8683>>\space must be 
  zero for the following two possible cases:
  \begin<<4506>>itemize<<4506>>
  \item the jth constraint is inactive, \begin<<8684>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8684>>$g_j(<<4507>>\begin<<15476>>tex2html_deferred<<15476>>\bf\end<<15477>>tex2html_deferred<<15477>>x<<4507>>^*)\ne 0$\end<<8685>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8685>>, \begin<<8686>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8686>>$\mu_j^*=0$\end<<8687>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8687>>;
  \item the jth constraint is active if \begin<<8688>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8688>>$\mu_j^*\ne 0$\end<<8689>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8689>>, \begin<<8690>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8690>>$g_j(<<4508>>\begin<<15478>>tex2html_deferred<<15478>>\bf\end<<15479>>tex2html_deferred<<15479>>x<<4508>>^*)=0$\end<<8691>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8691>>.
  \end<<4509>>itemize<<4509>>
\end<<4510>>itemize<<4510>>
\begin<<15480>>tex2html_deferred<<15480>>\par\end<<15481>>tex2html_deferred<<15481>>
\subsection*<<4511>>Linear Programming (LP)<<4511>>
\begin<<15482>>tex2html_deferred<<15482>>\par\end<<15483>>tex2html_deferred<<15483>>
The basic problem in linear programming (LP) is to maximize a linear 
objective function \begin<<8692>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8692>>$f(x_1,\cdots,x_N)=\sum_<<4512>>i=1<<4512>>^N c_ix_i$\end<<8693>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8693>>\space of \begin<<8694>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8694>>$N$\end<<8695>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8695>>\space variables
\begin<<8696>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8696>>$x_1,\cdots,x_N$\end<<8697>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8697>>\space (or minimize \begin<<8698>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8698>>$f'(x_1,\cdots,x_N)=-\sum_<<4513>>i=1<<4513>>^N c_ix_i$\end<<8699>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8699>>), 
under a set of \begin<<8700>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8700>>$M$\end<<8701>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8701>>\space linear constraints. 
\begin<<4514>>equation<<4514>>
  \begin<<4515>>array<<4515>><<4516>>ll<<4516>>
    \mbox<<4517>>maximize<<4517>>    ;SPMamp; 
    f(x_1,\cdots,x_N)=\sum_<<4518>>i=1<<4518>>^N c_ix_i \\ 
    \;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\\ 
    \mbox<<4519>>subject to:<<4519>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{ \begin<<4520>>array<<4520>><<4521>>l<<4521>> 
      \sum_<<4522>>i=1<<4522>>^n a_<<4523>>1i<<4523>>x_i\le b_1\\ 
      \cdots \cdots \cdots \cdots\\ 
      \sum_<<4524>>i=1<<4524>>^N a_<<4525>>Mi<<4525>>x_i \le b_M\\ 
      x_1\ge 0,\cdots,x_N\ge 0
    \end<<4526>>array<<4526>> \right.
  \end<<4527>>array<<4527>>
\end<<4528>>equation<<4528>>
For example, the objective function could be the total profit, the 
constraints could be some limited resources. Let \begin<<8702>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8702>>$x_1,\cdots,x_N$\end<<8703>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8703>>\space represent
the quantities of \begin<<8704>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8704>>$N$\end<<8705>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8705>>\space different types of products, \begin<<8706>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8706>>$c_1,\cdots,c_N$\end<<8707>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8707>>\space represent 
their unit prices, and \begin<<8708>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8708>>$a_<<4529>>ij<<4529>>$\end<<8709>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8709>>\space represent the consumption of the ith resource 
of quantity \begin<<8710>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8710>>$b_i$\end<<8711>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8711>>\space by the jth product, the goal is to maximize the profit 
\begin<<8712>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8712>>$f(x_1,\cdots,x_N)$\end<<8713>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8713>>\space subject to the constraints imposed by the limited 
resources \begin<<8714>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8714>>$b_1,\cdots,b_M$\end<<8715>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8715>>.
\begin<<15484>>tex2html_deferred<<15484>>\par\end<<15485>>tex2html_deferred<<15485>>
Here all variables are assumed to be non-negative. If there exists a
variable that is not restricted, it can be eliminated. 
Specifically, we can solve one of the constraining equations for the
variable and use the resulting expression of the variable to replace
all its appearances in the problem. For example:
\begin<<4530>>equation<<4530>>
  \begin<<4531>>array<<4531>><<4532>>ll<<4532>>
    \mbox<<4533>>maximize<<4533>>    ;SPMamp; f(x,y,z)=2x-y+3z \\ 
    \mbox<<4534>>subject to:<<4534>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{\begin<<4535>>array<<4535>><<4536>>l<<4536>> x-2y+z=3\\ 3x-y+4z=10\\ 
    y \ge 0,\;\; z\ge 0\end<<4537>>array<<4537>>\right.\\ 
  \end<<4538>>array<<4538>>
\end<<4539>>equation<<4539>>
Solving the first constraining equation for the free variable \begin<<8716>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8716>>$x$\end<<8717>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8717>>, 
we get \begin<<8718>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8718>>$x=3+2y-z$\end<<8719>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8719>>. Substituting this into the objective function and 
the other constraint, we get \begin<<8720>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8720>>$2x-y+z=3y+z+6$\end<<8721>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8721>>\space and \begin<<8722>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8722>>$5y+z=1$\end<<8723>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8723>>, and the
problem can be reformulated as:
\begin<<4540>>equation<<4540>>
  \begin<<4541>>array<<4541>><<4542>>ll<<4542>>
    \mbox<<4543>>maximize<<4543>>    ;SPMamp; f(y,z)=3y+z+6 \\ 
    \mbox<<4544>>subject to:<<4544>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{\begin<<4545>>array<<4545>><<4546>>l<<4546>> 5y+z=1 \\ 
    y \ge 0,\;\; z\ge 0\end<<4547>>array<<4547>>\right.\\ 
  \end<<4548>>array<<4548>>
\end<<4549>>equation<<4549>>
\begin<<15486>>tex2html_deferred<<15486>>\par\end<<15487>>tex2html_deferred<<15487>>
The LP problem can be more concisely represented in matrix form:
\begin<<4550>>equation<<4550>>
  \begin<<4551>>array<<4551>><<4552>>ll<<4552>>
    \mbox<<4553>>maximize<<4553>> ;SPMamp; <<4554>>\begin<<15488>>tex2html_deferred<<15488>>\bf\end<<15489>>tex2html_deferred<<15489>>c<<4554>>^T<<4555>>\begin<<15490>>tex2html_deferred<<15490>>\bf\end<<15491>>tex2html_deferred<<15491>>x<<4555>>\\ 
    \mbox<<4556>>subject to<<4556>> ;SPMamp; \left\{\begin<<4557>>array<<4557>><<4558>>l<<4558>>
         <<4559>>\begin<<15492>>tex2html_deferred<<15492>>\bf\end<<15493>>tex2html_deferred<<15493>>Ax<<4559>>-<<4560>>\begin<<15494>>tex2html_deferred<<15494>>\bf\end<<15495>>tex2html_deferred<<15495>>b<<4560>>\le <<4561>>\begin<<15496>>tex2html_deferred<<15496>>\bf\end<<15497>>tex2html_deferred<<15497>>0<<4561>>\\ 
         <<4562>>\begin<<15498>>tex2html_deferred<<15498>>\bf\end<<15499>>tex2html_deferred<<15499>>x<<4562>>\ge <<4563>>\begin<<15500>>tex2html_deferred<<15500>>\bf\end<<15501>>tex2html_deferred<<15501>>0<<4563>>\end<<4564>>array<<4564>>\right.\\ 
  \end<<4565>>array<<4565>>
\end<<4566>>equation<<4566>>
where
\begin<<4567>>equation<<4567>>
<<4568>>\begin<<15502>>tex2html_deferred<<15502>>\bf\end<<15503>>tex2html_deferred<<15503>>x<<4568>>=\left[\begin<<4569>>array<<4569>><<4570>>c<<4570>>x_1\\ \vdots\\ x_N\end<<4571>>array<<4571>>\right]
\;\;\;\;\;\;
<<4572>>\begin<<15504>>tex2html_deferred<<15504>>\bf\end<<15505>>tex2html_deferred<<15505>>c<<4572>>=\left[\begin<<4573>>array<<4573>><<4574>>c<<4574>>c_1\\ \vdots\\ c_N\end<<4575>>array<<4575>>\right]
\;\;\;\;\;\;
<<4576>>\begin<<15506>>tex2html_deferred<<15506>>\bf\end<<15507>>tex2html_deferred<<15507>>b<<4576>>=\left[\begin<<4577>>array<<4577>><<4578>>c<<4578>>b_1\\ \vdots\\ b_M\end<<4579>>array<<4579>>\right]
\;\;\;\;\;\;
<<4580>>\begin<<15508>>tex2html_deferred<<15508>>\bf\end<<15509>>tex2html_deferred<<15509>>A<<4580>>=\left[\begin<<4581>>array<<4581>><<4582>>ccc<<4582>>a_<<4583>>11<<4583>>;SPMamp;\cdots;SPMamp;a_<<4584>>1N<<4584>>\\ 
\vdots ;SPMamp; \ddots ;SPMamp; \vdots \\ a_<<4585>>M1<<4585>>;SPMamp;\cdots;SPMamp;a_<<4586>>MN<<4586>>\end<<4587>>array<<4587>>\right]
\end<<4588>>equation<<4588>>
and the less or greater than signs in a vector inequality is understood
as an element-wise relationship between to the corresponding elements of
the vectors on the two sides.
\begin<<15510>>tex2html_deferred<<15510>>\par\end<<15511>>tex2html_deferred<<15511>>
Given the LP problem above, now called the <<4589>>\begin<<15512>>tex2html_deferred<<15512>>\em\end<<15513>>tex2html_deferred<<15513>>primal problem<<4589>>, we 
can find its <<4590>>\begin<<15514>>tex2html_deferred<<15514>>\em\end<<15515>>tex2html_deferred<<15515>>dual problem<<4590>> as discussed before for the general 
constrained optimization problems. We first construct the Lagrangian
of primal problem:
\begin<<4591>>equation<<4591>>
  L(<<4592>>\begin<<15516>>tex2html_deferred<<15516>>\bf\end<<15517>>tex2html_deferred<<15517>>x<<4592>>)=<<4593>>\begin<<15518>>tex2html_deferred<<15518>>\bf\end<<15519>>tex2html_deferred<<15519>>c<<4593>>^T<<4594>>\begin<<15520>>tex2html_deferred<<15520>>\bf\end<<15521>>tex2html_deferred<<15521>>x<<4594>>-<<4595>>\begin<<15522>>tex2html_deferred<<15522>>\bf\end<<15523>>tex2html_deferred<<15523>>y<<4595>>^T(<<4596>>\begin<<15524>>tex2html_deferred<<15524>>\bf\end<<15525>>tex2html_deferred<<15525>>Ax<<4596>>-<<4597>>\begin<<15526>>tex2html_deferred<<15526>>\bf\end<<15527>>tex2html_deferred<<15527>>b<<4597>>)
  =(<<4598>>\begin<<15528>>tex2html_deferred<<15528>>\bf\end<<15529>>tex2html_deferred<<15529>>c<<4598>>-<<4599>>\begin<<15530>>tex2html_deferred<<15530>>\bf\end<<15531>>tex2html_deferred<<15531>>A<<4599>>^T<<4600>>\begin<<15532>>tex2html_deferred<<15532>>\bf\end<<15533>>tex2html_deferred<<15533>>y<<4600>>)^T<<4601>>\begin<<15534>>tex2html_deferred<<15534>>\bf\end<<15535>>tex2html_deferred<<15535>>x<<4601>>+<<4602>>\begin<<15536>>tex2html_deferred<<15536>>\bf\end<<15537>>tex2html_deferred<<15537>>y<<4602>>^T<<4603>>\begin<<15538>>tex2html_deferred<<15538>>\bf\end<<15539>>tex2html_deferred<<15539>>b<<4603>>
\end<<4604>>equation<<4604>>
Here \begin<<8724>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8724>>$<<4605>>\begin<<15540>>tex2html_deferred<<15540>>\bf\end<<15541>>tex2html_deferred<<15541>>y<<4605>>=[y_1,\cdots,y_M]^T$\end<<8725>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8725>>\space contains the Lagrange multipliers 
for the inequality constraints \begin<<8726>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8726>>$<<4606>>\begin<<15542>>tex2html_deferred<<15542>>\bf\end<<15543>>tex2html_deferred<<15543>>Ax<<4606>>-<<4607>>\begin<<15544>>tex2html_deferred<<15544>>\bf\end<<15545>>tex2html_deferred<<15545>>b<<4607>>\le<<4608>>\begin<<15546>>tex2html_deferred<<15546>>\bf\end<<15547>>tex2html_deferred<<15547>>0<<4608>>$\end<<8727>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8727>>, and
\begin<<8728>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8728>>$<<4609>>\begin<<15548>>tex2html_deferred<<15548>>\bf\end<<15549>>tex2html_deferred<<15549>>y<<4609>>\ge<<4610>>\begin<<15550>>tex2html_deferred<<15550>>\bf\end<<15551>>tex2html_deferred<<15551>>0<<4610>>$\end<<8729>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8729>>\space according to Table \ref<<4611>>PolarityTable<<4611>> given
before. We define the dual function as the maximum of \begin<<8730>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8730>>$L(<<4612>>\begin<<15552>>tex2html_deferred<<15552>>\bf\end<<15553>>tex2html_deferred<<15553>>x<<4612>>)$\end<<8731>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8731>> 
over \begin<<8732>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8732>>$<<4613>>\begin<<15554>>tex2html_deferred<<15554>>\bf\end<<15555>>tex2html_deferred<<15555>>x<<4613>>$\end<<8733>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8733>>:
\begin<<4614>>equation<<4614>>
  f_d(<<4615>>\begin<<15556>>tex2html_deferred<<15556>>\bf\end<<15557>>tex2html_deferred<<15557>>y<<4615>>)=\max_<<4616>>\begin<<15558>>tex2html_deferred<<15558>>\bf\end<<15559>>tex2html_deferred<<15559>>x<<4616>> L(<<4617>>\begin<<15560>>tex2html_deferred<<15560>>\bf\end<<15561>>tex2html_deferred<<15561>>x<<4617>>)
  =\max_<<4618>>\begin<<15562>>tex2html_deferred<<15562>>\bf\end<<15563>>tex2html_deferred<<15563>>x<<4618>> [ <<4619>>\begin<<15564>>tex2html_deferred<<15564>>\bf\end<<15565>>tex2html_deferred<<15565>>c<<4619>>^T<<4620>>\begin<<15566>>tex2html_deferred<<15566>>\bf\end<<15567>>tex2html_deferred<<15567>>x<<4620>>-<<4621>>\begin<<15568>>tex2html_deferred<<15568>>\bf\end<<15569>>tex2html_deferred<<15569>>y<<4621>>^T(<<4622>>\begin<<15570>>tex2html_deferred<<15570>>\bf\end<<15571>>tex2html_deferred<<15571>>Ax<<4622>>-<<4623>>\begin<<15572>>tex2html_deferred<<15572>>\bf\end<<15573>>tex2html_deferred<<15573>>b<<4623>>) ]
  =\max_<<4624>>\begin<<15574>>tex2html_deferred<<15574>>\bf\end<<15575>>tex2html_deferred<<15575>>x<<4624>> [ (<<4625>>\begin<<15576>>tex2html_deferred<<15576>>\bf\end<<15577>>tex2html_deferred<<15577>>c<<4625>>-<<4626>>\begin<<15578>>tex2html_deferred<<15578>>\bf\end<<15579>>tex2html_deferred<<15579>>A<<4626>>^T<<4627>>\begin<<15580>>tex2html_deferred<<15580>>\bf\end<<15581>>tex2html_deferred<<15581>>y<<4627>>)^T<<4628>>\begin<<15582>>tex2html_deferred<<15582>>\bf\end<<15583>>tex2html_deferred<<15583>>x<<4628>>+<<4629>>\begin<<15584>>tex2html_deferred<<15584>>\bf\end<<15585>>tex2html_deferred<<15585>>y<<4629>>^T<<4630>>\begin<<15586>>tex2html_deferred<<15586>>\bf\end<<15587>>tex2html_deferred<<15587>>b<<4630>> ]
\end<<4631>>equation<<4631>>
To find the value of \begin<<8734>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8734>>$<<4632>>\begin<<15588>>tex2html_deferred<<15588>>\bf\end<<15589>>tex2html_deferred<<15589>>x<<4632>>$\end<<8735>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8735>>\space that maximizes \begin<<8736>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8736>>$L(<<4633>>\begin<<15590>>tex2html_deferred<<15590>>\bf\end<<15591>>tex2html_deferred<<15591>>x<<4633>>)$\end<<8737>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8737>>, we set 
its gradient to zero:
\begin<<4634>>equation<<4634>>
  \bigtriangledown_<<4635>>\begin<<15592>>tex2html_deferred<<15592>>\bf\end<<15593>>tex2html_deferred<<15593>>x<<4635>>L(<<4636>>\begin<<15594>>tex2html_deferred<<15594>>\bf\end<<15595>>tex2html_deferred<<15595>>x<<4636>>)
  =\bigtriangledown_<<4637>>\begin<<15596>>tex2html_deferred<<15596>>\bf\end<<15597>>tex2html_deferred<<15597>>x<<4637>>[ (<<4638>>\begin<<15598>>tex2html_deferred<<15598>>\bf\end<<15599>>tex2html_deferred<<15599>>c<<4638>>-<<4639>>\begin<<15600>>tex2html_deferred<<15600>>\bf\end<<15601>>tex2html_deferred<<15601>>A<<4639>>^T<<4640>>\begin<<15602>>tex2html_deferred<<15602>>\bf\end<<15603>>tex2html_deferred<<15603>>y<<4640>>)^T<<4641>>\begin<<15604>>tex2html_deferred<<15604>>\bf\end<<15605>>tex2html_deferred<<15605>>x<<4641>>+<<4642>>\begin<<15606>>tex2html_deferred<<15606>>\bf\end<<15607>>tex2html_deferred<<15607>>y<<4642>>^T<<4643>>\begin<<15608>>tex2html_deferred<<15608>>\bf\end<<15609>>tex2html_deferred<<15609>>b<<4643>>]
  =<<4644>>\begin<<15610>>tex2html_deferred<<15610>>\bf\end<<15611>>tex2html_deferred<<15611>>c<<4644>>-<<4645>>\begin<<15612>>tex2html_deferred<<15612>>\bf\end<<15613>>tex2html_deferred<<15613>>A<<4645>>^T<<4646>>\begin<<15614>>tex2html_deferred<<15614>>\bf\end<<15615>>tex2html_deferred<<15615>>y<<4646>>=<<4647>>\begin<<15616>>tex2html_deferred<<15616>>\bf\end<<15617>>tex2html_deferred<<15617>>0<<4647>>
\end<<4648>>equation<<4648>>
and substitute it into \begin<<8738>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8738>>$L_d(<<4649>>\begin<<15618>>tex2html_deferred<<15618>>\bf\end<<15619>>tex2html_deferred<<15619>>y<<4649>>)=\max_<<4650>>\begin<<15620>>tex2html_deferred<<15620>>\bf\end<<15621>>tex2html_deferred<<15621>>x<<4650>>L(<<4651>>\begin<<15622>>tex2html_deferred<<15622>>\bf\end<<15623>>tex2html_deferred<<15623>>x<<4651>>)$\end<<8739>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8739>>\space to
get: \begin<<8740>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8740>>$f_d(<<4652>>\begin<<15624>>tex2html_deferred<<15624>>\bf\end<<15625>>tex2html_deferred<<15625>>y<<4652>>)=<<4653>>\begin<<15626>>tex2html_deferred<<15626>>\bf\end<<15627>>tex2html_deferred<<15627>>y<<4653>>^T<<4654>>\begin<<15628>>tex2html_deferred<<15628>>\bf\end<<15629>>tex2html_deferred<<15629>>b<<4654>>$\end<<8741>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8741>>, which is the maximum of
\begin<<8742>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8742>>$L(<<4655>>\begin<<15630>>tex2html_deferred<<15630>>\bf\end<<15631>>tex2html_deferred<<15631>>x<<4655>>,<<4656>>\begin<<15632>>tex2html_deferred<<15632>>\bf\end<<15633>>tex2html_deferred<<15633>>y<<4656>>)$\end<<8743>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8743>>, if \begin<<8744>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8744>>$<<4657>>\begin<<15634>>tex2html_deferred<<15634>>\bf\end<<15635>>tex2html_deferred<<15635>>c<<4657>>-<<4658>>\begin<<15636>>tex2html_deferred<<15636>>\bf\end<<15637>>tex2html_deferred<<15637>>A<<4658>>^T<<4659>>\begin<<15638>>tex2html_deferred<<15638>>\bf\end<<15639>>tex2html_deferred<<15639>>y<<4659>>\le 0$\end<<8745>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8745>>\space so that
the term \begin<<8746>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8746>>$(<<4660>>\begin<<15640>>tex2html_deferred<<15640>>\bf\end<<15641>>tex2html_deferred<<15641>>c<<4660>>-<<4661>>\begin<<15642>>tex2html_deferred<<15642>>\bf\end<<15643>>tex2html_deferred<<15643>>A<<4661>>^T<<4662>>\begin<<15644>>tex2html_deferred<<15644>>\bf\end<<15645>>tex2html_deferred<<15645>>y<<4662>>)^T<<4663>>\begin<<15646>>tex2html_deferred<<15646>>\bf\end<<15647>>tex2html_deferred<<15647>>x<<4663>>\le 0$\end<<8747>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8747>>\space contributes 
negatively to \begin<<8748>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8748>>$L(<<4664>>\begin<<15648>>tex2html_deferred<<15648>>\bf\end<<15649>>tex2html_deferred<<15649>>x<<4664>>)$\end<<8749>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8749>>\space (as \begin<<8750>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8750>>$<<4665>>\begin<<15650>>tex2html_deferred<<15650>>\bf\end<<15651>>tex2html_deferred<<15651>>x<<4665>>\ge 0$\end<<8751>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8751>>). Now \begin<<8752>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8752>>$f_d(<<4666>>\begin<<15652>>tex2html_deferred<<15652>>\bf\end<<15653>>tex2html_deferred<<15653>>y<<4666>>)$\end<<8753>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8753>>
is an upper bound of \begin<<8754>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8754>>$f_p(<<4667>>\begin<<15654>>tex2html_deferred<<15654>>\bf\end<<15655>>tex2html_deferred<<15655>>x<<4667>>)$\end<<8755>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8755>>:
\begin<<4668>>equation<<4668>>
f_d(<<4669>>\begin<<15656>>tex2html_deferred<<15656>>\bf\end<<15657>>tex2html_deferred<<15657>>y<<4669>>)=<<4670>>\begin<<15658>>tex2html_deferred<<15658>>\bf\end<<15659>>tex2html_deferred<<15659>>b<<4670>>^T<<4671>>\begin<<15660>>tex2html_deferred<<15660>>\bf\end<<15661>>tex2html_deferred<<15661>>y<<4671>>\ge L(<<4672>>\begin<<15662>>tex2html_deferred<<15662>>\bf\end<<15663>>tex2html_deferred<<15663>>x<<4672>>)
=<<4673>>\begin<<15664>>tex2html_deferred<<15664>>\bf\end<<15665>>tex2html_deferred<<15665>>c<<4673>>^T<<4674>>\begin<<15666>>tex2html_deferred<<15666>>\bf\end<<15667>>tex2html_deferred<<15667>>x<<4674>>-<<4675>>\begin<<15668>>tex2html_deferred<<15668>>\bf\end<<15669>>tex2html_deferred<<15669>>y<<4675>>^T(<<4676>>\begin<<15670>>tex2html_deferred<<15670>>\bf\end<<15671>>tex2html_deferred<<15671>>Ax<<4676>>-<<4677>>\begin<<15672>>tex2html_deferred<<15672>>\bf\end<<15673>>tex2html_deferred<<15673>>b<<4677>>) 
\ge<<4678>>\begin<<15674>>tex2html_deferred<<15674>>\bf\end<<15675>>tex2html_deferred<<15675>>c<<4678>>^T<<4679>>\begin<<15676>>tex2html_deferred<<15676>>\bf\end<<15677>>tex2html_deferred<<15677>>x<<4679>>=f_p(<<4680>>\begin<<15678>>tex2html_deferred<<15678>>\bf\end<<15679>>tex2html_deferred<<15679>>x<<4680>>)
\end<<4681>>equation<<4681>> 
We obtain the tightest upper bound by solving the following dual problem: 
\begin<<4682>>equation<<4682>>
  \begin<<4683>>array<<4683>><<4684>>ll<<4684>>
    \mbox<<4685>>minimize<<4685>> ;SPMamp; f_d(<<4686>>\begin<<15680>>tex2html_deferred<<15680>>\bf\end<<15681>>tex2html_deferred<<15681>>y<<4686>>)=<<4687>>\begin<<15682>>tex2html_deferred<<15682>>\bf\end<<15683>>tex2html_deferred<<15683>>b<<4687>>^T<<4688>>\begin<<15684>>tex2html_deferred<<15684>>\bf\end<<15685>>tex2html_deferred<<15685>>y<<4688>>\\ 
    \mbox<<4689>>subject to<<4689>> ;SPMamp; \left\{\begin<<4690>>array<<4690>><<4691>>l<<4691>>
         <<4692>>\begin<<15686>>tex2html_deferred<<15686>>\bf\end<<15687>>tex2html_deferred<<15687>>A<<4692>>^T<<4693>>\begin<<15688>>tex2html_deferred<<15688>>\bf\end<<15689>>tex2html_deferred<<15689>>y<<4693>>-<<4694>>\begin<<15690>>tex2html_deferred<<15690>>\bf\end<<15691>>tex2html_deferred<<15691>>c<<4694>>\ge <<4695>>\begin<<15692>>tex2html_deferred<<15692>>\bf\end<<15693>>tex2html_deferred<<15693>>0<<4695>>\\ 
         <<4696>>\begin<<15694>>tex2html_deferred<<15694>>\bf\end<<15695>>tex2html_deferred<<15695>>y<<4696>>\ge <<4697>>\begin<<15696>>tex2html_deferred<<15696>>\bf\end<<15697>>tex2html_deferred<<15697>>0<<4697>>\end<<4698>>array<<4698>>\right.\\ 
  \end<<4699>>array<<4699>>
\end<<4700>>equation<<4700>>
Following the same approach, we can also find the dual of a minimization
primal problem. Moreover, we can also show that the dual of a dual problem
is the original primal problem. Such duality relationships are summarized
below:
\begin<<4701>>equation<<4701>>
\left\{\begin<<4702>>array<<4702>><<4703>>ll<<4703>>\mbox<<4704>>max<<4704>>: ;SPMamp; <<4705>>\begin<<15698>>tex2html_deferred<<15698>>\bf\end<<15699>>tex2html_deferred<<15699>>c<<4705>>^T<<4706>>\begin<<15700>>tex2html_deferred<<15700>>\bf\end<<15701>>tex2html_deferred<<15701>>x<<4706>>\\ 
\mbox<<4707>>s.t.<<4707>> ;SPMamp; <<4708>>\begin<<15702>>tex2html_deferred<<15702>>\bf\end<<15703>>tex2html_deferred<<15703>>Ax<<4708>>-<<4709>>\begin<<15704>>tex2html_deferred<<15704>>\bf\end<<15705>>tex2html_deferred<<15705>>b<<4709>>\le<<4710>>\begin<<15706>>tex2html_deferred<<15706>>\bf\end<<15707>>tex2html_deferred<<15707>>0<<4710>>,\;\;<<4711>>\begin<<15708>>tex2html_deferred<<15708>>\bf\end<<15709>>tex2html_deferred<<15709>>x<<4711>>\ge<<4712>>\begin<<15710>>tex2html_deferred<<15710>>\bf\end<<15711>>tex2html_deferred<<15711>>0<<4712>>\end<<4713>>array<<4713>>\right.
\Longleftrightarrow
\left\{\begin<<4714>>array<<4714>><<4715>>ll<<4715>>\mbox<<4716>>min<<4716>> ;SPMamp; <<4717>>\begin<<15712>>tex2html_deferred<<15712>>\bf\end<<15713>>tex2html_deferred<<15713>>b<<4717>>^T<<4718>>\begin<<15714>>tex2html_deferred<<15714>>\bf\end<<15715>>tex2html_deferred<<15715>>y<<4718>>\\ 
\mbox<<4719>>s.t.<<4719>> ;SPMamp; <<4720>>\begin<<15716>>tex2html_deferred<<15716>>\bf\end<<15717>>tex2html_deferred<<15717>>Ay<<4720>>-<<4721>>\begin<<15718>>tex2html_deferred<<15718>>\bf\end<<15719>>tex2html_deferred<<15719>>c<<4721>>\ge<<4722>>\begin<<15720>>tex2html_deferred<<15720>>\bf\end<<15721>>tex2html_deferred<<15721>>0<<4722>>,\;\;<<4723>>\begin<<15722>>tex2html_deferred<<15722>>\bf\end<<15723>>tex2html_deferred<<15723>>y<<4723>>\ge<<4724>>\begin<<15724>>tex2html_deferred<<15724>>\bf\end<<15725>>tex2html_deferred<<15725>>0<<4724>>\end<<4725>>array<<4725>>\right.
\end<<4726>>equation<<4726>>
\begin<<4727>>equation<<4727>>
\left\{\begin<<4728>>array<<4728>><<4729>>ll<<4729>>\mbox<<4730>>min<<4730>>: ;SPMamp; <<4731>>\begin<<15726>>tex2html_deferred<<15726>>\bf\end<<15727>>tex2html_deferred<<15727>>c<<4731>>^T<<4732>>\begin<<15728>>tex2html_deferred<<15728>>\bf\end<<15729>>tex2html_deferred<<15729>>x<<4732>>\\ 
\mbox<<4733>>s.t.<<4733>> ;SPMamp; <<4734>>\begin<<15730>>tex2html_deferred<<15730>>\bf\end<<15731>>tex2html_deferred<<15731>>Ax<<4734>>-<<4735>>\begin<<15732>>tex2html_deferred<<15732>>\bf\end<<15733>>tex2html_deferred<<15733>>b<<4735>>\le<<4736>>\begin<<15734>>tex2html_deferred<<15734>>\bf\end<<15735>>tex2html_deferred<<15735>>0<<4736>>,\;\;<<4737>>\begin<<15736>>tex2html_deferred<<15736>>\bf\end<<15737>>tex2html_deferred<<15737>>x<<4737>>\ge<<4738>>\begin<<15738>>tex2html_deferred<<15738>>\bf\end<<15739>>tex2html_deferred<<15739>>0<<4738>>\end<<4739>>array<<4739>>\right.
\Longleftrightarrow
\left\{\begin<<4740>>array<<4740>><<4741>>ll<<4741>>\mbox<<4742>>max<<4742>> ;SPMamp; <<4743>>\begin<<15740>>tex2html_deferred<<15740>>\bf\end<<15741>>tex2html_deferred<<15741>>b<<4743>>^T<<4744>>\begin<<15742>>tex2html_deferred<<15742>>\bf\end<<15743>>tex2html_deferred<<15743>>y<<4744>>\\ 
\mbox<<4745>>s.t.<<4745>> ;SPMamp; <<4746>>\begin<<15744>>tex2html_deferred<<15744>>\bf\end<<15745>>tex2html_deferred<<15745>>Ay<<4746>>-<<4747>>\begin<<15746>>tex2html_deferred<<15746>>\bf\end<<15747>>tex2html_deferred<<15747>>c<<4747>>\le<<4748>>\begin<<15748>>tex2html_deferred<<15748>>\bf\end<<15749>>tex2html_deferred<<15749>>0<<4748>>,\;\;<<4749>>\begin<<15750>>tex2html_deferred<<15750>>\bf\end<<15751>>tex2html_deferred<<15751>>y<<4749>>\le<<4750>>\begin<<15752>>tex2html_deferred<<15752>>\bf\end<<15753>>tex2html_deferred<<15753>>0<<4750>>\end<<4751>>array<<4751>>\right.
\Longleftrightarrow
\left\{\begin<<4752>>array<<4752>><<4753>>ll<<4753>>\mbox<<4754>>max<<4754>> ;SPMamp; -<<4755>>\begin<<15754>>tex2html_deferred<<15754>>\bf\end<<15755>>tex2html_deferred<<15755>>b<<4755>>^T<<4756>>\begin<<15756>>tex2html_deferred<<15756>>\bf\end<<15757>>tex2html_deferred<<15757>>y<<4756>>\\ 
\mbox<<4757>>s.t.<<4757>> ;SPMamp; <<4758>>\begin<<15758>>tex2html_deferred<<15758>>\bf\end<<15759>>tex2html_deferred<<15759>>Ay<<4758>>+<<4759>>\begin<<15760>>tex2html_deferred<<15760>>\bf\end<<15761>>tex2html_deferred<<15761>>c<<4759>>\ge<<4760>>\begin<<15762>>tex2html_deferred<<15762>>\bf\end<<15763>>tex2html_deferred<<15763>>0<<4760>>,\;\;<<4761>>\begin<<15764>>tex2html_deferred<<15764>>\bf\end<<15765>>tex2html_deferred<<15765>>y<<4761>>\ge<<4762>>\begin<<15766>>tex2html_deferred<<15766>>\bf\end<<15767>>tex2html_deferred<<15767>>0<<4762>>\end<<4763>>array<<4763>>\right.
\end<<4764>>equation<<4764>>
\begin<<15768>>tex2html_deferred<<15768>>\par\end<<15769>>tex2html_deferred<<15769>>
If either the primal or the
dual is feasible and bounded, so is the other, and they form a
strong duality, the solution \begin<<8756>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8756>>$d^*$\end<<8757>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8757>>\space of the dual problem is the same
as the solution \begin<<8758>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8758>>$p^*$\end<<8759>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8759>>\space of the primal problem. Also, as the primal and
dual problems are completely symmetric, 
\begin<<15770>>tex2html_deferred<<15770>>\par\end<<15771>>tex2html_deferred<<15771>>
Similarly, we can also get the dual problem of an equality constrained 
standard LP problem:
\begin<<4765>>equation<<4765>>
  \begin<<4766>>array<<4766>><<4767>>ll<<4767>>
    \mbox<<4768>>minimize<<4768>> ;SPMamp; <<4769>>\begin<<15772>>tex2html_deferred<<15772>>\bf\end<<15773>>tex2html_deferred<<15773>>b<<4769>>^T<<4770>>\begin<<15774>>tex2html_deferred<<15774>>\bf\end<<15775>>tex2html_deferred<<15775>>y<<4770>>\\ 
    \mbox<<4771>>subject to<<4771>> ;SPMamp; <<4772>>\begin<<15776>>tex2html_deferred<<15776>>\bf\end<<15777>>tex2html_deferred<<15777>>A<<4772>>^T<<4773>>\begin<<15778>>tex2html_deferred<<15778>>\bf\end<<15779>>tex2html_deferred<<15779>>y<<4773>>-<<4774>>\begin<<15780>>tex2html_deferred<<15780>>\bf\end<<15781>>tex2html_deferred<<15781>>c<<4774>>\ge <<4775>>\begin<<15782>>tex2html_deferred<<15782>>\bf\end<<15783>>tex2html_deferred<<15783>>0<<4775>>\\ 
  \end<<4776>>array<<4776>>
\end<<4777>>equation<<4777>>
Note that the condition \begin<<8760>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8760>>$<<4778>>\begin<<15784>>tex2html_deferred<<15784>>\bf\end<<15785>>tex2html_deferred<<15785>>y<<4778>>\ge <<4779>>\begin<<15786>>tex2html_deferred<<15786>>\bf\end<<15787>>tex2html_deferred<<15787>>0<<4779>>$\end<<8761>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8761>>\space for the multipliers 
is dropped, due to the fact that the primal standard LP problem 
is equality constrained (instead of inequality constrained). The 
inequality constraints in the dual problem above can be further 
converted to equality constraints by introducing a set of 
<<4780>>\begin<<15788>>tex2html_deferred<<15788>>\em\end<<15789>>tex2html_deferred<<15789>>dual slack variables<<4780>> \begin<<8762>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8762>>$<<4781>>\begin<<15790>>tex2html_deferred<<15790>>\bf\end<<15791>>tex2html_deferred<<15791>>s<<4781>>\ge <<4782>>\begin<<15792>>tex2html_deferred<<15792>>\bf\end<<15793>>tex2html_deferred<<15793>>0<<4782>>$\end<<8763>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8763>>:
\begin<<4783>>equation<<4783>>
  \begin<<4784>>array<<4784>><<4785>>ll<<4785>>
    \mbox<<4786>>minimize<<4786>> ;SPMamp; <<4787>>\begin<<15794>>tex2html_deferred<<15794>>\bf\end<<15795>>tex2html_deferred<<15795>>b<<4787>>^T<<4788>>\begin<<15796>>tex2html_deferred<<15796>>\bf\end<<15797>>tex2html_deferred<<15797>>y<<4788>>\\ 
    \mbox<<4789>>subject to<<4789>> ;SPMamp; \left\{\begin<<4790>>array<<4790>><<4791>>l<<4791>>
         <<4792>>\begin<<15798>>tex2html_deferred<<15798>>\bf\end<<15799>>tex2html_deferred<<15799>>A<<4792>>^T<<4793>>\begin<<15800>>tex2html_deferred<<15800>>\bf\end<<15801>>tex2html_deferred<<15801>>y<<4793>>-<<4794>>\begin<<15802>>tex2html_deferred<<15802>>\bf\end<<15803>>tex2html_deferred<<15803>>s<<4794>>=<<4795>>\begin<<15804>>tex2html_deferred<<15804>>\bf\end<<15805>>tex2html_deferred<<15805>>c<<4795>>\\ 
         <<4796>>\begin<<15806>>tex2html_deferred<<15806>>\bf\end<<15807>>tex2html_deferred<<15807>>s<<4796>>\ge <<4797>>\begin<<15808>>tex2html_deferred<<15808>>\bf\end<<15809>>tex2html_deferred<<15809>>0<<4797>>\end<<4798>>array<<4798>>\right.\\ 
  \end<<4799>>array<<4799>>
\end<<4800>>equation<<4800>>
\begin<<15810>>tex2html_deferred<<15810>>\par\end<<15811>>tex2html_deferred<<15811>>
As \begin<<8764>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8764>>$<<4801>>\begin<<15812>>tex2html_deferred<<15812>>\bf\end<<15813>>tex2html_deferred<<15813>>c<<4801>>\le <<4802>>\begin<<15814>>tex2html_deferred<<15814>>\bf\end<<15815>>tex2html_deferred<<15815>>A<<4802>>^T<<4803>>\begin<<15816>>tex2html_deferred<<15816>>\bf\end<<15817>>tex2html_deferred<<15817>>y<<4803>>$\end<<8765>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8765>>\space and \begin<<8766>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8766>>$<<4804>>\begin<<15818>>tex2html_deferred<<15818>>\bf\end<<15819>>tex2html_deferred<<15819>>b<<4804>>\ge<<4805>>\begin<<15820>>tex2html_deferred<<15820>>\bf\end<<15821>>tex2html_deferred<<15821>>Ax<<4805>>$\end<<8767>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8767>>, we have the 
following
\begin<<4806>>equation<<4806>>
<<4807>>\begin<<15822>>tex2html_deferred<<15822>>\bf\end<<15823>>tex2html_deferred<<15823>>c<<4807>>^T<<4808>>\begin<<15824>>tex2html_deferred<<15824>>\bf\end<<15825>>tex2html_deferred<<15825>>x<<4808>>\le(<<4809>>\begin<<15826>>tex2html_deferred<<15826>>\bf\end<<15827>>tex2html_deferred<<15827>>A<<4809>>^T<<4810>>\begin<<15828>>tex2html_deferred<<15828>>\bf\end<<15829>>tex2html_deferred<<15829>>y<<4810>>)^T<<4811>>\begin<<15830>>tex2html_deferred<<15830>>\bf\end<<15831>>tex2html_deferred<<15831>>x<<4811>>
=<<4812>>\begin<<15832>>tex2html_deferred<<15832>>\bf\end<<15833>>tex2html_deferred<<15833>>y<<4812>>^T<<4813>>\begin<<15834>>tex2html_deferred<<15834>>\bf\end<<15835>>tex2html_deferred<<15835>>Ax<<4813>>=<<4814>>\begin<<15836>>tex2html_deferred<<15836>>\bf\end<<15837>>tex2html_deferred<<15837>>x<<4814>>^T<<4815>>\begin<<15838>>tex2html_deferred<<15838>>\bf\end<<15839>>tex2html_deferred<<15839>>A<<4815>>^T<<4816>>\begin<<15840>>tex2html_deferred<<15840>>\bf\end<<15841>>tex2html_deferred<<15841>>y<<4816>>
=(<<4817>>\begin<<15842>>tex2html_deferred<<15842>>\bf\end<<15843>>tex2html_deferred<<15843>>Ax<<4817>>)^T<<4818>>\begin<<15844>>tex2html_deferred<<15844>>\bf\end<<15845>>tex2html_deferred<<15845>>y<<4818>>\le<<4819>>\begin<<15846>>tex2html_deferred<<15846>>\bf\end<<15847>>tex2html_deferred<<15847>>b<<4819>>^T<<4820>>\begin<<15848>>tex2html_deferred<<15848>>\bf\end<<15849>>tex2html_deferred<<15849>>y<<4820>>
\end<<4821>>equation<<4821>>
therefore we get the dual gap \begin<<8768>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8768>>$<<4822>>\begin<<15850>>tex2html_deferred<<15850>>\bf\end<<15851>>tex2html_deferred<<15851>>b<<4822>>^T<<4823>>\begin<<15852>>tex2html_deferred<<15852>>\bf\end<<15853>>tex2html_deferred<<15853>>y<<4823>>\ge <<4824>>\begin<<15854>>tex2html_deferred<<15854>>\bf\end<<15855>>tex2html_deferred<<15855>>c<<4824>>^T<<4825>>\begin<<15856>>tex2html_deferred<<15856>>\bf\end<<15857>>tex2html_deferred<<15857>>x<<4825>>$\end<<8769>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8769>>.
\begin<<15858>>tex2html_deferred<<15858>>\par\end<<15859>>tex2html_deferred<<15859>>
The inequality constrained LP problem can be converted to an equality
constrained problem by introducing <<4826>>\begin<<15860>>tex2html_deferred<<15860>>\em\end<<15861>>tex2html_deferred<<15861>>slack variables<<4826>>:
\begin<<4827>>equation<<4827>>
  \sum_<<4828>>i=1<<4828>>^N a_ix_i\le b \;\;\;\Longrightarrow\;\;\;
  \sum_<<4829>>i=1<<4829>>^N a_ix_i + s = b,\;\;\;(s\ge 0)
\end<<4830>>equation<<4830>>
Now the inequality constrained LP problem can be reformulated to become 
an equality constrained problem, called the <<4831>>\begin<<15862>>tex2html_deferred<<15862>>\em\end<<15863>>tex2html_deferred<<15863>>standard form<<4831>>:
\begin<<4832>>equation<<4832>>
  \begin<<4833>>array<<4833>><<4834>>ll<<4834>>
    \mbox<<4835>>maximize<<4835>>    ;SPMamp; z=f(<<4836>>\begin<<15864>>tex2html_deferred<<15864>>\bf\end<<15865>>tex2html_deferred<<15865>>x<<4836>>)=<<4837>>\begin<<15866>>tex2html_deferred<<15866>>\bf\end<<15867>>tex2html_deferred<<15867>>c<<4837>>^T<<4838>>\begin<<15868>>tex2html_deferred<<15868>>\bf\end<<15869>>tex2html_deferred<<15869>>x<<4838>>=\sum_<<4839>>j=1<<4839>>^N c_jx_j\\ 
    \mbox<<4840>>subject to:<<4840>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{\begin<<4841>>array<<4841>><<4842>>llllll<<4842>>
    \sum_<<4843>>i=1<<4843>>^N a_<<4844>>1i<<4844>>x_i;SPMamp;+s_1;SPMamp; ;SPMamp; ;SPMamp; ;SPMamp; =b_1\\ 
    \sum_<<4845>>i=1<<4845>>^N a_<<4846>>2i<<4846>>x_i;SPMamp; ;SPMamp;+s_2;SPMamp; ;SPMamp; ;SPMamp; =b_2\\ 
    \cdots ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp;\cdots ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp;\cdots \\ 
    \sum_<<4847>>i=1<<4847>>^N a_<<4848>>Mi<<4848>>x_i ;SPMamp; ;SPMamp; ;SPMamp; ;SPMamp; +s_M;SPMamp; =b_M\\ 
    x_1\ge 0,;SPMamp;\cdots,;SPMamp; x_N\ge 0, ;SPMamp;s_1\ge 0,;SPMamp;\cdots;SPMamp; s_M\ge 0\end<<4849>>array<<4849>>\right.
  \end<<4850>>array<<4850>>
\end<<4851>>equation<<4851>>
We further redefine the following:
\begin<<4852>>itemize<<4852>>
\item \begin<<8770>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8770>>$<<4853>>\begin<<15870>>tex2html_deferred<<15870>>\bf\end<<15871>>tex2html_deferred<<15871>>x<<4853>>$\end<<8771>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8771>>\space is an \begin<<8772>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8772>>$N+M$\end<<8773>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8773>>\space dimensional augmented variable vector that
  includes the \begin<<8774>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8774>>$M$\end<<8775>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8775>>\space slack variables \begin<<8776>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8776>>$\{s_1,\cdots,s_M\}$\end<<8777>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8777>>\space as well as the 
  \begin<<8778>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8778>>$N$\end<<8779>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8779>>\space original variables \begin<<8780>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8780>>$\{x_1,\cdots,x_N\}$\end<<8781>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8781>>:
  \begin<<4854>>equation<<4854>>
  <<4855>>\begin<<15872>>tex2html_deferred<<15872>>\bf\end<<15873>>tex2html_deferred<<15873>>x<<4855>>=[x_1,\;x_2,\cdots,x_N,\,s_1,\;s_2,\cdots,s_M]^T
  \end<<4856>>equation<<4856>>
\item \begin<<8782>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8782>>$<<4857>>\begin<<15874>>tex2html_deferred<<15874>>\bf\end<<15875>>tex2html_deferred<<15875>>A<<4857>>$\end<<8783>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8783>>\space is redefined as an \begin<<8784>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8784>>$M\times (N+M)$\end<<8785>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8785>>\space augmented coefficient 
  matrix that includes coefficients for both types of variables:
  \begin<<4858>>equation<<4858>>
    <<4859>>\begin<<15876>>tex2html_deferred<<15876>>\bf\end<<15877>>tex2html_deferred<<15877>>A<<4859>>=\left[\begin<<4860>>array<<4860>><<4861>>cccc|cccc<<4861>>
        a_<<4862>>11<<4862>> ;SPMamp; a_<<4863>>12<<4863>> ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; a_<<4864>>1N<<4864>> ;SPMamp; 1 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; 0\\ 
        a_<<4865>>21<<4865>> ;SPMamp; a_<<4866>>22<<4866>> ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; a_<<4867>>1N<<4867>> ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 1 ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; 0\\ 
        \vdots;SPMamp;\vdots ;SPMamp; \ddots ;SPMamp;\vdots ;SPMamp;\vdots ;SPMamp; \vdots ;SPMamp; \ddots ;SPMamp; \vdots\\ 
        a_<<4868>>M1<<4868>> ;SPMamp; a_<<4869>>M2<<4869>> ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; a_<<4870>>MN<<4870>> ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 1\\ 
      \end<<4871>>array<<4871>>\right]_<<4872>>M\times (N+M)<<4872>>
    =[\;<<4873>>\begin<<15878>>tex2html_deferred<<15878>>\bf\end<<15879>>tex2html_deferred<<15879>>A<<4873>>_<<4874>>M\times N<<4874>>\;|\; <<4875>>\begin<<15880>>tex2html_deferred<<15880>>\bf\end<<15881>>tex2html_deferred<<15881>>I<<4875>>_<<4876>>M\times M<<4876>>\;]
  \end<<4877>>equation<<4877>>
  where \begin<<8786>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8786>>$<<4878>>\begin<<15882>>tex2html_deferred<<15882>>\bf\end<<15883>>tex2html_deferred<<15883>>A<<4878>>_<<4879>>M\times N<<4879>>$\end<<8787>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8787>>\space are the coefficients for the \begin<<8788>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8788>>$N$\end<<8789>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8789>> 
  original variables \begin<<8790>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8790>>$\{x_1,\cdots,x_N\}$\end<<8791>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8791>>, and the identity matrix 
  \begin<<8792>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8792>>$<<4880>>\begin<<15884>>tex2html_deferred<<15884>>\bf\end<<15885>>tex2html_deferred<<15885>>I<<4880>>_<<4881>>M\times M<<4881>>$\end<<8793>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8793>>\space is for the unity coefficients of the \begin<<8794>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8794>>$M$\end<<8795>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8795>>\space slack
  variables \begin<<8796>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8796>>$\{s_1,\cdots,s_M\}$\end<<8797>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8797>>, each of which appears in the \begin<<8798>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8798>>$M$\end<<8799>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8799>> 
  constraints only once.
\end<<4882>>itemize<<4882>>
\begin<<15886>>tex2html_deferred<<15886>>\par\end<<15887>>tex2html_deferred<<15887>>
Now the LP problem can be expressed in the standard form (original form 
on the left, with \begin<<8800>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8800>>$<<4883>>\begin<<15888>>tex2html_deferred<<15888>>\bf\end<<15889>>tex2html_deferred<<15889>>x<<4883>>$\end<<8801>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8801>>\space and \begin<<8802>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8802>>$<<4884>>\begin<<15890>>tex2html_deferred<<15890>>\bf\end<<15891>>tex2html_deferred<<15891>>A<<4884>>$\end<<8803>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8803>>\space redefined on the right):
\begin<<4885>>equation<<4885>> 
  \begin<<4886>>array<<4886>><<4887>>ll<<4887>>
    \mbox<<4888>>maximize<<4888>> ;SPMamp; <<4889>>\begin<<15892>>tex2html_deferred<<15892>>\bf\end<<15893>>tex2html_deferred<<15893>>c<<4889>>^T<<4890>>\begin<<15894>>tex2html_deferred<<15894>>\bf\end<<15895>>tex2html_deferred<<15895>>x<<4890>>\\ 
    \mbox<<4891>>subject to<<4891>> ;SPMamp;
    \left\{ \begin<<4892>>array<<4892>><<4893>>l<<4893>>
      <<4894>>\begin<<15896>>tex2html_deferred<<15896>>\bf\end<<15897>>tex2html_deferred<<15897>>A<<4894>><<4895>>\begin<<15898>>tex2html_deferred<<15898>>\bf\end<<15899>>tex2html_deferred<<15899>>x<<4895>>+<<4896>>\begin<<15900>>tex2html_deferred<<15900>>\bf\end<<15901>>tex2html_deferred<<15901>>s<<4896>>=<<4897>>\begin<<15902>>tex2html_deferred<<15902>>\bf\end<<15903>>tex2html_deferred<<15903>>b<<4897>>\\ 
      <<4898>>\begin<<15904>>tex2html_deferred<<15904>>\bf\end<<15905>>tex2html_deferred<<15905>>x<<4898>>\ge<<4899>>\begin<<15906>>tex2html_deferred<<15906>>\bf\end<<15907>>tex2html_deferred<<15907>>0<<4899>>,\;<<4900>>\begin<<15908>>tex2html_deferred<<15908>>\bf\end<<15909>>tex2html_deferred<<15909>>s<<4900>>\ge<<4901>>\begin<<15910>>tex2html_deferred<<15910>>\bf\end<<15911>>tex2html_deferred<<15911>>0<<4901>>
    \end<<4902>>array<<4902>>\right.
  \end<<4903>>array<<4903>>
  \;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\mbox<<4904>>or<<4904>>\;\;\;\;\;\;
  \begin<<4905>>array<<4905>><<4906>>ll<<4906>>
    \mbox<<4907>>maximize<<4907>> ;SPMamp; <<4908>>\begin<<15912>>tex2html_deferred<<15912>>\bf\end<<15913>>tex2html_deferred<<15913>>c<<4908>>^T<<4909>>\begin<<15914>>tex2html_deferred<<15914>>\bf\end<<15915>>tex2html_deferred<<15915>>x<<4909>>\\ 
    \mbox<<4910>>subject to<<4910>> ;SPMamp;
    \left\{ \begin<<4911>>array<<4911>><<4912>>l<<4912>>
      <<4913>>\begin<<15916>>tex2html_deferred<<15916>>\bf\end<<15917>>tex2html_deferred<<15917>>A<<4913>><<4914>>\begin<<15918>>tex2html_deferred<<15918>>\bf\end<<15919>>tex2html_deferred<<15919>>x<<4914>>=<<4915>>\begin<<15920>>tex2html_deferred<<15920>>\bf\end<<15921>>tex2html_deferred<<15921>>b<<4915>>\\ 
      <<4916>>\begin<<15922>>tex2html_deferred<<15922>>\bf\end<<15923>>tex2html_deferred<<15923>>x<<4916>>\ge<<4917>>\begin<<15924>>tex2html_deferred<<15924>>\bf\end<<15925>>tex2html_deferred<<15925>>0<<4917>>
    \end<<4918>>array<<4918>>\right.
  \end<<4919>>array<<4919>>
\end<<4920>>equation<<4920>>
\begin<<15926>>tex2html_deferred<<15926>>\par\end<<15927>>tex2html_deferred<<15927>>
An LP problem can be viewed geometrically. We can normalize 
\begin<<8804>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8804>>$<<4921>>\begin<<15928>>tex2html_deferred<<15928>>\bf\end<<15929>>tex2html_deferred<<15929>>c<<4921>>$\end<<8805>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8805>>\space so that \begin<<8806>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8806>>$||<<4922>>\begin<<15930>>tex2html_deferred<<15930>>\bf\end<<15931>>tex2html_deferred<<15931>>c<<4922>>||=1$\end<<8807>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8807>>, so that the objective function 
\begin<<8808>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8808>>$f(<<4923>>\begin<<15932>>tex2html_deferred<<15932>>\bf\end<<15933>>tex2html_deferred<<15933>>x<<4923>>)=<<4924>>\begin<<15934>>tex2html_deferred<<15934>>\bf\end<<15935>>tex2html_deferred<<15935>>c<<4924>>^T<<4925>>\begin<<15936>>tex2html_deferred<<15936>>\bf\end<<15937>>tex2html_deferred<<15937>>x<<4925>>$\end<<8809>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8809>>\space becomes the projection of \begin<<8810>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8810>>$<<4926>>\begin<<15938>>tex2html_deferred<<15938>>\bf\end<<15939>>tex2html_deferred<<15939>>x<<4926>>$\end<<8811>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8811>> 
onto vector \begin<<8812>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8812>>$<<4927>>\begin<<15940>>tex2html_deferred<<15940>>\bf\end<<15941>>tex2html_deferred<<15941>>c<<4927>>$\end<<8813>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8813>>. Each of the \begin<<8814>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8814>>$M$\end<<8815>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8815>>\space inequality constraints in 
\begin<<8816>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8816>>$<<4928>>\begin<<15942>>tex2html_deferred<<15942>>\bf\end<<15943>>tex2html_deferred<<15943>>A<<4928>><<4929>>\begin<<15944>>tex2html_deferred<<15944>>\bf\end<<15945>>tex2html_deferred<<15945>>x<<4929>>\le<<4930>>\begin<<15946>>tex2html_deferred<<15946>>\bf\end<<15947>>tex2html_deferred<<15947>>b<<4930>>$\end<<8817>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8817>>\space corresponds to a hyper-plane in the N-D 
vector space perpendicular to its normal direction 
\begin<<8818>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8818>>$<<4931>>\begin<<15948>>tex2html_deferred<<15948>>\bf\end<<15949>>tex2html_deferred<<15949>>a<<4931>>_j=[a_<<4932>>i1<<4932>>,\cdots,a_<<4933>>IN<<4933>>]^T$\end<<8819>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8819>>:
\begin<<4934>>equation<<4934>>
  \sum_<<4935>>j=1<<4935>>^N a_<<4936>>ij<<4936>>x_j=<<4937>>\begin<<15950>>tex2html_deferred<<15950>>\bf\end<<15951>>tex2html_deferred<<15951>>a<<4937>>_j^T<<4938>>\begin<<15952>>tex2html_deferred<<15952>>\bf\end<<15953>>tex2html_deferred<<15953>>x<<4938>>=b_i,\;\;\;\;\;\;\;(i=1,\cdots,M)
\end<<4939>>equation<<4939>>
Also, each of the \begin<<8820>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8820>>$N$\end<<8821>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8821>>\space non-negativity conditions \begin<<8822>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8822>>$x_j\ge 0$\end<<8823>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8823>>\space in
\begin<<8824>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8824>>$<<4940>>\begin<<15954>>tex2html_deferred<<15954>>\bf\end<<15955>>tex2html_deferred<<15955>>x<<4940>>\ge<<4941>>\begin<<15956>>tex2html_deferred<<15956>>\bf\end<<15957>>tex2html_deferred<<15957>>0<<4941>>$\end<<8825>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8825>>\space corresponds to a hyper-plane perpendicular to the 
jth standard basis vector \begin<<8826>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8826>>$<<4942>>\begin<<15958>>tex2html_deferred<<15958>>\bf\end<<15959>>tex2html_deferred<<15959>>e<<4942>>_j$\end<<8827>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8827>>. In the most general case (none 
of the hyper-planes is parallel to any others, no more than \begin<<8828>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8828>>$N$\end<<8829>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8829>> 
hyper-planes intersect at one point), every \begin<<8830>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8830>>$N$\end<<8831>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8831>>\space of these \begin<<8832>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8832>>$N+M$\end<<8833>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8833>> 
hyper-planes intersect at a point in the N-D space, and they form
\begin<<4943>>equation<<4943>>
  C_<<4944>>M+N<<4944>>^N=\frac<<4945>>(M+N)!<<4945>><<4946>>N!\;M!<<4946>>
\end<<4947>>equation<<4947>>
such intersection points in total.
The polytope enclosed by these \begin<<8834>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8834>>$N+M$\end<<8835>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8835>>\space hyper-planes is called the 
<<4948>>\begin<<15960>>tex2html_deferred<<15960>>\em\end<<15961>>tex2html_deferred<<15961>>feasible region<<4948>>, in which the optimal solution must lie. 
The vertices of the polytope of the feasible region are a subset 
of the \begin<<8836>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8836>>$C_<<4949>>M+N<<4949>>^N$\end<<8837>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8837>>\space intersections at which all constraints in 
\begin<<8838>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8838>>$<<4950>>\begin<<15962>>tex2html_deferred<<15962>>\bf\end<<15963>>tex2html_deferred<<15963>>A<<4950>><<4951>>\begin<<15964>>tex2html_deferred<<15964>>\bf\end<<15965>>tex2html_deferred<<15965>>x<<4951>>\le<<4952>>\begin<<15966>>tex2html_deferred<<15966>>\bf\end<<15967>>tex2html_deferred<<15967>>b<<4952>>$\end<<8839>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8839>>\space and \begin<<8840>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8840>>$<<4953>>\begin<<15968>>tex2html_deferred<<15968>>\bf\end<<15969>>tex2html_deferred<<15969>>x<<4953>>\ge<<4954>>\begin<<15970>>tex2html_deferred<<15970>>\bf\end<<15971>>tex2html_deferred<<15971>>0<<4954>>$\end<<8841>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8841>>\space are satisfied.
\begin<<15972>>tex2html_deferred<<15972>>\par\end<<15973>>tex2html_deferred<<15973>>
<<4955>>\begin<<15974>>tex2html_deferred<<15974>>\bf\end<<15975>>tex2html_deferred<<15975>>Fundamental theorem of linear programming<<4955>>
\begin<<15976>>tex2html_deferred<<15976>>\par\end<<15977>>tex2html_deferred<<15977>>
The optimal solution \begin<<8842>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8842>>$<<4956>>\begin<<15978>>tex2html_deferred<<15978>>\bf\end<<15979>>tex2html_deferred<<15979>>x<<4956>>^*$\end<<8843>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8843>>\space of a linear programming problem formulated 
above is either a vertex of the polytope feasible region \begin<<8844>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8844>>$P$\end<<8845>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8845>>, or lies on a 
hyper-surface of the polytope, on which all points all optimal solutions.
\begin<<15980>>tex2html_deferred<<15980>>\par\end<<15981>>tex2html_deferred<<15981>>
\htmladdimg<<4957>>figures/LPtheorem.png<<4957>>
\begin<<15982>>tex2html_deferred<<15982>>\par\end<<15983>>tex2html_deferred<<15983>>
<<4958>>\begin<<15984>>tex2html_deferred<<15984>>\bf\end<<15985>>tex2html_deferred<<15985>>Proof:<<4958>>
\begin<<15986>>tex2html_deferred<<15986>>\par\end<<15987>>tex2html_deferred<<15987>>
Assume the optimal solution \begin<<8846>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8846>>$<<4959>>\begin<<15988>>tex2html_deferred<<15988>>\bf\end<<15989>>tex2html_deferred<<15989>>x<<4959>>^*\in P$\end<<8847>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8847>>\space is interior to the polytope
feasible region \begin<<8848>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8848>>$P$\end<<8849>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8849>>, then there must exist some \begin<<8850>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8850>>$\epsilon;SPMgt;0$\end<<8851>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8851>>\space such that 
the hyper-sphere of radius \begin<<8852>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8852>>$\epsilon$\end<<8853>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8853>>\space centered at \begin<<8854>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8854>>$<<4960>>\begin<<15990>>tex2html_deferred<<15990>>\bf\end<<15991>>tex2html_deferred<<15991>>x<<4960>>^*$\end<<8855>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8855>>\space is inside 
\begin<<8856>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8856>>$P$\end<<8857>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8857>>. Evaluate the objective function at a point on the hyper-sphere
\begin<<4961>>equation<<4961>>
<<4962>>\begin<<15992>>tex2html_deferred<<15992>>\bf\end<<15993>>tex2html_deferred<<15993>>x<<4962>>'=<<4963>>\begin<<15994>>tex2html_deferred<<15994>>\bf\end<<15995>>tex2html_deferred<<15995>>x<<4963>>^*+\epsilon\;<<4964>>\begin<<15996>>tex2html_deferred<<15996>>\bf\end<<15997>>tex2html_deferred<<15997>>c<<4964>>/||<<4965>>\begin<<15998>>tex2html_deferred<<15998>>\bf\end<<15999>>tex2html_deferred<<15999>>c<<4965>>||\in P
\end<<4966>>equation<<4966>>
we get
\begin<<4967>>equation<<4967>>
f(<<4968>>\begin<<16000>>tex2html_deferred<<16000>>\bf\end<<16001>>tex2html_deferred<<16001>>x<<4968>>')=<<4969>>\begin<<16002>>tex2html_deferred<<16002>>\bf\end<<16003>>tex2html_deferred<<16003>>c<<4969>>^T<<4970>>\begin<<16004>>tex2html_deferred<<16004>>\bf\end<<16005>>tex2html_deferred<<16005>>x<<4970>>'
=<<4971>>\begin<<16006>>tex2html_deferred<<16006>>\bf\end<<16007>>tex2html_deferred<<16007>>c<<4971>>^T(<<4972>>\begin<<16008>>tex2html_deferred<<16008>>\bf\end<<16009>>tex2html_deferred<<16009>>x<<4972>>^*+\epsilon\;<<4973>>\begin<<16010>>tex2html_deferred<<16010>>\bf\end<<16011>>tex2html_deferred<<16011>>c<<4973>>/||<<4974>>\begin<<16012>>tex2html_deferred<<16012>>\bf\end<<16013>>tex2html_deferred<<16013>>c<<4974>>||)
=<<4975>>\begin<<16014>>tex2html_deferred<<16014>>\bf\end<<16015>>tex2html_deferred<<16015>>c<<4975>>^T<<4976>>\begin<<16016>>tex2html_deferred<<16016>>\bf\end<<16017>>tex2html_deferred<<16017>>x<<4976>>^*+\epsilon\;<<4977>>\begin<<16018>>tex2html_deferred<<16018>>\bf\end<<16019>>tex2html_deferred<<16019>>c<<4977>>^T<<4978>>\begin<<16020>>tex2html_deferred<<16020>>\bf\end<<16021>>tex2html_deferred<<16021>>c<<4978>>/||<<4979>>\begin<<16022>>tex2html_deferred<<16022>>\bf\end<<16023>>tex2html_deferred<<16023>>c<<4979>>||
=<<4980>>\begin<<16024>>tex2html_deferred<<16024>>\bf\end<<16025>>tex2html_deferred<<16025>>c<<4980>>^T<<4981>>\begin<<16026>>tex2html_deferred<<16026>>\bf\end<<16027>>tex2html_deferred<<16027>>x<<4981>>^*+\epsilon\;||<<4982>>\begin<<16028>>tex2html_deferred<<16028>>\bf\end<<16029>>tex2html_deferred<<16029>>c<<4982>>||;SPMgt;<<4983>>\begin<<16030>>tex2html_deferred<<16030>>\bf\end<<16031>>tex2html_deferred<<16031>>c<<4983>>^T<<4984>>\begin<<16032>>tex2html_deferred<<16032>>\bf\end<<16033>>tex2html_deferred<<16033>>x<<4984>>^*=f(<<4985>>\begin<<16034>>tex2html_deferred<<16034>>\bf\end<<16035>>tex2html_deferred<<16035>>x<<4985>>^*)
\end<<4986>>equation<<4986>>
i.e., \begin<<8858>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8858>>$<<4987>>\begin<<16036>>tex2html_deferred<<16036>>\bf\end<<16037>>tex2html_deferred<<16037>>x<<4987>>^*$\end<<8859>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8859>>\space cannot be the optimal solution as assumed. This contradiction
indicates that an optimal solution \begin<<8860>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8860>>$<<4988>>\begin<<16038>>tex2html_deferred<<16038>>\bf\end<<16039>>tex2html_deferred<<16039>>x<<4988>>^*$\end<<8861>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8861>>\space must be on the surface of \begin<<8862>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8862>>$P$\end<<8863>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8863>>,
either at one of its vertices or on one of its surfaces. Q.E.D.
\begin<<16040>>tex2html_deferred<<16040>>\par\end<<16041>>tex2html_deferred<<16041>>
Based on this theorem, the optimization of a linear programming problem 
could be solved by exhaustively checking each of the \begin<<8864>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8864>>$C_<<4989>>N+M<<4989>>^N$\end<<8865>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8865>>\space intersections
formed by \begin<<8866>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8866>>$N$\end<<8867>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8867>>\space of the \begin<<8868>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8868>>$N+M$\end<<8869>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8869>>\space hyper-planes to find (a) whether it is feasible 
(satisfying all \begin<<8870>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8870>>$N+M$\end<<8871>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8871>>\space constraints), and, if so, (b) whether the objective 
function \begin<<8872>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8872>>$f(<<4990>>\begin<<16042>>tex2html_deferred<<16042>>\bf\end<<16043>>tex2html_deferred<<16043>>x<<4990>>)$\end<<8873>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8873>>\space is maximized at the point. Specifically, we choose 
\begin<<8874>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8874>>$N$\end<<8875>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8875>>\space of the \begin<<8876>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8876>>$N+M$\end<<8877>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8877>>\space equations for the the constraints and solve this N-equation 
and N-unknown linear system to get the intersection point of \begin<<8878>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8878>>$N$\end<<8879>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8879>>\space corresponding
hyper-planes. This brute-force method is most straight forward, but the 
computational complexity is high when \begin<<8880>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8880>>$N$\end<<8881>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8881>>\space and \begin<<8882>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8882>>$M$\end<<8883>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8883>>, and therefore \begin<<8884>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8884>>$C_<<4991>>N+M<<4991>>^N$\end<<8885>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8885>>, 
become large.
\begin<<16044>>tex2html_deferred<<16044>>\par\end<<16045>>tex2html_deferred<<16045>>
<<4992>>\begin<<16046>>tex2html_deferred<<16046>>\bf\end<<16047>>tex2html_deferred<<16047>>Example:<<4992>>
\begin<<16048>>tex2html_deferred<<16048>>\par\end<<16049>>tex2html_deferred<<16049>>
\begin<<4993>>equation<<4993>>
  \begin<<4994>>array<<4994>><<4995>>ll<<4995>>
    \mbox<<4996>>maximize<<4996>>    ;SPMamp; f_p(x_1,x_2)=2x_1+3x_2 \\ 
    \mbox<<4997>>subject to:<<4997>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{ \begin<<4998>>array<<4998>><<4999>>l<<4999>>
      2x_1+ x_2 \le 18\\  6x_1+5x_2 \le 60 \\  2x_1+5x_2 \le 40 \\  x_1 \ge 0,\;\; x_2\ge 0
    \end<<5000>>array<<5000>>\right.
  \end<<5001>>array<<5001>>
  \;\;\;\;\;\;\mbox<<5002>>or<<5002>>\;\;\;\;\;\;
  \begin<<5003>>array<<5003>><<5004>>ll<<5004>>
    \mbox<<5005>>maximize<<5005>>    ;SPMamp; f_p(<<5006>>\begin<<16050>>tex2html_deferred<<16050>>\bf\end<<16051>>tex2html_deferred<<16051>>x<<5006>>)=<<5007>>\begin<<16052>>tex2html_deferred<<16052>>\bf\end<<16053>>tex2html_deferred<<16053>>c<<5007>>^T<<5008>>\begin<<16054>>tex2html_deferred<<16054>>\bf\end<<16055>>tex2html_deferred<<16055>>x<<5008>> \\ 
    \mbox<<5009>>subject to:<<5009>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{ \begin<<5010>>array<<5010>><<5011>>l<<5011>><<5012>>\begin<<16056>>tex2html_deferred<<16056>>\bf\end<<16057>>tex2html_deferred<<16057>>A<<5012>><<5013>>\begin<<16058>>tex2html_deferred<<16058>>\bf\end<<16059>>tex2html_deferred<<16059>>x<<5013>>\le<<5014>>\begin<<16060>>tex2html_deferred<<16060>>\bf\end<<16061>>tex2html_deferred<<16061>>b<<5014>>\\ <<5015>>\begin<<16062>>tex2html_deferred<<16062>>\bf\end<<16063>>tex2html_deferred<<16063>>x<<5015>>\ge <<5016>>\begin<<16064>>tex2html_deferred<<16064>>\bf\end<<16065>>tex2html_deferred<<16065>>0<<5016>>
    \end<<5017>>array<<5017>>\right.
  \end<<5018>>array<<5018>>
  \nonumber
\end<<5019>>equation<<5019>>
where
\begin<<5020>>equation<<5020>> 
  <<5021>>\begin<<16066>>tex2html_deferred<<16066>>\bf\end<<16067>>tex2html_deferred<<16067>>x<<5021>>=\left[\begin<<5022>>array<<5022>><<5023>>c<<5023>>x_1\\ x_2\end<<5024>>array<<5024>>\right],\;\;\;\;
  <<5025>>\begin<<16068>>tex2html_deferred<<16068>>\bf\end<<16069>>tex2html_deferred<<16069>>c<<5025>>=\left[\begin<<5026>>array<<5026>><<5027>>c<<5027>>2\\ 3\end<<5028>>array<<5028>>\right],\;\;\;\;
  <<5029>>\begin<<16070>>tex2html_deferred<<16070>>\bf\end<<16071>>tex2html_deferred<<16071>>b<<5029>>=\left[\begin<<5030>>array<<5030>><<5031>>c<<5031>>18\\ 60\\ 40\end<<5032>>array<<5032>>\right],\;\;\;\;
  <<5033>>\begin<<16072>>tex2html_deferred<<16072>>\bf\end<<16073>>tex2html_deferred<<16073>>A<<5033>>=\left[\begin<<5034>>array<<5034>><<5035>>cc<<5035>>2;SPMamp;1\\ 6;SPMamp;5\\ 2;SPMamp;5\end<<5036>>array<<5036>>\right]
  \nonumber
\end<<5037>>equation<<5037>>
\begin<<16074>>tex2html_deferred<<16074>>\par\end<<16075>>tex2html_deferred<<16075>>
\htmladdimg<<5038>>figures/SimplexEx0.png<<5038>>
\begin<<16076>>tex2html_deferred<<16076>>\par\end<<16077>>tex2html_deferred<<16077>>
This problem has \begin<<8886>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8886>>$N=2$\end<<8887>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8887>>\space variables with the same number of non-negativity
constraints and \begin<<8888>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8888>>$M=3$\end<<8889>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8889>>\space linear inequality constraints. The \begin<<8890>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8890>>$n+m=5$\end<<8891>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8891>>\space straight 
lines form \begin<<8892>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8892>>$C_<<5039>>N+M<<5039>>^N=C_5^2=10$\end<<8893>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8893>>\space intersections, out of which 5 are the 
vertices of the polygonal feasible region satisfying all constraints. 
The value of the objective function \begin<<8894>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8894>>$f_p(x_1,x_2)=<<5040>>\begin<<16078>>tex2html_deferred<<16078>>\bf\end<<16079>>tex2html_deferred<<16079>>c<<5040>>^T<<5041>>\begin<<16080>>tex2html_deferred<<16080>>\bf\end<<16081>>tex2html_deferred<<16081>>x<<5041>>=c_1x_1+c_2x_2$\end<<8895>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8895>> 
is proportional to the projection of the 2-D variable vector 
\begin<<8896>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8896>>$<<5042>>\begin<<16082>>tex2html_deferred<<16082>>\bf\end<<16083>>tex2html_deferred<<16083>>x<<5042>>=[x_1,\;x_2]^T$\end<<8897>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8897>>\space onto the coefficient vector \begin<<8898>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8898>>$<<5043>>\begin<<16084>>tex2html_deferred<<16084>>\bf\end<<16085>>tex2html_deferred<<16085>>c<<5043>>=[2,\;3]^T$\end<<8899>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8899>>. 
The goal here is to find a point in the polygonal feasible region with 
maximum projection onto vector \begin<<8900>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8900>>$<<5044>>\begin<<16086>>tex2html_deferred<<16086>>\bf\end<<16087>>tex2html_deferred<<16087>>c<<5044>>$\end<<8901>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8901>>. 
\begin<<16088>>tex2html_deferred<<16088>>\par\end<<16089>>tex2html_deferred<<16089>>
The \begin<<8902>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8902>>$C_5^2=10$\end<<8903>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8903>>\space intersections are listed in the table below together with
their feasibility (whether a vertex of the polygon or not) and the 
corresponding objective function value (proportional to the projection
in the parentheses). We see that out of the 5 feasible solutions at the
vertices of the polygon, the one at \begin<<8904>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8904>>$<<5045>>\begin<<16090>>tex2html_deferred<<16090>>\bf\end<<16091>>tex2html_deferred<<16091>>x<<5045>>^*=(5,\;6)$\end<<8905>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8905>>\space is optimal with 
maximum objective function value \begin<<8906>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8906>>$f_p(x_1,x_2)=2x_1+3x_2=2\times 5+3\times6=28$\end<<8907>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8907>> 
(proportional to the projection \begin<<8908>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8908>>$<<5046>>\begin<<16092>>tex2html_deferred<<16092>>\bf\end<<16093>>tex2html_deferred<<16093>>c<<5046>>^T<<5047>>\begin<<16094>>tex2html_deferred<<16094>>\bf\end<<16095>>tex2html_deferred<<16095>>x<<5047>>^*/||<<5048>>\begin<<16096>>tex2html_deferred<<16096>>\bf\end<<16097>>tex2html_deferred<<16097>>c<<5048>>||=28/3.61=7.77$\end<<8909>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8909>>. 
\begin<<16098>>tex2html_deferred<<16098>>\par\end<<16099>>tex2html_deferred<<16099>>
\begin<<5049>>equation<<5049>>
  \begin<<5050>>array<<5050>><<5051>>c|c|c|c<<5051>>\hline
    ;SPMamp; (x_1,\; x_2) ;SPMamp;  ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5052>>objective function (normalized)<<5052>> \\ \hline
    1 ;SPMamp; 5.00,\; 6.00 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5053>>feasible<<5053>>   ;SPMamp; 28\; (7.77) \\ 
    2 ;SPMamp; 6.25,\; 5.50 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5054>>infeasible<<5054>> ;SPMamp; 29\; (8.04) \\ 
    3 ;SPMamp; 7.50,\; 3.00 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5055>>feasible<<5055>>   ;SPMamp; 24\; (6.66) \\ 
    4 ;SPMamp;20.00,\; 0.00 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5056>>infeasible<<5056>> ;SPMamp; 40\; (11.1) \\ 
    5 ;SPMamp;10.00,\; 0.00 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5057>>infeasible<<5057>> ;SPMamp; 20\; (5.55) \\ 
    6 ;SPMamp; 9.00,\; 0.00 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5058>>feasible<<5058>>   ;SPMamp; 18\; (4.10) \\ 
    7 ;SPMamp; 0.00,\; 8.00 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5059>>feasible<<5059>>   ;SPMamp; 24\; (6.66) \\ 
    8 ;SPMamp; 0.00,\; 12.00 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5060>>infeasible<<5060>>;SPMamp; 36\; (9.98) \\ 
    9 ;SPMamp; 0.00,\; 18.00 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5061>>infeasible<<5061>>;SPMamp; 54\; (14.99) \\ 
    10;SPMamp; 0.00,\; 0.00 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5062>>feasible <<5062>>  ;SPMamp;  0\; (0.00) \\ \hline
  \end<<5063>>array<<5063>>
  \nonumber
\end<<5064>>equation<<5064>>
\begin<<16100>>tex2html_deferred<<16100>>\par\end<<16101>>tex2html_deferred<<16101>>
This problem can be converted to the standard form:
\begin<<5065>>equation<<5065>>
  \begin<<5066>>array<<5066>><<5067>>ll<<5067>>
    \mbox<<5068>>maximize<<5068>>    ;SPMamp; f_p(x_1,x_2)=2x_1+3x_2 \\ 
    \mbox<<5069>>subject to:<<5069>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{ \begin<<5070>>array<<5070>><<5071>>l<<5071>>
      2x_1+ x_2 \le 18\\  6x_1+5x_2 \le 60 \\  2x_1+5x_2 \le 40 \\ 
      x_1 \ge 0,\;\; x_2\ge 0
    \end<<5072>>array<<5072>>\right.
  \end<<5073>>array<<5073>>
  \;\;\;\;\;\;\Longrightarrow\;\;\;\;\;\;
  \begin<<5074>>array<<5074>><<5075>>ll<<5075>>
    \mbox<<5076>>maximize<<5076>>    ;SPMamp; f_p(x_1,x_2)=2x_1+3x_2 \\ 
    \mbox<<5077>>subject to:<<5077>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{ \begin<<5078>>array<<5078>><<5079>>l<<5079>>
      2x_1+ x_2+s_1=18\\  6x_1+5x_2+s_2=60 \\  2x_1+5x_2+s_3=40 \\  
      x_1 \ge 0,\; x_2\ge 0,\; s_1\ge 0,\; s_2\ge 0,\; s_3\ge0
    \end<<5080>>array<<5080>>\right.
  \end<<5081>>array<<5081>>
  \nonumber
\end<<5082>>equation<<5082>>
\begin<<16102>>tex2html_deferred<<16102>>\par\end<<16103>>tex2html_deferred<<16103>>
The goal of this linear programming problem can be intuitively understood 
as to push the hyper-plane \begin<<8910>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8910>>$<<5083>>\begin<<16104>>tex2html_deferred<<16104>>\bf\end<<16105>>tex2html_deferred<<16105>>c<<5083>>^T<<5084>>\begin<<16106>>tex2html_deferred<<16106>>\bf\end<<16107>>tex2html_deferred<<16107>>x<<5084>>=z$\end<<8911>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8911>>, here a line in 2-D space, 
along its normal direction \begin<<8912>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8912>>$<<5085>>\begin<<16108>>tex2html_deferred<<16108>>\bf\end<<16109>>tex2html_deferred<<16109>>c<<5085>>$\end<<8913>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8913>>, from the origin to as far away as 
possible inside the feasible region, to eventually arrive at one of the 
vertices of the polytope feasible region that is farthest away from the 
origin.
\begin<<16110>>tex2html_deferred<<16110>>\par\end<<16111>>tex2html_deferred<<16111>>
We can also consider the dual problem
\begin<<16112>>tex2html_deferred<<16112>>\par\end<<16113>>tex2html_deferred<<16113>>
\begin<<5086>>equation<<5086>>
  \begin<<5087>>array<<5087>><<5088>>ll<<5088>>
    \mbox<<5089>>minimize<<5089>>    ;SPMamp; f_d(y_1,y_2,y_3)=18y_1+60y_2+40y_3 \\ 
    \mbox<<5090>>subject to:<<5090>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{ \begin<<5091>>array<<5091>><<5092>>l<<5092>>
      2y_1+6y_2+2y_3\ge 2 \\  y_1+5y_2+5y_3\ge 3\\ 
      y_1\ge 0,\;y_2\ge 0,\;y_3\ge 0\\ 
    \end<<5093>>array<<5093>>\right.
  \end<<5094>>array<<5094>>
  \;\;\;\;\;\;\mbox<<5095>>or<<5095>>\;\;\;\;\;\;
  \begin<<5096>>array<<5096>><<5097>>ll<<5097>>
    \mbox<<5098>>minimize<<5098>>    ;SPMamp; f_d(<<5099>>\begin<<16114>>tex2html_deferred<<16114>>\bf\end<<16115>>tex2html_deferred<<16115>>y<<5099>>)=<<5100>>\begin<<16116>>tex2html_deferred<<16116>>\bf\end<<16117>>tex2html_deferred<<16117>>b<<5100>>^T<<5101>>\begin<<16118>>tex2html_deferred<<16118>>\bf\end<<16119>>tex2html_deferred<<16119>>y<<5101>> \\ 
    \mbox<<5102>>subject to:<<5102>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{ \begin<<5103>>array<<5103>><<5104>>l<<5104>><<5105>>\begin<<16120>>tex2html_deferred<<16120>>\bf\end<<16121>>tex2html_deferred<<16121>>A<<5105>>^T<<5106>>\begin<<16122>>tex2html_deferred<<16122>>\bf\end<<16123>>tex2html_deferred<<16123>>y<<5106>>\le<<5107>>\begin<<16124>>tex2html_deferred<<16124>>\bf\end<<16125>>tex2html_deferred<<16125>>b<<5107>>\\ <<5108>>\begin<<16126>>tex2html_deferred<<16126>>\bf\end<<16127>>tex2html_deferred<<16127>>y<<5108>>\ge <<5109>>\begin<<16128>>tex2html_deferred<<16128>>\bf\end<<16129>>tex2html_deferred<<16129>>0<<5109>>
    \end<<5110>>array<<5110>>\right.
  \end<<5111>>array<<5111>>
  \nonumber
\end<<5112>>equation<<5112>>
\begin<<16130>>tex2html_deferred<<16130>>\par\end<<16131>>tex2html_deferred<<16131>>
The five planes, \begin<<8914>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8914>>$m=2$\end<<8915>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8915>>\space from the constraining inequalities, and \begin<<8916>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8916>>$n=3$\end<<8917>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8917>>
for the non-negative constraints \begin<<8918>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8918>>$y_1\le 0$\end<<8919>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8919>>, \begin<<8920>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8920>>$y_2\le 0$\end<<8921>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8921>>, and \begin<<8922>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8922>>$y_3\le 0$\end<<8923>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8923>>
for the three variables, form \begin<<8924>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8924>>$10$\end<<8925>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8925>>\space intersection points:
\begin<<5113>>equation<<5113>>
  \begin<<5114>>array<<5114>><<5115>>c|c|c|c<<5115>>\hline
    ;SPMamp; (y_1,\,y_2,\,y_3)  ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5116>>objective function<<5116>> \\ \hline
    1 ;SPMamp; (1,0,0) ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5117>>infeasible<<5117>>   ;SPMamp; 18\\ 
    2 ;SPMamp; (3,0,0) ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5118>>feasible<<5118>>   ;SPMamp; 54\\ 
    3 ;SPMamp; (0,1/3,0) ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5119>>infeasible<<5119>>   ;SPMamp; 20\\ 
    4 ;SPMamp; (0,3/5,0) ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5120>>feasible<<5120>>   ;SPMamp; 36\\ 
    5 ;SPMamp; (0,0,1) ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5121>>feasible<<5121>>   ;SPMamp; 40\\ 
    6 ;SPMamp; (0,0,3/5) ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5122>>infeasible<<5122>>   ;SPMamp; 24\\ 
    7 ;SPMamp; (0,1/5,2/5) ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5123>>feasible<<5123>>   ;SPMamp; 28\\ 
    8 ;SPMamp; (1/2,0,1/2) ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5124>>feasible<<5124>>   ;SPMamp; 29\\ 
    9 ;SPMamp; (-2,1,0) ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5125>>infeasible<<5125>>   ;SPMamp; 24\\ 
    10 ;SPMamp; (0,0,0) ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5126>>infeasible<<5126>>   ;SPMamp; 0\\ \hline
  \end<<5127>>array<<5127>>
  \nonumber
\end<<5128>>equation<<5128>>
\begin<<16132>>tex2html_deferred<<16132>>\par\end<<16133>>tex2html_deferred<<16133>>
We see that at the feasible point \begin<<8926>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8926>>$(0,1/5,2/5)$\end<<8927>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8927>>, the dual function 
\begin<<8928>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8928>>$f_d(y_1,y_2,y_3)=18y_1+60y_2+40y_3$\end<<8929>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8929>>\space is minimized to be \begin<<8930>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8930>>$28$\end<<8931>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8931>>, the same 
as the maximum of the primal function \begin<<8932>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8932>>$f_p(x_1,x_2)=2x_1+3x_2$\end<<8933>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8933>>\space at \begin<<8934>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8934>>$(5,6)$\end<<8935>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8935>>.
\begin<<16134>>tex2html_deferred<<16134>>\par\end<<16135>>tex2html_deferred<<16135>>
\htmladdimg<<5129>>figures/LPdual1.png<<5129>>
\begin<<16136>>tex2html_deferred<<16136>>\par\end<<16137>>tex2html_deferred<<16137>>
<<5130>>\begin<<16138>>tex2html_deferred<<16138>>\bf\end<<16139>>tex2html_deferred<<16139>>Homework:<<5130>> 
\begin<<16140>>tex2html_deferred<<16140>>\par\end<<16141>>tex2html_deferred<<16141>>
Develop the code to find all \begin<<8936>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8936>>$C_<<5131>>N+M<<5131>>^N$\end<<8937>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8937>>\space intersections formed by \begin<<8938>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8938>>$N+M$\end<<8939>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8939>> 
given hyper-planes in an N-D space in terms of their equations
\begin<<8940>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8940>>$<<5132>>\begin<<16142>>tex2html_deferred<<16142>>\bf\end<<16143>>tex2html_deferred<<16143>>A<<5132>>_<<5133>>M\times N<<5133>><<5134>>\begin<<16144>>tex2html_deferred<<16144>>\bf\end<<16145>>tex2html_deferred<<16145>>x<<5134>>_<<5135>>N\times 1<<5135>>\le<<5136>>\begin<<16146>>tex2html_deferred<<16146>>\bf\end<<16147>>tex2html_deferred<<16147>>b<<5136>>_<<5137>>M\times 1<<5137>>$\end<<8941>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8941>>\space and 
\begin<<8942>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8942>>$<<5138>>\begin<<16148>>tex2html_deferred<<16148>>\bf\end<<16149>>tex2html_deferred<<16149>>x<<5138>>\ge <<5139>>\begin<<16150>>tex2html_deferred<<16150>>\bf\end<<16151>>tex2html_deferred<<16151>>0<<5139>>$\end<<8943>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8943>>, identify which of them are vertices of the polytope 
surrounded by these hype-planes, and find the vertex corresponding to the 
optimal solution that maximizes \begin<<8944>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8944>>$f(<<5140>>\begin<<16152>>tex2html_deferred<<16152>>\bf\end<<16153>>tex2html_deferred<<16153>>x<<5140>>)=<<5141>>\begin<<16154>>tex2html_deferred<<16154>>\bf\end<<16155>>tex2html_deferred<<16155>>c<<5141>>^T<<5142>>\begin<<16156>>tex2html_deferred<<16156>>\bf\end<<16157>>tex2html_deferred<<16157>>x<<5142>>$\end<<8945>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8945>>\space for a given 
\begin<<8946>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8946>>$<<5143>>\begin<<16158>>tex2html_deferred<<16158>>\bf\end<<16159>>tex2html_deferred<<16159>>c<<5143>>$\end<<8947>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8947>>.
\begin<<16160>>tex2html_deferred<<16160>>\par\end<<16161>>tex2html_deferred<<16161>>
\subsection*<<5144>>The Simplex Algorithm<<5144>>
\begin<<16162>>tex2html_deferred<<16162>>\par\end<<16163>>tex2html_deferred<<16163>>
Instead of exhausting all vertices of the feasible region to find
the optimal solution, the simplex algorithm is an iterative process 
that traverses along a sequence of edges of the polytopic feasible 
region, starting at the origin and through a sequence of vertices 
\begin<<8948>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8948>>$<<5145>>\begin<<16164>>tex2html_deferred<<16164>>\bf\end<<16165>>tex2html_deferred<<16165>>x<<5145>>$\end<<8949>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8949>>\space with progressively greater objective value \begin<<8950>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8950>>$f(<<5146>>\begin<<16166>>tex2html_deferred<<16166>>\bf\end<<16167>>tex2html_deferred<<16167>>x<<5146>>)$\end<<8951>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8951>>,
until eventually reaching the optimal solution.
\begin<<16168>>tex2html_deferred<<16168>>\par\end<<16169>>tex2html_deferred<<16169>>
To understand the algorithm, we first consider the equality constraint 
\begin<<8952>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8952>>$<<5147>>\begin<<16170>>tex2html_deferred<<16170>>\bf\end<<16171>>tex2html_deferred<<16171>>Ax<<5147>>=[<<5148>>\begin<<16172>>tex2html_deferred<<16172>>\bf\end<<16173>>tex2html_deferred<<16173>>A<<5148>>_<<5149>>M\times N<<5149>>\;|\;<<5150>>\begin<<16174>>tex2html_deferred<<16174>>\bf\end<<16175>>tex2html_deferred<<16175>>I<<5150>>_<<5151>>M\times M<<5151>>] <<5152>>\begin<<16176>>tex2html_deferred<<16176>>\bf\end<<16177>>tex2html_deferred<<16177>>x<<5152>>=<<5153>>\begin<<16178>>tex2html_deferred<<16178>>\bf\end<<16179>>tex2html_deferred<<16179>>b<<5153>>$\end<<8953>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8953>> 
of the standard LP problem. This is an under-determined linear system
of \begin<<8954>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8954>>$N+M$\end<<8955>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8955>>\space variables but only \begin<<8956>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8956>>$M$\end<<8957>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8957>>\space equations, only \begin<<8958>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8958>>$M$\end<<8959>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8959>>\space of its \begin<<8960>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8960>>$N+M$\end<<8961>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8961>> 
columns of the coefficient matrix \begin<<8962>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8962>>$<<5154>>\begin<<16180>>tex2html_deferred<<16180>>\bf\end<<16181>>tex2html_deferred<<16181>>A<<5154>>$\end<<8963>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8963>>\space are independent (assuming 
\begin<<8964>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8964>>$rank(<<5155>>\begin<<16182>>tex2html_deferred<<16182>>\bf\end<<16183>>tex2html_deferred<<16183>>A<<5155>>)=M$\end<<8965>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8965>>). Initially we choose the \begin<<8966>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8966>>$M$\end<<8967>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8967>>\space columns of the 
identity coefficient matrix \begin<<8968>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8968>>$<<5156>>\begin<<16184>>tex2html_deferred<<16184>>\bf\end<<16185>>tex2html_deferred<<16185>>I<<5156>>$\end<<8969>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8969>>\space as the independent columns, but
subsequently we can choose any other \begin<<8970>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8970>>$M$\end<<8971>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8971>>\space columns of \begin<<8972>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8972>>$<<5157>>\begin<<16186>>tex2html_deferred<<16186>>\bf\end<<16187>>tex2html_deferred<<16187>>A<<5157>>$\end<<8973>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8973>>\space as the 
independent columns and convert them into a standard basis vector by 
\htmladdnormallink<<5158>>Gauss-Jordan elimination<<5158>><<5159>>../ch0/node5.html<<5159>>,
together with the corresponding variables in \begin<<8974>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8974>>$<<5160>>\begin<<16188>>tex2html_deferred<<16188>>\bf\end<<16189>>tex2html_deferred<<16189>>x<<5160>>$\end<<8975>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8975>>. The resulting
equation \begin<<8976>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8976>>$<<5161>>\begin<<16190>>tex2html_deferred<<16190>>\bf\end<<16191>>tex2html_deferred<<16191>>Ax<<5161>>=<<5162>>\begin<<16192>>tex2html_deferred<<16192>>\bf\end<<16193>>tex2html_deferred<<16193>>b<<5162>>$\end<<8977>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8977>>\space remains equivalent to the original one,
i.e., the \begin<<8978>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8978>>$M$\end<<8979>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8979>>\space equality constraints are always preserved and never 
violated in the process.
\begin<<16194>>tex2html_deferred<<16194>>\par\end<<16195>>tex2html_deferred<<16195>>
For convenience of discussion and without loss of generality, we could
reorder (not actually carried out) the \begin<<8980>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8980>>$N+M$\end<<8981>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8981>>\space columns in \begin<<8982>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8982>>$<<5163>>\begin<<16196>>tex2html_deferred<<16196>>\bf\end<<16197>>tex2html_deferred<<16197>>A<<5163>>$\end<<8983>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8983>>, 
together with the corresponding variables in \begin<<8984>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8984>>$<<5164>>\begin<<16198>>tex2html_deferred<<16198>>\bf\end<<16199>>tex2html_deferred<<16199>>x<<5164>>$\end<<8985>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8985>>, so that the 
constraining equation would always takes the following form:
\begin<<5165>>equation<<5165>>
  <<5166>>\begin<<16200>>tex2html_deferred<<16200>>\bf\end<<16201>>tex2html_deferred<<16201>>A<<5166>><<5167>>\begin<<16202>>tex2html_deferred<<16202>>\bf\end<<16203>>tex2html_deferred<<16203>>x<<5167>>=[<<5168>>\begin<<16204>>tex2html_deferred<<16204>>\bf\end<<16205>>tex2html_deferred<<16205>>A<<5168>>_n\;\;<<5169>>\begin<<16206>>tex2html_deferred<<16206>>\bf\end<<16207>>tex2html_deferred<<16207>>I<<5169>>]
  \left[\begin<<5170>>array<<5170>><<5171>>c<<5171>><<5172>>\begin<<16208>>tex2html_deferred<<16208>>\bf\end<<16209>>tex2html_deferred<<16209>>x<<5172>>_n\\ <<5173>>\begin<<16210>>tex2html_deferred<<16210>>\bf\end<<16211>>tex2html_deferred<<16211>>x<<5173>>_b\end<<5174>>array<<5174>>\right]
  =<<5175>>\begin<<16212>>tex2html_deferred<<16212>>\bf\end<<16213>>tex2html_deferred<<16213>>A<<5175>>_n<<5176>>\begin<<16214>>tex2html_deferred<<16214>>\bf\end<<16215>>tex2html_deferred<<16215>>x<<5176>>_n+<<5177>>\begin<<16216>>tex2html_deferred<<16216>>\bf\end<<16217>>tex2html_deferred<<16217>>I<<5177>>\;<<5178>>\begin<<16218>>tex2html_deferred<<16218>>\bf\end<<16219>>tex2html_deferred<<16219>>x<<5178>>_b=<<5179>>\begin<<16220>>tex2html_deferred<<16220>>\bf\end<<16221>>tex2html_deferred<<16221>>b<<5179>>
\end<<5180>>equation<<5180>>
Now the variables in the M-D vector \begin<<8986>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8986>>$<<5181>>\begin<<16222>>tex2html_deferred<<16222>>\bf\end<<16223>>tex2html_deferred<<16223>>x<<5181>>_b$\end<<8987>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8987>>\space corresponding to the 
\begin<<8988>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8988>>$M$\end<<8989>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8989>>\space independent columns in \begin<<8990>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8990>>$<<5182>>\begin<<16224>>tex2html_deferred<<16224>>\bf\end<<16225>>tex2html_deferred<<16225>>I<<5182>>$\end<<8991>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8991>>\space are the <<5183>>\begin<<16226>>tex2html_deferred<<16226>>\em\end<<16227>>tex2html_deferred<<16227>>basic variables<<5183>>, 
while the N-D vector \begin<<8992>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8992>>$<<5184>>\begin<<16228>>tex2html_deferred<<16228>>\bf\end<<16229>>tex2html_deferred<<16229>>x<<5184>>_n$\end<<8993>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8993>>\space corresponding to the remaining \begin<<8994>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8994>>$N$\end<<8995>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8995>> 
dependent columns, now denoted by \begin<<8996>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8996>>$<<5185>>\begin<<16230>>tex2html_deferred<<16230>>\bf\end<<16231>>tex2html_deferred<<16231>>A<<5185>>_n$\end<<8997>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8997>>, are the <<5186>>\begin<<16232>>tex2html_deferred<<16232>>\em\end<<16233>>tex2html_deferred<<16233>>non-basic 
variables<<5186>>. This equation will always hold if \begin<<8998>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8998>>$<<5187>>\begin<<16234>>tex2html_deferred<<16234>>\bf\end<<16235>>tex2html_deferred<<16235>>x<<5187>>_n=<<5188>>\begin<<16236>>tex2html_deferred<<16236>>\bf\end<<16237>>tex2html_deferred<<16237>>0<<5188>>$\end<<8999>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<8999>>\space and
\begin<<9000>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9000>>$<<5189>>\begin<<16238>>tex2html_deferred<<16238>>\bf\end<<16239>>tex2html_deferred<<16239>>x<<5189>>_b=<<5190>>\begin<<16240>>tex2html_deferred<<16240>>\bf\end<<16241>>tex2html_deferred<<16241>>b<<5190>>$\end<<9001>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9001>>. Such a solution is called a <<5191>>\begin<<16242>>tex2html_deferred<<16242>>\em\end<<16243>>tex2html_deferred<<16243>>basic solution<<5191>> 
of the linear system \begin<<9002>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9002>>$<<5192>>\begin<<16244>>tex2html_deferred<<16244>>\bf\end<<16245>>tex2html_deferred<<16245>>A<<5192>><<5193>>\begin<<16246>>tex2html_deferred<<16246>>\bf\end<<16247>>tex2html_deferred<<16247>>x<<5193>>=<<5194>>\begin<<16248>>tex2html_deferred<<16248>>\bf\end<<16249>>tex2html_deferred<<16249>>b<<5194>>$\end<<9003>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9003>>:
\begin<<5195>>equation<<5195>>
  <<5196>>\begin<<16250>>tex2html_deferred<<16250>>\bf\end<<16251>>tex2html_deferred<<16251>>x<<5196>>=\left[\begin<<5197>>array<<5197>><<5198>>c<<5198>><<5199>>\begin<<16252>>tex2html_deferred<<16252>>\bf\end<<16253>>tex2html_deferred<<16253>>x<<5199>>_n\\ <<5200>>\begin<<16254>>tex2html_deferred<<16254>>\bf\end<<16255>>tex2html_deferred<<16255>>x<<5200>>_b\end<<5201>>array<<5201>>\right]
  =\left[\begin<<5202>>array<<5202>><<5203>>c<<5203>><<5204>>\begin<<16256>>tex2html_deferred<<16256>>\bf\end<<16257>>tex2html_deferred<<16257>>0<<5204>>\\ <<5205>>\begin<<16258>>tex2html_deferred<<16258>>\bf\end<<16259>>tex2html_deferred<<16259>>b<<5205>>\end<<5206>>array<<5206>>\right]
\end<<5207>>equation<<5207>>
Initially, \begin<<9004>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9004>>$<<5208>>\begin<<16260>>tex2html_deferred<<16260>>\bf\end<<16261>>tex2html_deferred<<16261>>A<<5208>>_n$\end<<9005>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9005>>\space is the coefficient matrix in the inequality 
constraint \begin<<9006>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9006>>$<<5209>>\begin<<16262>>tex2html_deferred<<16262>>\bf\end<<16263>>tex2html_deferred<<16263>>Ax<<5209>>\le <<5210>>\begin<<16264>>tex2html_deferred<<16264>>\bf\end<<16265>>tex2html_deferred<<16265>>b<<5210>>$\end<<9007>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9007>>, and the corresponding non-basic
variables \begin<<9008>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9008>>$<<5211>>\begin<<16266>>tex2html_deferred<<16266>>\bf\end<<16267>>tex2html_deferred<<16267>>x<<5211>>_n=<<5212>>\begin<<16268>>tex2html_deferred<<16268>>\bf\end<<16269>>tex2html_deferred<<16269>>0<<5212>>$\end<<9009>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9009>>\space is actually the origin. But through
the iteration, we will keep converting some other columns of \begin<<9010>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9010>>$<<5213>>\begin<<16270>>tex2html_deferred<<16270>>\bf\end<<16271>>tex2html_deferred<<16271>>A<<5213>>$\end<<9011>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9011>>
into standard basis vectors \begin<<9012>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9012>>$\{<<5214>>\begin<<16272>>tex2html_deferred<<16272>>\bf\end<<16273>>tex2html_deferred<<16273>>e<<5214>>_1,\cdots,<<5215>>\begin<<16274>>tex2html_deferred<<16274>>\bf\end<<16275>>tex2html_deferred<<16275>>e<<5215>>_M\}$\end<<9013>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9013>>, the 
column vectors of \begin<<9014>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9014>>$<<5216>>\begin<<16276>>tex2html_deferred<<16276>>\bf\end<<16277>>tex2html_deferred<<16277>>I<<5216>>$\end<<9015>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9015>>\space by Gauss-Jordan elimination. The variables
corresponding to the new \begin<<9016>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9016>>$<<5217>>\begin<<16278>>tex2html_deferred<<16278>>\bf\end<<16279>>tex2html_deferred<<16279>>I<<5217>>$\end<<9017>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9017>>\space become the basic variables, while
those corresponding to columns that become non-standard basis vectors 
become non-basis variables.
\begin<<16280>>tex2html_deferred<<16280>>\par\end<<16281>>tex2html_deferred<<16281>>
The basic solutions corresponding the \begin<<9018>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9018>>$C_<<5218>>N+M<<5218>>^M$\end<<9019>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9019>>\space ways to choose \begin<<9020>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9020>>$M$\end<<9021>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9021>> 
of the \begin<<9022>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9022>>$N+M$\end<<9023>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9023>>\space columns of \begin<<9024>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9024>>$<<5219>>\begin<<16282>>tex2html_deferred<<16282>>\bf\end<<16283>>tex2html_deferred<<16283>>A<<5219>>$\end<<9025>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9025>>\space as independent are actually the
intersections formed by any \begin<<9026>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9026>>$N$\end<<9027>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9027>>\space of the \begin<<9028>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9028>>$N+M$\end<<9029>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9029>>\space constraining hyper-planes 
in the N-D space. As noted before, only a subset of these \begin<<9030>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9030>>$C_<<5220>>N+M<<5220>>^M$\end<<9031>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9031>> 
basic solutions satisfy the \begin<<9032>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9032>>$M$\end<<9033>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9033>>\space constraints, and they are called 
<<5221>>\begin<<16284>>tex2html_deferred<<16284>>\em\end<<16285>>tex2html_deferred<<16285>>basic feasible solutions (BFS)<<5221>>. The goal of the iterative 
process in the simplex algorithm is to find the optimal basic feasible 
solution that maximizes \begin<<9034>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9034>>$f(<<5222>>\begin<<16286>>tex2html_deferred<<16286>>\bf\end<<16287>>tex2html_deferred<<16287>>x<<5222>>)$\end<<9035>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9035>>\space without exhausting all \begin<<9036>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9036>>$C_<<5223>>N+M<<5223>>^M$\end<<9037>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9037>> 
possibilities. This is done by selecting the columns in such a way 
that the value of the objective function will always be maximally 
increased, until eventually we find the optimal solution \begin<<9038>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9038>>$<<5224>>\begin<<16288>>tex2html_deferred<<16288>>\bf\end<<16289>>tex2html_deferred<<16289>>x<<5224>>^*$\end<<9039>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9039>>, 
the vertex of the polytopic feasible region at which \begin<<9040>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9040>>$f(<<5225>>\begin<<16290>>tex2html_deferred<<16290>>\bf\end<<16291>>tex2html_deferred<<16291>>x<<5225>>^*)$\end<<9041>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9041>> 
is maximized.
\begin<<16292>>tex2html_deferred<<16292>>\par\end<<16293>>tex2html_deferred<<16293>>
Specially, the implementation of the simplex algorithm is based on a 
tableau with \begin<<9042>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9042>>$N+M+1$\end<<9043>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9043>>\space columns and \begin<<9044>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9044>>$M+1$\end<<9045>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9045>>\space rows, initialized as below:
\begin<<5226>>itemize<<5226>>
\item The first \begin<<9046>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9046>>$M$\end<<9047>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9047>>\space rows are for the coefficients in the equality
  constraints \begin<<9048>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9048>>$\sum_<<5227>>j=1<<5227>>^N a_<<5228>>ij<<5228>>x_j+s_i=b_i$\end<<9049>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9049>>\space (\begin<<9050>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9050>>$i=1,\cdots,M$\end<<9051>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9051>>). An
  additional \begin<<9052>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9052>>$(M+1)st$\end<<9053>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9053>>\space row at the bottom is for the coefficients
  in the objective function \begin<<9054>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9054>>$f(<<5229>>\begin<<16294>>tex2html_deferred<<16294>>\bf\end<<16295>>tex2html_deferred<<16295>>x<<5229>>)=\sum_<<5230>>j=1<<5230>>^N c_jx_j$\end<<9055>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9055>>, which
  is zero initially at the origin \begin<<9056>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9056>>$x_1=\cdots=x_N=0$\end<<9057>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9057>>, i.e., 
  \begin<<9058>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9058>>$z-c_1x_1-\cdots-c_Nx_N=0$\end<<9059>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9059>>.
\item The first \begin<<9060>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9060>>$N+M$\end<<9061>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9061>>\space columns contain the coefficients for the \begin<<9062>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9062>>$N$\end<<9063>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9063>> 
  original variables \begin<<9064>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9064>>$\{x_1,\cdots,x_N\}$\end<<9065>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9065>>\space and the \begin<<9066>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9066>>$M$\end<<9067>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9067>>\space slack variables 
  \begin<<9068>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9068>>$\{s_1,\cdots,s_M\}$\end<<9069>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9069>>, and an additional \begin<<9070>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9070>>$(N+M+1)st$\end<<9071>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9071>>\space column is for 
  the constants \begin<<9072>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9072>>$<<5231>>\begin<<16296>>tex2html_deferred<<16296>>\bf\end<<16297>>tex2html_deferred<<16297>>b<<5231>>=[b_1,\cdots,b_M]^T$\end<<9073>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9073>>\space on the right-hand side of
  the \begin<<9074>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9074>>$M$\end<<9075>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9075>>\space constraint equations. The last element of the column is the 
  right-hand side of the objective equation \begin<<9076>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9076>>$z=f(<<5232>>\begin<<16298>>tex2html_deferred<<16298>>\bf\end<<16299>>tex2html_deferred<<16299>>x<<5232>>)$\end<<9077>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9077>>, which is 
  initially zero.
\end<<5233>>itemize<<5233>>
\begin<<16300>>tex2html_deferred<<16300>>\par\end<<16301>>tex2html_deferred<<16301>>
\begin<<5234>>equation<<5234>>
  \begin<<5235>>array<<5235>><<5236>>c||cccc|cccc||c<<5236>>\hline
    \mbox<<5237>>basic variables<<5237>> ;SPMamp; x_1   ;SPMamp; x_2   ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp;  x_N   ;SPMamp; s_1 ;SPMamp; s_2 ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; s_M ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5238>>basic solution<<5238>>   \\ \hline
    s_1   ;SPMamp; a_<<5239>>11<<5239>> ;SPMamp; a_<<5240>>12<<5240>> ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; a_<<5241>>1N<<5241>>  ;SPMamp; 1    ;SPMamp;  0   ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; 0    ;SPMamp; b_1  \\ 
    s_2   ;SPMamp; a_<<5242>>21<<5242>> ;SPMamp; a_<<5243>>22<<5243>> ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; a_<<5244>>2N<<5244>>  ;SPMamp; 0    ;SPMamp;  1   ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; 0    ;SPMamp; b_2  \\ 
    \vdots ;SPMamp; \vdots ;SPMamp; \vdots ;SPMamp; \ddots ;SPMamp; \vdots ;SPMamp; \vdots ;SPMamp; \vdots ;SPMamp; \ddots ;SPMamp; \vdots ;SPMamp; \vdots\\ 
    s_M  ;SPMamp; a_<<5245>>M1<<5245>> ;SPMamp; a_<<5246>>M2<<5246>> ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; a_<<5247>>MN<<5247>>  ;SPMamp; 0    ;SPMamp;  0   ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; 1    ;SPMamp; b_M   \\ \hline
    z   ;SPMamp; -c_1  ;SPMamp; -c_2  ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp;  -c_M  ;SPMamp; 0   ;SPMamp;  0   ;SPMamp; \cdots ;SPMamp; 0  ;SPMamp; 0\\ \hline
  \end<<5248>>array<<5248>>
\end<<5249>>equation<<5249>>
\begin<<16302>>tex2html_deferred<<16302>>\par\end<<16303>>tex2html_deferred<<16303>>
At this initial stage of the iteration, the \begin<<9078>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9078>>$N$\end<<9079>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9079>>\space original variables 
\begin<<9080>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9080>>$<<5250>>\begin<<16304>>tex2html_deferred<<16304>>\bf\end<<16305>>tex2html_deferred<<16305>>x<<5250>>_n=[x_1,\cdots,x_N]^T$\end<<9081>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9081>>\space are the non-basic variables, while the 
\begin<<9082>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9082>>$M$\end<<9083>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9083>>\space slack variables \begin<<9084>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9084>>$<<5251>>\begin<<16306>>tex2html_deferred<<16306>>\bf\end<<16307>>tex2html_deferred<<16307>>x<<5251>>_b=[s_1,\cdots,s_M]^T$\end<<9085>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9085>>\space are the basic variables 
and their coefficients form an \begin<<9086>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9086>>$M\times M$\end<<9087>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9087>>\space identity matrix \begin<<9088>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9088>>$<<5252>>\begin<<16308>>tex2html_deferred<<16308>>\bf\end<<16309>>tex2html_deferred<<16309>>I<<5252>>$\end<<9089>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9089>>, 
composed of the standard basis vectors. The corresponding feasible basic 
solution is simply
\begin<<5253>>equation<<5253>>
  <<5254>>\begin<<16310>>tex2html_deferred<<16310>>\bf\end<<16311>>tex2html_deferred<<16311>>x<<5254>>_b=[s_1,\cdots,s_M]^T=<<5255>>\begin<<16312>>tex2html_deferred<<16312>>\bf\end<<16313>>tex2html_deferred<<16313>>b<<5255>>,\;\;\;\;\; 
  <<5256>>\begin<<16314>>tex2html_deferred<<16314>>\bf\end<<16315>>tex2html_deferred<<16315>>x<<5256>>_n=[x_1,\cdots,x_N]^T=<<5257>>\begin<<16316>>tex2html_deferred<<16316>>\bf\end<<16317>>tex2html_deferred<<16317>>0<<5257>>
\end<<5258>>equation<<5258>>
that satisfies all the constraints
\begin<<9090>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9090>>$<<5259>>\begin<<16318>>tex2html_deferred<<16318>>\bf\end<<16319>>tex2html_deferred<<16319>>Ax<<5259>>=<<5260>>\begin<<16320>>tex2html_deferred<<16320>>\bf\end<<16321>>tex2html_deferred<<16321>>A<<5260>>_n<<5261>>\begin<<16322>>tex2html_deferred<<16322>>\bf\end<<16323>>tex2html_deferred<<16323>>x<<5261>>_n+<<5262>>\begin<<16324>>tex2html_deferred<<16324>>\bf\end<<16325>>tex2html_deferred<<16325>>I<<5262>><<5263>>\begin<<16326>>tex2html_deferred<<16326>>\bf\end<<16327>>tex2html_deferred<<16327>>x<<5263>>_b=<<5264>>\begin<<16328>>tex2html_deferred<<16328>>\bf\end<<16329>>tex2html_deferred<<16329>>b<<5264>>$\end<<9091>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9091>>. 
\begin<<16330>>tex2html_deferred<<16330>>\par\end<<16331>>tex2html_deferred<<16331>>
In each of the subsequent iterations, we will select one of the non-basic
variables, called the <<5265>>\begin<<16332>>tex2html_deferred<<16332>>\em\end<<16333>>tex2html_deferred<<16333>>entering variable<<5265>>, to replace one of the basic
variables, called the <<5266>>\begin<<16334>>tex2html_deferred<<16334>>\em\end<<16335>>tex2html_deferred<<16335>>leaving variable<<5266>>, in such a way that the value
of the objective function value \begin<<9092>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9092>>$z=f(<<5267>>\begin<<16336>>tex2html_deferred<<16336>>\bf\end<<16337>>tex2html_deferred<<16337>>x<<5267>>)$\end<<9093>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9093>>\space in the last row will be 
maximally increased, while all constraints remain satisfied. Here are the 
steps in each iteration:
\begin<<16338>>tex2html_deferred<<16338>>\par\end<<16339>>tex2html_deferred<<16339>>
\begin<<5268>>itemize<<5268>>
\item <<5269>>\begin<<16340>>tex2html_deferred<<16340>>\bf\end<<16341>>tex2html_deferred<<16341>>Selection of the entering variable<<5269>>
\begin<<16342>>tex2html_deferred<<16342>>\par\end<<16343>>tex2html_deferred<<16343>>
This section is based on the maximization of \begin<<9094>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9094>>$z=f(<<5270>>\begin<<16344>>tex2html_deferred<<16344>>\bf\end<<16345>>tex2html_deferred<<16345>>x<<5270>>)$\end<<9095>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9095>>. We select 
  \begin<<9096>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9096>>$x_j$\end<<9097>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9097>>\space in the jth column of the tableau if \begin<<9098>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9098>>$-c_j$\end<<9099>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9099>>\space is most negative, i.e.,
  \begin<<9100>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9100>>$x_j$\end<<9101>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9101>>\space is most heavily weighted by \begin<<9102>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9102>>$c_j=\max\{c_1,\cdots,c_N\}$\end<<9103>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9103>>, so that 
  it will increase \begin<<9104>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9104>>$z=\sum_<<5271>>j=1<<5271>>^N c_jx_j$\end<<9105>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9105>>\space more than any other \begin<<9106>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9106>>$x_k\;\;(k\ne j)$\end<<9107>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9107>>. 
\begin<<16346>>tex2html_deferred<<16346>>\par\end<<16347>>tex2html_deferred<<16347>>
\item <<5272>>\begin<<16348>>tex2html_deferred<<16348>>\bf\end<<16349>>tex2html_deferred<<16349>>Selection of the leaving variable<<5272>>
\begin<<16350>>tex2html_deferred<<16350>>\par\end<<16351>>tex2html_deferred<<16351>>
This selection is based on the constraints imposed on the selected 
  entering variable \begin<<9108>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9108>>$x_j$\end<<9109>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9109>>. In general, the restriction on \begin<<9110>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9110>>$x_j$\end<<9111>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9111>>\space set by 
  the kth constraint \begin<<9112>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9112>>$\sum_<<5273>>j=1<<5273>>^N a_<<5274>>kj<<5274>>x_j\le b_k$\end<<9113>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9113>>\space is \begin<<9114>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9114>>$x_j\le b_k/a_<<5275>>kj<<5275>>$\end<<9115>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9115>>
  when \begin<<9116>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9116>>$a_<<5276>>kj<<5276>>;SPMgt;0$\end<<9117>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9117>>. If \begin<<9118>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9118>>$b_i/a_<<5277>>ij<<5277>> \le b_k/a_<<5278>>kj<<5278>>$\end<<9119>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9119>>\space for all \begin<<9120>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9120>>$k=1,\cdots,M$\end<<9121>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9121>>,
  then the ith constraint is most restrictive on \begin<<9122>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9122>>$x_j$\end<<9123>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9123>>, we will therefore
  select the corresponding basic variable \begin<<9124>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9124>>$s_i$\end<<9125>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9125>>\space as the leaving variable,
  i.e., it becomes a non-basic variable to be set to zero, so that \begin<<9126>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9126>>$x_j$\end<<9127>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9127>>
  can be maximally increased without violating the constraints. If all 
  \begin<<9128>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9128>>$a_<<5279>>kj<<5279>>;SPMlt;0$\end<<9129>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9129>>\space for all \begin<<9130>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9130>>$k=1,\cdots,M$\end<<9131>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9131>>, variable \begin<<9132>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9132>>$x_j$\end<<9133>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9133>>\space is not bounded.
\begin<<16352>>tex2html_deferred<<16352>>\par\end<<16353>>tex2html_deferred<<16353>>
\item <<5280>>\begin<<16354>>tex2html_deferred<<16354>>\bf\end<<16355>>tex2html_deferred<<16355>>Gauss-Jordan elimination based on Pivoting<<5280>>
\begin<<16356>>tex2html_deferred<<16356>>\par\end<<16357>>tex2html_deferred<<16357>>
To convert the entering variable \begin<<9134>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9134>>$x_j$\end<<9135>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9135>>\space to a basic variable to replace the
  leaving variable \begin<<9136>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9136>>$s_i$\end<<9137>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9137>>, we need to turn the corresponding jth column into a
  standard basis vector \begin<<9138>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9138>>$<<5281>>\begin<<16358>>tex2html_deferred<<16358>>\bf\end<<16359>>tex2html_deferred<<16359>>e<<5281>>_i$\end<<9139>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9139>>. This is realized by pivoting on \begin<<9140>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9140>>$a_<<5282>>ij<<5282>>$\end<<9141>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9141>>
  in the following steps:
  \begin<<5283>>enumerate<<5283>>
  \item Divide the ith row by \begin<<9142>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9142>>$a_<<5284>>ij<<5284>>$\end<<9143>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9143>>: \begin<<9144>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9144>>$<<5285>>\begin<<16360>>tex2html_deferred<<16360>>\bf\end<<16361>>tex2html_deferred<<16361>>r<<5285>>_i\leftarrow<<5286>>\begin<<16362>>tex2html_deferred<<16362>>\bf\end<<16363>>tex2html_deferred<<16363>>r<<5286>>_i/a_<<5287>>ij<<5287>>$\end<<9145>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9145>>.
    Now \begin<<9146>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9146>>$a_<<5288>>ij<<5288>>=1$\end<<9147>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9147>>.
  \item Subtract \begin<<9148>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9148>>$a_<<5289>>kj<<5289>>$\end<<9149>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9149>>\space times the ith row from the kth row:
    \begin<<9150>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9150>>$<<5290>>\begin<<16364>>tex2html_deferred<<16364>>\bf\end<<16365>>tex2html_deferred<<16365>>r<<5290>>_k\leftarrow<<5291>>\begin<<16366>>tex2html_deferred<<16366>>\bf\end<<16367>>tex2html_deferred<<16367>>r<<5291>>_k-a_<<5292>>kj<<5292>><<5293>>\begin<<16368>>tex2html_deferred<<16368>>\bf\end<<16369>>tex2html_deferred<<16369>>r<<5293>>_i$\end<<9151>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9151>>. 
    Now \begin<<9152>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9152>>$a_<<5294>>kj<<5294>>=0$\end<<9153>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9153>>\space for all \begin<<9154>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9154>>$k=1,\cdots,M$\end<<9155>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9155>>, \begin<<9156>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9156>>$k\ne i$\end<<9157>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9157>>.
  \end<<5295>>enumerate<<5295>>
  Now the jth column corresponding to the entering variable \begin<<9158>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9158>>$x_j$\end<<9159>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9159>>\space becomes
  a standard basis vector \begin<<9160>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9160>>$<<5296>>\begin<<16370>>tex2html_deferred<<16370>>\bf\end<<16371>>tex2html_deferred<<16371>>e<<5296>>_i$\end<<9161>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9161>>, i.e., \begin<<9162>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9162>>$x_j$\end<<9163>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9163>>\space becomes a basic variable 
  that takes the value of \begin<<9164>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9164>>$b_i$\end<<9165>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9165>>, and the column corresponding to the leaving 
  variable \begin<<9166>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9166>>$s_i$\end<<9167>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9167>>\space is no longer a standard basis vector, and \begin<<9168>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9168>>$s_i=0$\end<<9169>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9169>>\space as it is
  now a non-basic variable.
\begin<<16372>>tex2html_deferred<<16372>>\par\end<<16373>>tex2html_deferred<<16373>>
\end<<5297>>itemize<<5297>>
\begin<<16374>>tex2html_deferred<<16374>>\par\end<<16375>>tex2html_deferred<<16375>>
As Gauss-Jordan elimination converts the linear equations to a set of 
equivalent equations, the constraints remain satisfied through out the 
process. Although the membership of the basic and non-basic variable 
groups keeps changing in the iteration, so long as \begin<<9170>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9170>>$<<5298>>\begin<<16376>>tex2html_deferred<<16376>>\bf\end<<16377>>tex2html_deferred<<16377>>x<<5298>>_b=<<5299>>\begin<<16378>>tex2html_deferred<<16378>>\bf\end<<16379>>tex2html_deferred<<16379>>b<<5299>>$\end<<9171>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9171>> 
and \begin<<9172>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9172>>$<<5300>>\begin<<16380>>tex2html_deferred<<16380>>\bf\end<<16381>>tex2html_deferred<<16381>>x<<5300>>_n=<<5301>>\begin<<16382>>tex2html_deferred<<16382>>\bf\end<<16383>>tex2html_deferred<<16383>>0<<5301>>$\end<<9173>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9173>>, the \begin<<9174>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9174>>$M$\end<<9175>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9175>>\space constraint equations 
\begin<<9176>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9176>>$<<5302>>\begin<<16384>>tex2html_deferred<<16384>>\bf\end<<16385>>tex2html_deferred<<16385>>Ax<<5302>>=<<5303>>\begin<<16386>>tex2html_deferred<<16386>>\bf\end<<16387>>tex2html_deferred<<16387>>A<<5303>>_n<<5304>>\begin<<16388>>tex2html_deferred<<16388>>\bf\end<<16389>>tex2html_deferred<<16389>>x<<5304>>_n+<<5305>>\begin<<16390>>tex2html_deferred<<16390>>\bf\end<<16391>>tex2html_deferred<<16391>>I<<5305>><<5306>>\begin<<16392>>tex2html_deferred<<16392>>\bf\end<<16393>>tex2html_deferred<<16393>>x<<5306>>_b=<<5307>>\begin<<16394>>tex2html_deferred<<16394>>\bf\end<<16395>>tex2html_deferred<<16395>>b<<5307>>$\end<<9177>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9177>>\space always holds.
\begin<<16396>>tex2html_deferred<<16396>>\par\end<<16397>>tex2html_deferred<<16397>>
This iterative process keeps replacing the slack variables 
\begin<<9178>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9178>>$\{s_1,\cdots,s_M\}$\end<<9179>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9179>>\space (the basic variables initially) by the original 
variables \begin<<9180>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9180>>$\{x_1,\cdots,x_N\}$\end<<9181>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9181>>\space (the non-basic variables initially), 
one at a time, until all elements in the last row are non-negative.
\begin<<16398>>tex2html_deferred<<16398>>\par\end<<16399>>tex2html_deferred<<16399>>
The final result can be read out directly from the tableau. The variables 
corresponding to the \begin<<9182>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9182>>$M$\end<<9183>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9183>>\space standard basis vectors \begin<<9184>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9184>>$<<5308>>\begin<<16400>>tex2html_deferred<<16400>>\bf\end<<16401>>tex2html_deferred<<16401>>e<<5308>>_i$\end<<9185>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9185>>\space (\begin<<9186>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9186>>$i=1,\cdots,M$\end<<9187>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9187>>) 
are the final basic variables that take the values in \begin<<9188>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9188>>$<<5309>>\begin<<16402>>tex2html_deferred<<16402>>\bf\end<<16403>>tex2html_deferred<<16403>>b<<5309>>$\end<<9189>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9189>>\space in the
right-most column of the tableau. They form the optimal basic solution, 
with the maximum of the objective function \begin<<9190>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9190>>$z=f(<<5310>>\begin<<16404>>tex2html_deferred<<16404>>\bf\end<<16405>>tex2html_deferred<<16405>>x<<5310>>)$\end<<9191>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9191>>\space given by the last 
element also in the last column. The remaining \begin<<9192>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9192>>$n$\end<<9193>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9193>>\space variables corresponding 
to non-standard columns are non-basic variables that take the value zero. 
When \begin<<9194>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9194>>$M;SPMgt;N$\end<<9195>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9195>>\space (more constraints than variables), some of the slack variables 
may remain in the basic variable group taking non-zero values; when \begin<<9196>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9196>>$M;SPMlt;N$\end<<9197>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9197>>, 
some of the original variable may be in the non-basic group taking the value
zero.
\begin<<16406>>tex2html_deferred<<16406>>\par\end<<16407>>tex2html_deferred<<16407>>
<<5311>>\begin<<16408>>tex2html_deferred<<16408>>\bf\end<<16409>>tex2html_deferred<<16409>>Example:<<5311>>
\begin<<16410>>tex2html_deferred<<16410>>\par\end<<16411>>tex2html_deferred<<16411>>
There are \begin<<9198>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9198>>$C_<<5312>>M+N<<5312>>^M=C_<<5313>>10<<5313>>^3=10$\end<<9199>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9199>>\space basic solutions as listed below, 
out of which five are basic feasible solutions with all \begin<<9200>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9200>>$M+N=5$\end<<9201>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9201>>
variables taking non-negative values. The remaining solutions 
are not feasible, as some of the variables take negative values.
\begin<<16412>>tex2html_deferred<<16412>>\par\end<<16413>>tex2html_deferred<<16413>>
\begin<<5314>>equation<<5314>>
  \begin<<5315>>array<<5315>><<5316>>c|ccccc|c|c<<5316>>\hline
    ;SPMamp; x_1 ;SPMamp; x_2 ;SPMamp; s_1 ;SPMamp; s_2 ;SPMamp; s_3 ;SPMamp; ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5317>>objective function (normalized)<<5317>> \\ \hline
    1 ;SPMamp; 5 ;SPMamp; 6 ;SPMamp; 2 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5318>>feasible<<5318>>   ;SPMamp; 28\; (7.77) \\ 
    2 ;SPMamp;6.25 ;SPMamp; 5.5 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; -5 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5319>>infeasible<<5319>> ;SPMamp; 29\; (8.04) \\ 
    3 ;SPMamp; 7.5 ;SPMamp; 3 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 10 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5320>>feasible<<5320>>   ;SPMamp; 24\; (6.66) \\ 
    4 ;SPMamp;20 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; -2 ;SPMamp; -60 ;SPMamp; 20  ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5321>>infeasible<<5321>> ;SPMamp; 40\; (11.1) \\ 
    5 ;SPMamp;10 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; -2 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 20 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5322>>infeasible<<5322>> ;SPMamp; 20\; (5.55) \\ 
    6 ;SPMamp; 9 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 6 ;SPMamp; 22 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5323>>feasible<<5323>>   ;SPMamp; 18\; (4.10) \\ 
    7 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 8 ;SPMamp; 10 ;SPMamp; 20 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5324>>feasible<<5324>>   ;SPMamp; 24\; (6.66) \\ 
    8 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 12 ;SPMamp; 6 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; -20 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5325>>infeasible<<5325>> ;SPMamp; 36\; (9.98) \\ 
    9 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 18 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; -30 ;SPMamp; -50 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5326>>infeasible<<5326>> ;SPMamp; 54\; (14.99) \\ 
    10;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 18 ;SPMamp; 60 ;SPMamp; 40 ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5327>>feasible<<5327>>   ;SPMamp;  0\; (0.00) \\ \hline
  \end<<5328>>array<<5328>>
  \nonumber
\end<<5329>>equation<<5329>>
\begin<<16414>>tex2html_deferred<<16414>>\par\end<<16415>>tex2html_deferred<<16415>>
<<5330>>\begin<<16416>>tex2html_deferred<<16416>>\bf\end<<16417>>tex2html_deferred<<16417>>Example:<<5330>>
\begin<<16418>>tex2html_deferred<<16418>>\par\end<<16419>>tex2html_deferred<<16419>>
We re-solve the LP problem considered in the previous examples, now 
in the standard form:
\begin<<5331>>equation<<5331>>
  \begin<<5332>>array<<5332>><<5333>>ll<<5333>>
    \mbox<<5334>>maximize<<5334>>    ;SPMamp; f(<<5335>>\begin<<16420>>tex2html_deferred<<16420>>\bf\end<<16421>>tex2html_deferred<<16421>>x<<5335>>)=2x_1+3x_2 \\ 
    \mbox<<5336>>subject to:<<5336>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{ \begin<<5337>>array<<5337>><<5338>>l<<5338>>
      2x_1+ x_2+s_1=18\\  6x_1+5x_2+s_2=60 \\  2x_1+5x_2+s_3=40 \\  
      x_1 \ge 0,\; x_2\ge 0,\; s_1\ge 0,\; s_2\ge 0,\; s_3\ge0
    \end<<5339>>array<<5339>>\right.
  \end<<5340>>array<<5340>>
  \nonumber
\end<<5341>>equation<<5341>>
The standard form is further converted to a tableau as shown below. The 
left-most column indicates the basic variables, the next \begin<<9202>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9202>>$N=2$\end<<9203>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9203>>\space columns 
are for the variables \begin<<9204>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9204>>$x$\end<<9205>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9205>>\space and \begin<<9206>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9206>>$y$\end<<9207>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9207>>,the next \begin<<9208>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9208>>$M=3$\end<<9209>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9209>>\space columns are for the slack 
variables \begin<<9210>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9210>>$u$\end<<9211>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9211>>, \begin<<9212>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9212>>$v$\end<<9213>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9213>>, and \begin<<9214>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9214>>$w$\end<<9215>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9215>>, the right most column is for the constants 
\begin<<9216>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9216>>$b_1$\end<<9217>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9217>>, \begin<<9218>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9218>>$b_2$\end<<9219>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9219>>, and \begin<<9220>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9220>>$b_3$\end<<9221>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9221>>\space on the right-hand side of the equations.
\begin<<16422>>tex2html_deferred<<16422>>\par\end<<16423>>tex2html_deferred<<16423>>
\begin<<5342>>equation<<5342>>
  \begin<<5343>>array<<5343>><<5344>>c|cc|ccc|c<<5344>>  \hline
    ;SPMamp; x_1 ;SPMamp; x_2 ;SPMamp; s_1 ;SPMamp; s_2 ;SPMamp; s_3 ;SPMamp; b  \\ \hline
    s_1 ;SPMamp; 2 ;SPMamp; 1 ;SPMamp; 1 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 18 \\ 
    s_2 ;SPMamp; 6 ;SPMamp; 5 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 1 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 60 \\ 
    s_3 ;SPMamp; 2 ;SPMamp; 5 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 1 ;SPMamp; 40 \\ \hline
    z ;SPMamp;-2 ;SPMamp;-3 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0  \\ \hline
  \end<<5345>>array<<5345>>
  \nonumber
\end<<5346>>equation<<5346>>
\begin<<16424>>tex2html_deferred<<16424>>\par\end<<16425>>tex2html_deferred<<16425>>
In this initial state, the basic variables are \begin<<9222>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9222>>$s_1=18$\end<<9223>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9223>>, \begin<<9224>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9224>>$s_2=60$\end<<9225>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9225>>, and 
\begin<<9226>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9226>>$s_3=40$\end<<9227>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9227>>, the non-basic variables are \begin<<9228>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9228>>$x_1=x_2=0$\end<<9229>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9229>>. The corresponding basic
feasible solution is at the origin.
\begin<<16426>>tex2html_deferred<<16426>>\par\end<<16427>>tex2html_deferred<<16427>>
\begin<<5347>>itemize<<5347>>
\item Select column \begin<<9230>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9230>>$j=2$\end<<9231>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9231>>\space as the pivot column, as \begin<<9232>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9232>>$-c_2=-3$\end<<9233>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9233>>\space is the most 
  negative coefficient.
\item Select row \begin<<9234>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9234>>$i=3$\end<<9235>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9235>>\space as the pivot row, as the ratio 
  \begin<<9236>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9236>>$b_3/a_<<5348>>32<<5348>>=40/5=8$\end<<9237>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9237>>\space is the minimum among all \begin<<9238>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9238>>$M=3$\end<<9239>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9239>>\space ratios \begin<<9240>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9240>>$b_k/a_<<5349>>k2<<5349>>$\end<<9241>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9241>>
  (\begin<<9242>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9242>>$18/1,\;60/5,\;40/5$\end<<9243>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9243>>).
\item Divide pivot row \begin<<9244>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9244>>$<<5350>>\begin<<16428>>tex2html_deferred<<16428>>\bf\end<<16429>>tex2html_deferred<<16429>>r<<5350>>_i=<<5351>>\begin<<16430>>tex2html_deferred<<16430>>\bf\end<<16431>>tex2html_deferred<<16431>>r<<5351>>_3=[2,\;5,\;0,\;0,\;1,\;40]$\end<<9245>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9245>>\space by 
  the pivot element \begin<<9246>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9246>>$a_<<5352>>ij<<5352>>=a_<<5353>>32<<5353>>=5$\end<<9247>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9247>>\space to get \begin<<9248>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9248>>$<<5354>>\begin<<16432>>tex2html_deferred<<16432>>\bf\end<<16433>>tex2html_deferred<<16433>>r<<5354>>_3=[0.4,\;1,\;0,\;0,\;0.2,\;8]$\end<<9249>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9249>>.
\item Subtract \begin<<9250>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9250>>$a_<<5355>>kj<<5355>>=a_<<5356>>k2<<5356>>$\end<<9251>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9251>>\begin<<9252>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9252>>$<<5357>>\begin<<16434>>tex2html_deferred<<16434>>\bf\end<<16435>>tex2html_deferred<<16435>>r<<5357>>_k$\end<<9253>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9253>>\space from row \begin<<9254>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9254>>$<<5358>>\begin<<16436>>tex2html_deferred<<16436>>\bf\end<<16437>>tex2html_deferred<<16437>>r<<5358>>_k$\end<<9255>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9255>>, so that 
  \begin<<9256>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9256>>$a_<<5359>>kj<<5359>>=a_<<5360>>k2<<5360>>=0, \;(k=1,2)$\end<<9257>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9257>>.
\item Subtract \begin<<9258>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9258>>$a_<<5361>>4j<<5361>><<5362>>\begin<<16438>>tex2html_deferred<<16438>>\bf\end<<16439>>tex2html_deferred<<16439>>r<<5362>>_i=a_<<5363>>42<<5363>><<5364>>\begin<<16440>>tex2html_deferred<<16440>>\bf\end<<16441>>tex2html_deferred<<16441>>r<<5364>>_3$\end<<9259>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9259>>\space from \begin<<9260>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9260>>$<<5365>>\begin<<16442>>tex2html_deferred<<16442>>\bf\end<<16443>>tex2html_deferred<<16443>>r<<5365>>_4$\end<<9261>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9261>>\space (last row).
\end<<5366>>itemize<<5366>>
\begin<<16444>>tex2html_deferred<<16444>>\par\end<<16445>>tex2html_deferred<<16445>>
\begin<<5367>>equation<<5367>>
  \begin<<5368>>array<<5368>><<5369>>c|cc|ccc|c<<5369>>     \hline
    ;SPMamp; x_1 ;SPMamp; x_2 ;SPMamp; s_1 ;SPMamp; s_2 ;SPMamp; s_3  ;SPMamp;  b  \\ \hline
    s_1 ;SPMamp;1.6;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 1 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp;-0.2;SPMamp; 10  \\ 
    s_2 ;SPMamp; 4 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 1 ;SPMamp;-1  ;SPMamp; 20  \\ 
    x_2 ;SPMamp;0.4;SPMamp;1.0;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0.2;SPMamp;  8  \\ \hline
    z ;SPMamp;-0.8;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp;0.6;SPMamp; 24  \\ \hline
  \end<<5370>>array<<5370>>
  \nonumber
\end<<5371>>equation<<5371>>
\begin<<16446>>tex2html_deferred<<16446>>\par\end<<16447>>tex2html_deferred<<16447>>
The entering variable \begin<<9262>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9262>>$y$\end<<9263>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9263>>\space becomes a basic variable to replace the 
leaving variable \begin<<9264>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9264>>$w$\end<<9265>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9265>>\space which becomes a non-basic variable. The corresponding
basic feasible solution is at \begin<<9266>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9266>>$x_1=0$\end<<9267>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9267>>, \begin<<9268>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9268>>$x_2=b_3=8$\end<<9269>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9269>>, with \begin<<9270>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9270>>$s_1=10$\end<<9271>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9271>>, \begin<<9272>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9272>>$s_2=20$\end<<9273>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9273>>,
\begin<<9274>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9274>>$s_3=0$\end<<9275>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9275>>. The objective function value is \begin<<9276>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9276>>$z=24$\end<<9277>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9277>>.
\begin<<16448>>tex2html_deferred<<16448>>\par\end<<16449>>tex2html_deferred<<16449>>
\begin<<5372>>itemize<<5372>>
\item Select column \begin<<9278>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9278>>$j=1$\end<<9279>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9279>>\space as the pivot column, as \begin<<9280>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9280>>$-c_1=-0.8$\end<<9281>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9281>>\space is the most 
  (only) negative coefficient.
\item Select row \begin<<9282>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9282>>$i=2$\end<<9283>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9283>>\space as the pivot row, as the ratio 
  \begin<<9284>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9284>>$b_2/a_<<5373>>21<<5373>>=20/4=5$\end<<9285>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9285>>\space is the minimum among all \begin<<9286>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9286>>$M=3$\end<<9287>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9287>>\space ratios \begin<<9288>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9288>>$b_k/a_<<5374>>k1<<5374>>$\end<<9289>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9289>>
  (\begin<<9290>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9290>>$10/1.6=6.25,\;20/4=5,\;8/0.4=20$\end<<9291>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9291>>).
\item Divide row \begin<<9292>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9292>>$<<5375>>\begin<<16450>>tex2html_deferred<<16450>>\bf\end<<16451>>tex2html_deferred<<16451>>r<<5375>>_i=<<5376>>\begin<<16452>>tex2html_deferred<<16452>>\bf\end<<16453>>tex2html_deferred<<16453>>r<<5376>>_2=[4,\;0,\;0,\;1,\;-1,\;20]$\end<<9293>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9293>>\space by the pivot 
  element \begin<<9294>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9294>>$a_<<5377>>21<<5377>>=4$\end<<9295>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9295>>\space to get \begin<<9296>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9296>>$<<5378>>\begin<<16454>>tex2html_deferred<<16454>>\bf\end<<16455>>tex2html_deferred<<16455>>r<<5378>>_2=[1,\;0,\;0,\;0.25,\;-0.25,\;5]$\end<<9297>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9297>>.
\item Subtract \begin<<9298>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9298>>$a_<<5379>>k1<<5379>>$\end<<9299>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9299>>\begin<<9300>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9300>>$<<5380>>\begin<<16456>>tex2html_deferred<<16456>>\bf\end<<16457>>tex2html_deferred<<16457>>r<<5380>>_k$\end<<9301>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9301>>\space from row \begin<<9302>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9302>>$<<5381>>\begin<<16458>>tex2html_deferred<<16458>>\bf\end<<16459>>tex2html_deferred<<16459>>r<<5381>>_k$\end<<9303>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9303>>, so that 
  \begin<<9304>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9304>>$a_<<5382>>k1<<5382>>=0, (k=1,3)$\end<<9305>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9305>>.
\item Subtract \begin<<9306>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9306>>$a_<<5383>>4j<<5383>><<5384>>\begin<<16460>>tex2html_deferred<<16460>>\bf\end<<16461>>tex2html_deferred<<16461>>r<<5384>>_i=a_<<5385>>41<<5385>><<5386>>\begin<<16462>>tex2html_deferred<<16462>>\bf\end<<16463>>tex2html_deferred<<16463>>r<<5386>>_4$\end<<9307>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9307>>\space from \begin<<9308>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9308>>$<<5387>>\begin<<16464>>tex2html_deferred<<16464>>\bf\end<<16465>>tex2html_deferred<<16465>>r<<5387>>_4$\end<<9309>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9309>>\space (last row).
\end<<5388>>itemize<<5388>>
\begin<<16466>>tex2html_deferred<<16466>>\par\end<<16467>>tex2html_deferred<<16467>>
\begin<<5389>>equation<<5389>>
  \begin<<5390>>array<<5390>><<5391>>c|cc|ccc|c<<5391>>       \hline
    ;SPMamp; x_1 ;SPMamp; x_2 ;SPMamp; s_1 ;SPMamp; s_2  ;SPMamp; s_3   ;SPMamp; b   \\ \hline
    s_1 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 1 ;SPMamp;-0.4;SPMamp; 0.2 ;SPMamp; 2   \\ 
    x_1 ;SPMamp; 1 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp;0.25;SPMamp;-0.25;SPMamp; 5   \\ 
    x_2 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 1 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp;-0,1;SPMamp; 0.3 ;SPMamp; 6   \\ \hline
    z ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0 ;SPMamp; 0.2;SPMamp; 0.4 ;SPMamp; 28  \\ \hline
  \end<<5392>>array<<5392>>
  \nonumber
\end<<5393>>equation<<5393>>
\begin<<16468>>tex2html_deferred<<16468>>\par\end<<16469>>tex2html_deferred<<16469>>
The entering variable \begin<<9310>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9310>>$x$\end<<9311>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9311>>\space becomes a basic variable to replace the leaving 
variable \begin<<9312>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9312>>$v$\end<<9313>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9313>>\space which becomes a non-basic variable. The corresponding basic 
feasible solution is at \begin<<9314>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9314>>$x_1=b_2=5$\end<<9315>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9315>>\space and \begin<<9316>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9316>>$y_2=b_3=6$\end<<9317>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9317>>, with \begin<<9318>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9318>>$s_1=2$\end<<9319>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9319>>, and 
\begin<<9320>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9320>>$s_2=s_3=0$\end<<9321>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9321>>. The objective function value is \begin<<9322>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9322>>$z=28$\end<<9323>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9323>>.
\begin<<16470>>tex2html_deferred<<16470>>\par\end<<16471>>tex2html_deferred<<16471>>
This problem has \begin<<9324>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9324>>$C_<<5394>>N+M<<5394>>^M=C_5^3=10$\end<<9325>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9325>>\space basic solutions, corresponding
to the same number of intersections, out of which five are feasible,
as previously obtained. The simplex method finds three of these feasible
solutions, starting from \begin<<9326>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9326>>$x_1=s_2=0$\end<<9327>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9327>>\space at the origin with \begin<<9328>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9328>>$z=0$\end<<9329>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9329>>, through 
the vertex at \begin<<9330>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9330>>$x_1=0$\end<<9331>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9331>>\space and \begin<<9332>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9332>>$x_2=8$\end<<9333>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9333>>\space with \begin<<9334>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9334>>$z=24$\end<<9335>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9335>>, to the optimal solution 
at \begin<<9336>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9336>>$x_1=5$\end<<9337>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9337>>\space and \begin<<9338>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9338>>$x_2=6$\end<<9339>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9339>>\space with \begin<<9340>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9340>>$z=28$\end<<9341>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9341>>.
\begin<<16472>>tex2html_deferred<<16472>>\par\end<<16473>>tex2html_deferred<<16473>>
\subsection*<<5395>>Quadratic Programming (QP)<<5395>>
\begin<<16474>>tex2html_deferred<<16474>>\par\end<<16475>>tex2html_deferred<<16475>>
A quadratic programming (QP) problem is to minimize a quadratic function 
subject to some equality and/or inequality constraints:
\begin<<5396>>equation<<5396>>
  \begin<<5397>>array<<5397>><<5398>>ll<<5398>>
    \mbox<<5399>>minimize<<5399>>    ;SPMamp; 
         f(<<5400>>\begin<<16476>>tex2html_deferred<<16476>>\bf\end<<16477>>tex2html_deferred<<16477>>x<<5400>>)=\frac<<5401>>1<<5401>><<5402>>2<<5402>>[<<5403>>\begin<<16478>>tex2html_deferred<<16478>>\bf\end<<16479>>tex2html_deferred<<16479>>x<<5403>>-<<5404>>\begin<<16480>>tex2html_deferred<<16480>>\bf\end<<16481>>tex2html_deferred<<16481>>m<<5404>>]^T<<5405>>\begin<<16482>>tex2html_deferred<<16482>>\bf\end<<16483>>tex2html_deferred<<16483>>Q<<5405>>[<<5406>>\begin<<16484>>tex2html_deferred<<16484>>\bf\end<<16485>>tex2html_deferred<<16485>>x<<5406>>-<<5407>>\begin<<16486>>tex2html_deferred<<16486>>\bf\end<<16487>>tex2html_deferred<<16487>>m<<5407>>]
         =\frac<<5408>>1<<5408>><<5409>>2<<5409>><<5410>>\begin<<16488>>tex2html_deferred<<16488>>\bf\end<<16489>>tex2html_deferred<<16489>>x<<5410>>^T<<5411>>\begin<<16490>>tex2html_deferred<<16490>>\bf\end<<16491>>tex2html_deferred<<16491>>Q<<5411>><<5412>>\begin<<16492>>tex2html_deferred<<16492>>\bf\end<<16493>>tex2html_deferred<<16493>>x<<5412>>+<<5413>>\begin<<16494>>tex2html_deferred<<16494>>\bf\end<<16495>>tex2html_deferred<<16495>>c<<5413>>^T<<5414>>\begin<<16496>>tex2html_deferred<<16496>>\bf\end<<16497>>tex2html_deferred<<16497>>x<<5414>>+c
    \;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\\ 
    \mbox<<5415>>subject to:<<5415>> ;SPMamp; <<5416>>\begin<<16498>>tex2html_deferred<<16498>>\bf\end<<16499>>tex2html_deferred<<16499>>A<<5416>><<5417>>\begin<<16500>>tex2html_deferred<<16500>>\bf\end<<16501>>tex2html_deferred<<16501>>x<<5417>>\le<<5418>>\begin<<16502>>tex2html_deferred<<16502>>\bf\end<<16503>>tex2html_deferred<<16503>>b<<5418>>
  \end<<5419>>array<<5419>>
\end<<5420>>equation<<5420>>
where \begin<<9342>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9342>>$<<5421>>\begin<<16504>>tex2html_deferred<<16504>>\bf\end<<16505>>tex2html_deferred<<16505>>Q<<5421>>=<<5422>>\begin<<16506>>tex2html_deferred<<16506>>\bf\end<<16507>>tex2html_deferred<<16507>>Q<<5422>>^T$\end<<9343>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9343>>\space is a positive definite matrix, \begin<<9344>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9344>>$<<5423>>\begin<<16508>>tex2html_deferred<<16508>>\bf\end<<16509>>tex2html_deferred<<16509>>c<<5423>>=-<<5424>>\begin<<16510>>tex2html_deferred<<16510>>\bf\end<<16511>>tex2html_deferred<<16511>>Qm<<5424>>,
\;c=<<5425>>\begin<<16512>>tex2html_deferred<<16512>>\bf\end<<16513>>tex2html_deferred<<16513>>m<<5425>>^T<<5426>>\begin<<16514>>tex2html_deferred<<16514>>\bf\end<<16515>>tex2html_deferred<<16515>>Q<<5426>><<5427>>\begin<<16516>>tex2html_deferred<<16516>>\bf\end<<16517>>tex2html_deferred<<16517>>m<<5427>>/2$\end<<9345>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9345>>. Here the scalar constant \begin<<9346>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9346>>$c$\end<<9347>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9347>>\space can be dropped
as it does not play any role in the optimization.
\begin<<16518>>tex2html_deferred<<16518>>\par\end<<16519>>tex2html_deferred<<16519>>
We let \begin<<9348>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9348>>$<<5428>>\begin<<16520>>tex2html_deferred<<16520>>\bf\end<<16521>>tex2html_deferred<<16521>>Q<<5428>>$\end<<9349>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9349>>\space be an \begin<<9350>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9350>>$N\times N$\end<<9351>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9351>>\space matrix, \begin<<9352>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9352>>$<<5429>>\begin<<16522>>tex2html_deferred<<16522>>\bf\end<<16523>>tex2html_deferred<<16523>>A<<5429>>$\end<<9353>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9353>>\space an \begin<<9354>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9354>>$m\times N$\end<<9355>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9355>>\space matrix,
and \begin<<9356>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9356>>$<<5430>>\begin<<16524>>tex2html_deferred<<16524>>\bf\end<<16525>>tex2html_deferred<<16525>>b<<5430>>$\end<<9357>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9357>>\space is an m-D vector, and \begin<<9358>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9358>>$<<5431>>\begin<<16526>>tex2html_deferred<<16526>>\bf\end<<16527>>tex2html_deferred<<16527>>x<<5431>>^T<<5432>>\begin<<16528>>tex2html_deferred<<16528>>\bf\end<<16529>>tex2html_deferred<<16529>>Q<<5432>><<5433>>\begin<<16530>>tex2html_deferred<<16530>>\bf\end<<16531>>tex2html_deferred<<16531>>x<<5433>>$\end<<9359>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9359>>\space is a hyper 
elliptic paraboloid with the minimum at point \begin<<9360>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9360>>$<<5434>>\begin<<16532>>tex2html_deferred<<16532>>\bf\end<<16533>>tex2html_deferred<<16533>>m<<5434>>$\end<<9361>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9361>>\space in the N-D space.
\begin<<16534>>tex2html_deferred<<16534>>\par\end<<16535>>tex2html_deferred<<16535>>
We first consider the special case where the QP problem is only subject to
equality constraints and we assume \begin<<9362>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9362>>$m\le N$\end<<9363>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9363>>, i.e., the number of constraints
is smaller than the number of unknowns in \begin<<9364>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9364>>$<<5435>>\begin<<16536>>tex2html_deferred<<16536>>\bf\end<<16537>>tex2html_deferred<<16537>>x<<5435>>$\end<<9365>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9365>>. Then the solution 
\begin<<9366>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9366>>$<<5436>>\begin<<16538>>tex2html_deferred<<16538>>\bf\end<<16539>>tex2html_deferred<<16539>>x<<5436>>$\end<<9367>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9367>>\space has to satisfy \begin<<9368>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9368>>$<<5437>>\begin<<16540>>tex2html_deferred<<16540>>\bf\end<<16541>>tex2html_deferred<<16541>>Ax<<5437>>-<<5438>>\begin<<16542>>tex2html_deferred<<16542>>\bf\end<<16543>>tex2html_deferred<<16543>>b<<5438>>=<<5439>>\begin<<16544>>tex2html_deferred<<16544>>\bf\end<<16545>>tex2html_deferred<<16545>>0<<5439>>$\end<<9369>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9369>>, i.e., it has to be on
\begin<<9370>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9370>>$m$\end<<9371>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9371>>\space hyper planes in the N-D space.
\begin<<16546>>tex2html_deferred<<16546>>\par\end<<16547>>tex2html_deferred<<16547>>
The Lagrangian function of the QP problem is:
\begin<<5440>>equation<<5440>>
  L(<<5441>>\begin<<16548>>tex2html_deferred<<16548>>\bf\end<<16549>>tex2html_deferred<<16549>>x<<5441>>,<<5442>>\begin<<16550>>tex2html_deferred<<16550>>\bf\end<<16551>>tex2html_deferred<<16551>>\lambda<<5442>>)=f(<<5443>>\begin<<16552>>tex2html_deferred<<16552>>\bf\end<<16553>>tex2html_deferred<<16553>>x<<5443>>)+<<5444>>\begin<<16554>>tex2html_deferred<<16554>>\bf\end<<16555>>tex2html_deferred<<16555>>\lambda<<5444>>^T(<<5445>>\begin<<16556>>tex2html_deferred<<16556>>\bf\end<<16557>>tex2html_deferred<<16557>>Ax<<5445>>-<<5446>>\begin<<16558>>tex2html_deferred<<16558>>\bf\end<<16559>>tex2html_deferred<<16559>>b<<5446>>)
  =\frac<<5447>>1<<5447>><<5448>>2<<5448>><<5449>>\begin<<16560>>tex2html_deferred<<16560>>\bf\end<<16561>>tex2html_deferred<<16561>>x<<5449>>^T<<5450>>\begin<<16562>>tex2html_deferred<<16562>>\bf\end<<16563>>tex2html_deferred<<16563>>Q<<5450>><<5451>>\begin<<16564>>tex2html_deferred<<16564>>\bf\end<<16565>>tex2html_deferred<<16565>>x<<5451>>+<<5452>>\begin<<16566>>tex2html_deferred<<16566>>\bf\end<<16567>>tex2html_deferred<<16567>>c<<5452>>^T<<5453>>\begin<<16568>>tex2html_deferred<<16568>>\bf\end<<16569>>tex2html_deferred<<16569>>x<<5453>>
  +<<5454>>\begin<<16570>>tex2html_deferred<<16570>>\bf\end<<16571>>tex2html_deferred<<16571>>\lambda<<5454>>^T(<<5455>>\begin<<16572>>tex2html_deferred<<16572>>\bf\end<<16573>>tex2html_deferred<<16573>>Ax<<5455>>-<<5456>>\begin<<16574>>tex2html_deferred<<16574>>\bf\end<<16575>>tex2html_deferred<<16575>>b<<5456>>)
\end<<5457>>equation<<5457>>
and then set its derivatives with respect to both \begin<<9372>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9372>>$<<5458>>\begin<<16576>>tex2html_deferred<<16576>>\bf\end<<16577>>tex2html_deferred<<16577>>x<<5458>>$\end<<9373>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9373>>\space and
\begin<<9374>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9374>>$<<5459>>\begin<<16578>>tex2html_deferred<<16578>>\bf\end<<16579>>tex2html_deferred<<16579>>\lambda<<5459>>$\end<<9375>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9375>>\space to zero:
\begin<<5460>>eqnarray<<5460>>
  \bigtriangledown_<<5461>>\begin<<16580>>tex2html_deferred<<16580>>\bf\end<<16581>>tex2html_deferred<<16581>>x<<5461>>L(<<5462>>\begin<<16582>>tex2html_deferred<<16582>>\bf\end<<16583>>tex2html_deferred<<16583>>x<<5462>>,<<5463>>\begin<<16584>>tex2html_deferred<<16584>>\bf\end<<16585>>tex2html_deferred<<16585>>\lambda<<5463>>)
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;\bigtriangledown_<<5464>>\begin<<16586>>tex2html_deferred<<16586>>\bf\end<<16587>>tex2html_deferred<<16587>>x<<5464>>f(<<5465>>\begin<<16588>>tex2html_deferred<<16588>>\bf\end<<16589>>tex2html_deferred<<16589>>x<<5465>>)
  +\bigtriangledown_<<5466>>\begin<<16590>>tex2html_deferred<<16590>>\bf\end<<16591>>tex2html_deferred<<16591>>x<<5466>><<5467>>\begin<<16592>>tex2html_deferred<<16592>>\bf\end<<16593>>tex2html_deferred<<16593>>\lambda<<5467>>^T(<<5468>>\begin<<16594>>tex2html_deferred<<16594>>\bf\end<<16595>>tex2html_deferred<<16595>>A<<5468>><<5469>>\begin<<16596>>tex2html_deferred<<16596>>\bf\end<<16597>>tex2html_deferred<<16597>>x<<5469>>-<<5470>>\begin<<16598>>tex2html_deferred<<16598>>\bf\end<<16599>>tex2html_deferred<<16599>>b<<5470>>)
  =<<5471>>\begin<<16600>>tex2html_deferred<<16600>>\bf\end<<16601>>tex2html_deferred<<16601>>Qx<<5471>>+<<5472>>\begin<<16602>>tex2html_deferred<<16602>>\bf\end<<16603>>tex2html_deferred<<16603>>c<<5472>>+<<5473>>\begin<<16604>>tex2html_deferred<<16604>>\bf\end<<16605>>tex2html_deferred<<16605>>A<<5473>>^T<<5474>>\begin<<16606>>tex2html_deferred<<16606>>\bf\end<<16607>>tex2html_deferred<<16607>>\lambda<<5474>>=<<5475>>\begin<<16608>>tex2html_deferred<<16608>>\bf\end<<16609>>tex2html_deferred<<16609>>0<<5475>>
  \nonumber\\ 
  \bigtriangledown_<<5476>>\begin<<16610>>tex2html_deferred<<16610>>\bf\end<<16611>>tex2html_deferred<<16611>>\lambda<<5476>>L(<<5477>>\begin<<16612>>tex2html_deferred<<16612>>\bf\end<<16613>>tex2html_deferred<<16613>>x<<5477>>,<<5478>>\begin<<16614>>tex2html_deferred<<16614>>\bf\end<<16615>>tex2html_deferred<<16615>>\lambda<<5478>>)
  ;SPMamp;=;SPMamp;<<5479>>\begin<<16616>>tex2html_deferred<<16616>>\bf\end<<16617>>tex2html_deferred<<16617>>Ax<<5479>>-<<5480>>\begin<<16618>>tex2html_deferred<<16618>>\bf\end<<16619>>tex2html_deferred<<16619>>b<<5480>>=<<5481>>\begin<<16620>>tex2html_deferred<<16620>>\bf\end<<16621>>tex2html_deferred<<16621>>0<<5481>>
\end<<5482>>eqnarray<<5482>>
These two equations can be combined and expressed in matrix form as:
\begin<<5483>>equation<<5483>>
  \left[\begin<<5484>>array<<5484>><<5485>>cc<<5485>><<5486>>\begin<<16622>>tex2html_deferred<<16622>>\bf\end<<16623>>tex2html_deferred<<16623>>Q<<5486>>;SPMamp;<<5487>>\begin<<16624>>tex2html_deferred<<16624>>\bf\end<<16625>>tex2html_deferred<<16625>>A<<5487>>^T\\ <<5488>>\begin<<16626>>tex2html_deferred<<16626>>\bf\end<<16627>>tex2html_deferred<<16627>>A<<5488>>;SPMamp;<<5489>>\begin<<16628>>tex2html_deferred<<16628>>\bf\end<<16629>>tex2html_deferred<<16629>>0<<5489>>\end<<5490>>array<<5490>>\right]
  \left[\begin<<5491>>array<<5491>><<5492>>c<<5492>><<5493>>\begin<<16630>>tex2html_deferred<<16630>>\bf\end<<16631>>tex2html_deferred<<16631>>x<<5493>>\\ <<5494>>\begin<<16632>>tex2html_deferred<<16632>>\bf\end<<16633>>tex2html_deferred<<16633>>\lambda<<5494>>\end<<5495>>array<<5495>>\right]
  =\left[\begin<<5496>>array<<5496>><<5497>>c<<5497>>-<<5498>>\begin<<16634>>tex2html_deferred<<16634>>\bf\end<<16635>>tex2html_deferred<<16635>>c<<5498>>\\ <<5499>>\begin<<16636>>tex2html_deferred<<16636>>\bf\end<<16637>>tex2html_deferred<<16637>>b<<5499>>\end<<5500>>array<<5500>>\right]
\end<<5501>>equation<<5501>>
Solving this system of \begin<<9376>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9376>>$m+N$\end<<9377>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9377>>\space equations, we get both \begin<<9378>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9378>>$<<5502>>\begin<<16638>>tex2html_deferred<<16638>>\bf\end<<16639>>tex2html_deferred<<16639>>x<<5502>>^*$\end<<9379>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9379>>\space and
\begin<<9380>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9380>>$<<5503>>\begin<<16640>>tex2html_deferred<<16640>>\bf\end<<16641>>tex2html_deferred<<16641>>\lambda<<5503>>^*$\end<<9381>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9381>>.
\begin<<16642>>tex2html_deferred<<16642>>\par\end<<16643>>tex2html_deferred<<16643>>
<<5504>>\begin<<16644>>tex2html_deferred<<16644>>\bf\end<<16645>>tex2html_deferred<<16645>>Example<<5504>> 
\begin<<5505>>equation<<5505>>
  \mbox<<5506>>Minimize:<<5506>>\;\;\;\;\;\;f(x_1,x_2)=x^2_1+x^2_2
  =\frac<<5507>>1<<5507>><<5508>>2<<5508>>[x_1,\;x_2]\left[\begin<<5509>>array<<5509>><<5510>>cc<<5510>>2;SPMamp;0\\ 0;SPMamp;2\end<<5511>>array<<5511>>\right]
  \left[\begin<<5512>>array<<5512>><<5513>>c<<5513>>x_1\\ x_2\end<<5514>>array<<5514>>\right]
  =\frac<<5515>>1<<5515>><<5516>>2<<5516>><<5517>>\begin<<16646>>tex2html_deferred<<16646>>\bf\end<<16647>>tex2html_deferred<<16647>>x<<5517>>^T<<5518>>\begin<<16648>>tex2html_deferred<<16648>>\bf\end<<16649>>tex2html_deferred<<16649>>Q<<5518>><<5519>>\begin<<16650>>tex2html_deferred<<16650>>\bf\end<<16651>>tex2html_deferred<<16651>>x<<5519>>
  \nonumber
\end<<5520>>equation<<5520>>
\begin<<16652>>tex2html_deferred<<16652>>\par\end<<16653>>tex2html_deferred<<16653>>
\begin<<5521>>equation<<5521>>
  \mbox<<5522>>subject to:<<5522>>\;\;\;\;\;\;
       <<5523>>\begin<<16654>>tex2html_deferred<<16654>>\bf\end<<16655>>tex2html_deferred<<16655>>Ax<<5523>>=[1,\;1]\left[\begin<<5524>>array<<5524>><<5525>>c<<5525>>x_1\\ x_2\end<<5526>>array<<5526>>\right]
       =x_1+x_2=<<5527>>\begin<<16656>>tex2html_deferred<<16656>>\bf\end<<16657>>tex2html_deferred<<16657>>b<<5527>>=1
  \nonumber
\end<<5528>>equation<<5528>>
where
\begin<<5529>>equation<<5529>>
  <<5530>>\begin<<16658>>tex2html_deferred<<16658>>\bf\end<<16659>>tex2html_deferred<<16659>>Q<<5530>>=\left[\begin<<5531>>array<<5531>><<5532>>cc<<5532>>2;SPMamp;0\\ 0;SPMamp;2\end<<5533>>array<<5533>>\right],\;\;\;
  <<5534>>\begin<<16660>>tex2html_deferred<<16660>>\bf\end<<16661>>tex2html_deferred<<16661>>A<<5534>>=[1,\;1],\;\;\;\;\;
  <<5535>>\begin<<16662>>tex2html_deferred<<16662>>\bf\end<<16663>>tex2html_deferred<<16663>>c<<5535>>=\left[\begin<<5536>>array<<5536>><<5537>>c<<5537>>0\\ 0\end<<5538>>array<<5538>>\right],\;\;\;\;\;
  <<5539>>\begin<<16664>>tex2html_deferred<<16664>>\bf\end<<16665>>tex2html_deferred<<16665>>b<<5539>>=1;
  \nonumber
\end<<5540>>equation<<5540>>
\begin<<16666>>tex2html_deferred<<16666>>\par\end<<16667>>tex2html_deferred<<16667>>
\begin<<5541>>equation<<5541>>
  \left[\begin<<5542>>array<<5542>><<5543>>rrr<<5543>>2;SPMamp;0;SPMamp;1\\ 0;SPMamp;2;SPMamp;1\\ 1;SPMamp;1;SPMamp;0\end<<5544>>array<<5544>>\right]
  \left[\begin<<5545>>array<<5545>><<5546>>r<<5546>>x_1\\ x_2\\ \lambda\end<<5547>>array<<5547>>\right]
  =\left[\begin<<5548>>array<<5548>><<5549>>r<<5549>>0\\ 0\\ 1\end<<5550>>array<<5550>>\right]
  \nonumber
\end<<5551>>equation<<5551>>
Solving this equation we get the solution \begin<<9382>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9382>>$x^*_1=x^*_2=0.5$\end<<9383>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9383>>\space and
\begin<<9384>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9384>>$\lambda^*=-1$\end<<9385>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9385>>, at which the function \begin<<9386>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9386>>$f(x^*_1,x^*_2)=0.5$\end<<9387>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9387>>\space is 
minimized subject to \begin<<9388>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9388>>$x_1+x_2=1$\end<<9389>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9389>>.
\begin<<16668>>tex2html_deferred<<16668>>\par\end<<16669>>tex2html_deferred<<16669>>
If \begin<<9390>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9390>>$m=N$\end<<9391>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9391>>, i.e., the number of equality constraints is the same
as the number of variables, then the variable \begin<<9392>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9392>>$<<5552>>\begin<<16670>>tex2html_deferred<<16670>>\bf\end<<16671>>tex2html_deferred<<16671>>x<<5552>>$\end<<9393>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9393>>\space is uniquely
determined by the linear system \begin<<9394>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9394>>$<<5553>>\begin<<16672>>tex2html_deferred<<16672>>\bf\end<<16673>>tex2html_deferred<<16673>>Ax<<5553>>=<<5554>>\begin<<16674>>tex2html_deferred<<16674>>\bf\end<<16675>>tex2html_deferred<<16675>>b<<5554>>$\end<<9395>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9395>>, as the intersect
of \begin<<9396>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9396>>$m=N$\end<<9397>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9397>>\space hyper planes, independent of the objective function 
\begin<<9398>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9398>>$f(<<5555>>\begin<<16676>>tex2html_deferred<<16676>>\bf\end<<16677>>tex2html_deferred<<16677>>x<<5555>>)$\end<<9399>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9399>>. Further if \begin<<9400>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9400>>$m;SPMgt;N$\end<<9401>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9401>>, i.e., the system \begin<<9402>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9402>>$<<5556>>\begin<<16678>>tex2html_deferred<<16678>>\bf\end<<16679>>tex2html_deferred<<16679>>Ax<<5556>>=<<5557>>\begin<<16680>>tex2html_deferred<<16680>>\bf\end<<16681>>tex2html_deferred<<16681>>b<<5557>>$\end<<9403>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9403>> 
is over constrained, and its solution does not exist in general.
It is therefore more interesting to consider QP problems subject to
both equality and inequality constraints:
\begin<<5558>>equation<<5558>>
  \begin<<5559>>array<<5559>><<5560>>ll<<5560>>
    \mbox<<5561>>minimize<<5561>>    ;SPMamp; 
    f(<<5562>>\begin<<16682>>tex2html_deferred<<16682>>\bf\end<<16683>>tex2html_deferred<<16683>>x<<5562>>)=\frac<<5563>>1<<5563>><<5564>>2<<5564>><<5565>>\begin<<16684>>tex2html_deferred<<16684>>\bf\end<<16685>>tex2html_deferred<<16685>>x<<5565>>^T<<5566>>\begin<<16686>>tex2html_deferred<<16686>>\bf\end<<16687>>tex2html_deferred<<16687>>Q<<5566>><<5567>>\begin<<16688>>tex2html_deferred<<16688>>\bf\end<<16689>>tex2html_deferred<<16689>>x<<5567>>+<<5568>>\begin<<16690>>tex2html_deferred<<16690>>\bf\end<<16691>>tex2html_deferred<<16691>>c<<5568>>^T<<5569>>\begin<<16692>>tex2html_deferred<<16692>>\bf\end<<16693>>tex2html_deferred<<16693>>x<<5569>>\\ 
    \;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\\ 
    \mbox<<5570>>subject to:<<5570>> ;SPMamp; <<5571>>\begin<<16694>>tex2html_deferred<<16694>>\bf\end<<16695>>tex2html_deferred<<16695>>Ax<<5571>>\le<<5572>>\begin<<16696>>tex2html_deferred<<16696>>\bf\end<<16697>>tex2html_deferred<<16697>>b<<5572>>
  \end<<5573>>array<<5573>>
  \nonumber
\end<<5574>>equation<<5574>>
\begin<<16698>>tex2html_deferred<<16698>>\par\end<<16699>>tex2html_deferred<<16699>>
\subsection*<<5575>>Interior Point Methods<<5575>>
\begin<<16700>>tex2html_deferred<<16700>>\par\end<<16701>>tex2html_deferred<<16701>>
Consider the a general constrained optimization problem:
\begin<<5576>>equation<<5576>>
  \begin<<5577>>array<<5577>><<5578>>ll<<5578>>
    \mbox<<5579>>minimize<<5579>> ;SPMamp; f(<<5580>>\begin<<16702>>tex2html_deferred<<16702>>\bf\end<<16703>>tex2html_deferred<<16703>>x<<5580>>) \\ 
    \mbox<<5581>>subject to:<<5581>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{ \begin<<5582>>array<<5582>><<5583>>l<<5583>>
         <<5584>>\begin<<16704>>tex2html_deferred<<16704>>\bf\end<<16705>>tex2html_deferred<<16705>>h<<5584>>(<<5585>>\begin<<16706>>tex2html_deferred<<16706>>\bf\end<<16707>>tex2html_deferred<<16707>>x<<5585>>)=<<5586>>\begin<<16708>>tex2html_deferred<<16708>>\bf\end<<16709>>tex2html_deferred<<16709>>0<<5586>>\\ 
         <<5587>>\begin<<16710>>tex2html_deferred<<16710>>\bf\end<<16711>>tex2html_deferred<<16711>>g<<5587>>(<<5588>>\begin<<16712>>tex2html_deferred<<16712>>\bf\end<<16713>>tex2html_deferred<<16713>>x<<5588>>)\le<<5589>>\begin<<16714>>tex2html_deferred<<16714>>\bf\end<<16715>>tex2html_deferred<<16715>>0<<5589>>\;\;\;\mbox<<5590>>or<<5590>>\;\;\;
         <<5591>>\begin<<16716>>tex2html_deferred<<16716>>\bf\end<<16717>>tex2html_deferred<<16717>>g<<5591>>(<<5592>>\begin<<16718>>tex2html_deferred<<16718>>\bf\end<<16719>>tex2html_deferred<<16719>>x<<5592>>)\ge<<5593>>\begin<<16720>>tex2html_deferred<<16720>>\bf\end<<16721>>tex2html_deferred<<16721>>0<<5593>>\\ 
         <<5594>>\begin<<16722>>tex2html_deferred<<16722>>\bf\end<<16723>>tex2html_deferred<<16723>>x<<5594>>\ge<<5595>>\begin<<16724>>tex2html_deferred<<16724>>\bf\end<<16725>>tex2html_deferred<<16725>>0<<5595>> 
    \end<<5596>>array<<5596>>\right.\end<<5597>>array<<5597>>
\end<<5598>>equation<<5598>>
By introducing slack variables \begin<<9404>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9404>>$<<5599>>\begin<<16726>>tex2html_deferred<<16726>>\bf\end<<16727>>tex2html_deferred<<16727>>s<<5599>>\ge<<5600>>\begin<<16728>>tex2html_deferred<<16728>>\bf\end<<16729>>tex2html_deferred<<16729>>0<<5600>>$\end<<9405>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9405>>, all inequality
constraints can be converted into equality constraints:
\begin<<5601>>equation<<5601>>
    <<5602>>\begin<<16730>>tex2html_deferred<<16730>>\bf\end<<16731>>tex2html_deferred<<16731>>g<<5602>>(<<5603>>\begin<<16732>>tex2html_deferred<<16732>>\bf\end<<16733>>tex2html_deferred<<16733>>x<<5603>>)\le<<5604>>\begin<<16734>>tex2html_deferred<<16734>>\bf\end<<16735>>tex2html_deferred<<16735>>0<<5604>>\;\Longrightarrow \;
    <<5605>>\begin<<16736>>tex2html_deferred<<16736>>\bf\end<<16737>>tex2html_deferred<<16737>>g<<5605>>(<<5606>>\begin<<16738>>tex2html_deferred<<16738>>\bf\end<<16739>>tex2html_deferred<<16739>>x<<5606>>)+<<5607>>\begin<<16740>>tex2html_deferred<<16740>>\bf\end<<16741>>tex2html_deferred<<16741>>s<<5607>>=<<5608>>\begin<<16742>>tex2html_deferred<<16742>>\bf\end<<16743>>tex2html_deferred<<16743>>0<<5608>>,\;\;\;\;\;\;\;
    <<5609>>\begin<<16744>>tex2html_deferred<<16744>>\bf\end<<16745>>tex2html_deferred<<16745>>g<<5609>>(<<5610>>\begin<<16746>>tex2html_deferred<<16746>>\bf\end<<16747>>tex2html_deferred<<16747>>x<<5610>>)\ge<<5611>>\begin<<16748>>tex2html_deferred<<16748>>\bf\end<<16749>>tex2html_deferred<<16749>>0<<5611>>\;\Longrightarrow \;
    <<5612>>\begin<<16750>>tex2html_deferred<<16750>>\bf\end<<16751>>tex2html_deferred<<16751>>g<<5612>>(<<5613>>\begin<<16752>>tex2html_deferred<<16752>>\bf\end<<16753>>tex2html_deferred<<16753>>x<<5613>>)-<<5614>>\begin<<16754>>tex2html_deferred<<16754>>\bf\end<<16755>>tex2html_deferred<<16755>>s<<5614>>=<<5615>>\begin<<16756>>tex2html_deferred<<16756>>\bf\end<<16757>>tex2html_deferred<<16757>>0<<5615>> 
\end<<5616>>equation<<5616>>
which can then be combined with the equality constraints and still 
denoted by \begin<<9406>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9406>>$<<5617>>\begin<<16758>>tex2html_deferred<<16758>>\bf\end<<16759>>tex2html_deferred<<16759>>h<<5617>>(<<5618>>\begin<<16760>>tex2html_deferred<<16760>>\bf\end<<16761>>tex2html_deferred<<16761>>x<<5618>>)=<<5619>>\begin<<16762>>tex2html_deferred<<16762>>\bf\end<<16763>>tex2html_deferred<<16763>>0<<5619>>$\end<<9407>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9407>>, while the slack variables 
\begin<<9408>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9408>>$<<5620>>\begin<<16764>>tex2html_deferred<<16764>>\bf\end<<16765>>tex2html_deferred<<16765>>s<<5620>>$\end<<9409>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9409>>\space are also combined with the original variables and still 
denoted by \begin<<9410>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9410>>$<<5621>>\begin<<16766>>tex2html_deferred<<16766>>\bf\end<<16767>>tex2html_deferred<<16767>>x<<5621>>$\end<<9411>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9411>>. We assume there are in total \begin<<9412>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9412>>$M$\end<<9413>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9413>>\space equality 
constraints and \begin<<9414>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9414>>$N$\end<<9415>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9415>>\space variables. Now the optimization problem can be
reformulated as:
\begin<<5622>>equation<<5622>>
  \begin<<5623>>array<<5623>><<5624>>ll<<5624>>
    \mbox<<5625>>minimize<<5625>> ;SPMamp; f(<<5626>>\begin<<16768>>tex2html_deferred<<16768>>\bf\end<<16769>>tex2html_deferred<<16769>>x<<5626>>) \\ 
    \mbox<<5627>>subject to:<<5627>> ;SPMamp; 
    \left\{\begin<<5628>>array<<5628>><<5629>>l<<5629>>
         <<5630>>\begin<<16770>>tex2html_deferred<<16770>>\bf\end<<16771>>tex2html_deferred<<16771>>h<<5630>>(<<5631>>\begin<<16772>>tex2html_deferred<<16772>>\bf\end<<16773>>tex2html_deferred<<16773>>x<<5631>>)=<<5632>>\begin<<16774>>tex2html_deferred<<16774>>\bf\end<<16775>>tex2html_deferred<<16775>>0<<5632>>\\ 
         <<5633>>\begin<<16776>>tex2html_deferred<<16776>>\bf\end<<16777>>tex2html_deferred<<16777>>x<<5633>>\ge<<5634>>\begin<<16778>>tex2html_deferred<<16778>>\bf\end<<16779>>tex2html_deferred<<16779>>0<<5634>>
    \end<<5635>>array<<5635>>\right.\end<<5636>>array<<5636>>
\end<<5637>>equation<<5637>>
The Lagrangian is
\begin<<5638>>equation<<5638>>
  L(<<5639>>\begin<<16780>>tex2html_deferred<<16780>>\bf\end<<16781>>tex2html_deferred<<16781>>x<<5639>>,<<5640>>\begin<<16782>>tex2html_deferred<<16782>>\bf\end<<16783>>tex2html_deferred<<16783>>\lambda<<5640>>,<<5641>>\begin<<16784>>tex2html_deferred<<16784>>\bf\end<<16785>>tex2html_deferred<<16785>>\mu<<5641>>)=f(<<5642>>\begin<<16786>>tex2html_deferred<<16786>>\bf\end<<16787>>tex2html_deferred<<16787>>x<<5642>>)
  +<<5643>>\begin<<16788>>tex2html_deferred<<16788>>\bf\end<<16789>>tex2html_deferred<<16789>>\lambda<<5643>>^T<<5644>>\begin<<16790>>tex2html_deferred<<16790>>\bf\end<<16791>>tex2html_deferred<<16791>>h<<5644>>(<<5645>>\begin<<16792>>tex2html_deferred<<16792>>\bf\end<<16793>>tex2html_deferred<<16793>>x<<5645>>)-<<5646>>\begin<<16794>>tex2html_deferred<<16794>>\bf\end<<16795>>tex2html_deferred<<16795>>\mu<<5646>>^T<<5647>>\begin<<16796>>tex2html_deferred<<16796>>\bf\end<<16797>>tex2html_deferred<<16797>>x<<5647>>
\end<<5648>>equation<<5648>>
The KKT conditions are
\begin<<5649>>equation<<5649>>
\left\{
\begin<<5650>>array<<5650>><<5651>>ll<<5651>>
  \bigtriangledown_<<5652>>\begin<<16798>>tex2html_deferred<<16798>>\bf\end<<16799>>tex2html_deferred<<16799>>x<<5652>> L(<<5653>>\begin<<16800>>tex2html_deferred<<16800>>\bf\end<<16801>>tex2html_deferred<<16801>>x<<5653>>,<<5654>>\begin<<16802>>tex2html_deferred<<16802>>\bf\end<<16803>>tex2html_deferred<<16803>>\lambda<<5654>>,<<5655>>\begin<<16804>>tex2html_deferred<<16804>>\bf\end<<16805>>tex2html_deferred<<16805>>\mu<<5655>>)
  =<<5656>>\begin<<16806>>tex2html_deferred<<16806>>\bf\end<<16807>>tex2html_deferred<<16807>>g<<5656>>_f(<<5657>>\begin<<16808>>tex2html_deferred<<16808>>\bf\end<<16809>>tex2html_deferred<<16809>>x<<5657>>)+<<5658>>\begin<<16810>>tex2html_deferred<<16810>>\bf\end<<16811>>tex2html_deferred<<16811>>J<<5658>>_<<5659>>\begin<<16812>>tex2html_deferred<<16812>>\bf\end<<16813>>tex2html_deferred<<16813>>h<<5659>>^T(<<5660>>\begin<<16814>>tex2html_deferred<<16814>>\bf\end<<16815>>tex2html_deferred<<16815>>x<<5660>>)<<5661>>\begin<<16816>>tex2html_deferred<<16816>>\bf\end<<16817>>tex2html_deferred<<16817>>\lambda<<5661>>-<<5662>>\begin<<16818>>tex2html_deferred<<16818>>\bf\end<<16819>>tex2html_deferred<<16819>>\mu<<5662>>
  =<<5663>>\begin<<16820>>tex2html_deferred<<16820>>\bf\end<<16821>>tex2html_deferred<<16821>>0<<5663>>;SPMamp;
  \mbox<<5664>>(stationarity)<<5664>>\\ 
  <<5665>>\begin<<16822>>tex2html_deferred<<16822>>\bf\end<<16823>>tex2html_deferred<<16823>>h<<5665>>(<<5666>>\begin<<16824>>tex2html_deferred<<16824>>\bf\end<<16825>>tex2html_deferred<<16825>>x<<5666>>)=<<5667>>\begin<<16826>>tex2html_deferred<<16826>>\bf\end<<16827>>tex2html_deferred<<16827>>0<<5667>>,\;\;\;\;<<5668>>\begin<<16828>>tex2html_deferred<<16828>>\bf\end<<16829>>tex2html_deferred<<16829>>x<<5668>>\ge<<5669>>\begin<<16830>>tex2html_deferred<<16830>>\bf\end<<16831>>tex2html_deferred<<16831>>0<<5669>> ;SPMamp; 
  \mbox<<5670>>(primal feasibility)<<5670>>\\ 
  <<5671>>\begin<<16832>>tex2html_deferred<<16832>>\bf\end<<16833>>tex2html_deferred<<16833>>\mu<<5671>>\ge <<5672>>\begin<<16834>>tex2html_deferred<<16834>>\bf\end<<16835>>tex2html_deferred<<16835>>0<<5672>> ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5673>>(dual feasibility)<<5673>>\\ 
  \mu_j x_j=0,\;\;\;\;(j=1,\cdots,N)\;\;\;\;\mbox<<5674>>or<<5674>>\;\;\;
  <<5675>>\begin<<16836>>tex2html_deferred<<16836>>\bf\end<<16837>>tex2html_deferred<<16837>>XM1<<5675>>=<<5676>>\begin<<16838>>tex2html_deferred<<16838>>\bf\end<<16839>>tex2html_deferred<<16839>>0<<5676>> ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5677>>(complementarity)<<5677>>
  \end<<5678>>array<<5678>>\right.
\end<<5679>>equation<<5679>>
where \begin<<9416>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9416>>$<<5680>>\begin<<16840>>tex2html_deferred<<16840>>\bf\end<<16841>>tex2html_deferred<<16841>>X<<5680>>=diag(x_1,\cdots,x_N)$\end<<9417>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9417>>, \begin<<9418>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9418>>$<<5681>>\begin<<16842>>tex2html_deferred<<16842>>\bf\end<<16843>>tex2html_deferred<<16843>>M<<5681>>=diag(\mu_1,\cdots,\mu_N)$\end<<9419>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9419>>,
and \begin<<9420>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9420>>$<<5682>>\begin<<16844>>tex2html_deferred<<16844>>\bf\end<<16845>>tex2html_deferred<<16845>>J<<5682>>_<<5683>>\begin<<16846>>tex2html_deferred<<16846>>\bf\end<<16847>>tex2html_deferred<<16847>>f<<5683>>(<<5684>>\begin<<16848>>tex2html_deferred<<16848>>\bf\end<<16849>>tex2html_deferred<<16849>>x<<5684>>)$\end<<9421>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9421>>\space is the Jacobian matrix of \begin<<9422>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9422>>$<<5685>>\begin<<16850>>tex2html_deferred<<16850>>\bf\end<<16851>>tex2html_deferred<<16851>>h<<5685>>(<<5686>>\begin<<16852>>tex2html_deferred<<16852>>\bf\end<<16853>>tex2html_deferred<<16853>>x<<5686>>)$\end<<9423>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9423>>:
\begin<<5687>>equation<<5687>>
<<5688>>\begin<<16854>>tex2html_deferred<<16854>>\bf\end<<16855>>tex2html_deferred<<16855>>X<<5688>>=\left[\begin<<5689>>array<<5689>><<5690>>ccc<<5690>>x_1;SPMamp;\cdots;SPMamp;0\\ 
    \vdots;SPMamp;\ddots;SPMamp;\vdots\\ 0;SPMamp;\cdots;SPMamp;x_n \end<<5691>>array<<5691>>\right]_<<5692>>N\times N<<5692>>,
  \;\;\;\;\;
<<5693>>\begin<<16856>>tex2html_deferred<<16856>>\bf\end<<16857>>tex2html_deferred<<16857>>M<<5693>>=\left[\begin<<5694>>array<<5694>><<5695>>ccc<<5695>>\mu_1;SPMamp;\cdots;SPMamp;0\\ 
    \vdots;SPMamp;\ddots;SPMamp;\vdots\\ 0;SPMamp;\cdots;SPMamp;\mu_N
    \end<<5696>>array<<5696>>\right]_<<5697>>N\times N<<5697>>,
  \;\;\;\;\;
<<5698>>\begin<<16858>>tex2html_deferred<<16858>>\bf\end<<16859>>tex2html_deferred<<16859>>J<<5698>>_<<5699>>\begin<<16860>>tex2html_deferred<<16860>>\bf\end<<16861>>tex2html_deferred<<16861>>h<<5699>>(<<5700>>\begin<<16862>>tex2html_deferred<<16862>>\bf\end<<16863>>tex2html_deferred<<16863>>x<<5700>>)=\left[\begin<<5701>>array<<5701>><<5702>>ccc<<5702>>
      \frac<<5703>>\partial h_1<<5703>><<5704>>\partial x_1<<5704>>;SPMamp;\cdots;SPMamp;
      \frac<<5705>>\partial h_1<<5705>><<5706>>\partial x_n<<5706>>\\ 
      \vdots ;SPMamp; \ddots ;SPMamp; \vdots\\ 
      \frac<<5707>>\partial h_m<<5707>><<5708>>\partial x_1<<5708>>;SPMamp;\cdots;SPMamp;
      \frac<<5709>>\partial h_m<<5709>><<5710>>\partial x_n<<5710>>\end<<5711>>array<<5711>>\right]_<<5712>>M\times N<<5712>>
\end<<5713>>equation<<5713>>
To simplify the problem, the non-negativity constraints can be removed 
by introducing an indicator function:
\begin<<5714>>equation<<5714>>
  I(x)=\left\{\begin<<5715>>array<<5715>><<5716>>ll<<5716>>0 ;SPMamp; x\ge 0\\ \infty;SPMamp; x;SPMlt;0\end<<5717>>array<<5717>>
\right.
\end<<5718>>equation<<5718>>
which, when used as a cost function, penalizes any violation of the 
non-negativity constraint \begin<<9424>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9424>>$x\ge 0$\end<<9425>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9425>>. Now the optimization problem can
be reformulated as shown below without the non-negative constants 
\begin<<9426>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9426>>$<<5719>>\begin<<16864>>tex2html_deferred<<16864>>\bf\end<<16865>>tex2html_deferred<<16865>>x<<5719>>\ge<<5720>>\begin<<16866>>tex2html_deferred<<16866>>\bf\end<<16867>>tex2html_deferred<<16867>>0<<5720>>$\end<<9427>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9427>>:
\begin<<5721>>equation<<5721>>
  \begin<<5722>>array<<5722>><<5723>>ll<<5723>>
  \mbox<<5724>>minimize<<5724>> ;SPMamp; f(<<5725>>\begin<<16868>>tex2html_deferred<<16868>>\bf\end<<16869>>tex2html_deferred<<16869>>x<<5725>>)+\sum_<<5726>>i=1<<5726>>^N I(x_i)\\ 
  \mbox<<5727>>subject to<<5727>> ;SPMamp; <<5728>>\begin<<16870>>tex2html_deferred<<16870>>\bf\end<<16871>>tex2html_deferred<<16871>>h<<5728>>(<<5729>>\begin<<16872>>tex2html_deferred<<16872>>\bf\end<<16873>>tex2html_deferred<<16873>>x<<5729>>)=<<5730>>\begin<<16874>>tex2html_deferred<<16874>>\bf\end<<16875>>tex2html_deferred<<16875>>0<<5730>>
  \end<<5731>>array<<5731>>
\end<<5732>>equation<<5732>>
However, as the indicator function is not smooth and therefore not
differentiable, it is approximated by the <<5733>>\begin<<16876>>tex2html_deferred<<16876>>\em\end<<16877>>tex2html_deferred<<16877>>logarithmic barrier function<<5733>> 
which approaches \begin<<9428>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9428>>$I(x)$\end<<9429>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9429>>\space when the parameter \begin<<9430>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9430>>$t;SPMgt;0$\end<<9431>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9431>>\space approaches infinity:
\begin<<5734>>equation<<5734>>
  -\frac<<5735>>1<<5735>><<5736>>t<<5736>>\ln(x)\;\;\stackrel<<5737>>t\rightarrow\infty<<5737>><<5738>>\Longrightarrow<<5738>>\;\;I(x)
\end<<5739>>equation<<5739>>
\begin<<16878>>tex2html_deferred<<16878>>\par\end<<16879>>tex2html_deferred<<16879>>
\htmladdimg<<5740>>figures/LogBarrier.png<<5740>>
\begin<<16880>>tex2html_deferred<<16880>>\par\end<<16881>>tex2html_deferred<<16881>>
Now the optimization problem can be written as:
\begin<<5741>>equation<<5741>>
  \begin<<5742>>array<<5742>><<5743>>ll<<5743>>
  \mbox<<5744>>minimize<<5744>> ;SPMamp; f(<<5745>>\begin<<16882>>tex2html_deferred<<16882>>\bf\end<<16883>>tex2html_deferred<<16883>>x<<5745>>)-\frac<<5746>>1<<5746>><<5747>>t<<5747>>\sum_<<5748>>i=1<<5748>>^N\ln x_i\\ 
  \mbox<<5749>>subject to<<5749>> ;SPMamp; <<5750>>\begin<<16884>>tex2html_deferred<<16884>>\bf\end<<16885>>tex2html_deferred<<16885>>h<<5750>>(<<5751>>\begin<<16886>>tex2html_deferred<<16886>>\bf\end<<16887>>tex2html_deferred<<16887>>x<<5751>>)=<<5752>>\begin<<16888>>tex2html_deferred<<16888>>\bf\end<<16889>>tex2html_deferred<<16889>>0<<5752>>
  \end<<5753>>array<<5753>>
\end<<5754>>equation<<5754>>
The Lagrangian is:
\begin<<5755>>equation<<5755>>
  L(<<5756>>\begin<<16890>>tex2html_deferred<<16890>>\bf\end<<16891>>tex2html_deferred<<16891>>x<<5756>>,<<5757>>\begin<<16892>>tex2html_deferred<<16892>>\bf\end<<16893>>tex2html_deferred<<16893>>\lambda<<5757>>,<<5758>>\begin<<16894>>tex2html_deferred<<16894>>\bf\end<<16895>>tex2html_deferred<<16895>>\mu<<5758>>)=f(<<5759>>\begin<<16896>>tex2html_deferred<<16896>>\bf\end<<16897>>tex2html_deferred<<16897>>x<<5759>>)
  +<<5760>>\begin<<16898>>tex2html_deferred<<16898>>\bf\end<<16899>>tex2html_deferred<<16899>>\lambda<<5760>>^T<<5761>>\begin<<16900>>tex2html_deferred<<16900>>\bf\end<<16901>>tex2html_deferred<<16901>>h<<5761>>(<<5762>>\begin<<16902>>tex2html_deferred<<16902>>\bf\end<<16903>>tex2html_deferred<<16903>>x<<5762>>)-\frac<<5763>>1<<5763>><<5764>>t<<5764>>\sum_<<5765>>j=1<<5765>>^N\ln x_j\\ 
\end<<5766>>equation<<5766>>
and its gradient is:
\begin<<5767>>equation<<5767>>
  \bigtriangledown_<<5768>>\begin<<16904>>tex2html_deferred<<16904>>\bf\end<<16905>>tex2html_deferred<<16905>>x<<5768>> L(<<5769>>\begin<<16906>>tex2html_deferred<<16906>>\bf\end<<16907>>tex2html_deferred<<16907>>x<<5769>>,<<5770>>\begin<<16908>>tex2html_deferred<<16908>>\bf\end<<16909>>tex2html_deferred<<16909>>\lambda<<5770>>,<<5771>>\begin<<16910>>tex2html_deferred<<16910>>\bf\end<<16911>>tex2html_deferred<<16911>>\mu<<5771>>)
  =<<5772>>\begin<<16912>>tex2html_deferred<<16912>>\bf\end<<16913>>tex2html_deferred<<16913>>g<<5772>>_f(<<5773>>\begin<<16914>>tex2html_deferred<<16914>>\bf\end<<16915>>tex2html_deferred<<16915>>x<<5773>>)+<<5774>>\begin<<16916>>tex2html_deferred<<16916>>\bf\end<<16917>>tex2html_deferred<<16917>>J<<5774>>_<<5775>>\begin<<16918>>tex2html_deferred<<16918>>\bf\end<<16919>>tex2html_deferred<<16919>>h<<5775>>^T(<<5776>>\begin<<16920>>tex2html_deferred<<16920>>\bf\end<<16921>>tex2html_deferred<<16921>>x<<5776>>)<<5777>>\begin<<16922>>tex2html_deferred<<16922>>\bf\end<<16923>>tex2html_deferred<<16923>>\lambda<<5777>>
  -\frac<<5778>>1<<5778>><<5779>>t<<5779>><<5780>>\begin<<16924>>tex2html_deferred<<16924>>\bf\end<<16925>>tex2html_deferred<<16925>>X<<5780>>^<<5781>>-1<<5781>><<5782>>\begin<<16926>>tex2html_deferred<<16926>>\bf\end<<16927>>tex2html_deferred<<16927>>1<<5782>>
\end<<5783>>equation<<5783>>
We define
\begin<<5784>>equation<<5784>>
  <<5785>>\begin<<16928>>tex2html_deferred<<16928>>\bf\end<<16929>>tex2html_deferred<<16929>>\mu<<5785>>=\frac<<5786>>\begin<<16930>>tex2html_deferred<<16930>>\bf\end<<16931>>tex2html_deferred<<16931>>x<<5786>><<5787>>t<<5787>>=\frac<<5788>>1<<5788>><<5789>>t<<5789>><<5790>>\begin<<16932>>tex2html_deferred<<16932>>\bf\end<<16933>>tex2html_deferred<<16933>>X<<5790>>^<<5791>>-1<<5791>><<5792>>\begin<<16934>>tex2html_deferred<<16934>>\bf\end<<16935>>tex2html_deferred<<16935>>1<<5792>>,
  \;\;\;\;\mbox<<5793>>i.e.<<5793>>\;\;\;
  <<5794>>\begin<<16936>>tex2html_deferred<<16936>>\bf\end<<16937>>tex2html_deferred<<16937>>X\mu<<5794>>=<<5795>>\begin<<16938>>tex2html_deferred<<16938>>\bf\end<<16939>>tex2html_deferred<<16939>>XM 1<<5795>>=\frac<<5796>>\begin<<16940>>tex2html_deferred<<16940>>\bf\end<<16941>>tex2html_deferred<<16941>>1<<5796>><<5797>>t<<5797>>
\end<<5798>>equation<<5798>>
and combine this equation with the KKT conditions of the new 
optimization problem to get
\begin<<5799>>equation<<5799>>
  \left\{
  \begin<<5800>>array<<5800>><<5801>>ll<<5801>>
    <<5802>>\begin<<16942>>tex2html_deferred<<16942>>\bf\end<<16943>>tex2html_deferred<<16943>>g<<5802>>_f(<<5803>>\begin<<16944>>tex2html_deferred<<16944>>\bf\end<<16945>>tex2html_deferred<<16945>>x<<5803>>)+<<5804>>\begin<<16946>>tex2html_deferred<<16946>>\bf\end<<16947>>tex2html_deferred<<16947>>J<<5804>>_<<5805>>\begin<<16948>>tex2html_deferred<<16948>>\bf\end<<16949>>tex2html_deferred<<16949>>h<<5805>>^T(<<5806>>\begin<<16950>>tex2html_deferred<<16950>>\bf\end<<16951>>tex2html_deferred<<16951>>x<<5806>>)<<5807>>\begin<<16952>>tex2html_deferred<<16952>>\bf\end<<16953>>tex2html_deferred<<16953>>\lambda<<5807>>-\mu=<<5808>>\begin<<16954>>tex2html_deferred<<16954>>\bf\end<<16955>>tex2html_deferred<<16955>>0<<5808>> ;SPMamp;
    \mbox<<5809>>(stationarity)<<5809>>\\ 
         <<5810>>\begin<<16956>>tex2html_deferred<<16956>>\bf\end<<16957>>tex2html_deferred<<16957>>h<<5810>>(<<5811>>\begin<<16958>>tex2html_deferred<<16958>>\bf\end<<16959>>tex2html_deferred<<16959>>x<<5811>>)=<<5812>>\begin<<16960>>tex2html_deferred<<16960>>\bf\end<<16961>>tex2html_deferred<<16961>>0<<5812>> ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5813>>(primal feasibility)<<5813>>\\ 
         <<5814>>\begin<<16962>>tex2html_deferred<<16962>>\bf\end<<16963>>tex2html_deferred<<16963>>XM1<<5814>>-<<5815>>\begin<<16964>>tex2html_deferred<<16964>>\bf\end<<16965>>tex2html_deferred<<16965>>1<<5815>>/t=<<5816>>\begin<<16966>>tex2html_deferred<<16966>>\bf\end<<16967>>tex2html_deferred<<16967>>0<<5816>> ;SPMamp; \mbox<<5817>>(complementarity)<<5817>>
  \end<<5818>>array<<5818>>\right.
  \label<<5819>>KKTconditionsIP<<5819>>
\end<<5820>>equation<<5820>>
The third condition is actually from the definition of \begin<<9432>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9432>>$<<5821>>\begin<<16968>>tex2html_deferred<<16968>>\bf\end<<16969>>tex2html_deferred<<16969>>\mu<<5821>>$\end<<9433>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9433>> 
given above, but here it is labeled as complementarity, so that 
these conditions can be compared with the KKT conditions of the 
original problem. We see that the two sets of KKT conditions are
similar to each other, with the following differences:
\begin<<5822>>itemize<<5822>>
\item The non-negativity \begin<<9434>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9434>>$<<5823>>\begin<<16970>>tex2html_deferred<<16970>>\bf\end<<16971>>tex2html_deferred<<16971>>x<<5823>>\ge<<5824>>\begin<<16972>>tex2html_deferred<<16972>>\bf\end<<16973>>tex2html_deferred<<16973>>0<<5824>>$\end<<9435>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9435>>\space in the primal feasibility
  of the original KKT is dropped;
\item Consequently the inequality \begin<<9436>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9436>>$<<5825>>\begin<<16974>>tex2html_deferred<<16974>>\bf\end<<16975>>tex2html_deferred<<16975>>\mu<<5825>>\ge<<5826>>\begin<<16976>>tex2html_deferred<<16976>>\bf\end<<16977>>tex2html_deferred<<16977>>0<<5826>>$\end<<9437>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9437>>\space in the dual 
  feasibility of the original KKT conditions is also dropped;
\item There is an extra term \begin<<9438>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9438>>$<<5827>>\begin<<16978>>tex2html_deferred<<16978>>\bf\end<<16979>>tex2html_deferred<<16979>>1<<5827>>/t$\end<<9439>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9439>>\space in complementarity which
  will vanish when \begin<<9440>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9440>>$t\rightarrow\infty$\end<<9441>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9441>>.
\end<<5828>>itemize<<5828>>
\begin<<16980>>tex2html_deferred<<16980>>\par\end<<16981>>tex2html_deferred<<16981>>
The optimal solution that minimizes the objective function \begin<<9442>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9442>>$f(<<5829>>\begin<<16982>>tex2html_deferred<<16982>>\bf\end<<16983>>tex2html_deferred<<16983>>x<<5829>>)$\end<<9443>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9443>>
can be found by solving the simultaneous equations in the modified
KKT conditions (with no inequalities) given above. To do so, we first
express the equations in the KKT conditions above as a nonlinear
equation system \begin<<9444>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9444>>$<<5830>>\begin<<16984>>tex2html_deferred<<16984>>\bf\end<<16985>>tex2html_deferred<<16985>>F<<5830>>(<<5831>>\begin<<16986>>tex2html_deferred<<16986>>\bf\end<<16987>>tex2html_deferred<<16987>>x<<5831>>,<<5832>>\begin<<16988>>tex2html_deferred<<16988>>\bf\end<<16989>>tex2html_deferred<<16989>>\lambda<<5832>>,<<5833>>\begin<<16990>>tex2html_deferred<<16990>>\bf\end<<16991>>tex2html_deferred<<16991>>\mu<<5833>>)=<<5834>>\begin<<16992>>tex2html_deferred<<16992>>\bf\end<<16993>>tex2html_deferred<<16993>>0<<5834>>$\end<<9445>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9445>>, and 
find its Jacobian matrix \begin<<9446>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9446>>$<<5835>>\begin<<16994>>tex2html_deferred<<16994>>\bf\end<<16995>>tex2html_deferred<<16995>>J<<5835>>_<<5836>>\begin<<16996>>tex2html_deferred<<16996>>\bf\end<<16997>>tex2html_deferred<<16997>>F<<5836>>$\end<<9447>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9447>>\space composed of the partial 
derivatives of the function \begin<<9448>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9448>>$<<5837>>\begin<<16998>>tex2html_deferred<<16998>>\bf\end<<16999>>tex2html_deferred<<16999>>F<<5837>>(<<5838>>\begin<<17000>>tex2html_deferred<<17000>>\bf\end<<17001>>tex2html_deferred<<17001>>x<<5838>>,<<5839>>\begin<<17002>>tex2html_deferred<<17002>>\bf\end<<17003>>tex2html_deferred<<17003>>\lambda<<5839>>,<<5840>>\begin<<17004>>tex2html_deferred<<17004>>\bf\end<<17005>>tex2html_deferred<<17005>>\mu<<5840>>)$\end<<9449>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9449>> 
with respect to each of the three variables \begin<<9450>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9450>>$<<5841>>\begin<<17006>>tex2html_deferred<<17006>>\bf\end<<17007>>tex2html_deferred<<17007>>x<<5841>>$\end<<9451>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9451>>, \begin<<9452>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9452>>$<<5842>>\begin<<17008>>tex2html_deferred<<17008>>\bf\end<<17009>>tex2html_deferred<<17009>>\lambda<<5842>>$\end<<9453>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9453>>, 
