\begin<<17112>>tex2html_deferred<<17112>>\par\end<<17113>>tex2html_deferred<<17113>>
We can now use the 
\htmladdnormallink<<5913>>Newton-Raphson method<<5913>><<5914>>../ch2/node7.html<<5914>>
to find the solution of the nonlinear equation 
\begin<<9460>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9460>>$<<5915>>\begin<<17114>>tex2html_deferred<<17114>>\bf\end<<17115>>tex2html_deferred<<17115>>F<<5915>>(<<5916>>\begin<<17116>>tex2html_deferred<<17116>>\bf\end<<17117>>tex2html_deferred<<17117>>x<<5916>>,<<5917>>\begin<<17118>>tex2html_deferred<<17118>>\bf\end<<17119>>tex2html_deferred<<17119>>\lambda<<5917>>,<<5918>>\begin<<17120>>tex2html_deferred<<17120>>\bf\end<<17121>>tex2html_deferred<<17121>>\mu<<5918>>)=<<5919>>\begin<<17122>>tex2html_deferred<<17122>>\bf\end<<17123>>tex2html_deferred<<17123>>0<<5919>>$\end<<9461>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9461>>\space iteratively:
\begin<<5920>>equation<<5920>>
  \left[\begin<<5921>>array<<5921>><<5922>>c<<5922>><<5923>>\begin<<17124>>tex2html_deferred<<17124>>\bf\end<<17125>>tex2html_deferred<<17125>>x<<5923>>_<<5924>>n+1<<5924>>\\ <<5925>>\begin<<17126>>tex2html_deferred<<17126>>\bf\end<<17127>>tex2html_deferred<<17127>>\lambda<<5925>>_<<5926>>n+1<<5926>>\\ 
