where \begin<<9462>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9462>>$\alpha$\end<<9463>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9463>>\space is a parameter that controls the step size and 
\begin<<9464>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9464>>$[\delta<<5943>>\begin<<17142>>tex2html_deferred<<17142>>\bf\end<<17143>>tex2html_deferred<<17143>>x<<5943>>_n,\delta<<5944>>\begin<<17144>>tex2html_deferred<<17144>>\bf\end<<17145>>tex2html_deferred<<17145>>\lambda<<5944>>_n,\delta<<5945>>\begin<<17146>>tex2html_deferred<<17146>>\bf\end<<17147>>tex2html_deferred<<17147>>\mu<<5945>>_n]^T$\end<<9465>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<9465>>\space is the
search direction (<<5946>>\begin<<17148>>tex2html_deferred<<17148>>\em\end<<17149>>tex2html_deferred<<17149>>Newton direction<<5946>>), which can be found by 
solving the following equation:
\begin<<5947>>eqnarray<<5947>>
